[03/08/23, 12:32:04 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: void f(vector<vector<int>> inp,vector<vector<int>>& output,int m,int n,int i,int j){
        //base case
        if(i == m or j==n){
            return;
        }
        if(output[i][j] == 1 or output[i][j] == 0){
            return;
        } 
        //recursive case
        int living = checknei(inp,i,j,m,n);
        if(inp[i][j] == 1){
            if(living == 2 or living == 3){
            output[i][j] = 1;
            //cell is living and will live 
            }
            else if(living < 2 or living > 3){
            //cell is living and will die
            output[i][j] = 0;
            }
        }
        else{
            if(living == 3 and inp[i][j] == 0){
            //cell is dead and will become living
            output[i][j] = 1;
            }
            else{
                output[i][j] = 0;
                //cell is dead and will remain dead
            }
        }
        if(j==n-1){ //you are at the end of the row so move to next row
            f(inp,output,m,n,i+1,0);
        }
        else{ //you are not not at the end so move to next column
           f(inp,output,m,n,i,j+1);
        }
    }

[03/08/23, 12:38:14 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    void f(vector<vector<int>> inp,vector<vector<int>>& output,int m,int n,int i,int j){
        //base case
        if(i == m){
            return;
        } 
        if(j==n){ //you are at the end of the row so move to next row
            f(inp,output,m,n,i+1,0);
        }
        //recursive case
        int living = checknei(inp,i,j,m,n);
        if(inp[i][j] == 1){
            if(living == 2 or living == 3){
            output[i][j] = 1;
            //cell is living and will live 
            }
        }
        else{
            if(living == 3 and inp[i][j] == 0){
            //cell is dead and will become living
            output[i][j] = 1;
            }
        }
        
         //you are not not at the end so move to next column
           f(inp,output,m,n,i,j+1);
        
    }
    int checknei(vector<vector<int>> board,int i,int j,int m,int n){
        int dx[8] = {-1,-1,-1,0,1,1,-1};
        int dy[8] = {-1,0,1,1,1,0,-1,-1};

        int count = 0;

        for(int k=0 ; k<8 ; k++){
            if((i+dx[k] >= 0 or i+dx[k]<=m-1) and (j+dy[k]>=0 or j+dy[k]<=n-1)){
                if(board[i+dx[k]][j+dy[k]] == 1) count ++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
    void gameOfLife(vector<vector<int>>& board) {
       int m = board.size();
       int n = board[0].size();

       vector<vector<int>> output(0);

        f(board,output,m,n,0,0);

        board = output;



        
    }
};

[03/08/23, 12:47:19 PM] Satvik Saini: void update_status(vector<vector<int>>& board, int n, int m, int i, int j, int &live, int &dead){
        if(i+1<n){
            board[i+1][j] == 0 ? dead++ : live++ ;
        }
        if(i-1>=0){
            board[i-1][j] == 0 ? dead++ : live++ ;
        }
        if(j+1<m){
            board[i][j+1] == 0 ? dead++ : live++ ;
        }
        if(j-1>=0){
            board[i][j-1] == 0 ? dead++ : live++ ;
        }
        if(i+1<n && j+1<m){
            board[i+1][j+1] == 0 ? dead++ : live++ ;
        }
        if(i+1<n && j-1>=0){
            board[i+1][j-1] == 0 ? dead++ : live++ ;
        }
        if(i-1>=0 && j+1<m){
            board[i-1][j+1] == 0 ? dead++ : live++ ;
        }
        if(i-1>=0 && j-1>=0){
            board[i-1][j-1] == 0 ? dead++ : live++ ;
        }
        return;
    }

    void solve(vector<vector<int>>& board, vector<vector<int>>& ans, int n, int m, int i, int j){

        //base case
        if(j == m){
            solve(board,ans,n,m,i+1,0);
            return;
        }

        if(i == n){
            return;
        }

        //recursive case
        int live = 0;
        int dead = 0;
        update_status(board,n,m,i,j,live,dead);
        
        if(board[i][j] == 1){
            if (live == 2 || live == 3){
                ans[i][j] = 1;
            }
        }
        else{
            if(live == 3){
                ans[i][j] = 1;
            }
        }

        solve(board,ans,n,m,i,j+1);
    }

    void gameOfLife(vector<vector<int>>& board) {
        int n = board.size();
        int m = board[0].size();

        vector<vector<int>> ans(n,vector<int>(m, 0));

        solve(board,ans,n,m,0,0);

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                board[i][j] = ans[i][j];
            }
        }
    }

[03/08/23, 6:29:51 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:

    void f(string s,string out,int idx,int dot,vector<string>& ans){
        //base case
        if(idx == s.size()){
            if(dot == 3){
                ans.push_back(out);
                return;
            }
            else{
                return;
            }
        }
        //recursive case        
        for(int i=idx ; i<s.size() ; i++){
            if(i-idx+1 > 3)  break;
            if(isokay(s.substr(idx,i-idx+1))){
                out+=s.substr(idx,i-idx+1);
                out.push_back('.');
                f(s,out,i+1,dot+1,ans);
                out.pop_back();
                for(int i=0 ; i<i-idx+1 ; i++){
                    out.pop_back();
                }
            }
        }
        
    } 
    bool isokay(string s){
        int a = stoi(s);
        if(s.size()!=1 and s[0] == 0) return false;
        if(a>=0 and a<=255)  return true;
        else return false;
        
    }

    vector<string> restoreIpAddresses(string s) {

        vector<string> ans;
        string out;
        f(s,out,0,0,ans);
        return ans;

        
    }
};
[03/08/23, 6:45:57 PM] Satvik Saini: bool isGood(string s){
        if(s.length()>1 && s[0] == '0') return false;

        int n = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            int dig = s[i] - '0';
            n = n*10 + dig;
        }
        if(n>=0 && n<=255) return true;
        return false;
    }

    void solve(string s, string out, vector<string> &ans, int i, int dot){
        //base case

        if(dot == 4 && i == s.length()){
            out.pop_back();
            ans.push_back(out);
            return;
        }

        if(dot>4) return;

        //recursive case

        int range = i+3>s.length() ? s.length() : i+3;

        for(int j=i;j<range;j++){
            if(isGood(s.substr(i,j-i+1))){
                solve(s,out+s.substr(i,j-i+1)+'.',ans,j+1,dot+1);   
            }
        }
    }


    vector<string> restoreIpAddresses(string s) {
        vector<string> ans;
        string out="";
        solve(s,out,ans,0,0);

        return ans;
    }

[04/08/23, 8:47:33 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * struct ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode *next;
 *     ListNode() : val(0), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x, ListNode *next) : val(x), next(next) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    void Insertattail(ListNode* head,int val){
        ListNode* temp = new ListNode(val);
        while(head->next!=NULL){
            head = head->next;
        }
        head->next = temp;
    }
    void Insertbeforedummy(ListNode* &head2,int val,ListNode* dummy){
        ListNode* newnode = new ListNode(val);
        if(head2 == dummy ){
            newnode->next = head2;
            head2 = newnode;
        }
        ListNode* temp = head2;
        
        if(temp->next == dummy){
            newnode->next = temp->next;
            temp->next = newnode;
        }

    }
    void deleteatdummy(ListNode* head){

        while(head->next->val!=-101){
            head = head->next;
        }
        ListNode* dummy = head->next;
        head->next = head->next->next;
        delete dummy;

    }
    ListNode* partition(ListNode* head, int x) {
        ListNode* dummy = new ListNode(-101);
        ListNode* head2 = dummy;
        while(head!=NULL){
            if(head->val > x){
                Insertattail(head2,head->val);
            }
            else{
                Insertbeforedummy(head2,head->val,dummy);
            }
            head = head->next;
        }
        deleteatdummy(head2);
        return head2;
        

    }
};
[04/08/23, 8:48:38 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/partition-list/
[04/08/23, 8:48:51 AM] Satvik Saini: ListNode* partition(ListNode* head, int x) {
        ListNode* left = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode* left_tail = left;
        ListNode* right = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode* right_tail = right;

        while(head){
            if(head->val < x){
                left_tail->next = head;
                left_tail = left_tail->next;
            }
            else{
                right_tail->next = head;
                right_tail = right_tail->next;
            }
            head = head->next;
        }

        left_tail->next = right->next;
        right_tail->next = NULL;

        return left->next;
    }
[04/08/23, 8:58:45 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * struct ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode *next;
 *     ListNode() : val(0), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x, ListNode *next) : val(x), next(next) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    void Insertattail(ListNode* head,int val){
        ListNode* temp = new ListNode(val);
        while(head->next!=NULL){
            head = head->next;
        }
        head->next = temp;
    }
    void Insertbeforedummy(ListNode* &head2,int val,ListNode* dummy){
        ListNode* newnode = new ListNode(val);
        if(head2 == dummy ){
            newnode->next = head2;
            head2 = newnode;
        }

        ListNode* temp = head2;
        while(temp->next!=dummy){
            temp = temp->next;
        }
        newnode->next = temp->next;
        temp->next = newnode;
        
    }
    void deleteatdummy(ListNode* head,ListNode* dummy){
        while(head->next!=dummy){
            head = head->next;
        }
        ListNode* dum = head->next;
        head->next = head->next->next;
        delete dum;

    }
    ListNode* partition(ListNode* head, int x) {
        ListNode* dummy = new ListNode(-101);
        ListNode* head2 = dummy;
        while(head!=NULL){
            if(head->val >= x){
                Insertattail(head2,head->val);
            }
            else{
                Insertbeforedummy(head2,head->val,dummy);
            }
            head = head->next;
        }
        // deleteatdummy(head2);
        return head2;
        

    }
};

[06/08/23, 9:56:41 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<iostream>
#include<stack>
#include<vector>

using namespace std;

void f(int* A, int n) {

	stack<pair<int, int>> s; // <value, index>

	vector<int> out;

	for (int i = 0; i <= n - 1; i++) {

		// find the index of nearest smaller element to the left of A[i]

		while (!s.empty() and s.top().first >= A[i]) {
			s.pop();
		}

		if (s.empty()) {
			out.push_back(-1);
		} else {
			out.push_back(s.top().second);
		}

		s.push({A[i], i});
	}

	for (int i = 0; i < out.size(); i++) {
		cout << out[i] << " ";
	}

	cout << endl;

}


int main() {

	int A[] = {0, 3, 5, 4, 1, 6, 2};
	int n = sizeof(A) / sizeof(int);

	f(A, n);

	return 0;
}

using namespace std;

void f(int* A, int n) {

	stack<pair<int, int>> s; // <value, index>

	vector<int> out;

	for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {

		// find the index of nearest smaller element to the right of A[i]

		while (!s.empty() and s.top().first >= A[i]) {
			s.pop();
		}

		if (s.empty()) {
			out.push_back(n);
		} else {
			out.push_back(s.top().second);
		}

		s.push({A[i], i});
	}

	reverse(out.begin(), out.end());

	for (int i = 0; i < out.size(); i++) {
		cout << out[i] << " ";
	}

	cout << endl;

}


int main() {

	int A[] = {2, 5, 1, 3, 6, 4, 0};
	int n = sizeof(A) / sizeof(int);

	f(A, n);

	return 0;
}

template<typename T>
class queue {

	T* arr; // pointer to array that internally represents queue

	int f;  // to store the array index at which we have performed
	// the last pop operation

	int r;  // to store the array index at which we have performed
	// the last push operation

	queue(int n) {

	}

	void push(T val) {

	}

	}

	T front() {

	}

	bool empty() {

	}

	int size() {

	}

};

int main() {

	queue<int> q(5);

	cout << "size : " << q.size() << endl;
	q.empty() ? cout << "Queue is empty!" << endl :
	                 cout << "Queue is not empty!" << endl;

	q.push(10);
	q.push(20);
	q.push(30);

	cout << "size : " << q.size() << endl;
	cout << "front : " << q.front() << endl;

	q.pop();

	cout << "size : " << q.size() << endl;
	cout << "front : " << q.front() << endl;

	q.pop();

	cout << "size : " << q.size() << endl;
	cout << "front : " << q.front() << endl;

	q.pop();
	q.empty() ? cout << "Queue is empty!" << endl :
	                 cout << "Queue is not empty!" << endl;

	return 0;
}

[06/08/23, 9:58:04 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<iostream>
#include<stack>
#include<vector>
#include<algorithm>

using namespace std;

int f(int* h, int n) {

	// 1. find the indices of nearest smaller element to the right for all the element in h[]

	stack<pair<int, int>> s; // <value, index>

	vector<int> v1;

	for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {

		// find the index of nearest smaller element to the right of h[i]

		while (!s.empty() and s.top().first >= h[i]) {
			s.pop();
		}

		if (s.empty()) {
			v1.push_back(n);
		} else {
			v1.push_back(s.top().second);
		}

		s.push({h[i], i});
	}

	reverse(v1.begin(), v1.end());

	// 2. find the indices of nearest smaller element to the left for all the element in h[]

	while (!s.empty()) {
		s.pop();
	}

	vector<int> v2;

	for (int i = 0; i <= n - 1; i++) {

		// find the index of nearest smaller element to the left of h[i]

		while (!s.empty() and s.top().first >= h[i]) {
			s.pop();
		}

		if (s.empty()) {
			v2.push_back(-1);
		} else {
			v2.push_back(s.top().second);
		}

		s.push({h[i], i});
	}

	int maxArea = 0;

	for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

		// find the area of the largest rectangle with the height as h[i]

		int w_best = v1[i] - v2[i] - 1;
		int a_best = h[i] * w_best;
		maxArea = max(maxArea, a_best);

	}

	return maxArea;

}

int main() {

	int h[] = {2, 1, 5, 6, 2, 3};
	int n = sizeof(h) / sizeof(int);

	cout << f(h, n) << endl;

	return 0;
}
[06/08/23, 9:58:21 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<iostream>
#include<vector>
#include<stack>

using namespace std;

bool find132pattern(vector<int>& nums) {

   int n = nums.size();
   vector<int> leftMin(n); // to track the minimum element upto the ith index

   leftMin[0] = nums[0];
   for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
      leftMin[i] = min(nums[i], leftMin[i - 1]);
   }

   for (int i = 0; i < leftMin.size(); i++) {
      cout << leftMin[i] << " ";
   }

   stack<int> s; // used to track nearest greater to the right of nums_i

   for (int j = n - 1; j >= 0; j--) {

      int nums_i = leftMin[j];

      // find the nearest greater element to the right of nums_i

      while (!s.empty() and s.top() <= nums_i) {
         s.pop();
      }

      if (!s.empty() and s.top() < nums[j]) { // !s.empty() -> you've found next greater element of nums_i
         // s.top() is nums_k therefore you've found 132 pattern
         cout << nums_i << " " << nums[j] << " " << s.top() << endl;
         return true;
      }

      s.push(nums[j]);

   }

   // there is no 132 pattern in nums[]
   return false;

}

int main() {

   vector<int> nums = {3, 4, 6, 2, 1, 5};

   find132pattern(nums) ? cout << "true" << endl :
                               cout << "false" << endl ;

}
[06/08/23, 9:59:19 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<iostream>
#include<queue>

using namespace std;

int main() {

	queue<char> q;

	char ch;

	int freq[26] = {0};

	while (true) {

		cin >> ch;

		freq[ch - 'a']++;
		if (freq[ch - 'a'] == 1) {
			// ch is non-repeating
			q.push(ch);
		}

		while (!q.empty() and freq[q.front() - 'a'] > 1) {
			q.pop();
		}

		if (q.empty()) {
			// after reading 'ch', stream doesn't have a non-repeating character
			cout << -1 << " ";
		} else {
			cout << q.front() << " ";
		}

	}


	return 0;
}
[06/08/23, 9:59:46 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /*

Implementation of the stack using two queues.

*/

#include<iostream>
#include<queue>

using namespace std;

template <typename T>
class stack {
	queue<T> q1;
	queue<T> q2;

public:

	// time : O(1)

	void push(T data) {
		if (q1.empty() && q2.empty()) {
			q1.push(data); // or q2.push(data)
		} else if (q1.empty() && !q2.empty()) {
			q2.push(data);
		} else {
			q1.push(data);
		}
	}

	// time : O(n)

	void pop() {
		if (q1.empty() && q2.empty()) {
			// stack is empty
		} else if (q1.empty() && !q2.empty()) {
			// transfer n-1 elements from q2 to q1
			while (q2.size() > 1) {
				q1.push(q2.front());
				q2.pop();
			}
			// pop stack top i.e. pop the nth element from q2
			q2.pop();
		} else {
			// transfer n-1 elements from q1 to q2
			while (q1.size() > 1) {
				q2.push(q1.front());
				q1.pop();
			}
			// pop stack top i.e. pop the nth element from q1
			q1.pop();
		}
	}

	T top() {
		if (q1.empty() && !q2.empty()) {
			// transfer n-1 elements from q2 to q1
			while (q2.size() > 1) {
				q1.push(q2.front());
				q2.pop();
			}
			// save & pop the nth element from q2 and transfer it to q1
			T ans = q2.front();
			q2.pop();
			q1.push(ans);
			return ans;
		} else {
			// transfer n-1 elements from q1 to q2
			while (q1.size() > 1) {
				q2.push(q1.front());
				q1.pop();
			}
			// save & pop the nth element from q1 and transfer it to q2
			T ans = q1.front();
			q1.pop();
			q2.push(ans);
			return ans;
		}
	}

	bool empty() {
		return q1.empty() && q2.empty();
	}

	int size() {
		return max(q1.size(), q2.size());
	}
};

int main() {

	stack<int> s;

	s.push(1);
	s.push(2);
	s.push(3);
	s.push(4);
	s.push(5);

	cout << "size = " << s.size() << endl;

	while (!s.empty()) {
		cout << s.top() << endl;
		s.pop();
	}

	cout << endl;

	s.empty() ? cout << "true" << endl : cout << "false" << endl;

	return 0;
}

[09/08/23, 9:33:20 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int no_of_path(int n, int m, int i, int j){
        
        //base case
        if(i == n || j == m){
            return 0;
        }

        if(i == n-1 && j == m-1){
            return 1;
        }

        //recursive case
        int count = 0;

        return count + no_of_path(n,m,i+1,j) +  no_of_path(n,m,i,j+1);

    }

    int uniquePaths(int m, int n) {
        return no_of_path(m,n,0,0);
    }
};

[10/08/23, 6:45:19 AM] Satvik Saini: int longestConsecutive(vector<int>& nums) {

        if(nums.empty()) return 0;

        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        int ans = 0;
        int temp = 1;

        int prev = nums[0];
        for(int i=1;i<nums.size();i++){
            if(nums[i]-prev == 1){
                temp++;
                prev++;
            }
            else if(nums[i] == nums[i-1]){
                while(i<nums.size() && nums[i] == nums[i-1]){
                    i++;
                }
                if(nums[i]-prev == 1){
                    temp++;
                    prev++;
                }
                else{
                    ans = max(ans,temp);
                    prev = nums[i];
                    temp = 1;
                }
            }
            else{
                ans = max(ans,temp);
                prev = nums[i];
                temp = 1;
            }
        }
        ans = max(ans,temp);

        return ans;
    }

[11/08/23, 9:44:11 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<iostream>
#include<algorithm>
#include<vector>
#include<stack>
#include<algorithm>
// #include<bits>

using namespace std;

vector<int> asteroidCollision(int* asteroids) {

	stack<int> s;

	for (int ast : asteroids) {
		if (ast < 0 and !s.empty() and s.top() > 0) {
			// there will be a collision
			bool flag = true; // assume 'ast' will destroy all the positive asteroids
			while (!s.empty() and s.top() > 0) {

				if (abs(ast) == s.top()) {
					// 'ast' and s.top() will be destroyed
					flag = false;
					s.pop();
					break;
				} else if (abs(ast) < s.top()) {
					// 'ast' will be destroyed
					flag = false;
					break;
				} else {
					// s.top() will be destroyed
					s.pop();
				}
			}

			if (flag == true) {
				// 'ast' has destroyed all the positive asteroids on the top of the stack
				s.push(ast);
			}


		} else {
			s.push(ast);
		}
	}

	vector<int> out;

	while (!s.empty()) {
		out.push_back(s.top());
		s.pop();
	}

	reverse(out.begin(), out.end());

	return out;

}

int main() {

	int asteroids[] = {7, 3, -4, 5, 2, -8, 2, 4, 1, -4};

	vector<int> out = asteroidCollision(asteroids);

	for (int i = 0; i < out.size(); i++) {

		cout << out[i] << " ";

	}

	cout << endl;

	return 0;
}

[12/08/23, 5:46:32 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    bool hasPathSum(TreeNode* root, int target) {
        // base case
        if(!root) {

            if(target == 0){
                return true;
            }else{
                return false;
            }
        }
        // if(!root->left && !root->right)  {
        //     if(target == root->val){
        //         return true;
        //     }else{
        //         return false;
        //     }
        // }

        //recursive case
        // you are at a node and you have not yet reached target so you will consider the value of this node and see if i get the sum from the right or from the left

        bool X = hasPathSum(root->left,target-root->val);
        bool Y = hasPathSum(root->right,target-root->val);

        return X or Y;  // whenever you can get ans from either side call the function directly in the return statement so that if we get true from one of the side we dont have to go to the other side 



        
    }
};
[12/08/23, 6:59:47 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */

class Solution {
public:

    void sum(TreeNode* root, int t,int& count){


        // base case
        if(!root)  return;
        if(root->val==t){
            std::cout<<root->val<<endl;
            count++;
            return;
        }
        //recursive casee
        
        //consider one with root involved
        sum(root->left,t-root->val,count);
        sum(root->right,t-root->val,count);
        //consider left subtree and root not involved 
        sum(root->left,t,count);
        //consider rigth sumtree and root not involved
        sum(root->right,t,count);

    }
    int pathSum(TreeNode* root, int targetSum) {

        int count = 0;
        sum(root,targetSum,count);
        return count;

        
    }
};

    // Write your code here

    long long currsum = 0;
    int currcount = 0;
    int cnt=0;
    int maxcount = 0;

    for(int i=0 ; i<a.size() ; i++){

        currsum+=a[i];
        currcount++;

        if(currsum>k){
            currsum = a[i];
            currcount = 1;
        }

            maxcount = max(currcount, maxcount);
            currsum = a[i];
            currcount = 1;
            cnt++;
        }

    }

    return maxcount;
}

[14/08/23, 9:02:59 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Node
{
public:
    int data;
    Node *next;

    Node(int d)
    {
        data = d;
        next = NULL;
    }
};

// This function gets two arguments - the head pointers of the two linked lists
// Return the node which is the intersection point of these linked lists
// It is assured that the two lists intersect

Node *intersectionOfTwoLinkedLists(Node *l1, Node *l2)
{
       Node* h1 = l1;
        Node* h2 = l2;

        int len1 = 0;
        int len2 = 0;

        while(h1){
            len1++;
            h1 = h1->next;
        }
        while(h2){
            len2++;
            h2 = h2->next;
        }

        h1 = l1;
        h2 = l2;

        if(len2>len1){
            while(len2>len1){
                h2 = h2->next;
                len2--;
            }
        }
        else{
            while(len1>len2){
                h1 = h1->next;
                len1--;
            }
        }

        while( h1 != h2){
            h1 = h1->next;
            h2 = h2->next;
        }

        return h1;
}

/*
*
*
*   You do not need to refer or modify any code below this. 
*   Only modify the above function definition.
*	Any modications to code below could lead to a 'Wrong Answer' verdict despite above code being correct.
*	You do not even need to read or know about the code below.
*
*
*
*/

Node *buildList(unordered_map<int, Node *> &hash)
{
    int x;
    cin >> x;
    Node *head = new Node(x);
    Node *current = head;
    hash[x] = head;
    while (x != -1)
    {
        cin >> x;
        if (x == -1)
            break;
        Node *n = new Node(x);
        hash[x] = n;
        current->next = n;
        current = n;
    }
    current->next = NULL;
    return head;
}

void printLinkedList(Node *head)
{
    while (head != NULL)
    {
        cout << head->data << " ";
        head = head->next;
    }
    cout << endl;
}

int main()
{
    unordered_map<int, Node *> hash;
    Node *l1 = buildList(hash);

    Node *l2 = NULL;
    int x;
    cin >> x;
    l2 = new Node(x);
    Node *temp = l2;

    while (x != -1)
    {
        cin >> x;
        if (x == -1)
            break;
        if (hash.find(x) != hash.end())
        {
            temp->next = hash[x];
            break;
        }
        Node *n = new Node(x);
        temp->next = n;
        temp = n;
    }

    cout << "L1 - ";
    printLinkedList(l1);
    cout << "L2 - ";
    printLinkedList(l2);

    Node *intersectionPoint = intersectionOfTwoLinkedLists(l1, l2);
    if(intersectionPoint == NULL){
        cout<<"Intersection at node with data = " << -1 << endl;
    }
    else
        cout << "Intersection at node with data = " << intersectionPoint->data << endl;

    return 0;
}

[14/08/23, 9:07:02 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: Node *intersectionOfTwoLinkedLists(Node *l1, Node *l2)
{

    // int len1 = length(l1);
    int len2 = length(l2);
    if(len1<len2){
        while(len1<len2){
        l2 = l2->next;
        l2--;
        }
    }else{
        while(len2<len1){
        l1 = l1->next;
        l1--;
        }
    }
    while(l1!=l2){
        l1 = l1->next;
        l2 = l2->next;
    }

    return l1;
}

[14/08/23, 9:14:49 AM] Satvik Saini: # include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Node{
public : 
    int data;
    Node* next;

	Node (int d){
		this->data = d;
		this->next = NULL;
	}
    
};

void insert_at_tail(Node* &head){
    int d;
    cin>>d;
    Node* temp = new Node(d);
	if(!head){
		head = temp;
		head->next = NULL;
		return;
	}
    head -> next = temp;
	temp->next = NULL;
}

void del_pos(Node* &head, int pos){
	if(pos == 0){
		head = head->next;
		return;
	}
	int c = 0;
	Node* curr = head;
	Node* prev = head;
	while(c != pos){
		prev = curr;
		curr = curr->next;
		c++;
	}
	prev->next = curr->next;
}

int main() {
    int t,q;
    cin>>t>>q;
    Node* head = NULL;
    for(int i=0;i<t;i++){
        insert_at_tail(head);
    }
	for(int i=0;i<q;i++){
		int pos;
		cin>>pos;
		del_pos(head,pos);
		Node* temp = head;
		while(temp){
			cout<<temp->data<<" ";
			temp = temp->next;
		}
		cout<<endl;
	}
    
}

	}
	cout<<endl;

Node* getnode(int pos,Node* head){
    int i=1;
    while(i<pos){
        head = head->next;
        i++;
    }
    return head;
}

void reverse(Node* &head, int left, int right) {

    if(!head || !head->next || left == right) return head;

    Node* left_node = getnode(left,head);
    Node* right_node = getnode(right,head);
    Node* prev = NULL;
    Node* after_right = getnode(right+1,head);

    if(left>1){
        prev = getnode(left-1,head);
    }
    if(prev!=NULL) prev->next = right_node;
    else head = right_node;

    Node* prev1 = left_node;
    Node* curr = left_node->next;
    Node* forward = curr->next;
    while(curr != after_right){
        forward = curr->next;
        curr->next = prev1;
        prev1 = curr;
        curr = forward;
    }
    left_node->next = after_right;

    return ;
}

int main(){
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    Node* head = NULL;
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        insertAtTail(head);
    }
    int s,e;   // positions, not idx
    cin>>s>>e;

    reverse(head,s,e);

    print(head);
       
}

void reverseinbw(Node* head , int l , int r){
    if(l!=0){
        Node* l_prev = getNode(head,l-1);
    }
    
    Node* left = getNode(l);
    Node* right = getNode(r);

    if(right!=NULL){
      Node* right_next = right->next;   
    }
    Node* curr = left->next;
    Node* prev = left;
    Node* forward = curr->next;

    while(curr!=NULL and curr!=right_next){
        forward = curr->next;
        curr->next = prev;
        prev = curr;
        curr = forward;
    }
    left->next = right_next;  //left->next = forward; 
    if(l == 0){
        head = prev;
    }else{
        l_prev->next = curr;
    } 

    print(head);
}

void insertAtTail(Node*& head) {
	 int val;
	 cin>>val;

	if (head == NULL) {
		insertAtHead(head, val);
		return;
	}

	Node* n = new Node(val);
	Node* tail = getTail(head);
	tail->next = n;
}

     Node* l_prev = NULL;
    if(l!=0){
       l_prev = getNode(head,l-1);

    Node* right = getNode(head,r);

        forward = curr->next;
        curr->next = prev;
        prev = curr;
        curr = forward;

    if(l == 0){
        head = prev;
    }else{
        l_prev->next = prev;
    } 

    print(head);

[17/08/23, 8:04:58 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution
{
public:
    bool checkmatrix(vector<vector<int>> temp)
    {

        for (int i = 0; i < temp.size(); i++)
        {

            for (int j = 0; j < temp[0].size(); j++)
            {

                if (temp[i][j] == 0)
                    return false;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
    int f(vector<vector<int>> grid, int i, int j, int ei, int ej, vector<vector<int>> p, int n, int m, int cnt){
        // base case

        if (i == n || j == m || i == -1 || j == -1)
        {
            return 0;
        }

        if (i == ei && j == ej && checkmatrix(p))
        {
            cnt++;
            return 1;
        }
        if (grid[i][j] == -1)
        {
            return 0;
        }

        // recursive case
        if (p[i][j] == 1)
            return 0;

        p[i][j] = 1;

        int x1 = f(grid, i + 1, j + 1, ei, ej, p, n, m, cnt);
        int x2 = f(grid, i + 1, j - 1, ei, ej, p, n, m, cnt);
        int x3 = f(grid, i - 1, j - 1, ei, ej, p, n, m, cnt);
        int x4 = f(grid, i - 1, j + 1, ei, ej, p, n, m, cnt);

        p[i][j] = 0;

        return x1+x2+x3+x4;
    }
    int uniquePathsIII(vector<vector<int>> &grid)
    {

        int n = grid.size();
        int m = grid[0].size();
        int s_i, s_j, e_i, e_j = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++)
            {
                if (grid[i][j] == 1)
                {
                    s_i = i;
                    s_j = j;
                }
                if (grid[i][j] == 2)
                {
                    e_i = i;
                    e_j = j;
                }
            }
        }

        vector<vector<int>> temp;

        int count = 0;

        f(grid, s_i, s_j, e_i, e_j, temp, n, m, count);

        return 0;
    }
};
[17/08/23, 8:12:00 AM] Satvik Saini: int dx[] = {0, 0, -1, 1};
int dy[] = {1, -1, 0, 0};


void f(char maze[][10], char path[][10], int m, int n, int i, int j) {

	// base case

	// rat can go out of box from any direction
	if (i == m || i == -1 || j == n || j == -1) {     
		return;
	}

	if (i == m - 1 and j == n - 1) {

		path[i][j] = '1';
		printPath(path, m, n);
		path[i][j] = '0';

		return;
	}

	if (maze[i][j] == 'X') {
		return;
	}

	// recursive case

	// while standing at the (i, j)th cell, decide the next step

	path[i][j] = '1';

	// blocking the cell for next call, otherwise will stuck in infinite loop.
	maze[i][j] = 'X';        

	for (int k = 0; k < 4; k++) {
		f(maze, path, m, n, i + dx[k], j + dy[k]);
	}

	path[i][j] = '0';        // backtracking
	maze[i][j] = '0';
}

[17/08/23, 9:45:59 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: vector<vector<int>> temp(n,vector<int> t(m,0));
[17/08/23, 10:03:03 AM] Satvik Saini: int dx[] = {0,0,1,-1};
int dy[] = {1,-1,0,0};

class Solution {
public:


    int count_path(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int i, int j, int x, int y, int n, int m, int non_obstacle, int movement){

        //base case
        if(i == -1 || i == n || j == -1 || j == m){
            return 0;
        }
        if(i == x && j == y){
            if(non_obstacle == movement){
                return 1;
            }
            return 0;
        }

        if(grid[i][j] == -1){
            return 0;
        }

        //recursive case

        if(grid[i][j] == 0){
            movement++;
        }
        grid[i][j] = 5;
        int count = 0;

        for(int l=0;l<4;l++){
            count += count_path(grid,i+dx[l],j+dy[l],x,y,n,m,non_obstacle,movement);
        }

        grid[i][j] = 0;

        return count;
    }

    int uniquePathsIII(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int n = grid.size();
        int m = grid[0].size();

        int non_obstacle = 0;
        int movement = 0;

        int s_c = 0, s_r = 0, e_c = 0, e_r = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(grid[i][j] == 1){
                    s_r = i;
                    s_c = j;
                }
                else if(grid[i][j] == 2){
                    e_r = i;
                    e_c = j;
                }
                else if (grid[i][j] == 0){
                    non_obstacle ++;
                }
            }
        }

        return count_path(grid,s_r,s_c,e_r,e_c,n,m,non_obstacle,movement);
    }
};
[17/08/23, 10:27:46 AM] Satvik Saini: int dx[] = {1,-1,0,0};
int dy[] = {0,0,1,-1};

class Solution {
public:

    int count_path(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int n, int m, int i, int j, int x, int y, int movement,vector<vector<int>> path,int obs){

        //base case
        if(i == -1 || i == n || j == -1 || j == m){
            return 0;
        }
        if(i == x && j == y){
            if(movement - 1 == n*m - obs - 2){
                return 1;
            }
            return 0;
        }
        if(grid[i][j] == -1){
            return 0;
        }

        //recursive case
        grid[i][j] = -1;
        path[i][j] = 1;

        int count = 0;
        for(int l=0;l<4;l++){
            count += count_path(grid,n,m,i+dx[l],j+dy[l],x,y,movement+1,path,obs);
        }

        grid[i][j] = 0;
        path[i][j] = 0;

        return count;

    }

    int uniquePathsIII(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int n = grid.size();
        int m = grid[0].size();

        int sr=0,sc=0,er=0,ec=0,obs=0;
        int movement = 0;

        vector<vector<int>> path(n,vector<int>(m));

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(grid[i][j] == 1){
                    sr = i;
                    sc = j;
                }
                else if(grid[i][j] == 2){
                    er = i;
                    ec = j;
                }
                else if(grid[i][j] == -1){
                    obs++;
                }
            }
        }

        return count_path(grid,n,m,sr,sc,ec,er,movement,path,obs);
    }
};
[17/08/23, 10:58:08 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    void combisum(vector<int> arr, int target,int i,vector<int> combination,vector<vector<int>>& ans){


        // base case
       
            if(target == 0){
            ans.push_back(combination);
            return;
            }
            
            if(i == arr.size())  return;

        
        //recursive case

        // you are at the ith index you have taken decision for arr[0..i-1th] 
        //see if you can take the ith element 

        if(target - arr[i] >= 0){
            combination.push_back(arr[i]);
            combisum(arr,target-arr[i],i+1,combination,ans);
            combination.pop_back();
        }
    }
    vector<vector<int>> combinationSum2(vector<int>& candidates, int target) {

        vector<vector<int>>  ans;
        vector<int> combination;

        combisum(candidates,target,0,combination,ans);

        return ans;


        
    }
};

[17/08/23, 11:09:18 AM] Satvik Saini: Self assessment test in this ppt will be as assignment 1 which students have to do in class on 24th August. Failure in the submission of assignments on 24th August by 12 noon, would be counted as -2 in internal assessment
[17/08/23, 11:24:52 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    void combisum(vector<int> arr, int target,int i,vector<int> combination,vector<vector<int>>& ans){


        // base case
       
            if(target == 0){
            ans.push_back(combination);
            return;
            }
            
            if(i == arr.size())  return;

        
        //recursive case

        for(int j=i ; j<arr.size() ; j++){

            if(i!=j and arr[j] == arr[j-1] )  continue;
            if(target - arr[j] >= 0){
            combination.push_back(arr[j]);
            combisum(arr,target-arr[j],j+1,combination,ans);
            combination.pop_back();
            }

        }
            
    }
    vector<vector<int>> combinationSum2(vector<int>& candidates, int target) {

        vector<vector<int>>  ans;
        vector<int> combination;

        combisum(candidates,target,0,combination,ans);

        return ans;


        
    }
};
[17/08/23, 11:56:42 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> twoSum(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        int i =0 , j = nums.size() -1;
        vector<int> ans;
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());

        while(i<j){
            if(nums[i]+nums[j] == target){
                ans.push_back(i);
                ans.push_back(j);
                i++;
                j--;
            }
            else if(nums[i]+nums[j] > target){

                j--;

            }else{
                i++;
            }
        }

        // for(int i =0 ; i< nums.size() -1 ; i++){
        //     for(int j = i+1 ; j< nums.size() ;j++ ){
        //         if(nums[i] + nums[j] == target )  {
        //             ans.push_back(i);
        //             ans.push_back(j);
        //         }
        //     }
        // }
        return ans;
        
    }
};
[17/08/23, 5:52:28 PM] Satvik Saini: # define long long ll

int studentCount(vector<int> &A, int pgLimit){
    int pg = 0;
    int students = 1;
    int i = 0;
    
    while(i<A.size()){
        pg += A[i];
        if(pg > pgLimit){
            students++;
            pg = A[i];
        }
        i++;
    }
    return students;
}

int Solution::books(vector<int> &A, int B) {
    ll s = 1, e = 10000000000;
    int ans = -1;
    while(s<=e){
        ll mid = s + (e - s) / 2;
        int x = studentCount(A,mid);
        if(x <= B){
            ans = mid;
            e = mid - 1;
        }
        else{
            s = mid + 1;
        }
    }
    
    return -1;
}

[19/08/23, 9:42:39 AM] Satvik Saini: ListNode* partition(ListNode* head, int x) {
        ListNode* left = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode* left_tail = left;
        ListNode* right = new ListNode(-1);
        ListNode* right_tail = right;

        while(head){
            if(head->val < x){
                left_tail->next = head;
                left_tail = left_tail->next;
            }
            else{
                right_tail->next = head;
                right_tail = right_tail->next;
            }
            head = head->next;
        }

        left_tail->next = right->next;
        right_tail->next = NULL;

        return left->next;
    }

    int i = 0;
    for (int n : nums)
        if (i < 2 || n > nums[i-2])
            nums[i++] = n;
    return i;

public:
    vector<int> rearrangeArray(vector<int>& nums) {
        map<int,int>  mpp;
        int n = nums.size();
        int poscnt=1;
        int negcnt=1;
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            if(nums[i]<0){
                mpp[i] = negcnt;
                negcnt++;
            }
            if(nums[i]<0){
                mpp[i] = poscnt;
                poscnt++;
            }
        }
        int i=0;
        for(auto num : mpp){
            if(num.first>0){
                nums[num.second] = num.first;
            }else{
                nums[n/2 + num.second] = num.first;
            }
        }

        return  nums;
        
    }
};

                ans[neg_idx] = it;

[21/08/23, 12:11:44 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int sum(TreeNode* root,bool isLeft) {

        // base case
        if(!root)  return 0;

        if(!root->left and !root->right){
            if(isLeft){
                return root->val;
            }
            return 0;
        }

        //recursive case
        
        // recursivly go in the left half to find you the sum of left leaf nodes of LST
        int x = sum(root->left,true);
        // recursivly go in the left half to find you the sum of left leaf nodes of RST
        int y = sum(root->right,false);

        return x + y;        
    }

[22/08/23, 10:00:19 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(NULL), right(NULL) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    pair<bool,TreeNode*>  LCA(TreeNode* root, TreeNode* p, TreeNode* q){

        // base case
        if(root == NULL){
            return{false,NULL};
        }
        if(root==p){
            return{true,root};
        }
        if(root==q){
            return{true,root};
        }

        //recursive case
        pair<bool,TreeNode*> my_pair;

        pair<bool,TreeNode*>  left = LCA(root->left,p,q);
        pair<bool,TreeNode*>  right = LCA(root->right,p,q);

        if(left.first && right.first){
            my_pair.first = true;
            my_pair.second = root;
        }else if(left.first and!right.first){
            my_pair.first = true;
            my_pair.second = left.second;
        }else{
            my_pair.first = true;
            my_pair.second = left.second;
        }
        return my_pair;
    }
    TreeNode* lowestCommonAncestor(TreeNode* root, TreeNode* p, TreeNode* q) {

        return LCA(root,p,q).second;
        
    }
};
[22/08/23, 7:40:40 PM] Satvik Saini: https://youtu.be/xvNwoz-ufXA
[22/08/23, 7:40:51 PM] Satvik Saini: bhai iska optimal approach samjhaio
[23/08/23, 7:51:45 AM] Satvik Saini: bool isPossible(vector<int>& arr, int n, int m, int maxPgs){
    int pgs = 0;
    int student = 1;

    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        pgs += arr[i];
        if(pgs > maxPgs){
            student++;
            pgs = arr[i];
            if(student > m){
                return false;
            }
        }
    }
    return true;
}

int findPages(vector<int>& arr, int n, int m) {
    int s = 1, e = INT_MAX;
    int ans = -1;

    while(s <= e){
        // mid denotes the max no of pages a student will read
        int mid = e + (s - e) / 2;

        if(isPossible(arr,n,m,mid)){
            // it is possible that max no of pages a student will read is mid
            // thus we need to minimise it
            ans = mid;
            e = mid - 1;
        }
        else{
            // it is not posible to maximise mid no of pages, thus we need to increase the mid
            s = mid + 1;
        }
    }

    return ans;
}

public:
    int climbStairs(int n) {

        // base case
        if(n<0){
            return 0;
        }
        if(n==0)  return 1;

        //recursive case
        // you take 1 step if its is possible 
        
        int X = climbStairs(n-1);
        

        // you take 2 steps 
        

        int Y = climbStairs(n-2);

        return X + Y;

    }
};

[29/08/23, 9:04:37 AM] Satvik Saini: class Pair{
public :
    TreeNode<int>* head;
    TreeNode<int>* tail;
};

Pair convert(TreeNode<int>* root) {

	Pair p;

	// base case

	if (root == NULL) {
		p.head = p.tail = NULL;
		return p;
	}

	// recursive case

	// 1. recursively convert the LST into a sorted LL
	Pair left = convert(root->left);

	if (left.head == NULL) {
		p.head = root;
	} else {
		left.tail->right = root;
		p.head = left.head;
	}

	// 2. recursively convert the RST into a sorted LL
	Pair right = convert(root->right);

	if (right.head == NULL) {
		p.tail = root;
	} else {
		root->right = right.head;
		p.tail = right.tail;
	}

	return p;

}

TreeNode<int>* flatten(TreeNode<int>* root)
{
    Pair ans = convert(root);
    return ans.head;
}

bool isSameTree(TreeNode* p, TreeNode* q) {
	//base case
    if(p == NULL && q == NULL) return true;
    if(p == NULL && q != NULL) return false;
    if(p != NULL && q == NULL) return false;

	//recursive case
    return (isSameTree(p->left,q->left) && isSameTree(p->right,q->right));
}

int main () {
	int n;
	cin>>n;

	TreeNode* root1 = NULL;
	TreeNode* root2 = NULL;

	// build the two trees
	root1 = buildTree(root1);
	root2 = buildTree(root2);

	isSameTree(root1,root2) ? cout<<"true"<<endl : cout<<"false"<<endl;
	
	
	return 0;
}

[31/08/23, 11:58:20 AM] Satvik Saini: #include<iostream>
#include<vector>
using namespace std;

class TreeNode{
public : 
    int val;
    TreeNode* left;
    TreeNode* right;

    TreeNode(int val){
        this->val = val;
        this->left = NULL;
        this->right = NULL;
    }
};

class node{
public :
    int data;
    node* prev;
    node* next;

    node(int d){
        this->data = d;
        this->prev = NULL;
        this->next = NULL;
    }
};

TreeNode* insert(TreeNode* root, int key){
    //base case
    if(root == NULL){
        root = new TreeNode(key);
        return root;
    }

    //recursive case
    if(root->val > key){
        root->left = insert(root->left, key);
    }
    else{
        root->right = insert(root->right, key);
    }
    return root;
}

void buildinOrder(TreeNode* root, vector<int> &inOrder){
    //base case
    if(root == NULL){
        return;
    }

    //recursive case
    buildinOrder(root->left,inOrder);
    inOrder.push_back(root->val);
    buildinOrder(root->right,inOrder);
}

int main () {
    int n;
    cin>>n;

    TreeNode* root = NULL;

    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        int d;
        cin>>d;
        root = insert(root,d);
    }

    vector<int> inOrder;
    buildinOrder(root,inOrder);

    node* head = NULL;
    node* tail = head;
    node* before_tail = head;

    for(int i=0;i<inOrder.size();i++){
        node* temp = new node(inOrder[i]);
        tail->next = temp;
        tail = temp;
        tail->prev = before_tail;
        before_tail = tail;
    }
    while(head)){
        cout<<head->val<<" ";
        head = head->next;
    }  
    return 0;
}

[31/08/23, 2:30:36 PM] Satvik Saini: #include<iostream>
#include<vector>
using namespace std;

class TreeNode{
public : 
    int val;
    TreeNode* left;
    TreeNode* right;

    TreeNode(int val){
        this->val = val;
        this->left = NULL;
        this->right = NULL;
    }
};

TreeNode* buildTree(TreeNode* root){
	int d;
	cin>>d;
	root = new TreeNode(d);
	bool left, right;
	cin>>left;

	if(left){
		root->left = buildTree(root->left);
	}
	cin>>right;
	if(right){
		root->right = buildTree(root->right);
	}
	return root;
}

TreeNode* remove_leaf(TreeNode* root){
	//base case
	if(root == NULL){
		return NULL;
	}
	if(root->left == NULL && root->right == NULL){
		return NULL;
	}

	//recursive case
	if(root->left){
		root->left = remove_leaf(root->left);
	}
	if(root->right){
		root->right = remove_leaf(root->right);
	}
	return root;
}

void print_bst(TreeNode* root){
	//base case
	if(root == NULL){
		return;
	}

	//recursive case
	if(root->left == NULL && root->right == NULL){
		cout<<"END => "<<root->val<<" <= END"<<endl;
	}
	if(root->left == NULL && root->right != NULL){
		cout<<root->right->val<<" => "<<root->val<<" <= END"<<endl;
	}
	if(root->left != NULL && root->right == NULL){
		cout<<root->left->val<<" => "<<root->val<<" <= END"<<endl;
	}
	if(root->left != NULL && root->right != NULL){
		cout<<root->left->val<<" => "<<root->val<<" <= "<<root->right->val<<endl;
	}
	print_bst(root->left);
	print_bst(root->right);
}

int main () {

    TreeNode* root = buildTree(root);

    root = remove_leaf(root);
	print_bst(root);

	
    return 0;
}

#include<vector>
#include<queue>
using namespace std;

class TreeNode{
public : 
    int val;
    TreeNode* left;
    TreeNode* right;

    TreeNode(int val){
        this->val = val;
        this->left = NULL;
        this->right = NULL;
    }
};

TreeNode* buildTree() {

	int rootData;
	cin >> rootData;

	TreeNode* root = new TreeNode(rootData);

	queue<TreeNode*> q;
	q.push(root);

	while (!q.empty()) {

		TreeNode* front = q.front();
		q.pop();

		int leftData;
		cin >> leftData;

		if (leftData != -1) {

			TreeNode* leftChild = new TreeNode(leftData);
			front->left = leftChild;
			q.push(leftChild);

		}

		int rightData;
		cin >> rightData;

		if (rightData != -1) {

			TreeNode* rightChild = new TreeNode(rightData);
			front->right = rightChild;
			q.push(rightChild);

		}
	}
	return root;
}

void print_leaf(TreeNode* root){
	//base case
	if(root == NULL){
		return;
	}
	if(root->left == NULL && root->right === NULL){
		cout<<root->val<<" ";
		return;
	}
	//recursive case
	print_leaf(root->left);
	print_leaf(root->right);
}

int main () {
    
    TreeNode* root = buildTree(root);

	print_leaf(root);
	
    return 0;
}

using namespace std;
class ListNode{
	public:
	int val;
	ListNode* next;

	ListNode(int val){
		this->val = val;
		next = NULL;
	}
};
void build_ll(ListNode* head,int n){

	while(n--){
		int x;
		cin>>x;
		head->next = new ListNode(x);
		head = head->next;
	}
	
}
void print_ll(ListNode* head){
	while(!head){
		cout<<head->val<<" ";
		head = head->next;
	}
}
void solve(ListNode* head1){

	// move to the mid element 



	ListNode* head2 = head1;
	ListNode* head = head1;
	ListNode* slow = head1;
	ListNode* fast = head1->next;

	while(fast != NULL and fast->next != NULL){

		fast = fast->next->next;
		slow = slow->next;
	}

	ListNode* prev = slow->next;
	ListNode* curr = prev->next;

	// reverse the middle part 

	while(curr!=NULL){
		ListNode* forward = curr->next;
		curr->next = prev;
		prev = curr;
		curr = forward;
	}
	slow->next = prev;

	head2 = prev;


	// now head1 is head of straight half of the linked list and head2 id the head of the reverse half of the linked list


	// now i need to meake temp1 and temp2 

	ListNode* temp1 = head1->next;
	ListNode* temp2 = head2->next;

	while(head2 != NULL){

		head1->next = head2;
		head2->next = temp1;

		head1 = temp1;
		head2 = temp2;

		temp1 = temp1->next;
		temp2 = temp2->next;
		
	}

	slow->next = NULL;

	print_ll(head);
}

int main () {
	int t;
	cin>>t;
	for(int l=0 ; l<t ; l++){
		ListNode* head = NULL;
		// code here...
		int n;
		cin>>n;
		build_ll(head,n);
		solve(head);
	}
	return 0;
}
[31/08/23, 3:59:34 PM] Satvik Saini: #include<iostream>
#include<vector>
#include<queue>
using namespace std;

class TreeNode{
public : 
    int val;
    TreeNode* left;
    TreeNode* right;

    TreeNode(int val){
        this->val = val;
        this->left = NULL;
        this->right = NULL;
    }
};

class node{
public :
    int data;
    node* prev;
    node* next;

    node(int d){
        this->data = d;
        this->prev = NULL;
        this->next = NULL;
    }
};

TreeNode* buildTree() {

	int rootData;
	cin >> rootData;

	TreeNode* root = new TreeNode(rootData);

	queue<TreeNode*> q;
	q.push(root);

	while (!q.empty()) {

		TreeNode* front = q.front();
		q.pop();

		int leftData;
		cin >> leftData;

		if (leftData != -1) {

			TreeNode* leftChild = new TreeNode(leftData);
			front->left = leftChild;
			q.push(leftChild);

		}

		int rightData;
		cin >> rightData;

		if (rightData != -1) {

			TreeNode* rightChild = new TreeNode(rightData);
			front->right = rightChild;
			q.push(rightChild);

		}
	}
	return root;
}

void buildinOrder(TreeNode* root, vector<int> &inOrder){
    //base case
    if(root == NULL){
        return;
    }

    //recursive case
    buildinOrder(root->left,inOrder);
    inOrder.push_back(root->val);
    buildinOrder(root->right,inOrder);
}

int main () {
    int n;
    cin>>n;

    TreeNode* root = NULL;
    root = buildTree();

    vector<int> inOrder;
    buildinOrder(root,inOrder);

    node* head = new node(inOrder[0]);
    node* tail = head;
    node* before_tail = head;

    for(int i=1;i<inOrder.size();i++){
        node* temp = new node(inOrder[i]);
        tail->next = temp;
        tail = temp;
        tail->prev = before_tail;
        before_tail = tail;
    }
    while(head){
        cout<<head->data<<" ";
        head = head->next;
    }
    return 0;
}
[31/08/23, 4:08:27 PM] Satvik Saini: class Pair{
public :
    TreeNode<int>* head;
    TreeNode<int>* tail;
};

Pair convert(TreeNode<int>* root) {

	Pair p;

	// base case

	if (root == NULL) {
		p.head = p.tail = NULL;
		return p;
	}

	// recursive case

	// 1. recursively convert the LST into a sorted LL
	Pair left = convert(root->left);

	if (left.head == NULL) {
		p.head = root;
	} else {
		left.tail->right = root;
		p.head = left.head;
	}

	// 2. recursively convert the RST into a sorted LL
	Pair right = convert(root->right);

	if (right.head == NULL) {
		p.tail = root;
	} else {
		root->right = right.head;
		p.tail = right.tail;
	}
	return p;
}

[31/08/23, 6:26:44 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/next-greater-element-ii/
[31/08/23, 6:26:56 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> nextGreaterElements(vector<int>& nums) {

        // if an element does not have a next greater to right check if it has one to the left , if not then it will definately not have one

        int n = nums.size();

        vector<int> v1;
        vector<int> v2;
        stack<int> stk;

        // next greater to right array 

        for(int i=n-1 ; i>=0 ; i--){

            // check is the stack has any element which is smaller that the current element 
            while(!stk.empty() && stk.top()<= nums[i])  {
                stk.pop();
            }
            if(stk.empty()){
                v1.push_back(-1);
            }else{
                v1.push_back(stk.top());
            }

            stk.push(nums[i]);

        }
        // next greater to left array 

        stack<int> stk2;
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){

            // check is the stack has any element which is smaller that the current element 
            while(!stk2.empty() && stk2.top()<= nums[i])  {
                stk2.pop();
            }
            if(stk2.empty()){
                v2.push_back(-1);
            }else{
                v2.push_back(stk.top());
            }

            stk2.push(nums[i]);

        }

        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            if(v1[i] == -1 and v2[i] != -1){
                v1[i] = v2[i];
            }
        }

        return v1;
    }
};

using namespace std;

class Node{
public : 
    int data;
    Node* next;

	Node(int d){
		data = d;
		next = NULL;
	}  
};
void insertAtHead(Node*& head, int val) {

	Node* n = new Node(val);
	n->next = head;
	head = n;
}
Node* getTail(Node* temp) {

	while (temp->next != NULL) {
		temp = temp->next;
	}
	return temp;

}

void insertAtTail(Node*& head) {
	 int val;
	 cin>>val;

	if (head == NULL) {
		insertAtHead(head, val);
		return;
	}

	Node* n = new Node(val);
	Node* tail = getTail(head);
	tail->next = n;
}
void print(Node* head){

	while(head!=NULL){
		cout<<head->data<<" ";
		head = head->next;
	}
	cout<<endl;
}

int main(){
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    Node* head = NULL;
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        insertAtTail(head);
    }
    Node* tails = head;
    while(tails->next != NULL){
        tails = tails->next;
    }
    print(head);
    tails->next = head;   // LL is now circular
    
    Node* prev = head;
    Node* slow = head;
    Node* fast = head->next;
    Node* head1 = NULL;
    Node* head2 = NULL;

    while(fast != head && fast->next != head){
        prev = slow;
        slow = slow->next;
        fast = fast->next->next;
    }
    
    if(fast == head){
        head1 = head;
        Node* temp = slow;
        while(temp->next != fast){
            temp = temp->next;
        }
        head2 = slow->next;
        temp->next = head2;
        slow->next = head;
    }
    else if (fast->next == head){
        head1 = head;
        head2 = slow->next;
        fast->next = slow->next;    
        slow->next = head;
    }

    Node* temp = head1->next;
    cout<<head1->data<<" ";
    while(temp != head1){
        cout<<temp->data<<" ";
        temp = temp->next;
    }cout<<endl;

    temp = head2->next;
    cout<<head2->data<<" ";
    while(temp != head2){
        cout<<temp->data<<" ";
        temp = temp->next;
    }cout<<endl;
}

class Node{
public : 
    int data;
    Node* next;

	Node(int d){
		data = d;
		next = NULL;
	}
    
};
void insertAtHead(Node*& head, int val) {

	Node* n = new Node(val);
	n->next = head;
	head = n;

}
Node* getTail(Node* temp) {

	while (temp->next != NULL) {
		temp = temp->next;
	}

	return temp;

}

void insertAtTail(Node*& head) {
	 int val;
	 cin>>val;
	//  cout<<val<<" ";

	if (head == NULL) {
		insertAtHead(head, val);
		return;
	}

	Node* n = new Node(val);

	Node* tail = getTail(head);

	tail->next = n;

}
void print(Node* head){
	// cout<<"in function";

	while(head!=NULL){
		cout<<head->data<<" ";
		head = head->next;
	}
	cout<<endl;
}
void split(Node* head,int n){

    Node* t1 = head;
    Node* t2 = head->next;
    Node* head2 = head;

    while(t2!=NULL and t2->next!= NULL){

        t2 = t2->next->next;
        t1 = t1->next;
    }
    head2 = t1->next;
    t1->next = NULL;

    print(head);
    print(head2);


}

int main() {
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    Node* head = NULL;
    Node* temp;
    for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
        insertAtTail(head);
    }
    split(head,n);

  return 0;
}

[03/09/23, 8:24:09 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int sumSubarrayMins(vector<int>& arr) {
        vector<int> left_smaller;
        vector<int> right_smaller;

        stack<int> stk;

        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++){
            while(!stk.empty() && stk.top() > arr[i]){
                stk.pop();
            }
            if(stk.empty()){
                left_smaller.push_back(-1);
            }
            else{
                left_smaller.push_back(stk.top());
            }
            stk.push(arr[i]);
        }

        for(int i=arr.size()-1;i>=0;i--){
            while(!stk.empty() && stk.top() > arr[i]){
                stk.pop();
            }
            if(stk.empty()){
                right_smaller.push_back(i + 1);
            }
            else{
                right_smaller.push_back(stk.top());
            }
            stk.push(arr[i]);
        }

        int sum = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++){
            int count = (i - left_smaller[i]) * (right_smaller[i] - i);
            sum += count * arr[i];
        }

        return sum;
    }
};

public:
    int sumSubarrayMins(vector<int>& arr) {
        vector<int> left_smaller;
        vector<int> right_smaller;

        stack<int> stk;

        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++){
            while(!stk.empty() && stk.top() >= arr[i]){
                stk.pop();
            }
            if(stk.empty()){
                left_smaller.push_back(-1);
            }
            else{
                left_smaller.push_back(stk.top());
            }
            stk.push(arr[i]);
        }

        for(int i=arr.size()-1;i>=0;i--){
            while(!stk.empty() && stk.top() > arr[i]){
                stk.pop();
            }
            if(stk.empty()){
                right_smaller.push_back(arr.size() - 1);
            }
            else{
                right_smaller.push_back(stk.top());
            }
            stk.push(arr[i]);
        }

        int sum = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++){
            int count = (i - left_smaller[i]) * (right_smaller[i] - i);
            sum += count * arr[i];
        }

        return sum;
    }

[03/09/23, 9:40:27 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int sumSubarrayMins(vector<int>& arr) {
       vector<long long> left;
       vector<long long> right;
       stack<int> stk1;
       stack<int> stk2;

       // building the left vector which stors size of sub-array in which the ith element is the smallest in this we will find till small or equal 

        for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size(); i++){
            while(!stk1.empty() && arr[stk1.top()] >= arr[i]){
                stk1.pop();
            }
            if(stk1.empty()){
                left.push_back(i+1);
            }else{
                left.push_back( i - stk1.top());
            }
            stk1.push(i);
        }
        
        // building the right vector which stores size of sub-array to the right in which the ith element is the smallest , in this we will find only till the smaller element as we have included the case of 

        for(int i=arr.size() -1  ; i>=0 ; i--){

            while(!stk2.empty() && arr[stk2.top()] > arr[i]){
                stk2.pop();
            }
            if(stk2.empty()){
                right.push_back(arr.size() - i);
            }else{
                right.push_back( stk2.top() - i);
            }

            stk2.push(i);

        }
        reverse(right.begin() , right.end());

        for(int x : left){
            std::cout<<x<<" ";
        }
        cout<<endl;
        for(int x : right){
            std::cout<<x<<" ";
        }

        long long sum =0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size() ; i++){
            sum += arr[i] * left[i] * right[i];
        }
        int mod = 1e9 + 7;
        return sum%mod;



    }
};
[03/09/23, 9:59:10 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    string removeKdigits(string num, int k) {

        if(num.length() <= k){
            return "0";
        }
        if(k == 0){
            return num;
        }

        string ans = "";
        stack<char> stk;
        stk.push(num[0]);

        for(int i=1;i<num.length();i++){
            while(k>0 && !stk.empty() && stk.top() > num[i]){
                // if k greater than 0 and our stack is not empty and the upcoming digit,
                // is less than the current top than we will pop the stack top
                stk.pop();
                k--;
            }

            stk.push(num[i]);

            // removing the preceding zeros
            if(stk.size() == 1 && stk.top() == '0'){
                stk.pop();
            }
        }
        while(!stk.empty() && k>0){
            // for cases like "456" where every num[i] > num.top()
            stk.pop();
            k--;
        }
        while(!stk.empty()){
            // pushing the ch from stk to ans string
            ans.push_back(stk.top());
            stk.pop();
        }

        reverse(ans.begin(), ans.end());

        if(ans.length() == 0) return "0";

        return ans;

    }
};

[05/09/23, 8:43:42 AM] Satvik Saini: int countPaths(TreeNode* root, int targetSum) {

	// base case

	if (root == NULL) {

		return 0;

	}

	int count = 0;

	if (root->val == targetSum) count++;

	// recursive case

	// count no. of paths that start at the root and sum up to targetSum

	// 1. ask your friend to count no. of paths in the leftSubtree that start at the root of the leftSubtree at sum up to targetSum-root->val

	count += countPaths(root->left, targetSum - root->val);

	// 2. ask your friend to count no. of paths in the rightSubtree that start at the root of the rightSubtree at sum up to targetSum-root->val

	count += countPaths(root->right, targetSum - root->val);

	return count;

}

[10/09/23, 7:56:51 AM] Satvik Saini: #include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class node{
public :
    int val;
    node* next;
    node(int val){
        this->val = val;
        this->next = NULL;
    }
};

class deque{
    node* head;
    node* tail;
    int count;
public :
    deque(){
        count = 0;
    }

    void push_front(int val){
        count++;
        if(!head){
            head = new node(val);
            tail = head;
            return;
        }
       node* temp = new node(val);
       temp->next = temp;
       head = temp;
    }
    void push_back(int val){
        count++;
        if(!head){
            head = new node(val);
            tail = head;
            return;
        }
       node* temp = new node(val);
       tail->next = temp;
       tail = temp;
    }

    void pop_front(){
        count--;
       if(!head) return;
       node* temp = head->next;
       delete head;
       head = temp;
    }
    void pop_back(){
        count--;
       node* temp = head;
       while(temp->next != tail){
        temp = temp->next;
       }
       delete tail;
       temp->next = NULL;
       tail = temp;
    }

    int front(){
        return head->val;
    }
    int back(){
        return tail->val;
    }

    int size(){
        return count;
    }

    bool empty(){
       return head == NULL;
    } 
};

int main(){
    deque q;
    q.push_back(10);
    // q.push_back(20);
    // q.push_front(30);
    cout<<q.size()<<endl;
    cout<<q.front()<<endl;
    return 0;
}

[10/09/23, 2:54:36 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: '#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
class complex {
    int a;
    int b;
    friend complex addNumbers(complex c1, complex c2);  // this gives acces sto the addNumbers function to access the data members of the class complex for a particular objectr 
    // you can access the privte data members from outside is you are iside of a friend function 
    

    public:
        void setNumber(int n1, int n2){
            a = n1;
            b = n2;
        }
        void PrintNumber(){
            cout<< a << " + "<< b<<'i'<<endl;
        }

};


complex addNumbers(complex c1, complex c2){
    complex c3;
    c3.a = c1.a + c2.a;
    c3.b = c1.b + c2.b;  // addNumbers function cannot access the value of c1.a and c2.a and .b rspectivelyy as the data members a and b are privte data members

    return c3; 
}
int main(){

#include<cmath>
using namespace std;
int distance;
class Point{
    int x,y;
    public:
    friend int distance(Point,Point);
        Point(int a, int b){
            x = a;
            y = b;
        }
        void displayPoint(){
            cout<<"the point is "<<x<<" , "<<y<<endl;
        }
        

};

int distance(Point a,Point b){

            // dist^2 = (x2-x1)^2 + (y2-y1)^2

            int x = a.x - b.x;
            x = x*x;
            int b = a.y - b.y;
            y = y*y;

            return sqrt(x + y);

    }

    Point q(2,4);
    p.displayPoint();
    q.displayPoint();

    return 0;
}

[11/09/23, 4:07:46 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <unordered_map>
using namespace std;

class node{
public :
    char ch;
    bool terminal;
    int freq;
    unordered_map<char,node*> mp;
    public:
    node(char ch){
        this->ch = ch;
        this->terminal = false;
        this->freq = 0;
    }
};

class trie{
    node* root;
public:
    trie(){
        root = new node('#');
    }
    void insert(string s){
        node* curr = root;
        for(char ch : s){
            if(curr->mp.find(ch) == curr->mp.end()){
                // no ch in child node
                // we need to create
                node* n = new node(ch);
                curr->mp[ch] = n;
            }
            curr->freq++;
            curr = curr->mp[ch];
        }
    }
    string uniquePrefix(string s){
        node* curr = root;
        string res = "";
        for(char ch : s){
            curr = curr->mp[ch];
            res += ch;
            if(curr->freq == 1){
                break;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};

int main() {
    trie t;
    int n; cin>>n;
    string words[n];
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
       cin>>words[i];
        t.insert(words[i]);
    }
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        cout<<t.uniquePrefix(words[i])<<" ";
    }
}

[17/09/23, 8:04:26 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>

using namespace std;

const int MOD = 1000000007;

int countArrays(vector<int>& arr) {
    int n = arr.size();

    // Initialize a 2D DP array to store the count of valid arrays.
    // dp[i][j] represents the count of valid arrays up to index i, considering j as the last element chosen.
    vector<vector<int>> dp(n, vector<int>(101, 0));

    // Initialize the base case.
    for (int j = 1; j <= arr[0]; ++j) {
        dp[0][j] = 1;
    }

    for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
        for (int j = 1; j <= 100; ++j) {
            // To find dp[i][j], we iterate through all possible values from 1 to j.
            // If we choose j as the last element, then dp[i][j] += dp[i-1][k] for all k in the range 1 to j-1.
            for (int k = 1; k < j; ++k) {
                dp[i][j] += dp[i - 1][k];
                dp[i][j] %= MOD;
            }
        }
    }

    // Sum up all valid arrays ending with different values in the last element.
    int total_count = 0;
    for (int j = 1; j <= 100; ++j) {
        total_count = (total_count + dp[n - 1][j]) % MOD;
    }

    return total_count;
}

int main() {
    vector<int> arr = {2, 3, 2};
    int result = countArrays(arr);
    cout << result << endl;  // Output: 8

    return 0;
}
[17/09/23, 8:04:37 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>

using namespace std;

const int MOD = 1000000007;

int countArrays(vector<int>& arr) {
    int n = arr.size();

    long long total_count = 1;  // Initialize the total count as 1.

    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        // Calculate the number of choices for the current element in the array.
        long long choices = arr[i] - i;

        // If choices become zero or negative, there are no valid arrays possible.
        if (choices <= 0) {
            return 0;
        }

        // Update the total count by multiplying with the number of choices.
        total_count = (total_count * choices) % MOD;
    }

    return static_cast<int>(total_count);
}

int main() {
    vector<int> arr = {2, 3, 2};
    int result = countArrays(arr);
    cout << result << endl;  // Output: 8

    return 0;
}

    Node* temp = head->next;
    while(temp->val != head->val){
        temp = temp->next;
    }
    head -> next = temp;
    Node* hff = remove_duplicates(temp);
    temp -> next = hff;
    return head;

}

[21/09/23, 7:23:53 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100 

struct Queue {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int front;
    int rear;
};

struct Queue* createQueue() {
    struct Queue* q = (struct Queue*)malloc(sizeof(struct Queue));
    q->front = -1; 
    q->rear = -1;
    return q;
}

int isEmpty(struct Queue* q) {
    return q->front == -1;
}

void push(struct Queue* q, int data) {
    if (q->rear + 1 == MAX_SIZE) {
        printf("Queue is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        q->front = 0;
    }
    q->rear++;
    q->items[q->rear] = data;
}

int pop(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = q->items[q->front];
    if (q->front == q->rear) {
        q->front = q->rear = -1; 
    } else {
        q->front++;
    }
    return data;
}

int peek(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot peek.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return q->items[q->front];
}

void display(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Queue: ");
    int i = q->front;
    while (i != q->rear) {
        printf("%d ", q->items[i]);
        i++;
    }
    printf("%d\n", q->items[i]);
}

int main() {
    struct Queue* q = createQueue();

    push(q, 1);
    push(q, 2);
    push(q, 3);

    display(q);

    printf("Front element: %d\n", peek(q));

    printf("popped element: %d\n", pop(q));

    display(q);

    printf("Is the q empty? %s\n", isEmpty(q) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(q);

    return 0;
}
[22/09/23, 9:59:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: Name Ambiguity:

Cause: Name ambiguity occurs when two or more base classes have members with the same name but different characteristics, such as different parameter types, return types, or number of parameters.
Resolution: To resolve name ambiguity, you often use techniques like function overloading or explicit qualification (using the scope resolution operator ::) to specify which version of the member to use.
Example: Multiple base classes have functions with the same name but different parameter lists.
Base Class Ambiguity:

Cause: Base class ambiguity occurs when a derived class inherits members from multiple base classes, and there is an ambiguity in accessing members of a common base class through different paths of inheritance.
Resolution: To resolve base class ambiguity, you use the scope resolution operator :: to specify the base class from which you want to access the member.
Example: A derived class inherits the same base class through multiple paths, and there is an ambiguity when accessing a member of that base class.

[30/09/23, 9:56:55 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>

typedef struct {
    int total_size;
    int used_size;
    int *baseadress;
}myArray;

void Array(myArray* a , int n){
    a->total_size = n;
    a->used_size = 0;
    a->baseadress = (int* ) malloc(n*sizeof(int));
}
void setval(myArray* a, int i , int val){
    
    (a->baseadress)[i] = val;
}
void setarray(myArray* a){
    for(int i=0 ; i<a->total_size ; i++){
        int x;
        scanf("%d",&x);
        a->baseadress[i] = x;
    }

}
void printarray(myArray* a){
    for(int i=0 ; i<a->total_size ; i++){
        printf(" %d " , a->baseadress[i]);
    }
    printf("\n");
}
int main(){
    myArray A;
    Array(&A , 5);
    setarray(&A);
    printarray(&A);



    return 0;
}

[30/09/23, 10:40:59 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: void insert_in_arr(int arr[] , int capacity , int size , int index , int element){

    if(size == capacity ){
        return;
    }

    for(int i=size-1 ; i>=index ; i--){
        arr[i+1] = arr[i];
    }
    arr[index] = element;

}

int main(){
    int arr[100] = {10 , 22 , 34 , 5 , 7};
    int size = 5, element = 10 , index = 1;

        printf("%d " , arr[i]);
    }

    for(int i=0 ; i<6 ; i++){
        printf("%d " , arr[i]);
