[01/10/23, 9:51:10 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎You deleted this message.
[01/10/23, 9:51:30 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: Yeh bhi nikal
[01/10/23, 9:51:43 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

struct Element
{
    int i;
    int j;
    int x;
};

struct Sparse
{
    int m;
    int n;
    int num;
    struct Element *ele;
};

void create(struct Sparse *s)
{
    printf("Enter the dimensions : ");
    scanf("%d %d", &s->m, &s->n);
    printf("Enter the number of non zero elements : ");
    scanf("%d", &s->num);
    s->ele = (struct Element *)malloc(s->num * sizeof(struct Element));
    printf("Enter the non zero elements : \n");
    for (int i = 0; i < s->num; i++) {
        scanf("%d %d %d", &s->ele[i].i, &s->ele[i].j, &s->ele[i].x);
    }
}

struct Sparse *add(struct Sparse *s1, struct Sparse *s2)
{
    if (s1->n != s2->n || s1->m != s2->m) {
        printf("Matrix addition is not possible!\n");
        return NULL;
    }

    struct Sparse *sum = (struct Sparse *)malloc(sizeof(struct Sparse));
    sum->ele = (struct Element *)malloc((s1->num + s2->num) * sizeof(struct Element));

    int i = 0, j = 0, k = 0;

    while (i < s1->num && j < s2->num){
        if (s1->ele[i].i > s2->ele[j].i){
            sum->ele[k++] = s2->ele[j++];
        }
        else if (s1->ele[i].i < s2->ele[j].i){
            sum->ele[k++] = s1->ele[i++];
        }
        else{
            if (s1->ele[i].j > s2->ele[j].j){
                sum->ele[k++] = s2->ele[j++];
            }
            else if (s1->ele[i].j < s2->ele[j].j){
                sum->ele[k++] = s1->ele[i++];
            }
            else{
                sum->ele[k] = s1->ele[i++];
                sum->ele[k].x += s2->ele[j++].x;
                k++;
            }
        }
    }
    while(i<s1->num){
        sum->ele[k++] = s1->ele[i++];
    }
    while(j<s2->num){
        sum->ele[k++] = s2->ele[j++];
    }
    sum->n = s1->n;
    sum->m = s1->m;
    sum->num = k;
    return sum;
}

struct Sparse *multiply(struct Sparse *s1, struct Sparse *s2)
{
    struct Sparse *result = (struct Sparse *)malloc(sizeof(struct Sparse));
    result->ele = (struct Element *)malloc(s1->num * s2->num * sizeof(struct Element));
    
    if (s1->n != s2->m) {
        printf("Matrix multiplication is not possible!\n");
        return NULL;
    }

    int k = 0;
    result->m = s1->m;
    result->n = s2->n;
    result->num = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i < s1->num; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < s2->num; j++) {
            if (s1->ele[i].j == s2->ele[j].i) {
                result->ele[k] = s1->ele[i];
                result->ele[k].x *= s2->ele[j].x;
                k++;
                result->num++;
            }
        }
    }
    return result;
}

// struct Sparse* transpose(struct Sparse* s){
//     struct Sparse *ans = (struct Sparse*)malloc(sizeof(struct Sparse));
//     ans->ele = (struct Element*)malloc(s->num*sizeof(struct Element));
//     for(int k=0;k<s->num;k++){
//         ans->ele[k].i = s->ele[k].j;
//         ans->ele[k].j = s->ele[k].i;
//         ans->ele[k].x = s->ele[k].x;
//     }
//     ans->m = s->m;
//     ans->n = s->n;
//     ans->num = s->num;
//     return ans;
// }

struct Sparse *transpose(struct Sparse *s)
{
    struct Sparse *result = (struct Sparse *)malloc(sizeof(struct Sparse));
    result->m = s->n;
    result->n = s->m;
    result->num = s->num;
    result->ele = (struct Element *)malloc(s->num * sizeof(struct Element));

    int *count = (int *)malloc((s->n) * sizeof(int));

    for (int i = 0; i < s->n; i++)
        count[i] = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i < s->num; i++)
        count[s->ele[i].j]++;

    int *index = (int *)malloc((s->n) * sizeof(int));
    index[0] = 0;

    for (int i = 1; i < s->n; i++)
        index[i] = index[i - 1] + count[i - 1];

    for (int i = 0; i < s->num; i++)
    {
        int j = s->ele[i].j;
        result->ele[index[j]].i = s->ele[i].j;
        result->ele[index[j]].j = s->ele[i].i;
        result->ele[index[j]].x = s->ele[i].x;
        index[j]++;
    }

    free(count);
    free(index);

    return result;
}

void display(struct Sparse s)
{
    printf("Displaying the matrix : \n");
    int k = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < s.m; i++){
        for (int j = 0; j < s.n; j++){
            if (i == s.ele[k].i && j == s.ele[k].j){
                printf("%d ", s.ele[k++].x);
            }
            else{
                printf("0 ");
            }
        }
        printf("\n");
    }
}

int main()
{
    struct Sparse s1,s2,*sum,*prod,*trans;
    create(&s1);
    // create(&s2);
    // sum = add(&s1,&s2);
    // prod = multiply(&s1,&s2);
    trans = transpose(&s1);
    // display(*sum);
    // display(*prod);
    display(*trans);
}
[01/10/23, 9:54:45 AM] Satvik Saini: In the provided code for computing the transpose of a sparse matrix, the `count` array is used to keep track of the number of non-zero elements in each column of the original matrix. It plays a crucial role in determining the positions where the elements of the transposed matrix will be stored.

Here's how `count` is used:

1. First, an array `count` is created, where each element of `count` corresponds to a column in the original matrix.

2. A loop iterates through all the non-zero elements of the original matrix and increments the corresponding element in the `count` array. This step counts how many non-zero elements are there in each column.

3. After counting the non-zero elements in each column, another array `index` is created. `index` stores the starting index in the `result->ele` array for each column of the transposed matrix.

4. The `index` array is populated based on the values in the `count` array. It calculates the starting index for each column in the `result->ele` array by summing up the counts of previous columns.

5. Finally, the loop copies the elements from the original matrix to the transposed matrix while ensuring they are placed in the correct column based on the calculated starting index from the `index` array.

In summary, the `count` array helps in counting the non-zero elements in each column of the original matrix, and the `index` array helps in determining where to place these elements in the transposed matrix efficiently. This allows for an efficient computation of the transposed sparse matrix.

[01/10/23, 9:58:43 AM] Satvik Saini: //IMPLEMENTATION OF STACK USING ARRAY

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100 // Maximum size of the stack

// Define a structure for the stack
struct Stack {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int top;
};

// Function to create an empty stack
struct Stack* createStack() {
    struct Stack* stk = (struct Stack*)malloc(sizeof(struct Stack));
    stk->top = -1; // Initialize the top to -1 to indicate an empty stack
    return stk;
}

int isEmpty(struct Stack* stk) {
    return stk->top == -1;
}

void push(struct Stack* stk, int item) {
    if (stk->top == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
        printf("Stack is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    stk->top++;
    stk->items[stk->top] = item;
}

int pop(struct Stack* stk) {
    if (isEmpty(stk)) {
        printf("Stack is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return stk->items[stk->top--];
}

int peek(struct Stack* stk) {
    if (isEmpty(stk)) {
        printf("Stack is empty. Cannot peek.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return stk->items[stk->top];
}

void display(struct Stack* stk) {
    if (isEmpty(stk)) {
        printf("Stack is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Stack: ");
    for (int i = 0; i <= stk->top; i++) {
        printf("%d ", stk->items[i]);
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    struct Stack* stk = createStack();

    push(stk, 1);
    push(stk, 2);
    push(stk, 3);

    display(stk);

    printf("Top element: %d\n", peek(stk));

    printf("Popped element: %d\n", pop(stk));

    display(stk);

    printf("Is the stack empty? %s\n", isEmpty(stk) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(stk);

    return 0;
}


// IMPLEMENTING 2 STACKS USING SINGLE ARRAY (MULTIPLE STACKS)

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100

struct TwoStacks {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int top1; 
    int top2; 
};

struct TwoStacks* createTwoStacks() {
    struct TwoStacks* ts = (struct TwoStacks*)malloc(sizeof(struct TwoStacks));
    
    ts->top1 = -1; 
    ts->top2 = MAX_SIZE; 
    return ts;
}

int isEmpty1(struct TwoStacks* ts) {
    return ts->top1 == -1;
}

int isEmpty2(struct TwoStacks* ts) {
    return ts->top2 == MAX_SIZE;
}

int isFull1(struct TwoStacks* ts) {
    return ts->top1 + 1 == ts->top2;
}


int isFull2(struct TwoStacks* ts) {
    return ts->top2 - 1 == ts->top1;
}

void push1(struct TwoStacks* ts, int item) {
    if (isFull1(ts)) {
        printf("Stack 1 is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    ts->top1++;
    ts->items[ts->top1] = item;
}

void push2(struct TwoStacks* ts, int item) {
    if (isFull2(ts)) {
        printf("Stack 2 is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    ts->top2--;
    ts->items[ts->top2] = item;
}

int pop1(struct TwoStacks* ts) {
    if (isEmpty1(ts)) {
        printf("Stack 1 is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return ts->items[ts->top1--];
}

int pop2(struct TwoStacks* ts) {
    if (isEmpty2(ts)) {
        printf("Stack 2 is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return ts->items[ts->top2++];
}

void display1(struct TwoStacks* ts) {
    if (isEmpty1(ts)) {
        printf("Stack 1 is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Stack 1: ");
    for (int i = 0; i <= ts->top1; i++) {
        printf("%d ", ts->items[i]);
    }
    printf("\n");
}

void display2(struct TwoStacks* ts) {
    if (isEmpty2(ts)) {
        printf("Stack 2 is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Stack 2: ");
    for (int i = MAX_SIZE - 1; i >= ts->top2; i--) {
        printf("%d ", ts->items[i]);
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    struct TwoStacks* ts = createTwoStacks();

    push1(ts, 1);
    push1(ts, 2);
    push1(ts, 3);

    push2(ts, 4);
    push2(ts, 5);
    push2(ts, 6);

    display1(ts);
    display2(ts);

    printf("Popped element from Stack 1: %d\n", pop1(ts));
    printf("Popped element from Stack 2: %d\n", pop2(ts));

    display1(ts);
    display2(ts);

    free(ts);

    return 0;
}


//STRING REVERSE

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100

struct Stack {
    char items[MAX_SIZE];
    int top;
};

struct Stack* createStack() {
    struct Stack* stk = (struct Stack*)malloc(sizeof(struct Stack));
    stk->top = -1;
    return stk;
}

int isEmpty(struct Stack* stk) {
    return stk->top == -1;
}

int isFull(struct Stack* stk) {
    return stk->top == MAX_SIZE - 1;
}

void push(struct Stack* stk, char item) {
    if (isFull(stk)) {
        printf("Stack is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    stk->items[++stk->top] = item;
}

char pop(struct Stack* stk) {
    if (isEmpty(stk)) {
        printf("Stack is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return stk->items[stk->top--];
}

int main() {
    struct Stack* stk = createStack();
    
    char input[MAX_SIZE];
    printf("Enter a string: ");
    fgets(input, sizeof(input), stdin);

    for (int i = 0; i < strlen(input); i++) {
        if (input[i] != '\n') {
            push(stk, input[i]);
        }
    }

    printf("Reversed string: ");
    while (!isEmpty(stk)) {
        printf("%c", pop(stk));
    }
    printf("\n");

    free(stk);

    return 0;
}


//PARENTHESIS CHECKER

int BalancedParentheses(char* str) {
    struct Stack* stk = createStack();
    int len = strlen(str);

    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        if (str[i] == '(' || str[i] == '{' || str[i] == '[') {
            push(stk, str[i]);
        }
        else if (str[i] == ')' || str[i] == '}' || str[i] == ']') {
            if (isEmpty(stk)) {
                free(stk);
                return 0; 
            }

            char top = pop(stk);
            if ((str[i] == ')' && top != '(') ||
                (str[i] == '}' && top != '{') ||
                (str[i] == ']' && top != '[')) {
                free(stk);
                return 0; 
            }
        }
    }
    return isEmpty(stk);
}

int main() {
    char str[100];
    printf("Enter string with parentheses: ");
    scanf("%s", str);

    if (BalancedParentheses(str)) {
        printf("Parentheses are balanced.\n");
    }
    else {
        printf("Parentheses are not balanced.\n");
    }

    return 0;
}

// PREFIX EVALUATION

// Approach : we start iterating the string from back to front, if we get a gidit we push into the stack. if we get an operator then we take out top2 elements and do the operation then push the resultant ans into the stack. at the end only one element is left in the stack which is the final ans

#include<iostream>
#include<stack>
using namespace std;

int main(){
    string s = "-+7*45+20";
    stack<int> stk;

    for(int i=s.length()-1;i>=0;i--){
        char ch = s[i];
        if(ch >= '0' && ch <= '9'){
            stk.push(ch - '0');
        }
        else{
            int dig1 = stk.top();
            stk.pop();
            int dig2 = stk.top();
            stk.pop();

            switch(ch){
            case '*' : stk.push(dig1 * dig2); break;
            case '/' : stk.push(dig1 / dig2); break;
            case '+' : stk.push(dig1 + dig2); break;
            case '-' : stk.push(dig1 - dig2); break;
            case '^' : stk.push(pow(dig1,dig2)); break;
            }
        }
    }
    cout<<"The result is "<<stk.top()<<endl;

    return 0;
}

// //POSTFIX EVALUATION

// Approach : we traverse the string from starting to end, if we found a digit, we push it inot the stack. If we found an operator then we take top 2 elements int the opp manner unlike the prefix evaluation and then do the operation and push it into the stack. At the end we will be left with only 1 element which is our final ans

#include<iostream>
#include<stack>
using namespace std;

int main(){
    string s = "46+2/5*7+";
    stack<int> stk;

    for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
        char ch = s[i];
        if(ch >= '0' && ch <= '9'){
            stk.push(ch - '0');
        }
        else{
            int dig2 = stk.top();
            stk.pop();
            int dig1 = stk.top();
            stk.pop();

            switch(ch){
            case '*' : stk.push(dig1 * dig2); break;
            case '/' : stk.push(dig1 / dig2); break;
            case '+' : stk.push(dig1 + dig2); break;
            case '-' : stk.push(dig1 - dig2); break;
            case '^' : stk.push(pow(dig1,dig2)); break;
            }
        }
    }
    cout<<"The result is "<<stk.top()<<endl;

    return 0;
}

// //INFIX TO POSTFIX

#include <iostream>
#include <stack>
using namespace std;

int prec(char ch)
{
    switch (ch)
    {
    case '^':
        return 3;
    case '*':
        return 2;
    case '/':
        return 2;
    case '+':
        return 1;
    case '-':
        return 1;
    default:
        return -1;
    }
}

int main()
{
    string s = "a+b*(c^d-e)^(f+g*h)-i";
    stack<char> stk;
    string result;

    for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
    {
        char c = s[i];

        // If the scanned character is
        // an operand, add it to output string.
        if ((c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= '0' && c <= '9'))
            result += c;

        // If the scanned character is an
        // ‘(‘, push it to the stack.
        else if (c == '(')
            stk.push('(');

        // If the scanned character is an ‘)’,
        // pop and add to output string from the stack
        // until an ‘(‘ is encountered.
        else if (c == ')')
        {
            while (stk.top() != '(')
            {
                result += stk.top();
                stk.pop();
            }
            stk.pop();
        }

        // If an operator is scanned
        else
        {
            while (!stk.empty() && prec(s[i]) <= prec(stk.top()))
            {
                result += stk.top();
                stk.pop();
            }
            stk.push(c);
        }
    }

    // Pop all the remaining elements from the stack
    while (!stk.empty())
    {
        result += stk.top();
        stk.pop();
    }

    cout << result << endl;
}

// //INFIX TO PRETFIX

#include <iostream>
#include <stack>
using namespace std;

int prec(char ch)
{
    switch (ch)
    {
    case '^':
        return 3;
    case '*':
        return 2;
    case '/':
        return 2;
    case '+':
        return 1;
    case '-':
        return 1;
    default:
        return -1;
    }
}

int main()
{
    string s = "a+b*(c^d-e)^(f+g*h)-i";
    stack<char> stk;
    string result;

    for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
        if(s[i] == '(') s[i] = ')';
        if(s[i] == ')') s[i] = '(';
    }

    for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
    {
        char c = s[i];

        // If the scanned character is
        // an operand, add it to output string.
        if ((c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= '0' && c <= '9'))
            result += c;

        // If the scanned character is an
        // ‘(‘, push it to the stack.
        else if (c == '(')
            stk.push('(');

        // If the scanned character is an ‘)’,
        // pop and add to output string from the stack
        // until an ‘(‘ is encountered.
        else if (c == ')')
        {
            while (stk.top() != '(')
            {
                result += stk.top();
                stk.pop();
            }
            stk.pop();
        }

        // If an operator is scanned
        else
        {
            while (!stk.empty() && prec(s[i]) <= prec(stk.top()))
            {
                result += stk.top();
                stk.pop();
            }
            stk.push(c);
        }
    }

    // Pop all the remaining elements from the stack
    while (!stk.empty())
    {
        result += stk.top();
        stk.pop();
    }

    cout << result << endl;
}

#include <stdlib.h>
typedef struct{
    int top;
    int *arr;
    int max_size;
}stack;

void create(stack* stk, int size){
    stk->arr = (int*)malloc(sizeof(int)*size);
    stk->top = -1;
    stk->max_size = size;
}
void push(stack* stk , int ele){
    if(stk->top = stk->max_size - 1 ){
        printf("stack overflow\n");
        return;
    }
    stk->arr[++stk->top] = ele;
}
void pop(stack* stk){
    if(stk->top = -1){
        printf("stack underflow\n");
        return;
    }
    stk->top--;
}
int peek(stack* stk){
    return stk->arr[stk->top];
}
int isEmpty(stack* stk){
    if(stk->top == -1 )return 1;
    return 0;
}

    if (isEmpty(stk)) {
        printf("Stack is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Stack: ");
    for (int i = 0; i <= stk->top; i++) {
        printf("%d ", stk->arr[i]);
    }
    printf("\n");
}

#define MAX_SIZE 100

    stk->top = -1;

        printf("Stack is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    stk->items[++stk->top] = item;
}

    if (isEmpty(stk)) {
        printf("Stack is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return;
    }
    stk->top--;
}

    return stk->items[stk->top];
}

[01/10/23, 3:42:44 PM] Satvik Saini: template <typename T>
class stack {
	queue<T> q1;
	queue<T> q2;

public:

	// time : O(1)

	void push(T data) {
		if (q1.empty() && q2.empty()) {
			q1.push(data); // or q2.push(data)
		} else if (q1.empty() && !q2.empty()) {
			q2.push(data);
		} else {
			q1.push(data);
		}
	}

	// time : O(n)

	void pop() {
		if (q1.empty() && q2.empty()) {
			// stack is empty
		} else if (q1.empty() && !q2.empty()) {
			// transfer n-1 elements from q2 to q1
			while (q2.size() > 1) {
				q1.push(q2.front());
				q2.pop();
			}
			// pop stack top i.e. pop the nth element from q2
			q2.pop();
		} else {
			// transfer n-1 elements from q1 to q2
			while (q1.size() > 1) {
				q2.push(q1.front());
				q1.pop();
			}
			// pop stack top i.e. pop the nth element from q1
			q1.pop();
		}
	}

	T top() {
		if (q1.empty() && !q2.empty()) {
			// transfer n-1 elements from q2 to q1
			while (q2.size() > 1) {
				q1.push(q2.front());
				q2.pop();
			}
			// save & pop the nth element from q2 and transfer it to q1
			T ans = q2.front();
			q2.pop();
			q1.push(ans);
			return ans;
		} else {
			// transfer n-1 elements from q1 to q2
			while (q1.size() > 1) {
				q2.push(q1.front());
				q1.pop();
			}
			// save & pop the nth element from q1 and transfer it to q2
			T ans = q1.front();
			q1.pop();
			q2.push(ans);
			return ans;
		}
	}

	bool empty() {
		return q1.empty() && q2.empty();
	}

	int size() {
		return max(q1.size(), q2.size());
	}
};
[01/10/23, 4:55:09 PM] Satvik Saini: // //INFIX TO POSTFIX

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <string.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100

struct Stack {
    char items[MAX_SIZE];
    int top;
};

struct Stack* createStack() {
    struct Stack* stk = (struct Stack*)malloc(sizeof(struct Stack));
    stk->top = -1;
    return stk;
}

int isEmpty(struct Stack* stk) {
    return stk->top == -1;
}

void push(struct Stack* stk, char item) {
    if (stk->top == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
        printf("Stack is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    stk->items[++stk->top] = item;
}

char pop(struct Stack* stk) {
    if (isEmpty(stk)) {
        printf("Stack is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return '\0'; // Return a sentinel value for error handling
    }
    return stk->items[stk->top--];
}

char top(struct Stack* stk){
    return stk->items[stk->top];
}

int isOperator(char ch) {
    return (ch == '+' || ch == '-' || ch == '*' || ch == '/' || ch == '^');
}

int precedence(char ch) {
    switch (ch) {
        case '^': return 3;
        case '*': case '/': return 2;
        case '+': case '-': return 1;
        default: return 0;
    }
}

void infixToPostfix(char infix[], char postfix[]) {
    struct Stack* stk = createStack();
    int j = 0;

    for(int i=0;i<strlen(infix);i++){
        char ch = infix[i];

        if ((ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z') || (ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z')) {
            postfix[j++] = ch;
        }
        else if (ch == '(') {
            push(stk, ch);
        }
        else if (ch == ')') {
            while (!isEmpty(stk) && top(stk) != '(') {
                postfix[j++] = pop(stk);
            }
            pop(stk); // Pop the '('
        }
        else if (isOperator(ch)) {
            while (!isEmpty(stk) && precedence(ch) <= precedence(top(stk))) {
                postfix[j++] = pop(stk);
            }
            push(stk, ch);
        }
    }

    while (!isEmpty(stk)) {
        postfix[j++] = pop(stk);
    }
    postfix[j] = '\0';
}

int main(){
    char infix[100], postfix[100];
    printf("Enter infix expression: ");
    scanf("%s", infix);
    
    infixToPostfix(infix, postfix);

    printf("Postfix expression: %s\n", postfix);

    return 0;
}

[01/10/23, 6:20:15 PM] Satvik Saini: // ARRAY IMPLEMENTATION

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100 

struct Queue {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int front;
    int rear;
};

struct Queue* createQueue() {
    struct Queue* q = (struct Queue*)malloc(sizeof(struct Queue));
    q->front = -1; 
    q->rear = -1;
    return q;
}

int isEmpty(struct Queue* q) {
    return q->front == -1;
}

void push(struct Queue* q, int data) {
    if (q->rear + 1 == MAX_SIZE) {
        printf("Queue is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        q->front = 0;
    }
    q->rear++;
    q->items[q->rear] = data;
}

int pop(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = q->items[q->front];
    if (q->front == q->rear) {
        q->front = q->rear = -1; 
    } else {
        q->front++;
    }
    return data;
}

int peek(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot peek.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return q->items[q->front];
}

void display(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Queue: ");
    int i = q->front;
    while (i != q->rear) {
        printf("%d ", q->items[i]);
        i++;
    }
    printf("%d\n", q->items[i]);
}

int main() {
    struct Queue* q = createQueue();

    push(q, 1);
    push(q, 2);
    push(q, 3);

    display(q);

    printf("Front element: %d\n", peek(q));

    printf("popped element: %d\n", pop(q));

    display(q);

    printf("Is the q empty? %s\n", isEmpty(q) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(q);

    return 0;
}

// DEQUE IMPLEMENTATION

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100 // Maximum size of the dq

// Define a structure for the dq
struct Deque {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int front;
    int rear;
    int size;
};

struct Deque* createDeque() {
    struct Deque* dq = (struct Deque*)malloc(sizeof(struct Deque));
   
    dq->front = -1; 
    dq->rear = -1;
    dq->size = 0; 
    return dq;
}

int isEmpty(struct Deque* dq) {
    return dq->size == 0;
}

void addFront(struct Deque* dq, int data) {
    if (dq->size == MAX_SIZE) {
        printf("Deque is full. Cannot add at the front.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = 0;
    }
    else if (dq->front == 0) {
        dq->front = MAX_SIZE - 1;
    }
    else {
        dq->front--;
    }
    dq->items[dq->front] = data;
    dq->size++;
}

void addRear(struct Deque* dq, int data) {
    if (dq->size == MAX_SIZE) {
        printf("Deque is full. Cannot add at the rear.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = 0;
    } else if (dq->rear == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
        dq->rear = 0;
    } else {
        dq->rear++;
    }
    dq->items[dq->rear] = data;
    dq->size++;
}

int removeFront(struct Deque* dq) {
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        printf("Deque is empty. Cannot remove from the front.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = dq->items[dq->front];
    if (dq->front == dq->rear) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = -1; 
    } else if (dq->front == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
        dq->front = 0;
    } else {
        dq->front++;
    }
    dq->size--;
    return data;
}

int removeRear(struct Deque* dq) {
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        printf("Deque is empty. Cannot remove from the rear.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = dq->items[dq->rear];
    if (dq->front == dq->rear) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = -1; 
    } else if (dq->rear == 0) {
        dq->rear = MAX_SIZE - 1;
    } else {
        dq->rear--;
    }
    dq->size--;
    return data;
}

void display(struct Deque* dq) {
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        printf("Deque is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Deque: ");
    int i = dq->front;
    while (1) {
        printf("%d ", dq->items[i]);
        if (i == dq->rear) {
            break;
        }
        if (i == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
            i = 0;
        } else {
            i++;
        }
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    struct Deque* dq = createDeque();

    addRear(dq, 1);
    addRear(dq, 2);
    addFront(dq, 3);

    display(dq);

    printf("Removed front element: %d\n", removeFront(dq));
    printf("Removed rear element: %d\n", removeRear(dq));

    display(dq);

    printf("Is the dq empty? %s\n", isEmpty(dq) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(dq);

    return 0;
}

// CIRCULAR IMPLEMENTATION

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100

struct CircularQueue {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int front;
    int rear;
};

struct CircularQueue* createCircularQueue() {
    struct CircularQueue* q = (struct CircularQueue*)malloc(sizeof(struct CircularQueue));
   
    q->front = -1; 
    q->rear = -1;
    return q;
}

int isEmpty(struct CircularQueue* q) {
    return q->front == -1;
}

void enqueue(struct CircularQueue* q, int data) {
    if ((q->rear + 1) % MAX_SIZE == q->front) {
        printf("Queue is full. Cannot enqueue.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        q->front = 0;
    }
    q->rear = (q->rear + 1) % MAX_SIZE;
    q->items[q->rear] = data;
}

int dequeue(struct CircularQueue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot dequeue.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = q->items[q->front];
    if (q->front == q->rear) {
        q->front = q->rear = -1; 
    } else {
        q->front = (q->front + 1) % MAX_SIZE;
    }
    return data;
}

int peek(struct CircularQueue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot peek.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return q->items[q->front];
}

void display(struct CircularQueue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Circular Queue: ");
    int i = q->front;
    while (1) {
        printf("%d ", q->items[i]);
        if (i == q->rear) {
            break;
        }
        i = (i + 1) % MAX_SIZE;
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    struct CircularQueue* q = createCircularQueue();

    enqueue(q, 1);
    enqueue(q, 2);
    enqueue(q, 3);

    display(q);

    printf("Front element: %d\n", peek(q));

    printf("Dequeued element: %d\n", dequeue(q));

    display(q);

    printf("Is the circular q empty? %s\n", isEmpty(q) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(q);

    return 0;
}


// APPLICATIONS OF QUEUE

/*
•Queues are widely used as waiting lists for a single shared resource like printer, disk, CPU.
•Queues are used to transfer data asynchronously (data not necessarily received at same rate as sent) between two processes (IO buffers), e.g., pipes, file IO, sockets.
•Queues are used as buffers on MP3 players and portable CD players, iPod playlist.
•Queues are used in Playlist for jukebox to add songs to the end, play from the front of the list.
•Queues are used in operating system for handling interrupts.
*/

// LINKED LIST IMPLEMENTATION

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node* next;
};

struct Queue {
    struct Node* front;
    struct Node* rear;
};

struct Queue* createQueue() {
    struct Queue* q = (struct Queue*)malloc(sizeof(struct Queue));
    q->front = q->rear = NULL;
    return q;
}

int isEmpty(struct Queue* q) {
    return q->front == NULL;
}

void enqueue(struct Queue* q, int data) {
    struct Node* newNode = (struct Node*)malloc(sizeof(struct Node));
    newNode->data = data;
    newNode->next = NULL;

    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        q->front = q->rear = newNode;
    }
    else {
        q->rear->next = newNode;
        q->rear = newNode;
    }
}

int dequeue(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot dequeue.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = q->front->data;
    struct Node* temp = q->front;
    q->front = q->front->next;
    free(temp);
    return data;
}

int peek(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot peek.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return q->front->data;
}

void display(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Queue: ");
    struct Node* current = q->front;
    while (current != NULL) {
        printf("%d ", current->data);
        current = current->next;
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    struct Queue* q = createQueue();

    enqueue(q, 1);
    enqueue(q, 2);
    enqueue(q, 3);

    display(q);

    printf("Front element: %d\n", peek(q));

    printf("Dequeued element: %d\n", dequeue(q));

    display(q);

    printf("Is the q empty? %s\n", isEmpty(q) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(q);

    return 0;
}

        q->front = 0;

        return -1;

        q->front = q->rear = -1;

// DEQUE IMPLEMENTATION

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100 // Maximum size of the dq

// Define a structure for the dq
struct Deque {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int front;
    int rear;
    int size;
};

struct Deque* createDeque() {
    struct Deque* dq = (struct Deque*)malloc(sizeof(struct Deque));
   
    dq->front = -1; 
    dq->rear = -1;
    dq->size = 0; 
    return dq;
}

int isEmpty(struct Deque* dq) {
    return dq->size == 0;
}

void addFront(struct Deque* dq, int data) {
    if (dq->size == MAX_SIZE) {
        printf("Deque is full. Cannot add at the front.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = 0;
    }
    else if (dq->front == 0) {
        dq->front = MAX_SIZE - 1;
    }
    else {
        dq->front--;
    }
    dq->items[dq->front] = data;
    dq->size++;
}

void addRear(struct Deque* dq, int data) {
    if (dq->size == MAX_SIZE) {
        printf("Deque is full. Cannot add at the rear.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = 0;
    } else if (dq->rear == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
        dq->rear = 0;
    } else {
        dq->rear++;
    }
    dq->items[dq->rear] = data;
    dq->size++;
}

int removeFront(struct Deque* dq) {
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        printf("Deque is empty. Cannot remove from the front.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = dq->items[dq->front];
    if (dq->front == dq->rear) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = -1; 
    } else if (dq->front == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
        dq->front = 0;
    } else {
        dq->front++;
    }
    dq->size--;
    return data;
}

int removeRear(struct Deque* dq) {
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        printf("Deque is empty. Cannot remove from the rear.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = dq->items[dq->rear];
    if (dq->front == dq->rear) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = -1; 
    } else if (dq->rear == 0) {
        dq->rear = MAX_SIZE - 1;
    } else {
        dq->rear--;
    }
    dq->size--;
    return data;
}

void display(struct Deque* dq) {
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        printf("Deque is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Deque: ");
    int i = dq->front;
    while (1) {
        printf("%d ", dq->items[i]);
        if (i == dq->rear) {
            break;
        }
        if (i == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
            i = 0;
        } else {
            i++;
        }
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    struct Deque* dq = createDeque();

    addRear(dq, 1);
    addRear(dq, 2);
    addFront(dq, 3);

    display(dq);

    printf("Removed front element: %d\n", removeFront(dq));
    printf("Removed rear element: %d\n", removeRear(dq));

    display(dq);

    printf("Is the dq empty? %s\n", isEmpty(dq) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(dq);

    return 0;
}

// CIRCULAR IMPLEMENTATION

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100

struct CircularQueue {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int front;
    int rear;
};

struct CircularQueue* createCircularQueue() {
    struct CircularQueue* q = (struct CircularQueue*)malloc(sizeof(struct CircularQueue));
   
    q->front = -1; 
    q->rear = -1;
    return q;
}

int isEmpty(struct CircularQueue* q) {
    return q->front == -1;
}

void enqueue(struct CircularQueue* q, int data) {
    if ((q->rear + 1) % MAX_SIZE == q->front) {
        printf("Queue is full. Cannot enqueue.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        q->front = 0;
    }
    q->rear = (q->rear + 1) % MAX_SIZE;
    q->items[q->rear] = data;
}

int dequeue(struct CircularQueue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot dequeue.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = q->items[q->front];
    if (q->front == q->rear) {
        q->front = q->rear = -1; 
    } else {
        q->front = (q->front + 1) % MAX_SIZE;
    }
    return data;
}

int peek(struct CircularQueue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot peek.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return q->items[q->front];
}

void display(struct CircularQueue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Circular Queue: ");
    int i = q->front;
    while (1) {
        printf("%d ", q->items[i]);
        if (i == q->rear) {
            break;
        }
        i = (i + 1) % MAX_SIZE;
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    struct CircularQueue* q = createCircularQueue();

    enqueue(q, 1);
    enqueue(q, 2);
    enqueue(q, 3);

    display(q);

    printf("Front element: %d\n", peek(q));

    printf("Dequeued element: %d\n", dequeue(q));

    display(q);

    printf("Is the circular q empty? %s\n", isEmpty(q) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(q);

    return 0;
}


// APPLICATIONS OF QUEUE

/*
•Queues are widely used as waiting lists for a single shared resource like printer, disk, CPU.
•Queues are used to transfer data asynchronously (data not necessarily received at same rate as sent) between two processes (IO buffers), e.g., pipes, file IO, sockets.
•Queues are used as buffers on MP3 players and portable CD players, iPod playlist.
•Queues are used in Playlist for jukebox to add songs to the end, play from the front of the list.
•Queues are used in operating system for handling interrupts.
*/

// LINKED LIST IMPLEMENTATION

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node* next;
};

struct Queue {
    struct Node* front;
    struct Node* rear;
};

struct Queue* createQueue() {
    struct Queue* q = (struct Queue*)malloc(sizeof(struct Queue));
    q->front = q->rear = NULL;
    return q;
}

int isEmpty(struct Queue* q) {
    return q->front == NULL;
}

void enqueue(struct Queue* q, int data) {
    struct Node* newNode = (struct Node*)malloc(sizeof(struct Node));
    newNode->data = data;
    newNode->next = NULL;

    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        q->front = q->rear = newNode;
    }
    else {
        q->rear->next = newNode;
        q->rear = newNode;
    }
}

int dequeue(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot dequeue.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = q->front->data;
    struct Node* temp = q->front;
    q->front = q->front->next;
    free(temp);
    return data;
}

int peek(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot peek.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return q->front->data;
}

void display(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty.\n");
        return;
    }
    printf("Queue: ");
    struct Node* current = q->front;
    while (current != NULL) {
        printf("%d ", current->data);
        current = current->next;
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main() {
    struct Queue* q = createQueue();

    enqueue(q, 1);
    enqueue(q, 2);
    enqueue(q, 3);

    display(q);

    printf("Front element: %d\n", peek(q));

    printf("Dequeued element: %d\n", dequeue(q));

    display(q);

    printf("Is the q empty? %s\n", isEmpty(q) ? "Yes" : "No");

    free(q);

    return 0;
}

    }
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = 0;
    }
    else if (dq->front == 0) {
        dq->front = MAX_SIZE - 1;
    }
    else {
        dq->front--;

    dq->items[dq->front] = data;
    dq->size++;
}

void addRear(struct Deque* dq, int data) {
    if (dq->size == MAX_SIZE) {
        printf("Deque is full. Cannot add at the rear.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = 0;
    } else if (dq->rear == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
        dq->rear = 0;
    } else {
        dq->rear++;
    }
    dq->items[dq->rear] = data;
    dq->size++;
}

int removeFront(struct Deque* dq) {
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        printf("Deque is empty. Cannot remove from the front.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = dq->items[dq->front];
    if (dq->front == dq->rear) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = -1; 
    } else if (dq->front == MAX_SIZE - 1) {
        dq->front = 0;
    } else {
        dq->front++;
    }
    dq->size--;
    return data;
}

int removeRear(struct Deque* dq) {
    if (isEmpty(dq)) {
        printf("Deque is empty. Cannot remove from the rear.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    int data = dq->items[dq->rear];
    if (dq->front == dq->rear) {
        dq->front = dq->rear = -1; 
    } else if (dq->rear == 0) {
        dq->rear = MAX_SIZE - 1;
    } else {
        dq->rear--;
    }
    dq->size--;
    return data;
}

[02/10/23, 9:35:27 AM] Satvik Saini: // min heap implementation

#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_HEAP_SIZE 100

struct MinHeap
{
    int arr[MAX_HEAP_SIZE];
    int size;
};

void swap(int *a, int *b)
{
    int temp = *a;
    *a = *b;
    *b = temp;
}

void minHeapify(struct MinHeap *heap, int i)
{
    int min_idx = i;
    int leftChild = 2 * i + 1;
    int rightChild = 2 * i + 2;

    if (leftChild < heap->size && heap->arr[leftChild] < heap->arr[min_idx])
        min_idx = leftChild;

    if (rightChild < heap->size && heap->arr[rightChild] < heap->arr[min_idx])
        min_idx = rightChild;

    if (min_idx != i)
    {
        swap(&heap->arr[i], &heap->arr[min_idx]);
        minHeapify(heap, min_idx);
    }
}

struct MinHeap *createMinHeap()
{
    struct MinHeap *heap = (struct MinHeap *)malloc(sizeof(struct MinHeap));
    heap->size = 0;
    return heap;
}

void push(struct MinHeap *heap, int data)
{
    if (heap->size >= MAX_HEAP_SIZE)
    {
        printf("Heap overflow!\n");
        return;
    }

    heap->arr[heap->size] = data;
    int i = heap->size;
    int parent_idx = (i - 1) / 2;
    heap->size++;

    while (i > 0 && heap->arr[i] < heap->arr[parent_idx])
    {
        swap(&heap->arr[i], &heap->arr[parent_idx]);
        i = parent_idx;
    }
}

int pop(struct MinHeap *heap)
{
    if (heap->size <= 0)
    {
        printf("Heap is empty!\n");
        return -1;
    }

    int root = heap->arr[0];
    heap->arr[0] = heap->arr[heap->size - 1];
    heap->size--;
    minHeapify(heap, 0);
    return root;
}

int top(struct MinHeap *heap)
{
    if (heap->size <= 0)
    {
        printf("Heap is empty!\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return heap->arr[0];
}

int isEmpty(struct MinHeap *heap)
{
    return (heap->size == 0);
}

int main()
{
    struct MinHeap *heap = createMinHeap();
    push(heap, 10);
    push(heap, 20);
    push(heap, 5);
    push(heap, 15);

    printf("Top element: %d\n", top(heap));

    printf("Elements popped from the heap: ");
    while (!isEmpty(heap))
    {
        printf("%d ", pop(heap));
    }

    free(heap);
    return 0;
}

// heap sort

#include <stdio.h>

void swap(int *a, int *b)
{
    int temp = *a;
    *a = *b;
    *b = temp;
}

void heapify(int arr[], int n, int i)
{
    int max_idx = i;      
    int left = 2 * i + 1; 
    int right = 2 * i + 2; 

    if (left < n && arr[left] > arr[max_idx])
        max_idx = left;

    if (right < n && arr[right] > arr[max_idx])
        max_idx = right;

    if (max_idx != i)
    {
        int temp = arr[i];
        arr[i] = arr[max_idx];
        arr[max_idx] = temp;

        heapify(arr, n, max_idx);
    }
}

void heapSort(int arr[], int n)
{
    // Build a max heap
    for (int i = n / 2 - 1; i >= 0; i--)
        heapify(arr, n, i);

    // One by one extract elements from the heap

    int heapsize = n;

    for (int i = n - 1; i > 0; i--)
    {
        // Move the current root to the end
        swap(arr[0], arr[heapsize - 1]);
        heapsize--;

        // Call heapify on the reduced heap
        heapify(arr, heapsize, 0);
    }
}

void printArray(int arr[], int n)
{
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        printf("%d ", arr[i]);
    printf("\n");
}

int main()
{
    int arr[] = {12, 11, 13, 5, 6, 7};
    int n = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]);

    printf("Unsorted array: \n");
    printArray(arr, n);

    heapSort(arr, n);

    printf("Sorted array: \n");
    printArray(arr, n);

    return 0;
}

[02/10/23, 10:21:30 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_SIZE 100

struct Queue {
    int items[MAX_SIZE];
    int front;
    int rear;
};

struct Queue* createQueue() {
    struct Queue* q = (struct Queue*)malloc(sizeof(struct Queue));
    q->front = -1;
    q->rear = -1;
    return q;
}

int isEmpty(struct Queue* q) {
    return q->front == -1;
}

int isFull(struct Queue* q) {
    return q->rear == MAX_SIZE - 1;
}

void push(struct Queue* q, int data) {
    if (isFull(q)) {
        printf("Queue is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        q->front = 0;
    }
    q->rear++;
    q->items[q->rear] = data;
}

void pop(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (q->front == q->rear) {
        q->front = q->rear = -1;
    } else {
        q->front++;
    }
}

int peek(struct Queue* q) {
    if (isEmpty(q)) {
        printf("Queue is empty. Cannot peek.\n");
        return -1;
    }
    return q->items[q->front];
}

struct stack {
    struct Queue* q1;
    struct Queue* q2;
};

struct stack* createstack() {
    struct stack* stk = (struct stack*)malloc(sizeof(struct stack));
    stk->q1 = createQueue(); // Initialize q1
    stk->q2 = createQueue(); // Initialize q2
    return stk;
}

void push_stack(struct stack* stk, int X) {
    if (isFull(stk->q1) || isFull(stk->q2)) {
        printf("Stack is full. Cannot push.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(stk->q1)) {
        push(stk->q1, X);
        while (!isEmpty(stk->q2)) {
            int num = peek(stk->q2);
            push(stk->q1, num);
            pop(stk->q2);
        }
    } else {
        push(stk->q2, X);
        while (!isEmpty(stk->q1)) {
            int num = peek(stk->q1);
            push(stk->q2, num);
            pop(stk->q1);
        }
    }
}

void pop_stack(struct stack* stk) {
    if (isEmpty(stk->q1) && isEmpty(stk->q2)) {
        printf("Stack is empty. Cannot pop.\n");
        return;
    }
    if (isEmpty(stk->q1)) {
        pop(stk->q2);
    } else {
        pop(stk->q1);
    }
}

int empty_stack(struct stack* stk) {
    return isEmpty(stk->q1) && isEmpty(stk->q2);
}

int top_stack(struct stack* stk) {
    if (isEmpty(stk->q1)) {
        return peek(stk->q2);
    }
    return peek(stk->q1);
}

int main() {
    struct stack* stk = createstack();
    push_stack(stk, 1);
    push_stack(stk, 2);
    push_stack(stk, 3);
    printf("%d\n", top_stack(stk));

    pop_stack(stk);
    printf("%d\n", top_stack(stk));

    return 0;
}

#include <stdlib.h>

#define MAX_HEAP_SIZE 100

typedef struct {
    int arr[MAX_HEAP_SIZE];
    int size;

{
    int temp = *a;
    *a = *b;
    *b = temp;

void createminheap(minheap* h){

    h = (minheap*)malloc(sizeof(minheap));
    h->size = 0; 
}

void push(minheap* h, int data){
    
    h->arr[h->size] = data;
    int child_idx = h->size;
    int parent_idx = (child_idx - 1)/2;
    

    while(child_idx != 0 && h->arr[child_idx] < h->arr[parent_idx]){
        swap(&h->arr[child_idx] , &h->arr[parent_idx]);
        child_idx = parent_idx;
        parent_idx = (child_idx - 1)/2;
    }
    h->size++;
}
void minheapify(minheap* h , int i){
    // only condition for this to work is that left subtree and right subtree of the given node hould follow heap property
     int min_idx = i;
     int lc = 2*i+1;
     int rc = 2*i+2;
     if(lc < h-> size && h->arr[min_idx] < h->arr[lc]){
        min_idx = lc;
     }
     if(rc < h-> size && h->arr[min_idx] < h->arr[rc]){
        min_idx = rc;
     }
    if(min_idx != i){
        swap(&h->arr[i] , &h->arr[min_idx]);
        minheapify(h , min_idx);
    }
    
}
void pop(minheap* h){

    h->arr[0] = h->arr[h->size - 1];
    h->size -- ;
    minheapify(h,0);

    // now i will have to place the new root node at its correct position 
}

    return h->size == 0;
}
int top(minheap* h){
    if(isEmpty(h)){
        return -1;
    }
    return h->arr[0];
}

[03/10/23, 4:08:35 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int compare(const void* a, const void* b) {
    return (*(int*)a - *(int*)b);
}

// Function to compare two arrays for equality (different order allowed)
int areArraysEqual(int arr1[], int arr2[], int n) {
    // Sort both arrays
    qsort(arr1, n, sizeof(int), compare);
    qsort(arr2, n, sizeof(int), compare);

    // Compare sorted arrays element by element
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (arr1[i] != arr2[i]) {
            return 0; // Arrays are not equal
        }
    }
    return 1; // Arrays are equal
}

[03/10/23, 6:38:14 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <stack>
using namespace std;

int prec(char ch)
{
    switch (ch)
    {
    case '^':
        return 3;
    case '*':
        return 2;
    case '/':
        return 2;
    case '+':
        return 1;
    case '-':
        return 1;
    default:
        return -1;
    }
}

int main()
{
    string s = "(a-b/c)*(a/k-l)";
    reverse(s.begin(),s.end());

    for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
        if(s[i] == '(') s[i] = ')';
        if(s[i] == ')') s[i] = '(';
    }

    stack<char> stk;
    string result;

    for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
    {
        char c = s[i];

        // If the scanned character is
        // an operand, add it to output string.
        if ((c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= '0' && c <= '9'))
            result += c;

        // If the scanned character is an
        // ‘(‘, push it to the stack.
        else if (c == '(')
            stk.push('(');

        // If the scanned character is an ‘)’,
        // pop and add to output string from the stack
        // until an ‘(‘ is encountered.
        else if (c == ')')
        {
            while (stk.top() != '(')
            {
                result += stk.top();
                stk.pop();
            }
            stk.pop();
        }

        // If an operator is scanned
        else
        {
            while (!stk.empty() && prec(s[i]) <= prec(stk.top()))
            {
                result += stk.top();
                stk.pop();
            }
            stk.push(c);
        }
    }

    // Pop all the remaining elements from the stack
    while (!stk.empty())
    {
        result += stk.top();
        stk.pop();
    }
    reverse(result.begin(),result.end());
    cout << result << endl;
}
[03/10/23, 6:42:33 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <stack>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

int prec(char ch)
{
    switch (ch)
    {
    case '^':
        return 3;
    case '*':
    case '/':
        return 2;
    case '+':
    case '-':
        return 1;
    default:
        return -1;
    }
}

int main()
{
    string s = "(a-b/c)*(a/k-l)";
    reverse(s.begin(), s.end());

    for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
    {
        if (s[i] == '(')
            s[i] = ')';
        else if (s[i] == ')')
            s[i] = '(';
    }

    stack<char> stk;
    string result;

    for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
    {
        char c = s[i];

        // If the scanned character is an operand or part of a multi-character operand, add it to the output string.
        if ((c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= '0' && c <= '9'))
            result += c;

        // If the scanned character is an ‘(‘, push it to the stack.
        else if (c == '(')
            stk.push('(');

        // If the scanned character is an ‘)’,
        // pop and add to the output string from the stack
        // until an ‘(‘ is encountered.
        else if (c == ')')
        {
            while (stk.top() != '(')
            {
                result += stk.top();
                stk.pop();
            }
            stk.pop(); // Pop the '('
        }

        // If an operator is scanned
        else
        {
            while (!stk.empty() && prec(s[i]) <= prec(stk.top()))
            {
                result += stk.top();
                stk.pop();
            }
            stk.push(c);
        }
    }

    // Pop all the remaining elements from the stack
    while (!stk.empty())
    {
        result += stk.top();
        stk.pop();
    }
    reverse(result.begin(), result.end());
    cout << result << endl;
}

[04/10/23, 7:20:51 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
#include <math.h>

struct Term
{
    int coeff;
    int exp;
};

struct Poly
{
    int n;
    struct Term *t;
};

void create(struct Poly *p)
{
    printf("Enter the no of terms : ");
    scanf("%d", &p->n);
    p->t = (struct Term *)malloc(p->n * sizeof(struct Term));
    printf("Enter the terms\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < p->n; i++){
        scanf("%d %d", &p->t[i].coeff, &p->t[i].exp);
    }
}

struct Poly *add(struct Poly *p1, struct Poly *p2)
{
    struct Poly *sum = (struct Poly *)malloc(sizeof(struct Poly));
    sum->t = (struct Term *)malloc((p1->n + p2->n) * sizeof(struct Term));

    int i = 0, j = 0, k = 0;

    while (i < p1->n && j < p2->n){
        if (p1->t[i].exp > p2->t[j].exp){
            sum->t[k++] = p1->t[i++];
        }
        else if (p1->t[i].exp < p2->t[j].exp){
            sum->t[k++] = p2->t[j++];
        }
        else{
            sum->t[k] = p1->t[i++];
            sum->t[k++].coeff += p2->t[j++].coeff;
        }
    }
    while (i < p1->n){
        sum->t[k++] = p1->t[i++];
    }
    while (j < p2->n){
        sum->t[k++] = p2->t[j++];
    }
    sum->n = k;
    return sum;
}

// struct Poly *multiply(struct Poly *p1, struct Poly *p2)
// {
//     struct Poly *result = (struct Poly *)malloc(sizeof(struct Poly));
//     result->t = (struct Term *)malloc((p1->n * p2->n) * sizeof(struct Term));
//     int k = 0;

//     for (int i = 0; i < p1->n; i++) {
//         for (int j = 0; j < p2->n; j++) {
//             result->t[k].coeff = p1->t[i].coeff * p2->t[j].coeff;
//             result->t[k].exp = p1->t[i].exp + p2->t[j].exp;
//             k++;
//         }
//     }

//     result->n = k;
//     return result;
// }

struct Poly* multiply(struct Poly* p1, struct Poly* p2)
{
    struct Poly* prod = (struct Poly*)malloc(sizeof(struct Poly));
    prod->n = p1->t[0].exp+p2->t[0].exp + 1;
    
    prod->t = (struct Term* )calloc(prod->n,sizeof(struct Term));

    for(int i=0;i<p1->n;i++){
        for(int j=0;j<p2->n;j++){
            prod->t[p1->t[i].exp+p2->t[j].exp].exp =  p1->t[i].exp+p2->t[j].exp;
            prod->t[p1->t[i].exp+p2->t[j].exp].coeff +=  p1->t[i].coeff*p2->t[j].coeff;
        }
    }
    return prod;
}

int evaluate(struct Poly p, int x){
    int sum = 0;
    for(int i=0;i<p.n;i++){
        sum += p.t[i].coeff*pow(x,p.t[i].exp);
    }
    return sum;
}

void display(struct Poly p)
{
    printf("Displaying the matrix :\n");
    for (int i = 0; i < p.n; i++){
        printf("%dx^%d+", p.t[i].coeff, p.t[i].exp);
    }
    printf("\n");
}

int main()
{
    struct Poly p1,p2,*sum,*prod;
    create(&p1);
    create(&p2);
    // printf("%d",evaluate(p1,1));
    prod = multiply(&p1,&p2);
    // create(&p2);
    // sum = add(&p1,&p2);
    // display(*sum);
    display(*prod);
}
[04/10/23, 7:21:21 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

struct Element
{
    int i;
    int j;
    int x;
};

struct Sparse
{
    int m;
    int n;
    int num;
    struct Element *ele;
};

void create(struct Sparse *s)
{
    printf("Enter the dimensions : ");
    scanf("%d %d", &s->m, &s->n);
    printf("Enter the number of non zero elements : ");
    scanf("%d", &s->num);
    s->ele = (struct Element *)malloc(s->num * sizeof(struct Element));
    printf("Enter the non zero elements : \n");
    for (int k = 0; k < s->num; k++) {
        scanf("%d %d %d", &s->ele[k].i, &s->ele[k].j, &s->ele[k].x);
    }
}

struct Sparse *add(struct Sparse *s1, struct Sparse *s2)
{
    if (s1->n != s2->n || s1->m != s2->m) {
        printf("Matrix addition is not possible!\n");
        return NULL;
    }

    struct Sparse *sum = (struct Sparse *)malloc(sizeof(struct Sparse));
    sum->ele = (struct Element *)malloc((s1->num + s2->num) * sizeof(struct Element));

    int i = 0, j = 0, k = 0;

    while (i < s1->num && j < s2->num){
        if (s1->ele[i].i > s2->ele[j].i){
            sum->ele[k++] = s2->ele[j++];
        }
        else if (s1->ele[i].i < s2->ele[j].i){
            sum->ele[k++] = s1->ele[i++];
        }
        else{
            if (s1->ele[i].j > s2->ele[j].j){
                sum->ele[k++] = s2->ele[j++];
            }
            else if (s1->ele[i].j < s2->ele[j].j){
                sum->ele[k++] = s1->ele[i++];
            }
            else{
                sum->ele[k] = s1->ele[i++];
                sum->ele[k].x += s2->ele[j++].x;
                k++;
            }
        }
    }
    while(i<s1->num){
        sum->ele[k++] = s1->ele[i++];
    }
    while(j<s2->num){
        sum->ele[k++] = s2->ele[j++];
    }
    sum->n = s1->n;
    sum->m = s1->m;
    sum->num = k;
    return sum;
}

struct Sparse *multiply(struct Sparse *s1, struct Sparse *s2)
{
    struct Sparse *result = (struct Sparse *)malloc(sizeof(struct Sparse));
    result->ele = (struct Element *)malloc(s1->num * s2->num * sizeof(struct Element));
    
    if (s1->n != s2->m) {
        printf("Matrix multiplication is not possible!\n");
        return NULL;
    }

    int k = 0;
    result->m = s1->m;
    result->n = s2->n;
    result->num = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i < s1->num; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < s2->num; j++) {
            if (s1->ele[i].j == s2->ele[j].i) {
                result->ele[k] = s1->ele[i];
                result->ele[k].x *= s2->ele[j].x;
                k++;
                result->num++;
            }
        }
    }
    return result;
}

struct Sparse* transpose(struct Sparse* s){
    struct Sparse* ans = (struct Sparse*)malloc(sizeof(struct Sparse));
    ans->ele = (struct Element*)malloc((s->num) * sizeof(struct Element));
    for(int k=0; k<s->num; k++){
        ans->ele[k].i = s->ele[k].j;
        ans->ele[k].j = s->ele[k].i;
        ans->ele[k].x = s->ele[k].x;
    }
    ans->m = s->n;
    ans->n = s->m;
    ans->num = s->num;
    return ans;
}

void display(struct Sparse s)
{
    printf("Displaying the matrix : \n");
    int k = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < s.m; i++){
        for (int j = 0; j < s.n; j++){
            if (i == s.ele[k].i && j == s.ele[k].j){
                printf("%d ", s.ele[k++].x);
            }
            else{
                printf("0 ");
            }
        }
        printf("\n");
    }
}

int main()
{
    struct Sparse s1,s2,*sum,*prod,*trans;
    create(&s1);
    // create(&s2);
    // sum = add(&s1,&s2);
    // prod = multiply(&s1,&s2);
    trans = transpose(&s1);
    // display(*sum);
    // display(*prod);
    display(*trans);
}

[05/10/23, 2:20:19 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;

class Person {
    string name;
    int age;
public:
    Person(const string& name, int age){
        this->name = name;
        this->age = age;
    }

    // Overload the << operator to customize the output
    friend ostream& operator<<(ostream& os, const Person& person) {
        os << "Name: " << person.name << ", Age: " << person.age;
        return os;
    }
};

int main() {
    Person p("Alice", 30);
    cout << "Person Information: " << p << endl;
    
    return 0;
}

[07/10/23, 12:09:35 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: bool isBiPartite() {
		bool flag = true; // assume graph is a biparite
		unordered_map<T, int> colorMap; // to store the mapping between
		// the vertices and their color
		for (pair<T, list<T>> vertex : neighbourMap) {
			T vertexLabel = vertex.first;
			if (colorMap.find(vertexLabel) == colorMap.end()) {
				// 'vertexLabel' not colored, hence not visited
				if (bfsHelper(vertexLabel, colorMap) == false) {
					// component is not bipartite
					flag = false;
					break;
				}
			}
		}

		return flag;
	}
};

[11/10/23, 6:59:51 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: void topologicalSort() {

		queue<T> q; // to keep track of vertices w/o any dependencies
		unordered_map<T, int> inDegMap; // to store the mapping b/w the
		// vertices and their in-degrees

		// populate the inDegMap

		for (pair<T, list<T>> vertex : neighbourMap) {
			list<T> neighbourList = vertex.second;
			for (T neighbour : neighbourList) {
				// account for directed edge from 'vertex' to 'neighbour'
				inDegMap[neighbour]++;
			}
		}

		// initialise queue with vertices w/o
		// any dependency i.e. zero in-degree

		for (pair<T, list<T>> vertex : neighbourMap) {
			T vertexLabel = vertex.first;
			if (inDegMap.find(vertexLabel) == inDegMap.end()) {
				// vertex with 'vertexLabel' has no dependency
				q.push(vertexLabel);
			}
		}

		while (!q.empty()) {
			T front = q.front();
			q.pop();

			// explore 'front'

			cout << front << " ";

			list<T> neighbourList = neighbourMap[front];
			for (T neighbour : neighbourList) {
				inDegMap[neighbour]--;
				if (inDegMap[neighbour] == 0) {
					// depencies of 'neighbour' have been resolved
					q.push(neighbour);
				}
			}

		}

		cout << endl;

	}

#include<list>
#include<unordered_map>
#include<unordered_set>
#include<queue>

using namespace std;


template <typename T>
class graph{
    bool isdirected;
    unordered_map<T , list<T> > neighbourMap;
    
    public:

    graph(bool flag = false){
        this->isdirected = flag;   
    }

    void addedge(T a , T b){
        // add an edge between a and b 
        // this means a become neighbour of b and b becomes neighbour of a 
        neighbourMap[a].push_back(b);
        if(!isdirected){
            neighbourMap[b].push_back(a);
        }
    }

    void print(){
        // iterate in te neighbour map 
        for(pair<T , list<T> >  P : neighbourMap){
            T vertex = P.first;
            list<T> neighbours = P.second;
            cout<<vertex<<" : ";
            for(T x : neighbours){
                cout<<x<<" ";
            }  
            cout<<endl;
        }
    }

    bool directed_backedge(){
        unordered_set<T> visited;
        for(pair<T,list<T> > p : neighbourMap){
            T vertexLabel = p.first;
            if(visited.find(vertexLabel) == visited.end()){
                // a new component is encountered
                unordered_set<T> function_stk;
                if(dfs_helper2(visited , vertexLabel , function_stk)){
                    return true;
                }
            }

        }
        return false;
    }
    void topologicalsort(){
        queue<T> q;
        unordered_map<T,int> indegreeMap;

        // populate the in degree map 
        // iterate in the neighbour map
        // populating the elements in the indegree map  
        for( pair<T , list<T> > p : neighbourMap){
            list<T> neighbourlist = p.second;
            for(T neighbour : neighbourlist ){
                indegreeMap[neighbour]++;
            }
        }
        // placing 0 indegree ones in queue 
        for(pair<T , list<T> > p : neighbourMap){
            T vertex_label = p.first;
            // if the dependency of tis neighbour becomes 
            if(indegreeMap.find(vertex_label) == indegreeMap.end()){
                q.push(vertex_label);
            }
        }
        // iterate on queue an pop and process the elements 
        while(!q.empty()){

            T front = q.front();
            q.pop();
            cout<<front<<" ";

            // process the 0 indegree element
            // reduce the indegree of all the neighbours of the front element 
            list<T> neighbourList = neighbourMap[front];
            for(T neighbour : neighbourList){
                indegreeMap[neighbour]--;
                if(indegreeMap[neighbour] == 0){
                    q.push(neighbour);
                }
            }
        


    }

}

[11/10/23, 7:12:10 PM] Satvik Saini: #include<iostream>
#include<map>
#include<list>
#include<unordered_set>
#include<queue>

using namespace std;

template <typename T>
class graph {

	unordered_map<T, list<T> > neighbourMap; // to store the graph representation

public :

	void addEdge(T u, T v) {
		// add a directed edge between vertex 'u' and 'v'
		neighbourMap[u].push_back(v);
	}

	void topologicalSort() {

		queue<T> q; // to keep track of vertices w/o any dependencies
		unordered_map<T, int> inDegMap; // to store the mapping b/w the
		// vertices and their in-degrees

		// populate the inDegMap

		for (pair<T, list<T> > vertex : neighbourMap) {
			list<T> neighbourList = vertex.second;
			for (T neighbour : neighbourList) {
				// account for directed edge from 'vertex' to 'neighbour'
				inDegMap[neighbour]++;
			}
		}

		// initialise queue with vertices w/o
		// any dependency i.e. zero in-degree

		for (pair<T, list<T> > vertex : neighbourMap) {
			T vertexLabel = vertex.first;
			if (inDegMap.find(vertexLabel) == inDegMap.end()) {
				// vertex with 'vertexLabel' has no dependency
				q.push(vertexLabel);
			}
		}

		while (!q.empty()) {
			T front = q.front();
			q.pop();

			// explore 'front'

			cout << front << " ";

			list<T> neighbourList = neighbourMap[front];
			for (T neighbour : neighbourList) {
				inDegMap[neighbour]--;
				if (inDegMap[neighbour] == 0) {
					// depencies of 'neighbour' have been resolved
					q.push(neighbour);
				}
			}
		}
	}
};

int main() {

	graph<char> g;

	g.addEdge('A', 'B');
	g.addEdge('A', 'C');
	g.addEdge('A', 'D');
	g.addEdge('B', 'D');
	g.addEdge('B', 'E');
	g.addEdge('D', 'C');
	g.addEdge('D', 'E');
	g.addEdge('D', 'F');
	g.addEdge('D', 'G');
	g.addEdge('D', 'H');
	g.addEdge('E', 'G');
	g.addEdge('F', 'C');
	g.addEdge('G', 'H');
	g.addEdge('H', 'F');

	g.topologicalSort();

	return 0;
}

#include<map>
#include<list>
#include<unordered_set>
#include<queue>

using namespace std;

template <typename T>
class graph {

	unordered_map<T, list<T> > neighbourMap; // to store the graph representation

public :

	void addEdge(T u, T v) {
		// add a directed edge between vertex 'u' and 'v'
		neighbourMap[u].push_back(v);
	}

	void topologicalSort() {

		queue<T> q; // to keep track of vertices w/o any dependencies
		unordered_map<T, int> inDegMap; // to store the mapping b/w the
		// vertices and their in-degrees

		// populate the inDegMap

		for (pair<T, list<T> > vertex : neighbourMap) {
			list<T> neighbourList = vertex.second;
			for (T neighbour : neighbourList) {
				// account for directed edge from 'vertex' to 'neighbour'
				inDegMap[neighbour]++;
			}
		}

		// initialise queue with vertices w/o
		// any dependency i.e. zero in-degree

		for (pair<T, list<T> > vertex : neighbourMap) {
			T vertexLabel = vertex.first;
			if (inDegMap.find(vertexLabel) == inDegMap.end()) {
				// vertex with 'vertexLabel' has no dependency
				q.push(vertexLabel);
			}
		}

		while (!q.empty()) {
			T front = q.front();
			q.pop();

			// explore 'front'

			cout << front << " ";

			list<T> neighbourList = neighbourMap[front];
			for (T neighbour : neighbourList) {
				inDegMap[neighbour]--;
				if (inDegMap[neighbour] == 0) {
					// depencies of 'neighbour' have been resolved
					q.push(neighbour);
				}
			}
		}
	}
};

using namespace std;

template <typename T>
class graph {

	unordered_map<T, list<T> > neighbourMap; // to store the graph representation

public :

	void addEdge(T u, T v) {
		// add a directed edge between vertex 'u' and 'v'
		neighbourMap[u].push_back(v);
	}

	void topologicalsort(){
        queue<T> q;
        unordered_map<T,int> indegreeMap;

        // populate the in degree map 
        // iterate in the neighbour map
        // populating the elements in the indegree map  
        for( pair<T , list<T> > p : neighbourMap){
            list<T> neighbourlist = p.second;
            for(T neighbour : neighbourlist ){
                indegreeMap[neighbour]++;

            }
        }
        for(pair<T , int > p : indegreeMap){
            T vertex_label = p.first;
            // if the dependency of tis neighbour becomes 
            cout<<vertex_label<<" ";
        }cout<<endl;

        // placing 0 indegree ones in queue 
        for(pair<T , list<T> > p : neighbourMap){
            T vertex_label = p.first;
            // if the dependency of tis neighbour becomes 
            if(indegreeMap.find(vertex_label) == indegreeMap.end()){
                q.push(vertex_label);

            }
        }
        
        // iterate on queue an pop and process the elements 
        while(!q.empty()){

            T front = q.front();
            q.pop();
            cout<<front<<" ";

            // process the 0 indegree element
            // reduce the indegree of all the neighbours of the front element 
            list<T> neighbourList = neighbourMap[front];
            for(T neighbour : neighbourList){
                indegreeMap[neighbour]--;
                if(indegreeMap[neighbour] == 0){
                    q.push(neighbour);
                }
            }
        


    }


}
