[03/01/24, 6:25:09 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    bool isPalindrome(string s){
        int i = 0;
        int j=s.size()-1;

        while(i<j){
            if(s[i] != s[j]) return false;

            i++;
            j--;
        }
        return true;

    }
    int longestPalin(int i, string s){

        // base case

        if(i == s.size())  return {0,0};


        // recursive case

        // you are at the ith index and you need to find the length of longest palindromic substr starting from i 
        int ans = {i,i};
        pair<int,int> pp;
        for(int j = i ; j<s.size() ; j++){

            if(isPalindrome(s.substr(i,j-i+1))){
                // if(j-i+1)
                pair<int,int> p = longestPalin(j+1,s);
                if(j-i > p.second - p.first ){
                    if(j-i > ans.second - ans.first){ 
                    pp.first = i;
                    pp.second = j;
                    } 
                }
                else{
                    if(p.second - p.first  > ans.second - ans.first){
                        pp.first = p.first;
                        pp.second = p.second;
                    }
                }

            }

        } 
        return ans;

    }
    string longestPalindrome(string s) {
        cout<< longestPalin(0,s);
        return "";
    }
};

[05/01/24, 9:53:13 AM] Satvik Saini: int dp[2001];
    int mod = 1e9+7;
    int fn(string &s, int i)
    {
        if(i==s.length())
            return 0;
        if(dp[i]!=-1)
            return dp[i];
        vector<int> vis(26,0);
        int  ans = 0;
        for(int j=i;j<s.length();j++)
        {
            if(vis[s[j]-'a'])
                continue;
            vis[s[j]-'a'] = 1;
            ans = (ans + 1 + fn(s,j+1))%mod;
        }
        return dp[i] = ans;
    }
    int distinctSubseqII(string s) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        return fn(s,0);
    }

[07/01/24, 10:17:45 AM] Satvik Saini: int minMovesToCaptureTheQueen(int a, int b, int c, int d, int e, int f) {
    if(a == e && !(a == c && d > min(b,f) && d < max(b,f) )) return 1; //rook and queen in same row
    if(b == f && !(b == d && c > min(a,e) && c < max(a,e) ))  return 1;  //rook and queen in the same column
    if(c + d == e + f && !(c + d == a + b && a > min(c , e) && a < max(c, e) )) return 1;  //bishop and queen in the same anti- diagonal
    if(c-d == e-f && !( c-d == a-b && a > min(c , e) && a < max(c, e) )) return 1;  // bishop and queen in the same diagonal
    return 2;
}

[07/01/24, 12:33:19 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:

    bool isBishopinpath(int rx, int ry, int bx, int by, int qx, int qy){

        if(qx == rx ){
            // check if bshop is in between 
            if(bx == rx && min(qy,ry) < by && max(qy,ry) > by){
                return true;
            }
            return false;
        }
        if(qy == ry){
            if(by == ry && min(qx,rx) < bx && max(qx,rx) > bx){
                return true;
            }
        }
            return false;

            

    }
    bool isrookinpath(int rx, int ry, int bx, int by, int qx, int qy){

        if(qx + qy == rx + ry || qx - qy == rx - ry || qy - qx == ry - rx){
            // diagonal is same 
            cout<<"helliii";
            if(rx > min(qx,bx) && rx < max(qx,bx) && ry > min(qy,by) && ry < max(qy,by)){
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;

    }
    int minMovesToCaptureTheQueen(int rx, int ry, int bx, int by, int qx, int qy) {
        if(qx+qy == bx+by || qx-qy == (bx-by) || qy - qx == by - bx ){
            if(!isrookinpath(rx,ry,bx,by,qx,qy)){
                // rook is not in path
                cout<<"in bishop move ";
                return 1; 
            }
            cout<<"hello"<<endl;

            return 2;

        }
        if(qx == rx || qy == ry){
            if(!isBishopinpath(rx,ry,bx,by,qx,qy)){
                cout<<"in rook move ";
                return 1;

            }
        }
            cout<<"hello"<<endl;

        return 2;
       
        
        
        
    }
};

[08/01/24, 4:13:13 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    bool f(int i, int j, string s, string t){
        if(i == j){
            if(s[i] == t[i]) return true;
            else return false;
        }
        for(int k = i; k<j;k++){
            string s1 = s.substr(i,k-i+1);
            string s2 = s.substr(k+1,j-k);
             string t1 = t.substr(i,k-i+1);
             string t2 = t.substr(k+1,j-k);
            if( (f(i,k,s1,t1) && f(k+1,j,s2,t2)) || (f(i,k,s2,t1) && f(k+1,j,s1,t2))) return true;
        }
        return false;
        
        
    }
    bool isScramble(string s1, string s2) {
        return f(0,s1.size()-1,s1,s2);
            
            
     

        
    }

[09/01/24, 7:36:06 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int CoinChangeTopDown(int n, vector<int> &den, vector<int> &dp){

    // base case
    if (n == 0){
        return 0;
    }

    // lookup
    if (dp[n] != -1){
        return dp[n];
    }

    // recursive case

    int ans = INT_MAX;
    for (int i = 0; i < den.size(); i++){
        if (n - den[i] >= 0){
            ans = min(ans, CoinChangeTopDown(n - den[i], den, dp));
        }
    }
    return dp[n] = (ans == INT_MAX) ? ans : 1 + ans;
}

    int coinChange(vector<int>& coins, int amount) {
        vector<int> dp(amount+1, -1);

        int ans = CoinChangeTopDown(amount, coins ,dp);
        return ans == INT_MAX ? -1 : ans;
    }
};

[09/01/24, 7:52:23 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    private:
    unordered_set<int> s;
    int f(vector<int>& arr, int start, int end){
        //base case
        if(start == end){
            return 0;
        }
        
        if(s.find(start) != s.end()){
            return 0;
        }
        
        //recursive case
        
        int count = INT_MAX;
        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++){
            count = min(count, f(arr, (start*arr[i])%100000, end));
        }
        return count == INT_MAX ? count : count + 1;
    }
  public:
    int minimumMultiplications(vector<int>& arr, int start, int end) {
       int ans = f(arr, start, end);
       
       return ans == INT_MAX ? -1 : ans;
       
    }
};

[09/01/24, 6:48:28 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:

    int ways(int amount, vector<int> &coins, int i, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        //base case
        if(i == coins.size()-1){
            return amount % coins[i] == 0;
        }

        //lookup
        if(dp[i][amount] != -1){
            return dp[i][amount];
        }

        //recursive case
        // do no take
        int x = ways(amount, coins, i+1, dp);

        //take
        int y = 0;
        if(coins[i] <= amount){
            y += ways(amount-coins[i], coins, i, dp);
        }

        return dp[i][amount] = x + y;
    }

    int change(int amount, vector<int>& coins) {
        vector<vector<int>> dp(coins.size()+1, vector<int>(amount+1, -1));

        return ways(amount, coins, 0, dp);
    }
};

[09/01/24, 9:28:12 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: # Closure

whenever a function is returned , it is never returned alone, it is always return with its lexical environment except  GEC  , so that you can use it even if the stack frames do not exist 

```
function fun(){
    let baba = "tanmay"
    function innerfunction(){
        console.log(baba);
    }
    return innerfunction;
}
// why are functions called first class citizens , or why are first class functions  when you assign a function to a variable it is called first class function
let returned_val = fun();// when you are returning an entire function this is what happens 

// let returned_val = function innerfunction(){
//     console.log(baba);
// }
// you expect that you should not be able to access the baba variable but you can , this is called closure  
console.log(returned_val);
```

gec appears as the anonymous 

- Closures :- whenever you return a function , it is never returned alone , it returns with the bundle of lexical environment along with it
- what is the use case of closure

→ it emulates the classes : ie it helps in privatization of methods and properties 

```jsx
function counter(){
    let count = 0;
    return {
        getcount : function(){
            console.log(count);
        },
        increment : function(){
            count++
        },
        reset : function(){
            count = 0;
        }
    }
}
let countrrr = counter()
countrrr.getcount();
```

→ we can access the count variable because all the functions are coming back with their lexical scope

[11/01/24, 7:34:02 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎Voice call, ‎9 min
[11/01/24, 7:37:50 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
    public:
    pair<int,int> f(TreeNode* root){

        // base case
        if(!root){
            return {INT_MAX, 0};
        }

        // recursive case
        pair<int, int> p;
        pair<int,int> p_r = f(root->right); // : (minimum value , maximum diff )
        pair<int,int> p_l = f(root -> left); // : (minimum value , maximum diff )
        p.second = max(p_r.second, max(p_l.second, max(root->val - p_r.first, root->val - p_l.first)));
        p.first = min({p_r.first,p_l.first,root->val});
        return p;
    }
    int maxAncestorDiff(TreeNode* root) {
        return f(root).second;
        
    }
};

[12/01/24, 10:29:08 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int lenLongestFibSubseq(vector<int>& A) {
        unordered_map<int, int> m;
        int N = A.size(), res = 0;
        int dp[N][N];
        for (int j = 0; j < N; ++j) {
            m[A[j]] = j;
            for (int i = 0; i < j; ++i) {
                int k = m.find(A[j] - A[i]) == m.end() ? -1 : m[A[j] - A[i]];
                dp[i][j] = (A[j] - A[i] < A[i] && k >= 0) ? dp[k][i] + 1 : 2;
                res = max(res, dp[i][j]);
            }
        }
        return res > 2 ? res : 0;
    }
[12/01/24, 10:29:21 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: Another solution is kind of dp.
dp[a, b] represents the length of fibo sequence ends up with (a, b)
Then we have dp[a, b] = (dp[b - a, a] + 1 ) or 2
The complexity reduce to O(N^2).
In C++/Java, I use 2D dp and index as key.
In Python, I use value as key.
[12/01/24, 12:27:49 PM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/make-array-strictly-increasing/?envType=list&envId=50wroh7h
[12/01/24, 12:27:54 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:

    int minMoves(vector<int>& arr1, vector<int>& arr2, int n, int m, int i, int j){
        //base case
        if(i == n-1){
            return 0;
        }
        if(j == m){
            return INT_MAX;
        }

        //recursive case
        if(arr1[i]<arr1[i+1]){
            // no need to do any operation
            return minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, i+1, j);
        }
        // operation need to be done to make arr1 strictly increasing

        int moves = INT_MAX;

        //op1 : make arr1[i] smaller than arr[i+1] but greater than arr[i-1]
        // can be done replacing some number from arr2

        for(int k=j;k<m;k++){
            if(i == 0){
                if(arr2[k] < arr1[i+1]){
                    moves = min(moves, minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, i+1, k+1));
                }
            }
            else{
                if(arr2[k] < arr1[i+1] && arr2[k] > arr1[i-1]){
                    moves = min(moves, minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, i+1, k+1));
                }
            }
        }

        //op2 : make arr1[i+1] greater than arr1[i]
        for(int k=j;k<m;k++){
            if(arr2[k] > arr1[i]){
                moves = min(moves, minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, i+1, k+1));
            }
        }

        return moves == INT_MAX ? moves : 1 + moves;
    }

    int makeArrayIncreasing(vector<int>& arr1, vector<int>& arr2) {
        sort(arr2.begin(), arr2.end());

        int n = arr1.size();
        int m = arr2.size();

        int ans = minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, 0, 0);

        return ans == INT_MAX ? -1 : ans;
    }
};

[12/01/24, 12:41:27 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:

    int minMoves(vector<int>& arr1, vector<int>& arr2, int n, int m, int i, int j){
        //base case
        if(i == n-1){
            return 0;
        }
        if(j == m){
            return INT_MAX;
        }

        //recursive case
        if(arr1[i] < arr1[i+1]){
            // no need to do any operation
            return minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, i+1, j);
        }
        // operation need to be done to make arr1 strictly increasing

        int moves = INT_MAX;

        //op1 : make arr1[i] smaller than arr[i+1] but greater than arr[i-1]
        // can be done replacing some number from arr2

        for(int k=j;k<m;k++){
            if(i == 0){
                if(arr2[k] < arr1[i+1]){
                    int temp = arr1[i];
                    arr1[i] = arr2[k];
                    moves = min(moves, minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, i+1, k+1));
                    arr1[i] = temp;
                }
            }
            else{
                if(arr2[k] < arr1[i+1] && arr2[k] > arr1[i-1]){
                    int temp = arr1[i];
                    arr1[i] = arr2[k];
                    moves = min(moves, minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, i+1, k+1));
                    arr1[i] = temp;
                }
            }
        }

        //op2 : make arr1[i+1] greater than arr1[i]
        for(int k=j;k<m;k++){
            if(arr2[k] > arr1[i]){
                int temp = arr1[i+1];
                arr1[i+1] = arr2[k];
                moves = min(moves, minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, i+1, k+1));
                arr1[i+1] = temp;
            }
        }

        return moves == INT_MAX ? moves : 1 + moves;
    }

    int makeArrayIncreasing(vector<int>& arr1, vector<int>& arr2) {
        sort(arr2.begin(), arr2.end());

        int n = arr1.size();
        int m = arr2.size();

        int ans = minMoves(arr1, arr2, n, m, 0, 0);

        return ans == INT_MAX ? -1 : ans;
    }
};

[12/01/24, 1:02:51 PM] Satvik Saini: vector<vector<int>> multiSourceBFS(vector<vector<int>> mat, int m, int n)
{
    vector<vector<int>> dist(m, vector<int>(n, INT_MAX));
    queue<pair<int, int>> q;

    // initialisation of multi-source BFS

    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            if (mat[i][j] == 0) {
                
                // (i,j)th cell corresponds to source vertex
                q.push({i, j});
                dist[i][j] = 0;
            }
        }
    }

    while (!q.empty()) {
        pair<int, int> front = q;
        q.pop();

        int i = front.first;
        int j = front.second;

        vector<int> dx = {0, 0, 1, -1};
        vector<int> dy = {1, -1, 0, 0};

        for (int k = 0; k < 4; k++) {
            int ii = i + dx[k];
            int jj = j + dy[k];

            if (ii >= 0 && ii < m && jj >= 0 && jj < n && dist[ii][jj] == INT_MAX) {

                // vertex {ii,jj} is not yet visited (dist[ii][jj] == INT_MAX)
                q.push({ii, jj});
                dist[ii][jj] = dist[i][j] + 1;  // dist(child) = 1 + dist(parent)
            }
        }
    }
}

int main() {
    vector<vector<int>> mat = {
        {0, 1, 1, 1, 0},
        {1, 1, 1, 1, 1},
        {1, 1, 0, 1, 1},
        {1, 1, 1, 1, 1},
        {0, 1, 1, 1, 0},
    }

    int m = mat.size();
    int n = mat[0].size();

    vector<vector<int>> out = miltiSourceBFS(mat, m, n);

    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            cout << mat[i][j] << " ";
        }
        cout << endl;
    }
    return 0;
}
[12/01/24, 1:18:07 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
    public int makeArrayIncreasing(int[] arr1, int[] arr2) {
        if (arr1 == null || arr1.length == 0) return -1;
        if (arr1.length == 1) return 0;
        TreeSet<Integer> ts = new TreeSet<>();
        if (arr2 != null) {
            for (int i = 0; i < arr2.length; i++) ts.add(arr2[i]);
        }
        
        int[][] dp = new int[arr1.length + 1][arr1.length + 1];
        for (int i = 0; i < dp.length; i++) Arrays.fill(dp[i], Integer.MAX_VALUE);
        dp[0][0] = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        
        for (int j = 1; j < dp.length; j++) {
            for (int i = 0; i <= j; i++) {
                if (arr1[j - 1] > dp[i][j - 1]) {
                    dp[i][j] = arr1[j - 1];
                }
                if (i > 0 && ts.higher(dp[i - 1][j - 1]) != null) {
                    dp[i][j] = Math.min(dp[i][j], ts.higher(dp[i - 1][j - 1]));
                }
                if (j == dp.length - 1 && dp[i][j] != Integer.MAX_VALUE) return i; 
            } 
        }
        return -1;
    }
}\
[12/01/24, 1:19:09 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution:
    def makeArrayIncreasing(self, arr1: List[int], arr2: List[int]) -> int:
        dp = {-1:0}
        arr2.sort()
        for i in arr1:
            tmp = collections.defaultdict(lambda: float('inf'))
            for key in dp:
                if i > key:
                    tmp[i] = min(tmp[i],dp[key])
                loc = bisect.bisect_right(arr2,key)
                if loc < len(arr2):
                    tmp[arr2[loc]] = min(tmp[arr2[loc]],dp[key]+1)
            dp = tmp
        if dp:
            return min(dp.values())
        return -1
[12/01/24, 1:20:06 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int help(map<pair<int,int>,int>&m,int prev,int i,vector<int>& arr1, vector<int>& arr2)
    {
        if(i==arr1.size())return 0;
        if(m.find({i,prev})!=m.end())return m[{i,prev}];
        int ans=INT_MAX/2;
        int f=upper_bound(arr2.begin(),arr2.end(),prev)-arr2.begin();
        if(arr1[i]>prev)ans=min(ans,help(m,arr1[i],i+1,arr1,arr2));
        if(f<arr2.size())ans=min(ans,help(m,arr2[f],i+1,arr1,arr2)+1);
        return m[{i,prev}]=ans;
    }
    int makeArrayIncreasing(vector<int>& arr1, vector<int>& arr2) 
    {
        sort(arr2.begin(),arr2.end());
        map<pair<int,int>,int> m;
        int ans= help(m,INT_MIN,0,arr1,arr2);
        return ans>=INT_MAX/4?-1:ans;
    }
};
[12/01/24, 1:20:11 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: c++
[12/01/24, 1:22:27 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: -> The maximum number of operations we can apply is equal to 'm' (size of vector 'b'). We will return -1 if the number of operations exceeds 'm'.
-> Sort the vector 'b'.
-> Initialize a 2D vector 'dp' of size 'n+1' by 'm+1', where 'n' is the size of vector 'a' and 'm' is the size of vector 'b'.
-> Initialize the previous value 'x' with -1, as there are no negative values in the array.
-> Check the base cases.
-> If 'j == m' and 'a[i] <= x', it means we can't make the array increasing, so return 'mx'.
-> If 'j < m', it means we can swap the next element of vector 'a' with an element from vector 'b' i.e. we can take an element from vector 'b', so increment the number of operations by 1 and make a recursive call.
-> Another case is if 'a[i] > x', i.e., if the current element of vector 'a' is greater than the previous one, then there is no need to take an element from vector 'b' and make a recursive call with that.
-> Return the answer as the minimum of 'take' and 'notTake' while storing it in the 'dp' tab
[12/01/24, 1:22:33 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Intuition
-> The first thing that comes to mind when we encounter questions where we need to choose which element to take or not take for minimum operations/cost/path is recursion + dynamic programming (DP).
[12/01/24, 1:25:35 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int mx,n,m;
    int solve(vector<int>&a,vector<int>&b,vector<vector<int>>&dp,int i,int j,int x){
        if(i>=n)return 0;
        j=upper_bound(b.begin()+j,b.end(),x)-b.begin();
        if(j==m && a[i]<=x)return mx;
        if(dp[i][j]!=-1)return dp[i][j];
        int take=mx,notTake=mx;
        if(j<m)take=solve(a,b,dp,i+1,j+1,b[j])+1;
        if(a[i]>x)notTake=solve(a,b,dp,i+1,j,a[i]);
        return dp[i][j]=min(take,notTake);
    }
    int makeArrayIncreasing(vector<int>& a, vector<int>&b) {
        n=a.size(),m=b.size();
        mx=m+1;
        sort(b.begin(),b.end());
        vector<vector<int>>dp(n+1,vector<int>(m+1,-1));
        int x=solve(a,b,dp,0,0,-1);
        if(x==mx)return -1;
        return x;
    }
};
[12/01/24, 1:29:19 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: this solution doesn't work anymore because there is some cases where same i and j value but different last value, which will give different answer, i fixed it by adding some array, just look at my code

class Solution {
public:
[12/01/24, 1:29:29 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int memo[2002][2002][3];

int dp(int a,int b,int w,vector<int>& arr1,vector<int>& arr2) {
    if (a == arr1.size()) return 0;

    int last;
    if (w == 0) last = -1;
    else if (w == 1) last = arr1[a-1];
    else last = arr2[b];
    // last[1] -> take the arr1 value
    // last[2] -> take the arr2 value

    b = (upper_bound(arr2.begin(),arr2.end(),last) - arr2.begin());

    if (memo[a][b][w] != -1) return memo[a][b][w];

    int ret = 1e9;

    // don't take the arr2 value
    if (arr1[a] > last) ret = min(ret,dp(a+1,b,1,arr1,arr2));

    // take the arr2 value
    if (b < arr2.size()) ret = min(ret,dp(a+1,b,2,arr1,arr2) + 1);

    return memo[a][b][w] = ret;
}

int makeArrayIncreasing(vector<int>& arr1, vector<int>& arr2) {
    sort(arr2.begin(),arr2.end());
    memset(memo,-1,sizeof memo);
    int ans = dp(0,0,0,arr1,arr2);
    if (ans == 1e9) return -1;
    return ans;
}

[13/01/24, 4:19:29 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int findMinIndex(int arr[], int N, int idx, int val) {
    int result = INT_MAX;
    int currentOr = 0;

    for (int i = idx; i < N; i++) {
        currentOr |= arr[i];

        while (currentOr >= val) {
            result = min(result, i - idx + 1);
            currentOr ^= arr[idx++];
        }
    }

    return (result == INT_MAX) ? -1 : result;

[13/01/24, 4:20:42 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

struct TrieNode {
    TrieNode* child[2];
    int count;

    TrieNode() : count(0) {
        child[0] = child[1] = nullptr;
    }
};

class Trie {
public:
    Trie() {
        root = new TrieNode();
    }

    void insert(int num) {
        TrieNode* node = root;
        for (int i = 31; i >= 0; i--) {
            int bit = (num >> i) & 1;
            if (!node->child[bit]) {
                node->child[bit] = new TrieNode();
            }
            node = node->child[bit];
            node->count++;
        }
    }

    int query(int val, int prefix) {
        TrieNode* node = root;
        int result = 0;

        for (int i = 31; i >= 0; i--) {
            int valBit = (val >> i) & 1;
            int prefixBit = (prefix >> i) & 1;

            if (valBit == 1 && prefixBit == 0) {
                if (node->child[1]) {
                    result |= (1 << i);
                    node = node->child[1];
                } else {
                    return -1; // No such index i exists
                }
            } else if (valBit == 0 && prefixBit == 0) {
                if (node->child[0]) {
                    node = node->child[0];
                } else {
                    return -1; // No such index i exists
                }
            } else if (valBit == 1 && prefixBit == 1) {
                if (node->child[1]) {
                    node = node->child[1];
                } else {
                    return -1; // No such index i exists
                }
            } else { // valBit == 0 && prefixBit == 1
                if (node->child[0]) {
                    result |= (1 << i);
                    node = node->child[0];
                } else {
                    return -1; // No such index i exists
                }
            }
        }

        return result;
    }

private:
    TrieNode* root;
};

int findMinIndex(int arr[], int N, int idx, int val) {
    Trie trie;
    trie.insert(0);

    int prefix = 0;
    int result = -1;

    for (int i = idx; i < N; i++) {
        prefix |= arr[i];
        trie.insert(prefix);

        int res = trie.query(val, prefix);
        if (res != -1 && (result == -1 || res < result)) {
            result = res;
        }
    }

    return result;
}

int main() {
    int N, idx, val;
    cout << "Enter the size of the array (N): ";
    cin >> N;

    int arr[N];
    cout << "Enter the array elements: ";
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        cin >> arr[i];
    }

    cout << "Enter the index (idx): ";
    cin >> idx;

    cout << "Enter the value (val): ";
    cin >> val;

    int result = findMinIndex(arr, N, idx, val);

    if (result != -1) {
        cout << "Minimum index i: " << result << endl;
    } else {
        cout << "No such index i exists." << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}

[13/01/24, 4:39:48 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

struct Node {
    int value;
};

class SegmentTree {
public:
    SegmentTree(int n) {
        size = 1;
        while (size < n) {
            size *= 2;
        }
        tree.resize(2 * size, {0});
    }

    void build(vector<int>& arr, int v, int tl, int tr) {
        if (tl == tr) {
            if (tl < arr.size()) {
                tree[v].value = arr[tl];
            }
        } else {
            int tm = (tl + tr) / 2;
            build(arr, 2 * v, tl, tm);
            build(arr, 2 * v + 1, tm + 1, tr);
            tree[v].value = tree[2 * v].value | tree[2 * v + 1].value;
        }
    }

    int query(int v, int tl, int tr, int l, int r, int val) {
        if (l > r) {
            return -1;
        }
        if (l == tl && r == tr) {
            if ((tree[v].value & val) == val) {
                return -1; // Subarray already satisfies the condition
            }
            if (tl == tr) {
                return tl; // Single element, not satisfying the condition
            }
        }
        
        int tm = (tl + tr) / 2;
        int left = query(2 * v, tl, tm, l, min(r, tm), val);
        if (left != -1) {
            return left;
        }
        return query(2 * v + 1, tm + 1, tr, max(l, tm + 1), r, val);
    }

    void update(int v, int tl, int tr, int pos, int new_val) {
        if (tl == tr) {
            tree[v].value = new_val;
        } else {
            int tm = (tl + tr) / 2;
            if (pos <= tm) {
                update(2 * v, tl, tm, pos, new_val);
            } else {
                update(2 * v + 1, tm + 1, tr, pos, new_val);
            }
            tree[v].value = tree[2 * v].value | tree[2 * v + 1].value;
        }
    }

private:
    int size;
    vector<Node> tree;
};

int findMinIndex(int arr[], int N, int idx, int val) {
    SegmentTree segmentTree(N);
    segmentTree.build(vector<int>(arr, arr + N), 1, 0, N - 1);

    int result = -1;
    for (int i = idx; i < N; i++) {
        int res = segmentTree.query(1, 0, N - 1, idx, i, val);
        if (res != -1 && (result == -1 || res < result)) {
            result = res;
        }
    }

    return result;
}

int main() {
    int N, idx, val;
    cout << "Enter the size of the array (N): ";
    cin >> N;

    int arr[N];
    cout << "Enter the array elements: ";
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        cin >> arr[i];
    }

    cout << "Enter the index (idx): ";
    cin >> idx;

    cout << "Enter the value (val): ";
    cin >> val;

    int result = findMinIndex(arr, N, idx, val);

    if (result != -1) {
        cout << "Minimum index i: " << result << endl;
    } else {
        cout << "No such index i exists." << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}

[13/01/24, 6:50:10 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int superEggDrop(int K, int N) {
        vector<vector<int>> dp(N + 1, vector<int>(K + 1, 0));
        int m = 0;
        while (dp[m][K] < N) {
            m++;
            for (int k = 1; k <= K; ++k)
                dp[m][k] = dp[m - 1][k - 1] + dp[m - 1][k] + 1;
        }
        return m;
    }

[14/01/24, 9:18:53 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> beautifulIndices(string& ss, string& aa, string& bb, int k) {

          
        vector<int> vec;
        unsigned int s = ss.size();
        unsigned int a = aa.size();
        unsigned int b = bb.size();
        int prev_j = -1;
        if(s < a || s < b) return vec;
        for(int i=0 ; i<=s-a ; i++){
            if(  ss.substr(i,a) == aa){
                // cout<<i<<endl;
                if(prev_j <= i+k && prev_j>=i-k && prev_j != -1 && prev_j+b-1 <= i+k && prev_j>=0 && prev_j<=s-b){
                    // yes just directly add i 
                    // does prev j exist in the new window ? 
                    vec.push_back(i);
                }
                else{
                    for(int j = i-k ; j<=i+k ; j++){
                    
                        if(j>=0 && j<=s-b ){
                            if(ss.substr(j,b) == bb){
                            prev_j = j;
                            vec.push_back(i);
                            break;
                                }
                            }
                        }
                   }   
            }
        }
        // sort(vec.begin(), vec.end());
        return vec;
         
    }
};

        vector<int> ans;
        
        if(a.length() > s.length() || b.length() > s.length()) return ans;
        
        for(int i=0;i<=s.length() - a.length();i++){
            if(s.substr(j, b.length()) == b){
                arr.push_back(j);
            }
            if(s.substr(i, a.length()) == a){
                int ul = s.length() - b.length() > i+k ? i+k : s.length() - b.length();
                for(int j=max(i-k,0);j<=ul;j++){
                    if(s.substr(j, b.length()) == b){
                        ans.push_back(i);
                        break;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        return ans;
    }

[19/01/24, 11:48:03 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int minPath(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int n, int m, int i, int j, vector<vector<int>>& dp){
        //base case
        if(i == n-1){
            return matrix[i][j];
        }

        //lookup
        if(dp[i][j] != INT_MIN){
            return dp[i][j];
        }

        //recursive case

        //op1 : go down
        int ans = minPath(matrix, n, m, i+1, j, dp);

        //op2 : go down left diagonal
        if(j - 1 >= 0){
            ans = min(ans, minPath(matrix, n, m, i+1, j-1, dp));
        }

        //op2 : go down right diagonal
        if(j + 1 < m){
            ans = min(ans, minPath(matrix, n, m, i+1, j+1, dp));
        }

        return dp[i][j] = ans + matrix[i][j];
    }
public:
    int minFallingPathSum(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {
        int n = matrix.size();
        int m = matrix[0].size();

        int ans = INT_MAX;
        for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
            vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1, vector<int>(m+1, INT_MIN));
            ans = min(ans, minPath(matrix, n, m, 0, j, dp));
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

[19/01/24, 1:47:31 PM] Satvik Saini: int minPathBottomUp(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int n, int m){
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1, vector<int>(m+1));

        for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
            dp[n-1][j] = matrix[n-1][j];
        }

        for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){
            for(int j=m-1;j>=0;j--){
                //op1 : go down
                int ans = dp[i+1][j];

                //op2 : go down left diagonal
                if(j - 1 >= 0){
                    ans = min(ans, dp[i+1][j-1]);
                }

                //op2 : go down right diagonal
                if(j + 1 < m){
                    ans = min(ans, dp[i+1][j+1]);
                }

                dp[i][j] = ans + matrix[i][j];
            }
        }

        int mini = dp[0][0];
        
        for(int j=1;j<m;j++){
            mini = min(mini, dp[0][j]);
        }
        return mini; 
    }
public:
    int minFallingPathSum(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {
        int n = matrix.size();
        int m = matrix[0].size();

        return minPathBottomUp(matrix, n, m);
    }
};

[20/01/24, 11:30:39 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int search(vector<int>& nums, int target) 
{
        auto skip_left  = [&]( int x) { return x >= nums[0] ? numeric_limits<int>::min() : x; };
        auto skip_right = [&] (int x) { return x < nums[0] ? numeric_limits<int>::max() : x; };
        auto adjust = [&] (int x) { return target < nums[0] ? skip_left(x) : skip_right(x); };
  
        auto it = lower_bound( nums.begin(), nums.end(), target, [&] (int x, int y) { return adjust(x) < adjust(y); } );
            
        return it != nums.end() && *it == target ? it-nums.begin() : -1;
}
[20/01/24, 11:31:36 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int search(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
    int lo = 0, hi = nums.size();
    while (lo < hi) {
        int mid = (lo + hi) / 2;
        
        double num = (nums[mid] < nums[0]) == (target < nums[0])
                   ? nums[mid]
                   : target < nums[0] ? -INFINITY : INFINITY;
                   
        if (num < target)
            lo = mid + 1;
        else if (num > target)
            hi = mid;
        else
            return mid;
    }
    return -1;
}

[21/01/24, 9:23:22 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> countOfPairs(int n, int x, int y) {
        
        vector<int> adj[n+1];
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            adj[i].push_back(i+1);
            adj[i+1].push_back(i);
        }
        adj[x].push_back(y);
        adj[y].push_back(x);
        
        vector<vector<int>> distMap(n+1, vector<int>(n+1));
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            distMap[i][i] = 0;
            unordered_set<int> visited;
            visited.insert(i);
            queue<int> q;
            q.push(i);
            
            while(!q.empty()){
                int front = q.front();
                q.pop();
                for(auto neighbour : adj[front]){
                    if(visited.find(neighbour) == visited.end()){
                        distMap[i][neighbour] = distMap[i][front] + 1;
                        q.push(neighbour);
                        visited.insert(neighbour);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=n;j++){
                mp[distMap[i][j]]++;
            }
        }
        
        vector<int> ans;
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            ans.push_back(mp[i]);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[21/01/24, 10:48:52 AM] Satvik Saini: int minimumPushes(string word) {
    vector<int> freq(26, 0);
    for(auto c: word) freq[c - 'a']++;
    sort(freq.begin(), freq.end(), greater<int>());
    int ans = 0;
    for(int i = 0; i < 26; i++){
        ans += freq[i]*((i/8) + 1);
    }
    return ans;
}

public:
    int minimumPushes(string word) {
        int n = word.size();
        
        if(n <= 8) return n;
        n = n-8;
        if(n <= 8) return 2*n + 8;
        n = n-8;
        if(n <= 8) return 3*n + 16+8;
        n = n-8;
        return 4*n +24+16+8;
        
        
    }
};
[21/01/24, 11:06:55 AM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> countOfPairs(int n, int x, int y) {
        // to make sure that x<=y in every case
        if(x>y)
            return countOfPairs(n, y, x);
        
        vector<int> res(n, 0);
        
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<i;j++){
                int idx = i-j;          
                idx = min(idx, abs(j-x) + 1 + abs(i-y));
                if(idx>=1)
                    res[idx-1]+=2;  // add 2 as we can go from j->i and i->j
            }
        }
        return res;
        
    }

[21/01/24, 3:05:47 PM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-increasing-path-in-a-matrix/
[21/01/24, 3:05:55 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> dx = {0,0,1,-1};
    vector<int> dy = {1,-1,0,0};
    int f(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int m, int n, int i, int j, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
    
        if(dp[i][j] != -1) return dp[i][j];

        int cnt = 1;
        for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
            int ii = i + dx[k];
            int jj = j + dy[k];

            if(ii >=0 && ii < m && jj >= 0 && jj < m && matrix[ii][jj] > matrix[i][j]){
                cnt = max(cnt, 1 + f(matrix, m, n, ii, jj, dp));
            }
        }

        return dp[i][j] = cnt;

    }

    int longestIncreasingPath(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {

        int ans = 0;
        int m = matrix.size();
        int n = matrix[0].size();

        vector<vector<int>> dp(m, vector<int>(n, -1));

        for(int i=0;i<m;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                ans = max(ans, f(matrix, m, n, i, j, dp));
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

[21/01/24, 7:12:45 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int shortestPathAllKeys(vector<string>& grid) {
        int x = -1, y = -1, m = grid.size(), n = grid[0].size(), max_len = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
                char c = grid[i][j];
                if (c == '@') {
                    x = i;
                    y = j;
                }
                if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f') {
                    max_len = max(c - 'a' + 1, max_len);
                }
            }
        }

        vector<int> start = {0, x, y};
        queue<vector<int>> q;
        unordered_set<string> visited;
        visited.insert(to_string(0) + " " + to_string(x) + " " + to_string(y));
        q.push(start);
        int step = 0;
        vector<vector<int>> dirs{{-1, 0}, {1, 0}, {0, 1}, {0, -1}};

        while (!q.empty()) {
            int size = q.size();
            for (int k = 0; k < size; ++k) {
                vector<int> curr = q.front();
                q.pop();
                if (curr[0] == (1 << max_len) - 1)
                    return step;
                for (auto& d : dirs) {
                    int i = curr[1] + d[0];
                    int j = curr[2] + d[1];
                    int keys = curr[0];
                    if (i >= 0 && i < m && j >= 0 && j < n) {
                        char c = grid[i][j];
                        if (c == '#')
                            continue;
                        if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f')
                            keys |= 1 << (c - 'a');
                        if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F' &&
                            ((keys >> (c - 'A')) & 1) == 0) {
                            continue;
                        }
                        if (!visited.count(to_string(keys) + " " + to_string(i) + " " + to_string(j))) {
                            visited.insert(to_string(keys) + " " + to_string(i) + " " + to_string(j));
                            q.push({keys, i, j});
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
            ++step;
        }
        return -1;
    }
};

[24/01/24, 8:01:54 AM] Satvik Saini: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
    int countPaths(TreeNode* root, vector<int> &freq, int len){
        //base case
        if(root == NULL){
            return 0;
        }
        if(root->left == NULL && root->right == NULL){
            freq[root->val]++;
            len++;
            int cnt_duplicates = 0;
            int cnt_ones = 0;
            for(int i=1;i<=9;i++){
                for(int j=0;j<freq[i];j++){
                    cout<<i<<" ";
                }
                if(freq[i] == 1) cnt_ones++;
                if(freq[i] % 2 == 0) cnt_duplicates += freq[i] / 2;
            }
            cout<<endl;

            if((len%2 != 0 && cnt_ones == 1 && cnt_duplicates == (len - 1) / 2) || (len%2 == 0 && cnt_ones == 0 && cnt_duplicates == len / 2) || (cnt_ones == 0 && cnt_duplicates == 0)) {
                freq[root->val]--;
                len--;
                return 1;
            }

            freq[root->val]--;
            len--;

            return 0;
        }

        //recursive case
        freq[root->val]++;
        int x = countPaths(root->left, freq, len+1);
        int y = countPaths(root->right, freq, len+1);
        freq[root->val]--;

        return x + y;
    }
public:
    int pseudoPalindromicPaths (TreeNode* root) {
        vector<int> freq(10, 0);

        return countPaths(root, freq, 0); 
    }
};
[24/01/24, 8:02:12 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    bool isPalindrome(vector<int> arr){
        for(int i=0 ; i<9 ; i++){
            arr[i] = arr[i]%2;
        } 
        int onecount = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<9 ; i++){
            if(arr[i] == 1) onecount++;
            if(onecount > 1) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
    int f(TreeNode* root, vector<int> &arr){

        // base case
        if(root == NULL){

            if(isPalindrome(arr)) {
                for(int i=0 ; i<9 ; i++) cout<< i+1 << " : "<<arr[i]<<" , ";
                cout<<endl;
                return 1;

                }
            return 0;

        }

        // recursive case
        arr[root->val - 1]++;
        int x = f(root->left,arr);
        int y = f(root->right,arr);
        arr[root->val - 1]--;
        return x + y;

    }
    int pseudoPalindromicPaths (TreeNode* root) {
        vector<int> arr(9,0);
        return f(root,arr);
    }
};

[24/01/24, 8:13:32 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    bool isPalindrome(vector<int> arr){
        for(int i=0 ; i<9 ; i++){
            arr[i] = arr[i]%2;
        } 
        int onecount = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<9 ; i++){
            if(arr[i] == 1) onecount++;
            if(onecount > 1) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
    int f(TreeNode* root, vector<int> &arr){
        if(root == NULL ) return 0;
        // base case
        if(root->left == NULL && root->right == NULL){
            arr[root->val -1 ] ++;
            if(isPalindrome(arr)) {
                for(int i=0 ; i<9 ; i++) cout<< i+1 << " : "<<arr[i]<<" , ";
                cout<<endl;
                arr[root->val -1 ] --;
                return 1;
                }
            arr[root->val -1 ] --;

            return 0;
        }


        // recursive case
        arr[root->val - 1]++;
        int x = f(root->left,arr);
        int y = f(root->right,arr);
        arr[root->val - 1]--;
        return x + y;

    }
    int pseudoPalindromicPaths (TreeNode* root) {
        vector<int> arr(9,0);
        return f(root,arr);
    }
};

[24/01/24, 9:04:05 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution{
public:
  int pseudoPalindromicPaths(TreeNode *root, int count = 0){
    // dfs way to find the number of pseudo palindromic paths
    if (!root)
      return 0;
    count ^= 1 << root->val;
    int res = pseudoPalindromicPaths(root->left, count) + pseudoPalindromicPaths(root->right, count);
    if (!root->left && !root->right && (count & (count - 1)) == 0)
      res++;
    return res;
  }

[24/01/24, 9:34:14 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int findExcessEdges(vector<int> adj[], int source,vector<int> &visited){
        queue<int> q;
        q.push(source);
        visited[source] = 1;
        int nodecnt = 0;
        int edgecnt = 0;
        // no of excess edges = no of edges - no of node + 1
        while(!q.empty()){
            int front = q.front();
            nodecnt++;
            q.pop();
            for(int neighbour : adj[front]){
                edgecnt++;
                if(visited[neighbour] == 0){
                    q.push(neighbour);
                    visited[neighbour] = 1;
                }
            }
        }
        return edgecnt - nodecnt + 1;
    }
    int makeConnected(int n, vector<vector<int>>& connections) {
        vector<int> adj[n];
        for(int i=0 ; i<connections.size() ; i++){
            int a = connections[i][0];
            int b = connections[i][1];
            adj[a].push_back(b);
            adj[b].push_back(a);
        }
        vector<int> visited;
        int excess = 0;
        int No_comp = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            if(visited[i] == 0){
                No_comp++;
                excess+=findExcessEdges(adj,i,visited);
            }
        }
        return excess >= No_comp-1;
    }
};

[24/01/24, 9:51:49 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    void dfs_helper(vector<int> adj[], int node, vector<int> &vis){
        vis[node] = 1;

        for(auto adjNode : adj[node]){
            if(!vis[adjNode]){
                dfs_helper(adj, adjNode, vis);
            }
        }
    }
public:
    int makeConnected(int n, vector<vector<int>>& connections) {

        int total_edges = connections.size();
        if(total_edges < n-1) return -1;

        vector<int> adj[n];

        for(auto it : connections){
            int u = it[0];
            int v = it[1];

            adj[u].push_back(v);
            adj[v].push_back(u);
        }

        int numComponents = 0;
        vector<int> vis(n, 0);

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(!vis[i]){
                numComponents++;
                dfs_helper(adj, i, vis);     
            }
        }

        return numComponents-1;
    }
};

[24/01/24, 12:40:37 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool dfs_helper(int src, vector<int> adj[], vector<int>& vis, int dest){
        //base case
        if(src == dest){
            return true;
        }

        //recursive case
        vis[src] = 1;
        for(auto it : adj[src]){
            if(!vis[it]){
                if(dfs_helper(it, adj, vis, dest)) return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
public:
    int minReorder(int n, vector<vector<int>>& connections) {

        vector<int> adj[n];

        for(auto it : connections){
            int u = it[0];
            int v = it[1];

            adj[u].push_back(v);
        }

        queue<int>q;
        q.push(0);

        vector<int> visited(n, 0);
        visited[0] = 1;

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            vector<int> vis(n, 0);
            if(dfs_helper(i, adj, vis, 0)){
                visited[i] = 1;
                q.push(i);
            }
        }

        int reverse_edge = 0;

        while(!q.empty()){
            int front = q.front();
            q.pop();

            for(auto adjNode : adj[front]){
                if(!visited[adjNode]){
                    reverse_edge++;
                    q.push(adjNode);
                    visited[adjNode] = 1;
                }
            }
        }

        return reverse_edge;
    }
};
[24/01/24, 12:43:59 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    bool f(vector<int> adj[], int source,int n,vector<int>&visited){
        // 
        if(source == 0) return true;
        visited[source] = 1;
        for(int neighbour : adj[source]){
            if(!visited[neighbour]){
                if(f(adj,neighbour,n,visited)) return true;
            }
        }
        return false;

    } 
    int minReorder(int n, vector<vector<int>>& arr) {
        // queue ke andar voh eleemts hopone chahiye jinse 0 tk path hai including zero 
        // uske baad bfs laga denge 
        vector<int> adj[n];
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            adj[arr[i][0]].push_back(arr[i][1]);
        }
        queue<int> q;
        q.push(0);
        for(int i=1 ; i<n ; i++){
            vector<int> visited(n,0);
            if(f(adj,i,n,visited)) visited[i] = 1; q.push(i);
        }
        int cnt = 0;
        vector<int> vis(n,0);
        vis[0] = 1;
        while(!q.empty()){
            int front = q.front();
            q.pop();
            for(int neighbor : adj[front]){
                if(!vis[neighbor]){
                    cnt++;
                    q.push(neighbor);
                    vis[neighbor] = 1;
                }
            }
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};

	string s_a = to_string(a);
	string s_b = to_string(b);

	string x = s_a + s_b;
	string y = s_b + s_a;

	if (x > y) {
		// you don't a swap to sort x_arr[] in decreasing order
		return true;
	}
	// you need a swap to sort x_arr[] in decreasing order
	return false;
}

[25/01/24, 8:52:51 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: bool sortbysize(string &a,string &b) { 
    return (a.size() < b.size()); 
} 
class Solution {
public:
    bool ispredecessor(string a, string b){
        int i=0;
        int j=0;
        // a is the longer string    a: abcdxre 
        //                           b: abcdre
        int f = 1;
        while(i<b.size()){
            if(f && a[j] != b[i]){ 
                f = 0;
                j++;
                continue;
            }
            else if(!f && a[j] != b[i]) return false;
            i++;
            j++;
        }
        return true;


    }
    int f(int i,vector<string>& words, int p ){

    // base case
    if(i == words.size()){
        return 0;
    }

    // recursive case
    int take = 0;
    if(p == -1 || (words[i].size() == words[p].size()+1 && ispredecessor(words[i],words[p]))){
        take = 1 + f(i+1,words,i);
    }
    int not_take = f(i+1,words,p);
    return max(take,not_take);
    }
    
    int longestStrChain(vector<string>& words) {
        sort(words.begin(),words.end(),sortbysize);
        for(auto x : words) cout<<x<<" ";
        return f(0,words,-1);
    }
};

[25/01/24, 2:27:22 PM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-cost-to-convert-string-i/solutions/4449584/multi-source-bfs-djikstra-easy-to-understand/
[25/01/24, 2:27:27 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string source, string target, vector<char>& original, vector<char>& changed, vector<int>& cost) {
        pair<string, int> adj[26];
        vector<vector<int>> distMap(26, vector<int>(26, INT_MAX));

        for(int i=0;i<26;i++){
            distMap[i][i] = 0;
        }

        for(int i=0;i<changed.size();i++){
            int u = original[i];
            int v = changed[i];
            int wt = cost[i];

            adj[u - 'a'].first = v - 'a';
            adj[u - 'a'].second = wt;
            distMap[u - 'a'][v - 'a'] = wt;
        }

        for(int via=0;via<26;via++){
            for(int i=0;i<26;i++){
                for(int j=0;j<26;j++){
                    if(distMap[i][via] != INT_MAX && distMap[via][j] != INT_MAX){
                        distMap[i][j] = min(distMap[i][j], distMap[i][via] + distMap[via][j]);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        long long minCost = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<source.length();i++){
            int cost = distMap[source[i] - 'a'][target[i] - 'a'];
            if(cost == INT_MAX) return -1;
            minCost += cost;
        }

        return minCost;
    }
};

[25/01/24, 2:28:32 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int mod = 10e7;
    int f(int i, int p, int k, int n, int m){

        // base case
        
        if(i == n) {
            if(k == 0) return 1;
            return 0;
        }
        if(k == 0) return 0;

        // recursive case
        //take
        int ans = 0;
        for(int j=0 ; j<=m ; j++){
            ans = ( ans + f(i+1,j, j > p ? k-1 : k , n,m) )%mod;
        }

        return ans;

    }
    int numOfArrays(int n, int m, int k) {
        if(k>n) return 0;
        return f(0,0,k,n,m);
    }
};

public:
    int mod = 10e7;
    int dp[51][101][51];
    int f(int i, int p, int k, int n, int m){
        // base case
        if(k == -1) return 0;
        if(dp[i][p][k] != -1) return dp[i][p][k];

        
        if(i == n) {
            if(k == 0) return 1;
            return 0;
        }

        // recursive case
        //take
        int ans = 0;
        for(int j=1 ; j<=m ; j++){
            ans = ( ans + f(i+1,max(j,p), j > p ? k-1 : k , n,m) )%mod;
        }

        return dp[i][p][k] = ans;

    }
    int numOfArrays(int n, int m, int k) {
        if(k>n) return 0;
        int maxi = 0;
        // for(int i=0 ; i<=m ; i++){
        //     maxi = max(maxi,f(1,i,k-1,n,m));
        // }
        // return maxi;
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        return f(0,0,k,n,m);
        
    }

[25/01/24, 7:50:58 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
    
    long[][][] memo;
    long mod = (long)1e9 + 7;
    int N, M;
    long rec(int i, int msf, int kleft) {
        if (i == N) {
            return kleft == 0 ? 1 : 0;
        }        
        if (kleft < 0) return 0;
        if (memo[i][msf][kleft] != -1)  return memo[i][msf][kleft];
        
        long ans = 0;
        for (int j = 1; j <= M; j++) {
            ans = (ans + rec(i+1, Math.max(msf, j), j > msf ? kleft-1 : kleft)) % mod;
        }
                   
        return memo[i][msf][kleft] = ans;
    }
    
    
    public int numOfArrays(int n, int m, int K) {
        memo = new long[n+1][m+1][K+1];
        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= m; j++) {
                for (int k = 0; k <= K; k++) {
                    memo[i][j][k] = -1;
                }
            }
        }
        this.N = n;
        M = m;
        long ans = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= m; i++) {
            ans = (ans + rec(1, i, K-1)) % mod;
        }
        return (int)ans;
    }
}

[26/01/24, 8:16:05 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int findPaths(int m, int n, int maxMove, int i, int j) {
        //base case

        if(i == -1 || j == -1 || i == m || j == n){
            return 1;
        }

        if(maxMove == 0){
            return 0;
        }

        //recursive case

        int cnt = 0;

        int dx[] = {1, -1, 0, 0};
        int dy[] = {0, 0, 1, -1};

        for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
            int ii = i + dx[k];
            int jj = j + dy[k];

            cnt += findPaths(m, n, maxMove-1, ii, jj);
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};

[26/01/24, 8:44:45 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:

    int helper(int i,vector<int>& nums,vector<int>& dp ){
        if(dp[i] != -1) return dp[i];
        if(i == nums.size()-1) return 1;
        // find the longest increasing subsequence starting at the ith index 
        //  it is starting at the ith index that means we must include theith index 
        // choose for next 
        int ans = 0;
        for(int j=i+1 ; j<nums.size() ; j++){
            if(nums[j] > nums[i]){
                ans =  max( helper(j,nums,dp) , ans);
            }
        }
        cout<<i<<" : "<<ans<<" ";
        return dp[i] = 1 + ans;

    }
    int lengthOfLIS(vector<int>& nums) {

            vector<int> dp(nums.size(), -1);
           int ans = 0;
           for(int i=0 ; i<nums.size() ; i++){
               ans = max(ans,helper(i,nums,dp));
               cout<<"THE MAX LEN FROM "<<i<<" is :"<<ans<<endl;
           }
           return ans;
    }
};
[26/01/24, 8:45:27 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLIS(vector<int>& nums) {

        vector<int> temp;
        int n = nums.size();
        temp.push_back(nums[0]);
        for(int i=1 ; i<n ; i++){

            if(nums[i] > temp.back()){
                temp.push_back(nums[i]);
            }
            else{
                // find the right place where nums[i] belongs in temp, when we do it by making subsequences , we copy all elements from the previous array till the elements are lesser than nums[i] and then start building that array so instead of using that we are using our first array         
                auto ind = lower_bound(temp.begin(),temp.end(),nums[i]);
                *ind = nums[i];
            }

        }
        return temp.size();
        
    }
};

[26/01/24, 12:39:22 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    long long f(int i, int p, int k, vector<int>& nums){
        if(k == 0){
            return 0;
        }
        if(i == nums.size()){
            // you have answers for arr[0..n-1] 
            // max sum if i == n whaterver may be the size of subsequence yet , you cannot get max sum 
            return 0;
        }     

        // find the max sum of balanced subsequence from i..n-1 of size k  which is balanced and last chose element was p 
        // you can include the ith element 

        long long take = INT_MIN;
        if(p == -1 || nums[i] - nums[p] >= i-p){
            take = nums[i] + f(i+1,i,k-1,nums);
        }

        // you can exclude it
        long long  not_take = f(i+1,p,k,nums); 
        std:: cout<<"take : "<<take<<" not take : "<<not_take<<" , ";
        return max(take,not_take);
        
    }
    long long maxBalancedSubsequenceSum(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        long long maxi = INT_MIN;
        for(int k=1 ; k<=n ; k++){
            maxi = max(maxi , f(0,-1,k,nums));
        }
        return maxi;
        
    }
};
[26/01/24, 12:53:27 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://github.com/abhishek18124/DSA-Live-Sessions/blob/main/Dynamic%20Programming/Knapsack%20Problems/01Knapsack.cpp
[26/01/24, 12:55:04 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /*

Given an integer array 'A', return the length of the longest increasing subsequence.

A subsequence is a sequence that can be derived from an array by deleting some or no elements without
changing the order of the remaining elements.

Example 1:
	Input: A[] = [10, 9, 2, 5, 3, 7, 18]
	Output: 4
	Explanation: The longest increasing subsequence is [2, 5, 7, 18], therefore the output is 4.

Example 2:
	Input: A[] = [0,1,0,3,2,3]
	Output: 4
	Explanation: The longest increasing subsequence is [0, 1, 2, 3], therefore the output is 4.
*/


#include<iostream>
#include<vector>
#include<climits>

using namespace std;

int LIS_K(vector<int> A, int n, int i) {

	// base case

	if (i == n - 1) {
		// compute the length of the LIS of A[n-1...n-1]
		return 1;
	}

	// recursive case

	// compute the length of the LIS of A[i...n-1]

	int maxSoFar = 0;

	for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {

		if (A[j] > A[i]) {

			maxSoFar = max(maxSoFar, LIS_K(A, n, j));

		}

	}

	return 1 + maxSoFar;

}

int LIS(vector<int> A, int n) {
	int ans = 0;
	for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
		ans = max(ans, LIS_K(A, n, k));
	}
	return ans;
}

// time : O(n^2)
// space : O(n)

int LIS_BottomUp(vector<int> A, int n) {

	vector<int> dp(n);

	dp[n - 1] = 1; // at the n-1th index of dp[], we store f(n-1)
	int ans = dp[n - 1];

	for (int i = n - 2; i >= 0; i--) {

		// dp[i] = f(i) : length of the LIS starting at the ith index

		int maxSoFar = 0;

		for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {

			if (A[j] > A[i]) {

				maxSoFar = max(maxSoFar, dp[j]);

			}

		}

		dp[i] = 1 + maxSoFar;
		ans = max(ans, dp[i]);

	}

	return ans;

}


int main() {

	vector<int> A = {1, 2, 5, 3, 0, 4, 6};
	int n = A.size();

	cout << LIS_BottomUp(A, n) << endl;

	return 0;
}

[26/01/24, 3:29:30 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {

    bool isPossible(string curr, string prev){

        if(curr.length() - prev.length() != 1) return false;

        int i = 0, j = 0;

        while(i < prev.length() && j < curr.length()){
            if(prev[i] == curr[j]){
                i++;
            }
            j++;
        }
        
        return i == prev.length();
    }

    int f(vector<string> &words, int n, int curr, int prev, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        // base case
        if(curr == n){
            return 0;
        }

        //lookup
        if(dp[curr][prev+1] != -1){
            return dp[curr][prev+1];
        }

        // recursive case
        // op1: take the string
        int take = 0;
        if(prev == -1 || isPossible(words[curr], words[prev])){
            take = 1 + f(words, n, curr + 1, curr, dp);
        }

        // op2: not take the string
        int notTake = f(words, n, curr + 1, prev, dp);

        return dp[curr][prev+1] = max(take, notTake);
    }
public:
    static bool len(string &a, string &b){
        return a.length() < b.length();
    }
    int longestStrChain(vector<string>& words) {
        sort(words.begin(), words.end(), len);

        int n = words.size();
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n, vector<int>(n+1, -1));

        return f(words, n, 0, -1, dp);
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    int dp[1001][1001];
    bool ispredecessor(string a, string b){
        int i=0;
        int j=0;
        // a is the longer string    a: abcdxre 
        //                           b: abcdre
        int f = 1;
        while(i<b.size()){
            if(f && a[j] != b[i]){ 
                f = 0;
                j++;
                continue;
            }
            else if(!f && a[j] != b[i]) return false;
            i++;
            j++;
        }
        return true;


    }
    int f(int i,vector<string>& words, int p ){

    if(p != -1 && dp[i][p] != -1)return dp[i][p];
    // base case
    if(i == words.size()){
        return 0;
    }
    
    // recursive case
    int take = 0;
    if(p == -1 || (words[i].size() == words[p].size()+1 && ispredecessor(words[i],words[p]))){
        take = 1 + f(i+1,words,i);
    }
    int not_take = f(i+1,words,p);
    if(p != -1) dp[i][p] = max(take,not_take);
    return max(take,not_take);
    }
    
    int longestStrChain(vector<string>& words) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        sort(words.begin(),words.end(),sortbysize);
        for(auto x : words) cout<<x<<" ";
        return f(0,words,-1);
        /*
        
        */


        
    }

[26/01/24, 5:29:05 PM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long

class Solution {
    int f(vector<int>& nums, int n, int curr, int prev, vector<vector<ll>> &dp){
        //base case
        if(curr == n){
            return 0;
        }

        //lookup
        if(dp[curr][prev+1] != -1){
            return dp[curr][prev+1];
        }

        //recursive case
        //op1 : take the element
        ll take = 0;
        if(prev == -1 || nums[curr] - nums[prev] >= curr - prev){
            take = nums[curr] + f(nums, n, curr+1, curr, dp);
        }

        //op2 : do not take the element
        ll notTake = f(nums, n, curr+1, prev, dp);

        return dp[curr][prev+1] = max(take, notTake);
    }
public:
    long long maxBalancedSubsequenceSum(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();

        vector<vector<ll>> dp(n, vector<ll>(n+1, -1));
        return f(nums, n, 0, -1, dp);
    }
};

[26/01/24, 5:44:12 PM] Satvik Saini: ll bottomUp(vector<int> &nums, int n){
        vector<ll> currRow(n+1, 0);
        vector<ll> nextRow(n+1, 0);

        for(int curr=n-1;curr>=0;curr--){
            for(int prev=curr-1;prev>=-1;prev--){
                //op1 : take the element
                ll take = 0;
                if(prev == -1 || nums[curr] - nums[prev] >= curr - prev){
                    take = nums[curr] + nextRow[curr+1];
                }

                //op2 : do not take the element
                ll notTake = nextRow[prev+1];

                currRow[prev+1] = max(take, notTake);
            }
            nextRow = currRow;
        }
        return nextRow[0];
    }
public:
    long long maxBalancedSubsequenceSum(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();

        int max_ele = nums[0];

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            max_ele = max(max_ele, nums[i]);
            if(nums[i] > 0) return bottomUp(nums, n);
        }
        return max_ele;
    }
};

[26/01/24, 5:45:59 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    long long maxBalancedSubsequenceSum(vector<int>& nums) {
        
        int n = nums.size();
        long long ans = *max_element(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        if(ans<=0) return ans;
        long long  maxi = LLONG_MIN;
        vector<long long> dp(n+1,0);
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++) dp[i] = nums[i];
        for(int i=n-1 ; i>=0 ; i--){
            for(int j=i+1 ; j<n ; j++){

                if(nums[j] - j >= nums[i] - i){
                    dp[i] = max<long long>( dp[i], dp[j] + nums[i]);
                }
            }
            maxi = max<long long>(maxi , dp[i]); // this is tracking the maximum sum when you start at ith index , you will have maxi of all possible dp[i] 

        }
        return maxi > ans ? maxi : ans;

    }
};

[27/01/24, 10:04:49 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool isPossible(string s1, string s2, string s3, int n, int m, int o, int i, int j, int k){
        //base case
        if(i == n){
            // length of n+m-j is already formed
            // check if s2[j...m] == s3[o-j...o]
            return s2.substr(j) == s3.substr(o-j);
        }

        if(j == m){
            // length of n+m-i is already formed
            // check if s1[i...m] == s3[o-i...o]
            return s1.substr(i) == s3.substr(o-i);
        }

        // if(k == o){
        //     cout<<"im in"<<endl;
        //     return false;
        // }

        //recursive case
        for(int x=0;x<n-i;x++){
            string sub_s1 = s1.substr(i,x);
            for(int y=0;y<min(k-x,m-j);y++){
                string sub_s2 = s2.substr(j,y);
                if(sub_s1 + sub_s2 == s3.substr(k,x+y)){
                    if(isPossible(s1, s2, s3, n, m, o, i+x, j+y, k+x+y)) return true;
                }
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
public:
    bool isInterleave(string s1, string s2, string s3) {
        int n = s1.length();
        int m = s2.length();
        int o = s3.length();

        // sum of lengths are not equal
        if(n + m != o) return false;

        return isPossible(s1, s2, s3, n, m, o, 0, 0, 0);
    }
};

    def isInterleave(self, s1, s2, s3):
        @lru_cache(None)
        def dp(i, j):
            if i == -1 and j == -1: return True
            return (j >= 0 and s2[j] == s3[i+j+1] and dp(i, j-1)) or (i >= 0 and s1[i] == s3[i+j+1] and dp(i-1,j))
        
        return len(s1) + len(s2) == len(s3) and dp(len(s1) - 1, len(s2) - 1)
[27/01/24, 11:52:09 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    bool f(string& s1, string& s2, string& s3, int i, int j, int n, int m, vector<vector<int>>& dp) {
        // base case
        if (i == n && j == m){
            return true;
        }

        // lookup
        if (dp[i][j] != -1)
            return dp[i][j];

        // recursive case
        bool result = false;

        // op1 : take ith char if possible
        if (i < n && s1[i] == s3[i + j]){
            result = f(s1, s2, s3, i + 1, j, n, m, dp);
        }

        // op2 : take jth char if possible
        if (!result && j < m && s2[j] == s3[i + j]){
            result = f(s1, s2, s3, i, j + 1, n, m, dp);
        }

        return dp[i][j] = result;
    }

    bool isInterleave(string s1, string s2, string s3) {

        int n = s1.length();
        int m = s2.length();
        int o = s3.length();

        if (o != n + m)
            return false;

        vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 1, vector<int>(m + 1, -1));
        return f(s1, s2, s3, 0, 0, n, m, dp);
    }
};

[28/01/24, 10:08:50 AM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long double

class Solution {
public:
    int maximumLength(vector<int>& nums) {
        
        
        ll maxLen = 1;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            
            unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        
            for(int ele : nums){
                mp[ele]++;
            }
            
            if(nums[i] == 1){
                maxLen = max(maxLen, (ll)mp[1] - (mp[1]%2 == 0));
                continue;
            }
            
            ll start_val = nums[i];
            ll prev_start_val = -1;
            ll len = 0;
         
            while(mp[start_val] != 0){
                prev_start_val = start_val;
                mp[start_val]--;
                if(mp[start_val] != 0){
                    start_val *= start_val;
                    len++;
                }
            }

            if(prev_start_val != start_val) len--;
            len = len*2 + 1;
            cout<<len<<" ";
            maxLen = max(maxLen, len);
        }
        
        return (int)maxLen;
        
    }
};
[28/01/24, 10:10:35 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    unordered_map<int,int> maap;
    int f(unordered_map<int,int> mpp, int x){
        if(maap.find(x) != maap.end()) return maap[x];
        if(mpp.find(x) == mpp.end()) return 0;
        if(mpp[x] < 2) return 1;
        if((long long)x*x > 1e9 ) return 1;
            
        
        // return subset which has max len and can follow pattern and starts with x
         return maap[x] = 1 + f(mpp,x*x);
        
    }
    int maximumLength(vector<int>& nums) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
        for(int x : nums) mpp[x]++;
        
        int maxlen = 0;


        
        for(auto x : mpp){
            int num = x.first;
            int freq = x.second;
            
            // cout<<num<<" : "<<freq<<endl;
            
            if(num == 1){
                
                if(freq % 2 == 0) maxlen = max(maxlen,freq/2);
                else maxlen = max(maxlen,(freq+1)/2) ;
                int a = freq%2 == 0 ? freq/2 :(freq+1)/2;
                // cout<<"maxlen due to 1 is "<<maxlen<<" it should be "<< a <<endl;
            }
            else{
                
            maxlen = max(maxlen , f(mpp,num));
            // cout<<"maxlen yet is : "<<maxlen<<" ";
                
            }
            
            
        }
        return 2*maxlen-1;
        
    }
};

[28/01/24, 10:28:27 AM] Satvik Saini: int maximumLength(vector<int>& nums) {
    long long ans = 0;
    map<int, int> freq;
    for(auto n: nums) freq[n]++;
    for(auto [k,f] : freq){
        long long t = k, count = 0;
        if(t == 1) { count += freq[t]; freq[t] = 0; } 
        while(t < INT_MAX && freq[t] > 0){
            count += 2;
            if(freq[t] == 1) break; 
            freq[t] = 0;                 // set to zero, so that we do not check for this sequence again
            t = t * t;
        }
        if(count % 2 == 0) count--;
        ans = max(ans, count);
    }
    return ans;
}
[28/01/24, 10:42:01 AM] Satvik Saini: long long flowerGame(int n, int m) {
    long long ans = 0;
    for(int i = 1; i <= min(n, m); i++){
        ans += (long long)((m - i + 1)/2);
        ans += (long long)((n - i + 1)/2);
    }
    return ans;
}
[28/01/24, 10:42:45 AM] Satvik Saini: for each count in first group(let say x) the next group should be larger number (x + 1, x + 3, x + 5, etc ) so that Alice will win. If x is odd then take all larger even possible and if its even take all the larger odd in other group.
Note : There may be mathmatical formula to get the solution, but in the contest its make sence to go with iterative rather than spending time on fomulating the final answer.
[28/01/24, 10:45:12 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    long long flowerGame(int n, int m) {
        long long oddx=0, eveny=0, evenx=0, oddy=0;
        
        evenx = n/2;
        oddx = n%2 == 0 ? evenx : evenx+1;
        eveny = m/2;
        oddy = m%2 == 0 ? eveny : eveny+1;
        
        return oddx*eveny + evenx*oddy;
    }
};

[28/01/24, 8:33:29 PM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimize-or-of-remaining-elements-using-operations/description/
[28/01/24, 8:33:41 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int f(vector<int>& nums, int k, int i, int n){
        //base case
        if(i >= n-1 || k == 0){
            int ans = 0;
            for(int k=0;k<n;k++){
                ans |= nums[k];
            }
            return ans;
        }
        
        //recursive case
        //op1 : dont AND nums[i] and nums[i+1]
        int x = f(nums, k, i+1, n);
        
        //op2 : AND nums[i] and nums[i+1];
        vector<int> new_nums;
        for(int l=0;l<i;l++){
            new_nums.push_back(nums[l]);
        }
        new_nums.push_back(nums[i] & nums[i+1]);
        for(int l=i+2;l<n;l++){
            new_nums.push_back(nums[l]);
        }
        int y = f(new_nums, k-1, i, n-1);
        
        return min(x,y);
    }
public:
    int minOrAfterOperations(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        return f(nums, k, 0, nums.size());
    }
};

[29/01/24, 6:44:29 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int dp[1001][1001];
    int f(int i, int j, vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2){
        if(dp[i][j] != -1 ) return dp[i][j];
        if(i >= nums1.size() || j >= nums2.size()){
            return 0;
        }
        // recursive case
        int cnt = 0;
        if(nums1[i] == nums2[j]){
            while(i!=nums1.size() && j!= nums2.size() && nums1[i] == nums2[j]){
                cnt++;
                i++;
                j++;
            }
        }

        return dp[i][j] = max({f(i+1,j,nums1,nums2),f(i,j+1,nums1,nums2),cnt});

    }
    int findLength(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));

        return f(0,0,nums1,nums2);
    }
};

[29/01/24, 7:01:33 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution { // 344 ms, faster than 21.07%
public:
    int findLength(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {
        int m = nums1.size(), n = nums2.size();
        vector<vector<int>> dp(m+1, vector<int>(n+1));
        int ans = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= m; ++i) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= n; ++j) {
                if (nums1[i-1] == nums2[j-1])
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1] + 1;
                else dp[i][j] = 0;
                ans = max(ans, dp[i][j]);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[29/01/24, 7:02:26 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
	int ans = 0;
	int findLength(vector<int>& A, vector<int>& B) {
		solve(A, B, 0, 0);
		return ans;
	}
	int solve(vector<int>& A, vector<int>& B, int i, int j) {
		if(i >= size(A) || j >= size(B)) return 0;
		solve(A, B, i+1, j), solve(A, B, i, j+1);                   // recurse to solve for each possible (i, j)
		int common = A[i] == B[j] ? 1 + solve(A, B, i+1, j+1) : 0;  // longest common subarray starting at A[i] & B[j]
		ans = max(ans, common);                                     // update ans to hold max length found till now
		return common;
	}
};

    {

        int tl=t.size();
        vector<vector<int>> koiMilGaya(sl+1,vector<int>(tl+1,0));
        int sabseLambi=0;
        for(int i=1;i<=sl;i++)
        {
            for(int j=1;j<=tl;j++)
            {
                if(s[i-1]==t[j-1])
                    koiMilGaya[i][j]=koiMilGaya[i-1][j-1]+1;
                sabseLambi=max(sabseLambi,koiMilGaya[i][j]);
            }
        }
        return sabseLambi;
    }

    }

    return create(inorder, postorder, 0, inorder.size() - 1, 0, postorder.size() - 1);
}

TreeNode* create(vector<int> &inorder, vector<int> &postorder, int is, int ie, int ps, int pe){
    if(ps > pe){
        return nullptr;
    }
    TreeNode* node = new TreeNode(postorder[pe]);
    int pos;
    for(int i = is; i <= ie; i++){
        if(inorder[i] == node->val){
            pos = i;
            break;
        }
    }
    node->left = create(inorder, postorder, is, pos - 1, ps, ps + pos - is - 1);
    node->right = create(inorder, postorder, pos + 1, ie, pe - ie + pos, pe - 1);
    return node;
}
