[31/01/24, 5:53:17 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /*

	Implementation of HashMap/HashTable

*/

#include<iostream>

using namespace std;

class ListNode {

public :

	int K;
	int V;
	ListNode* next;

	ListNode(int K, int V) {
		this->K = K;
		this->V = V;
		this->next = NULL;
	}

};

class HashMap {
	int N; //  to store the hash table capacity
	int M; //  to store the hash table size
	double L; // to store the load factor threshold

	ListNode** T; // to store the pointer to the  dynamic
	// array that represents the hash table

	int hashFn(int K) {
		// transform K into a hash index
		return K % N;
	}

	void transfer(ListNode* head) {
		// 1. rehash (K, V) pairs present in the linkedList represented
		//    by "head" pointer to the updated hashMap
		ListNode* temp = head;
		while (temp != NULL) {
			insert(temp->K, temp->V);
			temp = temp->next;
		}

		// 2. release memory allocated for the linkedList represented
		//    by "head" pointer
		temp = head;
		while (head != NULL) {
			head = head->next;
			delete temp;
			temp = head;
		}
	}

	void rehash() {

		// 1. save pointer to the current hashMap and its capacity
		ListNode** oldT = T;
		int oldN = N;

		// 2. create a hashMap with double capacity
		N = 2 * N;
		T = new ListNode*[N];
		for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
			T[i] = NULL;
		}
		M = 0;

		// 3. transfer (K, V) pairs from old hashMap to the updated hashMap
		for (int i = 0; i < oldN; i++) {
			transfer(oldT[i]);
		}

		// 4. release the memory allocated to the old hashMap
		delete [] oldT;

	}

public :

	HashMap(int N = 5, double L = 0.7) {
		this->N = N;
		this->M = 0;
		this->L = L;

		T = new ListNode*[N];
		for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
			T[i] = NULL;
		}
	}

	void insert(int K, int V) {

		// 1. transform the key into hash index using the hash function
		int hashIdx = hashFn(K);

		// 2. create a ListNode with the given (K, V) pair and insert it at
		//    head of the linkedList stored at the hash index
		ListNode* n = new ListNode(K, V);

		// 3. update the pointer to the head of the linkedList stored at
		//    the hash index such that it holds the address of the newly
		//    created ListNode
		n->next = T[hashIdx];
		T[hashIdx] = n;
		M++;

		// 4. rehash, if loadFactor exceeds the loadFactor Threshold
		double loadFactor = M * 1.0 / N;
		if (loadFactor > L) {
			cout << "rehashing due to loadFactor = " << loadFactor << endl;
			rehash();
		}


	}

	ListNode* find(int K) {

		// 1. transform the key into hash index using the hash function
		int hashIdx = hashFn(K);

		// 2. search for the ListNode with the given key in the  linkedList
		//    stored at the hash index
		ListNode* temp = T[hashIdx];
		while (temp != NULL) {
			if (temp->K == K) {
				break;
			}
			temp = temp->next;
		}
		return temp;

	}

	void erase(int K) {

		// 1. transform the key into hash index using the hash function
		int hashIdx = hashFn(K);

		// 2. delete the ListNode with the given key from the linkedList
		//    stored at the hash index
		ListNode* temp = T[hashIdx];

		if (temp == NULL) {
			return;
		}

		if (temp->K == K) {
			// delete the head node
			T[hashIdx] = temp->next;
			delete temp;
			M--;
			return;
		}

		ListNode* prev = NULL;
		while (temp != NULL) {
			if (temp->K == K) {
				// delete the temp node
				prev->next = temp->next;
				delete temp;
				M--;
				break;
			}
			prev = temp;
			temp = temp->next;
		}

	}

	void printLinkedList(ListNode* head) {
		while (head) { // head != NULL
			cout << "(" << head->K << ", " << head->V << ") ";
			head = head->next;
		}
		cout << endl;
	}

	void printHashMap() {
		// iterate over buckets in the hashMap
		for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
			// print the linkedList stored ith bucket of the hashMap
			cout << i << " : ";
			printLinkedList(T[i]);
		}
		cout << endl;
	}
};

int main() {

	HashMap hashMap;

	hashMap.insert(0, 0);
	hashMap.insert(5, 25);
	hashMap.insert(6, 36);

	hashMap.printHashMap();

	int K = 6;

	ListNode* n = hashMap.find(K);

	if (n != NULL) {
		// you've found K in the hashMap
		cout << n->V << endl;
	} else {
		cout << K << " is not present in the hashMap" << endl;
	}

	K = 0;

	hashMap.erase(K);

	n = hashMap.find(K);

	if (n != NULL) {
		// you've found K in the hashMap
		cout << n->V << endl;
	} else {
		cout << K << " is not present in the hashMap" << endl;
	}

	hashMap.printHashMap();

	hashMap.insert(1, 1);

	hashMap.insert(7, 49);

	hashMap.printHashMap();

	return 0;
}

    void f(int low, int high, int i, int num, vector<int> &v){
        //base case
        if(num >= low && num <= high){
            v.push_back(num);
        }
        if(num > high || i > 9){
            return;
        }

        //recursive case
        f(low, high, i+1, num*10 + i, v);
    }
public:
    vector<int> sequentialDigits(int low, int high) {
        vector<int> v;
        for(int i=1;i<=9;i++){
            f(low,high,i,0,v);
        }
        sort(v.begin(),v.end());

        return v;
    }

        while(num <= high  && sp<=8){
            cout<<"hi";
            sp++;
            num = num*10 + sp;
            if(num <= high && num >= low)  vec.push_back(num);
        }
    }
    vector<int> sequentialDigits(int low, int high) {
        int lb = low;
        int ub = high;
        while(lb/10 != 0){
            lb/=10;
        }
        while(ub/10 != 0){
            ub/=10;
        }
        vector<int> vec;
        for(int i=1 ; i<=9 ; i++){
                f(i,low,high,vec);
        }
        sort(vec.begin(),vec.end());
        return vec;
        
    }

[02/02/24, 9:59:37 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
    public List<Integer> sequentialDigits(int low, int high) {
        int[] allNums = {12,23,34,45,56,67,78,89,
                         123,234,345,456,567,678,789,
                         1234,2345,3456,4567,5678,6789,
                         12345,23456,34567,45678,56789,
                         123456,234567,345678,456789,
                         1234567,2345678,3456789,
                         12345678,23456789,
                         123456789};
        List<Integer> res = new ArrayList<>();
        int n = allNums.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (allNums[i] < low) continue;
            if (allNums[i] > high) break;
            res.add(allNums[i]);
        }
        return res;
    }
}

[02/02/24, 10:10:31 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int cnt = 0;
    vector<int> f(TreeNode* root, int distance){

        vector<int> ans(101, -1);

        //base case
        if(!root) return ans;

        if(!root->left && !root->right){
            ans[root->val] = 0;
        }

        //recursive case
        vector<int> leftV = f(root->left, distance);
        vector<int> rightV = f(root->right, distance);

        for(int i=1;i<=100;i++){
            if(leftV[i] != -1){
                ans[i] = leftV[i] + 1;
                for(int j=1;j<=100;j++){
                    if(rightV[j] != -1){
                        ans[j] = rightV[j] + 1;
                        if(leftV[i] + rightV[j] <= distance){
                            cnt++;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
public:
    int countPairs(TreeNode* root, int distance) {
        vector<int> v = f(root, distance);
        return cnt;
    }
};

[02/02/24, 10:18:26 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    int count = 0;
    unordered_map<int,int> f(TreeNode* root, int distance){
        if(root == NULL){
            unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
            return mpp;
        }

        if(root->left == NULL && root->right == NULL){
            cout<<"in leaf";
            unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
            mpp[root->val] = 0;
            return mpp;
        }

        // recursive case
        unordered_map<int,int> leftmap;
        if(root -> left != NULL){
            leftmap = f(root->left,distance);
        }
        unordered_map<int,int> rightmap;
        if(root -> left != NULL){
            rightmap = f(root->right,distance);
        }
        
        for(auto x : leftmap){
            for(auto y : rightmap){
                leftmap[y.first] = y.second;
                if(x.second+y.second<=distance) count++;
            }
        }
        for(auto& x : leftmap){
            x.second++;
        }
        return leftmap;
        

    }    
    int countPairs(TreeNode* root, int distance) {
        f(root,distance);

        return count;
    }
};
[02/02/24, 10:28:22 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎Voice call, ‎23 sec
[02/02/24, 10:32:16 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎3 min
[02/02/24, 10:42:08 AM] Satvik Saini: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    int countPairs(TreeNode* root, int distance) {
        int res = 0;
        dfs(root, distance, res);
        return res;
    }
    
    vector<int> dfs(TreeNode* root, int distance, int& res) {
        if (!root->left && !root->right) return {1};
        vector<int> left, right;
        if (root->left) left = dfs(root->left, distance, res);
        if (root->right) right = dfs(root->right, distance, res);
        for (int i = 0; i < left.size(); ++i) {
            for (int j = 0; j < right.size(); ++j) {
                if (left[i] + right[j] <= distance) ++res;
            }
        }
        vector<int> res_vec;
        for (int i = 0; i < left.size(); ++i) {
            if (left[i] + 1 < distance) res_vec.push_back(left[i] + 1);
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < right.size(); ++i) {
            if (right[i] + 1 < distance) res_vec.push_back(right[i] + 1);
        }
        return res_vec;
    }
};

[02/02/24, 10:43:53 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    int count = 0;
    unordered_map<int,int> f(TreeNode* root, int distance){
        unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
        
        if(root == NULL){
            return mpp;
        }

        if(root->left == NULL && root->right == NULL){
            mpp[root->val] = 0;
            return mpp;
        }

        // recursive case
        unordered_map<int,int> leftmap = f(root->left,distance);

        unordered_map<int,int> rightmap = f(root->right,distance);

        if(root->val == 1){
            cout<<"lefttMap "<<endl;

            for(auto x : leftmap){
                cout<<x.first<<" "<<x.second<<endl;
            }
            cout<<"rightMap "<<endl;
            for(auto x : rightmap){
                cout<<x.first<<" "<<x.second<<endl;
            }

        }
        if(leftmap.empty()){
            for(auto& x : rightmap){
                x.second++;
            }
            return rightmap;
        }
        
        for(auto x : leftmap){
            mpp[x.first] = x.second;
            for(auto y : rightmap){
                mpp[y.first] = y.second;
                if(x.second+y.second+2<=distance) count++;
            }
        }

        for(auto& x : mpp){
            x.second++;
        }
        return mpp;
        

    }    
    int countPairs(TreeNode* root, int distance) {
        f(root,distance);

        return count;
    }
};

[02/02/24, 12:56:37 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-consecutive-sequence/description/
[02/02/24, 12:57:48 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /*
	https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-consecutive-sequence/
*/

#include<iostream>
#include<vector>
#include<unordered_map>

using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
	int longestConsecutive(vector<int>& nums) {

		// time : O(n) space : O(n)

		unordered_map<int, bool> startMap;

		for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {

			if (startMap.find(nums[i] - 1) != startMap.end()) {
				startMap[nums[i]] = false;
			} else {
				startMap[nums[i]] = true;
			}

			if (startMap.find(nums[i] + 1) != startMap.end()) {
				startMap[nums[i] + 1] = false;
			}

		}

		int maxLen = 0;

		for (pair<int, bool> p : startMap) {
			int key = p.first;
			bool value = p.second;
			if (value == true) {
				// we can start a sequence of consecutive elements from 'key'
				int count = 0;
				while (startMap.find(key) != startMap.end()) {
					count++;
					key++;
				}
				maxLen = max(maxLen, count);
			}
		}

		return maxLen;

	}
};

int main() {

	Solution s;

	vector<int> nums = {0, 1, 4, 5, 6, 11, 12, 13, 14};

	cout << s.longestConsecutive(nums) << endl;

}
[02/02/24, 12:59:42 PM] Satvik Saini: if(nums.empty()) return 0;

    int length = 1;
    unordered_set<int> mp;
     
    for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
        mp.insert(nums[i]);
    }

    for(auto it : mp){
        if(mp.find(it-1) == mp.end()){
            int cnt = 1;
            int x = it;

            while(mp.find(x+1) != mp.end()){
                cnt++;
                x++;
            }

            length = max(length, cnt);
        }
    }
    return length;
    }
[02/02/24, 1:00:00 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: lass Solution {
public:
    int longestConsecutive(vector<int>& nums) {
        unordered_set<int> set;
        for(int num : nums){
            set.insert(num);
        }
        int longestConsecutiveSequence = 0;
        for(int num : nums){
            if(set.find(num-1) == set.end()){
                int currentNumber = num;
                int currentConsecutiveSequence = 1;
                while(set.find(currentNumber+1) != set.end()){
                    currentNumber++;
                    currentConsecutiveSequence++;
                }
                longestConsecutiveSequence = max(longestConsecutiveSequence, currentConsecutiveSequence);
            }
        }
        return longestConsecutiveSequence;
    }
};
‎[02/02/24, 1:08:02 PM] Satvik Saini: ‎image omitted
[02/02/24, 1:11:37 PM] Satvik Saini: pair<int, TreeNode*> dfs(TreeNode *root) {
    if (!root) return {0, nullptr};
    auto [d1, r1] = dfs(root->left);
    auto [d2, r2] = dfs(root->right);
    return {max(d1, d2) + 1, d1 == d2 ? root : d1 > d2 ? r1 : r2};
}

TreeNode* subtreeWithAllDeepest(TreeNode* root) {
    return dfs(root).second;
}
[02/02/24, 1:12:02 PM] Satvik Saini: int depth(TreeNode *root) {
    return !root ? 0 : max(depth(root->left), depth(root->right)) + 1;
}

TreeNode* subtreeWithAllDeepest(TreeNode* root) {
    int d = depth(root->left) - depth(root->right);
    return !d ? root : subtreeWithAllDeepest(d > 0 ? root->left : root->right);
}

[04/02/24, 9:53:23 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int minimumTimeToInitialState(string word, int k) {
        int i=k;
        if(k == word.size()) return 1;
        int cnt = 1;
        while(i<word.size()){
            cout<<"i am at "<<word[i]<<" ";
        
            int j=0;
            int m=i;
            while(m<word.size()  && word[m] == word[j]){
                m++;
                j++;
            }
            if(m == word.size()){
                return cnt;
            }
            else{
                i+=k;
                cnt++;
                cout<<" count is "<<cnt<<endl;
            }
            
            
        }
        return cnt;
        
    }
};

[04/02/24, 10:04:46 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution:
    def minimumTimeToInitialState(self, word: str, k: int) -> int:
        for i in range(k, len(word), k):
            if word[i:] == word[0:len(word) - i]:
                return i//k
        return math.ceil(len(word)/k)
[04/02/24, 10:05:45 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int minimumTimeToInitialState(string word, int k) {
    auto z = z_function(word);
    for (int i = k, n = word.size(); i < n; i += k)
        if (z[i] == n - i)
            return i / k;
    return (word.size() + k - 1) / k;
}

[04/02/24, 10:09:10 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> resultGrid(vector<vector<int>>& image, int threshold) {
        int n = image[0].size();
        int m = image.size();
        vector<vector< pair<int,int> >> result;
        for(int i=0 ; i<m ; i++){
            vector<pair<int, int>> row;
            for(int j=0 ; j<n ; j++){
                row.push_back(make_pair(0,0) );
            }
            result.push_back(row);
        }
      
        int dx[4] = {1,-1,0,0};
        int dy[4] = {0,0,1,-1};
        for(int x=0 ; x<=m-3 ; x++){
            for(int y=0 ; y<=n-3 ; y++){  
                // 3 * 3 matrix 
                // (x,y) --> (x+2,y+2);
                bool isValid = true;
                int sum = 0;
                // check is it is a valid region 
                for(int i=x ; i<x+3 ; i++){
                    for(int j=y ; j<y+3 ; j++){
                            sum+=image[i][i];
                        
                        for(int k=0 ; k<4 ; k++){
                            int nx = i+dx[k];
                            int ny = j+dy[k];
                            if(nx >=0 && ny<n && nx<m && ny>=0 ){
                                if(abs(image[i][j] - image[nx][ny]) > threshold){
                                    isValid = false;
                                    break;
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
                // if valid then populate the result vector 
                if(isValid){
                    cout<<"sum is "<<sum<<" ";
                    cout<<"valid matix is "<<x<<","<<x+2<<"->"<<y<<","<<y+2<<endl;
                    int average = sum/9;
                    cout<<" average is "<<average<<"  ";
                    for(int i=x ; i<x+3 ; i++){
                        for(int j=y ; j<y+3 ; j++){
                            // if(result[i][j].first == -1) result[i][j].first = 0;
                            result[i][j].first += average;
                            result[i][j].second++;
                        }
                    }
                }

            }
        }
        vector<vector<int>> res(m,vector<int>(n,0));
       for (int i = 0; i < m; ++i) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
            pair<int, int> p = result[i][j];
            // if(p.first = -1){
            //     p.first = image[i][j];
            //     p.second = 1;
            // }
            cout<<"("<<p.first<<","<<p.second<<")"<<" ";
            res[i][j] = p.first / p.second;
        }
           cout<<endl;
    }
        return res;
        
        
        
    }   
};
[04/02/24, 10:11:27 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-grid-of-region-average/
[04/02/24, 10:12:34 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> resultGrid(vector<vector<int>>& image, int threshold) {
        int n = image.size();
        int m = image[0].size();
        
        vector<vector<int>> ans(n, vector<int>(m,0));
        vector<vector<int>> cnt(n, vector<int>(m,0));
        
        vector<vector<int>> csum = image;
        
        
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                csum[i][j] += csum[i-1][j];
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<m;j++){
                csum[i][j] += csum[i][j-1];
            }
        }
        
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(i+2 < n && j+2 < m){
                    // 3x3 grid is possible
                    bool adj_val = true;
                    for(int x=i;x<=i+2;x++){
                        for(int y=j;y<=j+2;y++){
                            if(x-1 >= 0 && abs(image[x-1][y] - image[x][y]) > threshold){
                                adj_val = false;
                                break;
                            }
                            if(y-1 >= 0 && abs(image[x][y-1] - image[x][y]) > threshold){
                                adj_val = false;
                                break;
                            }
                            if(x+1 < n && abs(image[x+1][y] - image[x][y]) > threshold){
                                adj_val = false;
                                break;
                            }
                            if(y+1 < m && abs(image[x][y+1] - image[x][y]) > threshold){
                                adj_val = false;
                                break;
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    if(adj_val){
                        // 3x3 grid is satisfying rule
                        
                        for(int x=i;x<=i+2;x++){
                            for(int y=j;y<=j+2;y++){
                                cnt[x][y]++;
                            }
                        }
                        
                        ans[i][j] += csum[i+2][j+2];
                        ans[i][j] -= (i-1 >= 0 ? csum[i-1][j+2] : 0);
                        ans[i][j] -= j-1 >= 0 ? csum[i+2][j-1] : 0;
                        if(i-1 >= 0 && j-1 >= 0){
                            ans[i][j] += image[i-1][j-1];
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        cout<<"ans before"<<endl;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                cout<<ans[i][j]<<" ";
            }cout<<endl;
        }
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(ans[i][j] == 0){
                    ans[i][j] = image[i][j];
                }
                else{
                    ans[i][j] /= 9;
                }
            }
        }
        cout<<"csum"<<endl;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                cout<<csum[i][j]<<" ";
            }cout<<endl;
        }
        cout<<"count"<<endl;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                cout<<cnt[i][j]<<" ";
            }cout<<endl;
        }
        
        
        return ans;
    }
};
[04/02/24, 10:13:54 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    
    vector<vector<int>> resultGrid(vector<vector<int>>& image, int th) {
        int m = image.size();
        int n = image[0].size();
        vector<vector<int>> result(m, vector<int>(n, 0)), cnt(m, vector<int>(n, 0));
        vector<int> dx={0,1,0,-1}, // movements
                    dy={1,0,-1,0}; 
        for (int i = 0; i < m-2; i++) { //Len of 3 requires 3 empty spaces
            for (int j = 0; j < n-2; j++) {  //Width of 3 requires 3 empty spaces
                int sum = 0;
                int no=0;
                for(int x=i;x<i+3;x++) { //Len of 3 formation (square)
                    for(int y=j;y<j+3;y++) { //Width of 3
                        bool ad=0; //To add only once
                        for(int z=0;z<4;z++) { //For all the adjacent directions
                            int nx=x+dx[z],ny=y+dy[z];
                            if(nx>=i and nx<i+3 and ny>=j and ny<j+3) { //Checking if it is valid and in the square
                                if(abs(image[nx][ny]-image[x][y])<=th) { //Checking if it is less than threshold
                                    if(!ad) //If added once, no need to add again else repetation will result in WA
                                    sum+=image[x][y],ad=1; //Mark as added by ad=1
                                }
                                else {
                                    no=1; //If outside threshold, not possible, break
                                    break;
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
                if(no) continue;
                sum/=9; //Square of 3*3 = 9
                for(int x=i;x<i+3;x++) {
                    for(int y=j;y<j+3;y++) {
                        result[x][y]+=sum; //Add the sum
                        cnt[x][y]++;  //Count to get the average in the end
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<m;i++) { //For answer
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++) {
                // cout<<result[i][j]<<" "<<cnt[i][j]<<" "<<i<<" "<<j<<endl;
                if(cnt[i][j]==0)  
                    result[i][j]=image[i][j];
                else
                    result[i][j]/=cnt[i][j]; 
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
};

[04/02/24, 10:30:22 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> dx = {0,0,1,-1};
    vector<int> dy = {1,-1,0,0};
    vector<vector<int>> resultGrid(vector<vector<int>>& image, int threshold) {
        int n = image.size();
        int m = image[0].size();
        
        vector<vector<int>> ans(n, vector<int>(m,0));
        vector<vector<int>> cnt(n, vector<int>(m,0));
        
        for(int i=0;i<n-2;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m-2;j++){
                bool isValid = true;
                for(int x=i;x<=i+2;x++){
                    for(int y=j;y<=j+2;y++){
                        for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
                            int nx = i + dx[k];
                            int ny = j + dy[k];
                            if(nx >= 0 && nx < n && ny < m && ny >= 0 ){
                                if(abs(image[i][j] - image[nx][ny]) > threshold){
                                    isValid = false;
                                    break;
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    if(isValid){
                        // 3x3 grid is satisfying rule
                        int sum = 0;
                        for(int x=i;x<=i+2;x++){
                            for(int y=j;y<=j+2;y++){
                                cnt[x][y]++;
                                sum += image[x][y];
                            }
                        }
                        sum /= 9;
                        for(int x=i;x<=i+2;x++){
                            for(int y=j;y<=j+2;y++){
                                ans[x][y] = sum;
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        
        cout<<"ans before"<<endl;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                cout<<ans[i][j]<<" ";
            }cout<<endl;
        }
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(cnt[i][j] == 0){
                    ans[i][j] = image[i][j];
                }
                else{
                    ans[i][j] /= cnt[i][j];
                }
            }
        }
        cout<<"count"<<endl;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                cout<<cnt[i][j]<<" ";
            }cout<<endl;
        }   
        return ans;
    }
};

[04/02/24, 10:50:12 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int minimumTimeToInitialState(string word, int k) {
        int n = word.length();

        int time = 1;
        int i = k;

        while(i < n){
            if(word.substr(i) == word.substr(0,n-i)){
               return time;
            }
            else{
                time++;
                i += k;
            }
        }
        return time;
    }
};

[04/02/24, 10:56:31 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> dx = {0, 0, 1, -1};
    vector<int> dy = {1, -1, 0, 0};
    vector<vector<int>> resultGrid(vector<vector<int>>& image, int threshold) {
        int n = image.size();
        int m = image[0].size();

        vector<vector<int>> ans(n, vector<int>(m, 0));
        vector<vector<int>> cnt(n, vector<int>(m, 0));

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 2; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m - 2; j++) {
                // going over 3x3 matrices starting from (i,j) as top left
                // corner
                bool isValid = true;
                for (int x = i; x <= i + 2; x++) {
                    for (int y = j; y <= j + 2; y++) {
                        // check for validity of 3x3 matrix
                        for (int k = 0; k < 4; k++) {
                            int nx = i + dx[k];
                            int ny = j + dy[k];
                            if (nx >= 0 && nx < n && ny >= 0 && ny < m) {
                                if (abs(image[i][j] - image[nx][ny]) >
                                    threshold) {
                                    isValid = false;
                                    break;
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
                if (isValid) {
                    // 3x3 grid is satisfying rule
                    int sum = 0;
                    cout << "i : " << i << " j : " << j << endl;
                    for (int x = i; x <= i + 2; x++) {
                        for (int y = j; y <= j + 2; y++) {
                            cnt[x][y]++;
                            sum += image[x][y];
                        }
                    }
                    sum /= 9;
                    for (int x = i; x <= i + 2; x++) {
                        for (int y = j; y <= j + 2; y++) {
                            ans[x][y] += sum;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        cout << "ans before" << endl;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                cout << ans[i][j] << " ";
            }
            cout << endl;
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                if (cnt[i][j] == 0) {
                    ans[i][j] = image[i][j];
                } else {
                    ans[i][j] /= cnt[i][j];
                }
            }
        }
        cout << "count" << endl;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                cout << cnt[i][j] << " ";
            }
            cout << endl;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[04/02/24, 4:52:37 PM] Satvik Saini: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
    TreeNode* f(string traversal, int n, int i, int dash){
        //base case
        if(traversal.length() == 0) return NULL;
        if(i == n) return NULL;

        //recursive case
        TreeNode* root = new TreeNode(traversal[i] - '0');
        int k = i + dash + 1;
        int d = 0, temp = 0;
        while(k < n || d != dash){
            if(traversal[k++] != '-'){
                d = temp;
            }
            else temp++;
        }
        root->left = f(traversal.substr(i,k-i-1), k-i-1, 0, dash+1);
        if(d == dash){
            root->right = f(traversal.substr(k), n-k, 0, dash+1);
        }
        return root;

    }
public:
    TreeNode* recoverFromPreorder(string traversal) {
        if(traversal.size() == 1) return new TreeNode(traversal[0]-'0');
        return f(traversal, traversal.size(), 0, 1);
    }
};

[04/02/24, 5:24:11 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    TreeNode* f(vector<int>& nums,int i,int k){
        // base case
        if(i == k-1)new TreeNode(nums[k]);
        if(i >= k) return NULL;

        // rcursive case
        // partition left and right subtree 
        // if only one subtree it is left subtree for sure 
        int curr_level = nums[i];
        TreeNode* root = new TreeNode(nums[i+1]);

        int left_end = i;
        for(int j=i+1 ; j<nums.size() ; j++){
            if(nums[j] == curr_level-1){
                left_end = j-1;
            }
        }
        bool flag = false;
        if(left_end == i){
            flag = true;
            left_end = k;
        }

        root -> left = f(nums,i+2,left_end);
        if(!flag) root->right = f(nums,left_end+1,k);
        return root;
    }
    TreeNode* recoverFromPreorder(string arr) {
        if( arr.size() == 1) return new TreeNode(arr[0]-'a');
        vector<int> vec;
        vec.push_back(0);
        int i=0;
        while(i<arr.size()){
            if(arr[i] == '-'){
                vec.push_back(arr[i]);
                i++;
            }
            else{
                int count = 0;
                while(arr[i] != '-') {
                    i++; 
                    count--;
                }
                vec.push_back(count);
            }
        }

            // 1 -1 2 -2 3 -2 4 -1 5 -2 6 -2 7
            // find khere to where is left subtree 
            // find where to where is right subtree 
            return f(vec,0,vec.size()-1);

    }
};

[06/02/24, 1:40:45 PM] Satvik Saini: class SmallestInfiniteSet {
    set<int> st;  // storing the element which is less than curr (eg. added 1 after popping 1, 2, 3 and curr = 4 at this stage)
    // so if set is not empty, then the next smallest no possible is always the the beginning of the set
    int curr;     // storing the current minimum element
public:
    SmallestInfiniteSet() {     // O(1)
        curr = 1;
    }
    
    int popSmallest() {          // O(log1000)
        if(st.size()){
            int popped = *st.begin();
            st.erase(st.begin());
            return popped;
        }
        curr++;
        return curr - 1;
    }
    
    void addBack(int num) {      // O(log1000)
        if(curr > num){
            st.insert(num);
        }
    }
};

[07/02/24, 7:44:01 AM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long

class Solution {
    ll reverse(int n){
        ll rev = 0;
        while(n){
            int rem = n%10;
            rev = rev * 10 + (ll)rem;
            n /= 10;
        }
        return rev;
    }
public:
    int countNicePairs(vector<int>& nums) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;

        for(int ele : nums){
            mp[ele - reverse(ele)]++;
        }

        ll cnt = 0;

        for(int ele : nums){
            cnt += mp[ele - reverse(ele)] - 1;
        }

        return cnt / 2;
    }
};

[07/02/24, 7:55:38 AM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long

class Solution {
    ll reverse(int n){
        ll rev = 0;
        while(n){
            int rem = n%10;
            rev = rev * 10 + (ll)rem;
            n /= 10;
        }
        return rev;
    }
public:
    int countNicePairs(vector<int>& nums) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;

        // for(int ele : nums){
        //     mp[ele - reverse(ele)]++;
        // }

        ll cnt = 0;

        for(int ele : nums){
            if(mp.find(ele - reverse(ele)) != mp.end()){
                cnt += mp[ele - reverse(ele)];
            }
            mp[ele - reverse(ele)]++;
        }

        return cnt;
    }
};

[07/02/24, 7:53:31 PM] Satvik Saini: class LRUCache {
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    // int recent;
    int size;
    int cap;
    queue<int> q;

public:
    LRUCache(int capacity) {
        size = 0;
        cap = capacity;
    }
    
    int get(int key) {
        return mp.find(key) == mp.end() ? -1 : mp[key];
    }
    
    void put(int key, int value) {
        if(size == cap){
            int least_recent = q.front();
            q.pop();
            mp[least_recent] = -1;
            mp[key] = value;
            // recent = key;
            q.push(key);
        }
        else{
            size++;
            q.push(key);
            mp[key] = value;
            // recent = key;
        }
        for(auto it : mp){
            cout<<it.first<<" "<<it.second<<endl;
        }cout<<endl;
    }
};

/**
 * Your LRUCache object will be instantiated and called as such:
 * LRUCache* obj = new LRUCache(capacity);
 * int param_1 = obj->get(key);
 * obj->put(key,value);
 */
[07/02/24, 8:49:40 PM] Satvik Saini: class LRUCache {
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    queue<int> q;
    int cap;
public:
    LRUCache(int capacity) {
        cap = capacity;
    }
    
    int get(int key) {
        return mp.find(key) == mp.end() ? -1 : mp[key];
    }
    
    void put(int key, int value) {
        if(q.size() == cap){
            int least_recent = q.front();
            q.pop();
            mp[least_recent] = -1;
        }
        q.push(key);
        mp[key] = value;
    }
};

/**
 * Your LRUCache object will be instantiated and called as such:
 * LRUCache* obj = new LRUCache(capacity);
 * int param_1 = obj->get(key);
 * obj->put(key,value);
 */

[07/02/24, 9:30:40 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class LRUCache {
public:
    unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
    queue<int> q;
    int cap;
    LRUCache(int capacity) {
        cap = capacity;
        
    }
    
    int get(int key) {
        if(mpp.find(key) == mpp.end()) return -1;
        else return mpp[key];
    }
    
    void put(int key, int value) {
        // updation
        if(mpp.find(key) != mpp.end()){ mpp[key] = value; return;}
        // insertion
        q.push(key);
        if(q.size() == cap+1){
            int k = q.front();
            q.pop();
            mpp.erase(k);
            return;
        }
        mpp[key] = value;
    }
};

/**
 * Your LRUCache object will be instantiated and called as such:
 * LRUCache* obj = new LRUCache(capacity);
 * int param_1 = obj->get(key);
 * obj->put(key,value);
 */

[08/02/24, 6:40:02 PM] Satvik Saini: class TimeMap {
    unordered_map<string,vector<pair<int,string>>> mp;
public:
    TimeMap() {
    }
    
    void set(string key, string value, int timestamp) {
        mp[key].push_back({timestamp, value});
    }
    
    string get(string key, int timestamp) {
        if(mp.find(key) != mp.end()){
            string s;
            int t = 0;
            for(auto it : mp){
                if(it.first == key){
                    for(auto p : it.second){
                        int time = p.first;
                        if(time <= timestamp && time > t){
                            t = time;
                            s = p.second;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
            return s;
        }
        return "";
    }
};

/**
 * Your TimeMap object will be instantiated and called as such:
 * TimeMap* obj = new TimeMap();
 * obj->set(key,value,timestamp);
 * string param_2 = obj->get(key,timestamp);
 */

[09/02/24, 9:33:22 AM] Satvik Saini: class FoodRatings {
    unordered_map<string,pair<string,int>> mp;
public:
    FoodRatings(vector<string>& foods, vector<string>& cuisines, vector<int>& ratings) {
        for(int i=0;i<foods.size();i++){
            mp[foods[i]] = {cuisines[i], ratings[i]};
        }
    }
    
    void changeRating(string food, int newRating) {
        auto it = mp.find(food);
        cout<<it->first<<" "<<it->second.second<<" "<<it->second.first<<endl;
        it->second.second = newRating;
    }
    
    string highestRated(string cuisine) {
        string s;
        int rating = 0;
        for(auto it : mp){
            if(it.second.first == cuisine){
                if(it.second.second > rating){
                    s = it.first;
                }
                else if(it.second.second == rating){
                    s = min(s, it.first);
                }
            }
        }
        return s;
    }
};

/**
 * Your FoodRatings object will be instantiated and called as such:
 * FoodRatings* obj = new FoodRatings(foods, cuisines, ratings);
 * obj->changeRating(food,newRating);
 * string param_2 = obj->highestRated(cuisine);
 */

[09/02/24, 11:54:22 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public: 
    int dp[301];
    unordered_set<string> mpp;
    bool f(int i, const string& s ){
        if(i == s.size()){
            return true;
        }
        if(dp[i] != -1) return dp[i];

        // start fro ith index of s , keep checking for its substrings 
        bool ans = false;
        for(int k=i ; k<s.size() ; k++){
            if(mpp.find(s.substr(i,k-i+1)) != mpp.end()){
                ans =  f(k+1,s);
                if(ans == true) return dp[i] = true;
            }
        }
        return dp[i] = false;

    }
    bool wordBreak(string s, vector<string>& wordDict) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        for(auto& x : wordDict) mpp.insert(x);
        return f(0,s);
    }
};

[09/02/24, 12:01:24 PM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎11 min
[09/02/24, 12:01:52 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:

    bool isPossible(string s, vector<string>& wordDict, int i, vector<int> &dp){
        //base case
        if(i == s.length()){
            return true;
        }

        //lookup
        if(dp[i] != -1){
            return dp[i];
        }
    
        //recursive case
        string str = "";
        for(int j=i;j<s.length();j++){
            str += s[j];
            auto it = find(wordDict.begin(), wordDict.end(), str);

            if(it != wordDict.end()){
                if(isPossible(s, wordDict, j+1, dp)){
                    return dp[i] = true;
                }
            } 
        }
        return dp[i] = false;
    }

    bool wordBreak(string s, vector<string>& wordDict) {
        vector<int> dp(s.length()+1, -1);
        return isPossible(s, wordDict, 0, dp);
    }
};
[09/02/24, 12:05:01 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: 3ms

[09/02/24, 12:05:34 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:

    bool isPossible(string s, unordered_set<string>& wordDict, int i, vector<int> &dp){
        //base case
        if(i == s.length()){
            return true;
        }

        //lookup
        if(dp[i] != -1){
            return dp[i];
        }
    
        //recursive case
        string str = "";
        for(int j=i;j<s.length();j++){
            str += s[j];
            auto it = wordDict.find(str);

            if(it != wordDict.end()){
                if(isPossible(s, wordDict, j+1, dp)){
                    return dp[i] = true;
                }
            } 
        }
        return dp[i] = false;
    }

    bool wordBreak(string s, vector<string>& wordDict) {
        vector<int> dp(s.length()+1, -1);
        unordered_set<string> st;
        return isPossible(s, st, 0, dp);
    }
};

    bool f(int i, const string& s ){

            return true;
        }

        if(dp[i] != -1) return dp[i];
        // start for ith index of s , keep checking for its substrings 

        bool ans = false;
        string temp  = "";
        for(int k=i ; k<s.size() ; k++){
            temp += s[k]; 
            if(mpp.find(temp) != mpp.end()){
                ans =  f(k+1,s);
                if(ans == true) return dp[i] = true;
            }
        }
        return dp[i] = false;

    }
    bool wordBreak(string s, vector<string>& wordDict) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        for(auto& x : wordDict) mpp.insert(x);
        return f(0,s);
    }

[09/02/24, 12:30:11 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public: 
    int dp[21];
    unordered_set<string> mpp;
    vector<string> res;
    int f(int i, const string& s,string temp_string ){
        if(i == s.size()){
            res.push_back(temp_string);
            return 1;
        }

        if(dp[i] != -1) return dp[i];
        // start for ith index of s , keep checking for its substrings 

        int ans = 0;
        string temp  = "";
        for(int k=i ; k<s.size() ; k++){
            temp += s[k]; 
            if(mpp.find(temp) != mpp.end()){
                if(i != 0)
                temp_string += ' ';
                cout<<endl;
                cout<<"temp string befire call : "<<temp_string<<" ";
                ans += f(k+1,s,temp_string + temp);
                cout<<"temp string after call : "<<temp_string<<" ";
                cout<<endl;
                if(i != 0)
                temp.pop_back();
            }
        }
        return dp[i] = ans;

    }
    vector<string> wordBreak(string s, vector<string>& wordDict) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        for(auto& x : wordDict) mpp.insert(x);
        string temp = "";
         cout<<f(0,s,temp)<<" ";
         return res;
    }
};

[09/02/24, 1:22:29 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public: 
    int dp[21];
    unordered_set<string> mpp;
    vector<string> res;
    void f(int i, const string& s,string temp_string ){
        if(i == s.size()){
            temp_string.pop_back();
            res.push_back(temp_string);
            return ;
        }

        if(dp[i] != -1) return dp[i];
        // start for ith index of s , keep checking for its substrings 

        int ans = 0;
        string temp  = "";
        for(int k=i ; k<s.size() ; k++){
            temp += s[k]; 
            if(mpp.find(temp) != mpp.end()){
                
                cout<<endl;
                cout<<"temp string befire call : "<<temp_string<<" ";
                f(k+1,s,temp_string + temp + ' ');
                cout<<"temp string after call : "<<temp_string<<" ";
                cout<<endl;
                
            }
        }

    }
    vector<string> wordBreak(string s, vector<string>& wordDict) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        for(auto& x : wordDict) mpp.insert(x);
        string temp = "";
         f(0,s,temp)<<" ";
         return res;
    }
};

class MyCalendar {
    map<int,int> mp;
public:
    MyCalendar() {
    }
    
    bool book(int start, int end) {
        auto it = mp.upper_bound(start);
        if(it == mp.end() || it->second >= end){
            mp[end] = start;
            return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
};

    }
    
    bool book(int start, int end) {
        for(auto &x : mpp){
            if((start >= x.first && start <= x.second) || (end - 1 >= x.first && end - 1<=x.second) || (start <= x.first && end-1 >= x.second)) return false;
        }
        mpp[start] = end - 1;
        return true;

    }

[09/02/24, 7:29:32 PM] Satvik Saini: class MyCalendarTwo {
    map<int,int> single_booking;
    map<int,int> double_booking;
public:
    MyCalendarTwo() {
    }
    
    bool book(int start, int end) {
        for(auto it : double_booking){
            int s = it.first;
            int e = it.second;

            if((start < e) && (end > s)){
                // current booking lies in the range of double booking which is not possible
                return false;
            }
        }
        // now check if this booking creates any double booking
        // if yes, then add it into the double booking
        for(auto it : single_booking){
            int s = it.first;
            int e = it.second;

            if((start < e) && (end > s)){
                // double booking is created
                int dbl_s = max(start, e);
                int dbl_e = min(end, s);

                double_booking[dbl_s] = dbl_e;
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
};

 * MyCalendarTwo* obj = new MyCalendarTwo();
 * bool param_1 = obj->book(start,end);
 */

[09/02/24, 7:43:52 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class MyCalendarTwo {
public:
    unordered_map<int,int> singlebook;
    unordered_map<int,int> doublebook;
    MyCalendarTwo() {
        
    }
    
    bool book(int start, int end) {

        for(auto&x : doublebook){
            int s = x.first;
            int e = x.second;
            if(start < e && end > s){
                return false;
            }
        }
        for(auto&x : singlebook){
            int s = x.first;
            int e = x.second;
            if(start<e && end>s){
                doublebook[max(start,s)] = min(end,e);
            }
        }
        singlebook[start] = end;
        return true;

    }
};

// Comparator For Set Of Pair
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;

// Declaring a custom comparator
struct comp {
	// Operator() overloading
	bool operator()(const pair<int, int>& p1,
					const pair<int, int>& p2)
	{
		// new definition
		return p1.second - p2.second;
	}
};

int main()
{
	// Declaring a set of pairs with comparator
	set<pair<int, int>, comp> s;

	// Adding pairs into the set
	s.insert({ 4, 3 });
	s.insert({ 5, 2 });
	s.insert({ 6, 1 });
	s.insert({ 7, 0 });

	for (auto i = s.begin(); i != s.end(); i++) {
		cout << i->first << " " << i->second << endl;
	}

	return 0;
}

// Comparator For Set Of Pair
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;

// Declaring a custom comparator
struct comp {
	// Operator() overloading
	bool operator()(const pair<char, int>& p1,
					const pair<char, int>& p2)
	{
		// new definition
		if (p1.first == p2.first) {
			return p1.second > p2.second;
		}
		return p1.first < p2.first;
	}
};

int main()
{
	// Declaring a set of pairs with comparator
	set<pair<char, int>, comp> s;

	// Adding pairs into the set
	s.insert({ 'a', 3 });
	s.insert({ 'c', 2 });
	s.insert({ 'c', 4 });
	s.insert({ 'c', 5 });
	s.insert({ 'b', 4 });
	s.insert({ 'b', 3 });

	for (auto i = s.begin(); i != s.end(); i++) {
		cout << i->first << " " << i->second << endl;
	}

	return 0;
}

[10/02/24, 11:44:00 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    const  int MOD = 1e9 + 7;
    unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
    int f(int t, vector<int>& nums){
        // t is the target
        // select two elements which can make upto this target
        // check if equal or not 
        // then find out how many trees can be made using the selected elements 
        // return count += all A*B 
        int count = 0;
        for(int x = 0 ; x < t ; x++){
            if(nums[t] % nums[x] == 0 && mpp.find(nums[t]/nums[x]) != mpp.end()){
                count = (count + f(x,nums)*f(mpp[nums[t]/nums[x]],nums) ) % MOD;
            }
        }
        return 1 + count;
        
    }
    int numFactoredBinaryTrees(vector<int>& arr) {
        sort(arr.begin(),arr.end());
        int count = 0; 
       for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size() ; i++){mpp[arr[i]] = i;}
       for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size() ; i++){
            count = (count + f(i,arr)) % MOD;
        }
        return count;
        
    }
};

‎[10/02/24, 12:01:39 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎image omitted
[10/02/24, 12:03:01 PM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long

class Solution {
    int mod = 1e9 + 7;
public:
    int numFactoredBinaryTrees(vector<int>& arr) {
        // sorted the arr because we want to check for the factors
        sort(arr.begin(), arr.end());

        // set is created to find whether i/j is present in arr or not in O(1)
        unordered_set<int> st(arr.begin(), arr.end());

        // initialised dp with 1 because each element is itself a binary tree
        unordered_map<int,int> dp;
        for(int ele : arr){
            dp[ele] = 1;
        }

        for(int i : arr){
            for(int j : arr){
                if(j > sqrt(i)) break;
                if(i % j == 0 && st.find(i/j) != st.end()){
                    // j is divisible by i and also i/j is in the arr
                    ll temp = (ll)(dp[j]) * dp[i/j];

                    if(i/j == j){
                        // left and right child are same, so no combinations possible
                        dp[i] = (dp[i] + temp) % mod;
                    }
                    else{
                        // due to the combinations of placing the i and i/j element as left child or right child
                        dp[i] = (dp[i] + (temp * 2)) % mod;
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        int cnt = 0;
        for(auto it : dp){
            cnt = (cnt + it.second) % mod;
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};
[10/02/24, 12:08:22 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎Voice call, ‎6 min
[10/02/24, 12:08:20 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    const  int MOD = 1e9 + 7;
    unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
    int f(int root, vector<int>& nums){
        // t is the target
        // select two elements which can make upto this target
        // check if equal or not 
        // then find out how many trees can be made using the selected elements 
        if(mpp.find(root) != mpp.end()) return mpp[root];

        long long  count = 0;
        for(int x = 0 ; x < nums.size() && nums[x] < root ; x++){
            if(root % nums[x] == 0 && mpp.find(root/nums[x]) != mpp.end()){
                count = (count + (long long)f(nums[x],nums)*f(root/nums[x],nums)) % MOD;
            }
        }
        return  mpp[root] = 1 + count;
        
    }
    int numFactoredBinaryTrees(vector<int>& arr) {
        sort(arr.begin(),arr.end());
        int count = 0; 
    //    for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size() ; i++){mpp[arr[i]] = 1;}
       for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size() ; i++){
            count = (count + f(i,arr)) % MOD;
        }
        return count;
        
    }
};

[12/02/24, 1:12:56 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    string choice = "AGCT";
    bool isOk(string s, string e){
        vector<int> check(26,0);
        for(auto& x : s) check[x-'a']++;
        for(auto& x : e) check[x-'a']--;
        sort(check.begin(),check.end());
        if(check[0] == -1 && check[25] == 1) return true;
        return false;
        
    }
    int f(string s, string e, unordered_set<string>& bank,unordered_set<string>& stt ){

        if(s == e) return 0;  // agar s = e no moves needed 
        
        int cnt = 1e4;
        for(auto& x : bank){
            if(isOk(s,x) && stt.find(x) == stt.end()){
                // aap x pr ja sakte ho and aap pehele x pr nhi gai ho 
                stt.insert(x);// x ko path me dalo 
                cnt = min(cnt,f(x,e,bank,stt));  // x -> e me kitne moves laganege ??
                stt.erase(x); // x ko path se nikalo 
            }
        }
        return cnt == 1e4 ? 1e4 : cnt+1; // cannot convert s -> e then return 1e4

    }
    int minMutation(string s, string e, vector<string>& bank) {
        unordered_set<string> stt; // bank 
        for(auto& x : bank) stt.insert(x);  // bank me sab daldo 
        if(stt.find(e) == stt.end()) return -1;
        unordered_set<string> set; // path 
        set.insert(s); // first element ko path me dalo 

        int x = f(s,e,stt,set);  // s -> e me kitne moves laganege ??
        return x != 1e4 ? x : -1;

    }
};

[12/02/24, 6:33:37 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-genetic-mutation/
[12/02/24, 6:35:25 PM] Satvik Saini: // we used a visited set bec if we go from gene_A to gene_B 
// bec of 1 difference, then for gene_B we can again go to gene_A 
// which will create a problem

class Solution {

    bool isAdjacent(string s1, string s2){
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<8;i++){
            if(s1[i] != s2[i]) cnt++;
            if(cnt > 1) return false;
        }
        return cnt == 1;
    }

    int minMoves(string curr, string end, vector<string>& bank, unordered_set<string> &vis){
        //base case
        if(curr == end){
            return 0;
        }

        //recursive case

        int moves = INT_MAX;

        for(string s : bank){
            if(isAdjacent(curr, s) && vis.find(s) == vis.end()){
                vis.insert(s);
                moves = min(moves, 1 + minMoves(s, end, bank, vis));
                vis.erase(s);
            }
        }
        return moves == INT_MAX ? INT_MAX - 1 : moves;
    }
public:
    int minMutation(string start, string end, vector<string>& bank) {
        // end word is not present in bank
        if(find(bank.begin(), bank.end(), end) == bank.end()) return -1;

        unordered_set<string> vis;
        
        int ans = minMoves(start, end, bank, vis);

        return ans == INT_MAX - 1 ? -1 : ans;
    }
};

public:
    unordered_map<string,set<pair<int,string>> > mpp;
    TimeMap() {
    }
    
    void set(string key, string v, int t) {
        mpp[key].insert({t,v});
    }
    
    string get(string key, int t) {
        auto x = mpp[key];
        string ans = "";
        auto it = x.upper_bound({t,""});
        if(it == x.begin()) {return "";}
        else it--;

        return it->second;
    }
};

[12/02/24, 7:11:41 PM] Satvik Saini: class TimeMap {
    unordered_map<string,vector<pair<int,string>>> mp;
public:
    TimeMap() {
    }
    
    void set(string key, string value, int timestamp) {
        mp[key].push_back({timestamp, value});
    }
    
    string get(string key, int timestamp) {
        if(mp.find(key) != mp.end()){
            string s;
            int t = 0;
            for(auto it : mp){
                if(it.first == key){
                    for(auto p : it.second){
                        int time = p.first;
                        if(time <= timestamp && time > t){
                            t = time;
                            s = p.second;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
            return s;
        }
        return "";
    }
};

[13/02/24, 7:54:49 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: # Tech Stack

- **Node.js** for our backend code which would be running graphql server inside node.js environment.
- **GraphQL** for our API, which provides a flexible and efficient way to define our data model and query it.
- **Prisma ORM** for our database ORM, which provides a type-safe and easy-to-use interface for interacting with our PostgreSQL database.
- **PostgreSQL** as our database, which is a powerful and reliable relational database system.
- **Supabase** for hosting and managing cloud postgresql db.
- **Redis** for query caching on server side and increase query speeds
- **Google OAuth** for Signin with Google
- **JSON WEB TOKENS** for authentication
- **Next.js** for our frontend, which is a popular framework for building React applications with server-side rendering and optimized performance.
- **TailwindCSS** for styling and re-useable components.
- **Codegen** for typesafe graphql queries and mitations.
- **Graphql-Request**  as API client for client server communication
- **React-Query** for client side data caching and query caching
- **Typescript** to maintain code quality and write type-safe code.
- **Amazon Web Services** for storage and deployments.

[13/02/24, 9:52:59 AM] Satvik Saini: class WordDictionary {
    unordered_set<string> st;
public:
    WordDictionary() {
    }
    
    void addWord(string word) {
        st.insert(word);
    }
    
    bool search(string word) {
        if(st.find(word) != st.end()) return true;
        // either '.' is in the string or the string is not present in the set
        
        for(string s : st){
            if(s.length() == word.length()){
                int i = 0;
                for(;i<word.length();i++){
                    if(word[i] != '.' && s[i] != word[i]){
                        break;
                    }
                }
                if(i == word.length()){
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};

[13/02/24, 9:54:53 AM] Satvik Saini: class LRUCache {
public:
    class node {
    public:
        int key;
        int val;
        node* next;
        node* prev;
        node(int _key, int _val) {
            key = _key;
            val = _val;
        }
    };

    node* head = new node(-1, -1);
    node* tail = new node(-1, -1);

    int cap;
    unordered_map<int, node*> m;

    LRUCache(int capacity) {
        cap = capacity;
        head->next = tail;
        tail->prev = head;
    }

    void addnode(node* newnode) {
        node* temp = head->next;
        newnode->next = temp;
        newnode->prev = head;
        head->next = newnode;
        temp->prev = newnode;
    }

    void deletenode(node* delnode) {
        node* delprev = delnode->prev;
        node* delnext = delnode->next;
        delprev->next = delnext;
        delnext->prev = delprev;
    }

    int get(int key_) {
        if (m.find(key_) != m.end()) {
            node* resnode = m[key_];
            int res = resnode->val;
            m.erase(key_);
            deletenode(resnode);
            addnode(resnode);
            m[key_] = head->next;
            return res;
        }

        return -1;
    }

    void put(int key_, int value) {
        if (m.find(key_) != m.end()) {
            node* existingnode = m[key_];
            m.erase(key_);
            deletenode(existingnode);
        }
        if (m.size() == cap) {
            m.erase(tail->prev->key);
            deletenode(tail->prev);
        }

        addnode(new node(key_, value));
        m[key_] = head->next;
    }
};
[13/02/24, 9:54:57 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class LRUCache {
public:
    
    unordered_map< int,pair<list<int> :: iterator , int> > mpp;
    list<int> Mylist;
    int cap;
    LRUCache(int capacity) {
        cap = capacity;
    }
    
    int get(int key) {
        // check if present in map 
        if(mpp.find(key) == mpp.end()) return -1;

        //key is in the map 
        Mylist.erase(mpp[key].first);
        Mylist.push_back(key);
        mpp[key].first = --Mylist.end();
        return mpp[key].second;
        

    }
    
    void put(int key, int value) {

        // if already present 
        // update value and order 
        if(mpp.find(key) != mpp.end() ){
            
            Mylist.erase(mpp[key].first);
            Mylist.push_back(key);
            mpp[key].first = --Mylist.end();
            mpp[key].second = value;
            return;
        }

        Mylist.push_back(key);
        mpp[key].first = --Mylist.end();
        mpp[key].second = value;

        if(Mylist.size() == cap+1){
            mpp.erase(*Mylist.begin());
            Mylist.erase(Mylist.begin());
        }
    } 

};

/**
 * Your LRUCache object will be instantiated and called as such:
 * LRUCache* obj = new LRUCache(capacity);
 * int param_1 = obj->get(key);
 * obj->put(key,value);
 */

[13/02/24, 10:10:07 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class WordDictionary {
public:
    WordDictionary() {}
    
    void addWord(string word) {
        words[word.size()].push_back(word);
    }
    
    bool search(string word) {
        for(auto s: words[word.size()]) if(isEqual(s, word)) return true;
        return false;
    }
    
private:
    unordered_map<int, vector<string>>words;
    
    bool isEqual(string a, string b){
        for(int i = 0; i < a.size(); i++){
            if(b[i] == '.') continue;
            if(a[i] != b[i]) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
[13/02/24, 10:11:29 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/zefengsong/
[13/02/24, 10:12:40 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: struct TrieNode{
    bool isKey;
    TrieNode* next[26];
    TrieNode():isKey(false){
        memset(next, NULL, sizeof(next));
    }
};

class WordDictionary {
public:
    WordDictionary() {
        root = new TrieNode();
    }
    
    void addWord(string word) {
        TrieNode* node = root;
        for(auto c: word){
            if(!node->next[c - 'a']) node->next[c - 'a'] = new TrieNode();
            node = node->next[c - 'a'];
        }
        node->isKey = true;
    }
    
    bool search(string word) {
        return helper(word, root);
    }

private:
    TrieNode* root;
    
    bool helper(string word, TrieNode* node){
        for(int i = 0; i < word.size(); i++){
            char c = word[i];
            if(c != '.'){
                if(!node->next[c - 'a']) return false;
                node = node->next[c - 'a'];
            }
            else{
                bool found = false;
                int j = 0;
                for(; j < 26; j++){
                    if(node->next[j]) found |= helper(word.substr(i + 1), node->next[j]);
                    if(found) return true;
                }
                if(j == 26) return false;
            }
        }
        return node->isKey;
    }
};

[13/02/24, 10:53:27 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class LFUCache {
public:

    map<int,list<pair<int,int>>> m;
    unordered_map<int,map<int,list<pair<int,int>>> :: iterator> mpp;
    int cap ; 
    LFUCache(int capacity) {
        cap = capacity;
    }
    
    int get(int key) {

        auto pos = std::find_if(mpp[key]->second.begin(), mpp[key]->second.end(),
                        [key](std::pair<int, int> const &b) { 
                            return b.first == key; 
                        }); 
        if(pos == mpp[key]->second.end())

        int freq = mpp[key]->first;
        int val = pos->second;x

        mpp[key]->second.erase(pos);
        m[++freq].push_back({key,val});
        mpp[key] = m.find(freq);
        return val;
        
    }
    
    void put(int key, int value) {

        // element is already present 
        if(mpp.find(key) != mpp.end()){

            auto pos = std::find_if(mpp[key]->second.begin(), mpp[key]->second.end(),
                        [key](std::pair<int, int> const &b) { 
                            return b.first == key; 
                        }); 

            int freq = mpp[key]->first;
            int val = pos->second;

            mpp[key]->second.erase(pos);
            m[freq+1].push_back({key,value});
            mpp[key] = m.find(freq+1);
            return ;

        }




        if(mpp.size() == cap){

            // remove lfu element and then add new element
            (m.begin()->second).erase((m.begin()->second).begin());
            m[1].push_back({key,value});
            mpp[key] = m.begin();
        }


        
    }
};

/**
 * Your LFUCache object will be instantiated and called as such:
 * LFUCache* obj = new LFUCache(capacity);
 * int param_1 = obj->get(key);
 * obj->put(key,value);
 */

public:

    map<int,list<pair<int,int>>> m;
    unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
    int cap ; 
    LFUCache(int capacity) {
        cap = capacity;
    }
    
    int get(int key) {

        cout<<"last get";
        if(mpp.find(key) == mpp.end()) return -1; 

        // for(auto& x : m){
        //     cout<<x.first<<" ";
        //     for(auto& y : x.second){
        //         cout<<y.first<<","<<y.second<<" , ";
        //     }
        //     cout<<endl;
        // }
        //     cout<<endl;
        //     cout<<endl;

        for(auto x : mpp){
            cout<<x.first<<" "<<x.second<<"     ";
        }

        auto pos = std::find_if(m[mpp[key]].begin(), m[mpp[key]].end(),
                        [key](std::pair<int, int> const &b) { 
                            return b.first == key; 
                        }); 


        int freq = mpp[key];
        int val = pos->second;

        m[mpp[key]].erase(pos);
        m[++freq].push_back({key,val});
        mpp[key] = freq;
        return val;
        
    }
    
    void put(int key, int value) {
        cout<<"last put";

        // element is already present 
        if(mpp.find(key) != mpp.end()){
            auto pos = find_if(m[mpp[key]].begin(), m[mpp[key]].end(),
                        [key](std::pair<int, int> const &b) { 
                            return b.first == key; 
                        }); 

            int freq = mpp[key];
            int val = pos->second;

            m[mpp[key]].erase(pos);
            m[++freq].push_back({key,value});
            mpp[key] = freq;
            return ;
        }
        // you have to insert now 
        if(mpp.size() == cap){
            // remove lfu element and then add new element
            if((m.begin()-> second).empty() ) return;
            auto it = (m.begin()->second).begin();
            mpp.erase(it->first);  
            (m.begin()->second).erase(it);
        }
        // aapke paas jagah for sure hai 
        m[1].push_back({key,value});
        mpp[key] = 1;
        
    }
};

[13/02/24, 5:30:12 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Twitter {
public:
    unordered_map<int,unordered_set<int>> followMap; // follow maps 
    // unordered_map<int,list<int>> tweetMap; // tracks tweets by each person 
    list<pair<int,int>> tweetMap; // tracks latest tweets
    unordered_set<int> users;


    Twitter() {
        
    }
    
    void postTweet(int u, int t) {
        tweetMap.push_back({u,t});
    }
    
    vector<int> getNewsFeed(int u) {

        vector<int> temp;
        int cnt = 0;
        for(auto it = tweetMap.rbegin() ; it != tweetMap.rend() ; it++){

            if(it->first == u || followMap[u].find(it->first) != followMap[u].end()){
                cnt++;
                temp.push_back(it->second);
            }
            if(cnt == 10) break;
        }  
        return temp;   
    }
    
    void follow(int followerId, int followeeId) {

        followMap[followerId].insert(followeeId);
        users.insert(followerId);
        users.insert(followeeId);
    }
    
    void unfollow(int followerId, int followeeId) {
        if(users.find(followerId) == users.end()) return;
        auto it = followMap[followerId].find(followeeId);
        if(it == followMap[followerId].end()) return;
        followMap[followerId].erase(it);
        
    }
};

[13/02/24, 5:34:24 PM] Satvik Saini: class Twitter {
    unordered_map<int,unordered_map<int,bool>> Follow;    // < followerId, < followeeId, isFollower > >
    vector<pair<int,int>> tweet;                          // <userId, tweetId>
public:
    Twitter() {
    }
    
    void postTweet(int userId, int tweetId) {
        tweet.push_back({userId, tweetId});
    }
    
    vector<int> getNewsFeed(int userId) {
        vector<int> feeds;
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int i=tweet.size()-1;i>=0;i--){
            if(cnt == 10) break;
            if(tweet[i].first == userId || Follow[userId][tweet[i].first] == true){
                // either tweet[i].first is itself userId or is a follower of userId, then only tweet will be pushed into feeds
                feeds.push_back(tweet[i].second);
                cnt++;
            }
        }
        return feeds;
    }
    
    void follow(int followerId, int followeeId) {
        Follow[followerId][followeeId] = true;
    }
    
    void unfollow(int followerId, int followeeId) {
        Follow[followerId][followeeId] = false;
    }
};

[14/02/24, 9:32:07 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <limits>

using namespace std;

class fenwick
{
    public:
    vector<int> bit;
    int size;

    fenwick(int n) : size(n), bit(n + 1, 0) {}

    void upd(int id, int val)
    {
        while (id <= size)
        {
            bit[id] += val;
            id += (id & -id);
        }
    }

    int query(int id)
    {
        int sum = 0;
        while (id > 0)
        {
            sum += bit[id];
            id -= (id & -id);
        }
        return sum;
    }

    int rangeQuery(int l, int r)
    {
        return query(r) - query(l - 1);
    }
};

// Function to find the maximum element in a range [l, r]
int maxInRange(fenwick &tree, int l, int r)
{
    return tree.rangeQuery(l, r);
}

// Function to find the minimum element in a range [l, r]
int minInRange(fenwick &tree, int l, int r)
{
    int n = tree.size;
    return tree.rangeQuery(l, r) / (r - l + 1);
}

int main()
{
    vector<int> arr; 
    arr.push_back(1);
    arr.push_back(3);
    arr.push_back(2);
    arr.push_back(7);
    arr.push_back(9);
    arr.push_back(11);
    int n = arr.size();
    fenwick tree(n); // Construct Fenwick Tree with size n

    // Build Fenwick Tree from array
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
    {
        tree.upd(i + 1, arr[i]);
    }

    int l = 2, r = 5; // Range to find minimum and maximum in [l, r]
    int maxElementInRange = maxInRange(tree, l, r);
    int minElementInRange = minInRange(tree, l, r);

    cout << "Maximum element in the range [" << l << ", " << r << "]: " << maxElementInRange << endl;
    cout << "Minimum element in the range [" << l << ", " << r << "]: " << minElementInRange << endl;

    return 0;
}
[14/02/24, 9:55:48 AM] Satvik Saini: class MagicDictionary {
    unordered_map<int,vector<int>> mp;
public:
    MagicDictionary() {
    }
    
    void buildDict(vector<string> dictionary) {
        for(string s : dictionary){
            mp[s.length()].push_back(s);
        }
    }

    bool isFound(string s1, string s2){
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<s1.length();i++){
            if(s1[i] != s2[i]) cnt++;
            if(cnt > 1) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
    
    bool search(string searchWord) {
        for(string s : mp[searchWord.length()]){
            if(isFound(s, searchWord)){
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};

/**

 * MagicDictionary* obj = new MagicDictionary();
 * obj->buildDict(dictionary);
 * bool param_2 = obj->search(searchWord);
 */

[14/02/24, 12:32:39 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Node{
    public:
    int data;
    Node* next;
    Node(int d){
        data = d;
        next = NULL;
    }
};

class MyLinkedList {
public:
    int len;
    Node* head;
    Node* tail;

    MyLinkedList() {
        len = 0;
        head = NULL;
        tail = NULL;
    }

    Node* getNode(int idx){

        if(idx >= len || idx < 0) return NULL; // index out of bound hai then null
        int t = 0;
        Node* temp = head; 
        while(idx--){
            temp = temp -> next;
        }
        return temp;
    }
    
    int get(int index) {
        Node* temp = getNode(index);
        if(temp == NULL) return -1;
        return temp->data;
    }
    
    void addAtHead(int val) {

        if(len == 0){
            head = tail = new Node(val);
            len++;
            return;
        }
            Node* temp = new Node(val);
            temp->next = head;
            head = temp;
            len++;
    }
    
    void addAtTail(int val) {

        Node* temp = new Node(val);
        tail -> next = temp;
        tail = temp;
        len++;
    }

    
    void addAtIndex(int index, int val) {
        if(index == 0){
            addAtHead(val);
            return;
        }
        if(index == len){
            addAtTail(val);
            return;
        }
        if(index > len) return;

        Node* prev = getNode(index-1);
        Node* temp = new Node(val);
        temp->next = prev->next;
        prev->next = temp;
        len++;
    }
    
    void deleteAtIndex(int index) {

        if(index < 0 || index >= len) return;

        Node* prev = getNode(index-1);
        Node* temp = prev->next;
        delete temp;
        prev->next = prev->next->next;
        len--;

    }
};

/**
 * Your MyLinkedList object will be instantiated and called as such:
 * MyLinkedList* obj = new MyLinkedList();
 * int param_1 = obj->get(index);
 * obj->addAtHead(val);
 * obj->addAtTail(val);
 * obj->addAtIndex(index,val);
 * obj->deleteAtIndex(index);
 */

[17/02/24, 7:06:14 PM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/n-queens/description/
class Solution {
private:
    bool isAttacking(vector<string> set,int i,int j,int n) {
        // base case
        if(n==0) return 0;
        if(n==2 || n==3) return 1;
        //recursive case
        bool ans=0;
        if(n==1) {
            ans=0;
            set.push_back("Q");
        }
        i=0;j=0;
        int dx[]={1,-1,0,0,1,-1,1,-1};
        int dy[]={0,0,1,-1,1,-1,-1,1};
        while(i!=0 && j!=0 && i!=n-1 && j!=n-1) {
            for(int k=0;k<8;i++) {
                int i2=i+dx[k];
                int j2=j+dy[k];
                ans|=isAttacking(set,i2,j2,n); 
            }
        }
        //i=0;j=0;
        return ans;
    }
public:
    vector<vector<string>> solveNQueens(int n) {
        vector<vector<string> > ans;
        vector<string> s(n);
        if(isAttacking(s,0,0,n)==0) ans.push_back(s);
        return ans;
    }
};
//Debug krde

[17/02/24, 8:46:15 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool isPossible(vector<int>& gas, vector<int>& cost, int s){
        int fuel = 0;
        int idx = s;
        bool flag = false;
        while(fuel >= 0){
            fuel += gas[idx] - cost[idx];
            idx = (idx+1) % gas.size();
            if(idx == s && fuel >= 0){
                flag = true;
                break;
            }
        }
        return flag;
    }
public:
    int canCompleteCircuit(vector<int>& gas, vector<int>& cost) {
        // vector<int> start;
        // int max_diff = INT_MIN;
        // for(int i=0;i<gas.size();i++){
        //     if(max_diff < gas[i] - cost[i]){
        //         max_diff = gas[i] - cost[i];
        //         start.clear();
        //         start.push_back(i);
        //     }
        //     else if(max_diff == gas[i] - cost[i]){
        //         start.push_back(i);
        //     }
        // }

        for(int i=0;i<gas.size();i++){
            if(gas[i] >= cost[i] && isPossible(gas, cost, i)) return i;
        }
        return -1;
    }
};

[18/02/24, 9:30:48 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    vector<int> Lps(string s){
        int n = s.length();
        vector<int> prefix(n, 0);

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            int j = prefix[i-1];

            while(j > 0 && s[i] != s[j]){
                j = prefix[j-1];
            }
            if(s[i] == s[j]){
                j++;
            }
            prefix[i] = j;
        }
        return prefix;
    }

    vector<string> prefixSuffix(string s) {
        vector<string> result;
        int n = s.length();
        vector<int> lps = Lps(s);

        // for (int i=0;i<n;i++) {
        //     if (lps[i] > 0) {
        //         result.push_back(s.substr(0, lps[i]));
        //     }
        // }
        for(int i=0;i<lps[lps.size()-1];i++){
            result.push_back(s.substr(0,i+1));
        }
        // if(lps[lps.size()-1] == s.length()-1) result.push_back(s);
        result.push_back(s);
        return result;
    }
public:
    long long countPrefixSuffixPairs(vector<string>& words) {
        unordered_map<string,vector<int>> mp;  // <string,[idx]>
        
        for(int i=0;i<words.size();i++){
            mp[words[i]].push_back(i);
        }
        
        for(auto p : mp){
            cout<<p.first<<" : ";
            for(auto it : p.second){
                cout<<it<<",";
            }cout<<endl;
        }cout<<"start"<<endl;
        
        
        long long cnt = 0;
        
        for(int i=0;i<words.size();i++){
            vector<string> v = prefixSuffix(words[i]);
            
            // vector<int> lps = Lps(words[i]);
            // cout<<"lps"<<" ";
            // for(int it : lps){
            //     cout<<it<<" ";
            // }cout<<endl;
    
            // cout<<words[i]<<" : ";
            // for(auto ss : v){
            //     cout<<ss<<", ";
            // }cout<<endl;
            for(string str : v){
                if(mp.find(str) == mp.end()) continue;
                for(auto it : mp[str]){
                    if(it < i){
                        cout<<"count increase "<<str<<" "<<words[i]<<", ";
                        cnt++;
                    }
                }
                cout<<endl;
            }
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};
