[19/02/24, 7:43:08 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int findLongestChain(std::vector<std::vector<int>>& pairs) {
        std::sort(pairs.begin(), pairs.end(), [](const std::vector<int>& a, const std::vector<int>& b) {
            return a[1] < b[1];
        });
        
        int cur = INT_MIN, ans = 0;
        
        for (const auto& pair : pairs) {
            if (cur < pair[0]) {
                cur = pair[1];
                ans++;
            }
        }
        
        return ans;
    }
};

[21/02/24, 7:24:30 AM] Satvik Saini: int findPlatform(int arr[], int dep[], int n)
    {
    	vector<pair<int,int>> train;
    	
    	for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
    	    train.push_back({dep[i],arr[i]});
    	}
    	
    	sort(train.begin(), train.end());
    	
    	set<int> st;
    	st.insert(train[0].first);
    	
    	int ans = 1;
    	
    	// we have to select that element from the set which has just smaller value than its arr time
    	
    	for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
    	   // bool flag = false;
    	   // for(auto it : st){
    	   //     if(it < train[i].second){
    	   //         st.erase(it);
    	   //         st.insert(train[i].first);
    	   //         flag = true;
    	   //         break;
    	   //     }
    	   // }
    	   auto it = st.lower_bound(train[i].second);
    	   if(it != st.end()){
    	       st.erase(it);
    	   }
    	   st.insert(train[i].first);
    	   // if(!flag){
    	   //     st.insert(train[i].first);
    	   // }
    	    int sz = st.size();
    	    ans = max(ans, sz);
    	}
    	return ans;
    // return st.size();
    }
[21/02/24, 7:38:31 AM] Satvik Saini: int findPlatform(int arr[], int dep[], int n)
    {
    	vector<pair<int,int>> train;
    	
    	for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
    	    train.push_back({dep[i],arr[i]});
    	}
    	
    	sort(train.begin(), train.end());
    	
    	set<int> st;
    	st.insert(train[0].first);
    	
    	int ans = 1;
    	
    	// we have to select that element from the set which has just smaller value than its arr time
    	
    	for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
    	   
    	   auto it = st.lower_bound(train[i].second);
    	   if(it == st.begin()){
    	       // smaller value does not exists
    	       st.insert(train[i].first);
    	       int sz = st.size();
    	        ans = max(ans, sz);
    	       continue;
    	   }
    	   it--;
    	   st.erase(it);
    	   st.insert(train[i].first);
    
    	}
    	return ans;
    }

[21/02/24, 8:54:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: vector<int> Solution::solve(vector<int> &nums, int B) {
    
    unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
    for(auto& x : nums) mpp[x]++;
    
    int n = nums.size();
    
    for(int i=0 ; i<nums.size() && B!=0  ; i++){
        // cout<<"hi";
        if(nums[i] != n){
            int a = nums[i];
            nums[i] = n;
            int b = mpp[n];
            nums[b] = a;
            swap(mpp[a],mpp[n]);
            B--;
            n--;
        }
    }
    return nums;
     
}

[21/02/24, 9:08:31 AM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> Solution::solve(vector<int> &nums, int B) {
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    
    for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
        mp[nums[i]] = i;
    }
    
    int N = nums.size();
    
    for(int i=0;i<nums.size() && B!=0; i++){
        if(nums[i] != N){
            int a = nums[i];
            nums[i] = N;
            int b = mp[N];
            nums[b] = a;
            // swapping values in map also
            mp[a] = b;
            mp[N] = i;
            B--;      
        }
        N--;
    }
    return nums;
}

[24/02/24, 8:10:45 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎22 min
[24/02/24, 8:23:42 AM] Satvik Saini: // APPROACH
// we will maintain a priority queue where the priority will be based on the time of the meeting
// at the top will be the meeting with lowest time
// if the time of some meeting are same, then take that meeting first which has a secret with one of the members
vector<bool> hasSecret(100,0);
class cmp{
    public:
    bool operator()(pair<int,pair<int,int>> &p1, pair<int,pair<int,int>> &p2){
        if(p1.first < p2.first) return true;
        if(p1.first == p2.first){
            return hasSecret[p1.second.first] || hasSecret[p1.second.second];
        }
        return true;
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> findAllPeople(int n, vector<vector<int>>& meetings, int firstPerson) {
        // vector<bool> hasSecret(n,0);
        hasSecret[0] = 1;
        hasSecret[firstPerson] = 1;

        priority_queue<pair<int,pair<int,int>>, vector<int,pair<int,int>>, cmp()> pq;
        for(int i=0;i<meetings.size();i++){
            pq.push({meetings[2],{meetings[0],meetings[1]}});
        }
        vector<int> ans;
        ans.push_back(0);

        while(!pq.empty()){
            int x = pq.top().second.first;
            int y = pq.top().second.second;
            pq.pop();

            if(hasSecret[x] || hasSecret[y]){
                hasSecret[x] = 1;
                hasSecret[y] = 1;
                ans.push_back(x);
                ans.push_back(y);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[24/02/24, 8:31:46 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: // APPROACH
// we will maintain a priority queue where the priority will be based on the time of the meeting
// at the top will be the meeting with lowest time
// if the time of some meeting are same, then take that meeting first which has a secret with one of the members

class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> m;
    inline bool cmp(pair<int,pair<int,int>> &p1, pair<int,pair<int,int>> &p2){
        if(p1.first < p2.first) return true;
        if(p1.first == p2.first){
            return hasSecret[p1.second.first] || hasSecret[p1.second.second];
        }
        return false;
    }
    bool hasSecret(){

    }
    vector<int> findAllPeople(int n, vector<vector<int>>& meetings, int firstPerson) {
        // vector<bool> hasSecret(n,0);
        m = meetings;
        hasSecret[0] = 1;
        hasSecret[firstPerson] = 1;

        priority_queue<pair<int,pair<int,int>>, vector<int,pair<int,int>>, cmp()> pq;
        for(int i=0;i<meetings.size();i++){
            pq.push({meetings[2],{meetings[0],meetings[1]}});
        }
        vector<int> ans;
        ans.push_back(0);

        while(!pq.empty()){
            int x = pq.top().second.first;
            int y = pq.top().second.second;
            pq.pop();

            if(hasSecret[x] || hasSecret[y]){
                hasSecret[x] = 1;
                hasSecret[y] = 1;
                ans.push_back(x);
                ans.push_back(y);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[24/02/24, 8:39:21 AM] Satvik Saini: // APPROACH
// we will maintain a priority queue where the priority will be based on the time of the meeting
// at the top will be the meeting with lowest time
// if the time of some meeting are same, then take that meeting first which has a secret with one of the members


class Solution {
public:
    vector<bool> hasSecret;
    class cmp{
        public:
        bool operator()(pair<int,pair<int,int>> &p1, pair<int,pair<int,int>> &p2){
            if(p1.first < p2.first) return true;
            if(p1.first == p2.first){
                return hasSecret[p1.second.first] || hasSecret[p1.second.second];
            }
            return false;
        }
    };
    vector<int> findAllPeople(int n, vector<vector<int>>& meetings, int firstPerson) {
        // vector<bool> hasSecret(n,0);
        hasSecret = vector<int>(n,0);
        hasSecret[0] = 1;
        hasSecret[firstPerson] = 1;

        priority_queue<pair<int,pair<int,int>>, vector<int,pair<int,int>>, cmp()> pq;
        for(int i=0;i<meetings.size();i++){
            pq.push({meetings[2],{meetings[0],meetings[1]}});
        }
        vector<int> ans;
        ans.push_back(0);

        while(!pq.empty()){
            int x = pq.top().second.first;
            int y = pq.top().second.second;
            pq.pop();

            if(hasSecret[x] || hasSecret[y]){
                hasSecret[x] = 1;
                hasSecret[y] = 1;
                ans.push_back(x);
                ans.push_back(y);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[24/02/24, 8:50:34 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> findAllPeople(int n, vector<vector<int>>& meetings, int firstPerson) {
        vector<int> res;
        set<int> ust;
        ust.insert(0);
        ust.insert(firstPerson);
        map<int,vector<pair<int,int>>> mp;
        for (auto &m : meetings) {
            mp[m[2]].push_back({m[0],m[1]});
        }
        for (auto &m : mp) {
            for (auto &v : m.second) { //front to back
                if (ust.count(v.first)) {
                    ust.insert(v.second);
                }
                if (ust.count(v.second)) {
                    ust.insert(v.first);
                }
            }
            for (auto it = m.second.rbegin(); it != m.second.rend(); ++it) { //back to front
                if (ust.count((*it).first)) {
                    ust.insert((*it).second);
                }
                if (ust.count((*it).second)) {
                    ust.insert((*it).first);
                }
            }
        }
        for (auto it = ust.begin(); it != ust.end(); ++it)
            res.push_back(*it);
        return res;
    }
};

[25/02/24, 9:33:19 AM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long

class Solution {
public:
    long long largestSquareArea(vector<vector<int>>& bottomLeft, vector<vector<int>>& topRight) {
        ll maxArea = 0;
        
        int n = bottomLeft.size();
        
        for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
            for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++){
                int down = max(bottomLeft[i][1], bottomLeft[j][1]);
                int up = min(topRight[i][1], topRight[j][1]);
                int left = max(bottomLeft[i][0], bottomLeft[j][0]);
                int right = min(topRight[i][0], topRight[j][0]);
                
                ll height = up - down;
                ll width = right - left;
                
                if(height < 0 || width < 0) continue;
                
                ll sl = min(height, width);
                
                maxArea = max(maxArea, sl*sl);
            }
        }
        return maxArea;
    }
};
[25/02/24, 9:35:47 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int f(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& changeIndices, int s, unordered_map<int,int> &mp){
        //base case
        if(mp.size() == nums.size()){
            return s-1;
        }
            
        if(s == changeIndices.size()){
            return s;
        }
        
        //recursive case
        
        int sec = INT_MAX;
        
        //op1
        if(nums[changeIndices[s]-1] == 0){
            int temp = changeIndices[s];
            changeIndices[s] = 0;
            mp[s] = 0;
            sec = min(sec, f(nums, changeIndices, s+1, mp));
            changeIndices[s] = temp;
            mp.erase(s);
        }
        
        //op2
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            if(nums[i] == 0) continue; 
            nums[i]--;
            sec = min(sec, f(nums, changeIndices, s+1, mp));
            nums[i]++;
        }
        
        //op3
        sec = min(sec, f(nums, changeIndices, s+1, mp));
        
        return sec;
    }
public:
    int earliestSecondToMarkIndices(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& changeIndices) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        int ans = f(nums, changeIndices, 0, mp);
        return ans >= changeIndices.size() ? -1 : ans + 1;
    }
};

        for(int i=1 ; i<=nums.size() ; i++){
            sum+=nums[i-1];
            if(mpp.find(i) == mpp.end()) return -1;
            if(mpp[i] != 0 && mpp[i]<nums[i-1]) return -1;
        }

[03/03/24, 10:16:47 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: from sortedcontainers import SortedList
class Solution:
    def resultArray(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:
        sl1 = SortedList()
        sl2 = SortedList()
        a1 = []
        a2 = []        
        a1.append(nums[0])
        a2.append(nums[1])
        sl1.add(nums[0])
        sl2.add(nums[1])

        for n in nums[2:]:
            num_larger1 = len(sl1) - sl1.bisect_right(n)
            num_larger2 = len(sl2) - sl2.bisect_right(n)
            if num_larger1 > num_larger2:
                sl1.add(n)
                a1.append(n)
            elif num_larger1 < num_larger2:
                sl2.add(n)
                a2.append(n)
            else:
                if len(a1) > len(a2):
                    sl2.add(n)
                    a2.append(n)
                else:
                    sl1.add(n)
                    a1.append(n)
        
        # print(a1, a2)
        return a1 + a2
[03/03/24, 10:17:10 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution(object):
    def resultArray(self, nums):
        """
        :type nums: List[int]
        :rtype: List[int]
        """
        def greaterCount(arr, val):
            return len(arr)-bisect.bisect(arr,val)
            
            
        a1,arr1=[nums[0]],[nums[0]]
        a2,arr2=[nums[1]],[nums[1]]
        for i in range(2,len(nums)):
            if greaterCount(a1, nums[i]) > greaterCount(a2, nums[i]): 
                arr1.append(nums[i])
                bisect.insort(a1, nums[i]) 
            elif greaterCount(a1, nums[i]) < greaterCount(a2, nums[i]): 
                arr2.append(nums[i])
                bisect.insort(a2, nums[i]) 
            elif greaterCount(a1, nums[i]) == greaterCount(a2, nums[i]) and len(arr1)<=len(arr2):
                arr1.append(nums[i])
                bisect.insort(a1, nums[i]) 
            else: 
                arr2.append(nums[i])
                bisect.insort(a2, nums[i]) 
            
        return arr1+arr2
[03/03/24, 10:23:34 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/distribute-elements-into-two-arrays-ii/solutions/4813886/ordered-set-made-easy/
[03/03/24, 10:30:11 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int greaterCount(vector<int>& arr, int val) {
        // binary search
        int r = arr.size() - 1;
        int l = 0;
        int m;
        while(l <= r){
            m = (r + l) / 2;
            if(arr[m] > val) l = m + 1;
            else if(arr[m] <= val) r = m - 1;
        }
        return l;
    }
    vector<int> resultArray(vector<int>& nums) {
        vector<int> arr1, arr2, arr1Sorted, arr2Sorted;
        arr1.push_back(nums[0]);
        arr2.push_back(nums[1]);
        arr1Sorted.push_back(nums[0]);
        arr2Sorted.push_back(nums[1]);
        for(int i = 2 ; i < nums.size() ; i++) {
            // Find the count of elements greater than nums[i] in the sorted arrays
            int a = greaterCount(arr1Sorted, nums[i]);
            int b = greaterCount(arr2Sorted, nums[i]);
            if(a > b || (a == b && arr1.size() <= arr2.size())){
                arr1Sorted.insert(arr1Sorted.begin() + a, nums[i]);
                arr1.push_back(nums[i]);
            } 
            else{
                arr2Sorted.insert(arr2Sorted.begin() + b, nums[i]);
                arr2.push_back(nums[i]);
            } 
        }
        arr1.insert(arr1.end(), arr2.begin(), arr2.end());
        return arr1;
    }
};

[03/03/24, 10:36:35 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int f(vector<vector<int>>& grid,int val){
        // cout<<"ELLO";
        
        int center = grid.size()/2;
        int cost = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<grid.size() ; i++){
            for(int j=0 ; j<grid.size() ; j++){
                 // cout<<"ELLO in func";
                    
                if(i == j && i <= center){
                    // leave
                }
                else if(i + j == grid.size()-1 && i <= center ){
                    // leave
                }
                else if(i >= center && j == center){
                    // leave
                }
                else{
                    // check
                    if(grid[i][j] != val){
                        cost++;
                    }
                }
                
            }
        }
        return cost;
    }
    
    int minimumOperationsToWriteY(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int n = grid.size();
        int a = f(grid , 0);
        int b = f(grid , 1);
        int c = f(grid, 2);
        int center = n/2;
        int ans = INT_MAX;
        // change the Y to 0 
        // move left up 
        // cout<<"ELLO";
        int i = center;
        int j = center;
        // cout<<" C : "<<center<<" ";
        int costX = 0;
        while(i >= 0 ){
            // cout<<"ELLOewdwed";
            // cout<<"i = "<<i<<" ";
            if(grid[i][i] != 0) costX++;
            i--;
            // if(i < 0) break;
        }
        i = center - 1;
        j = center + 1;
        while(i >= 0 && j <= n-1){
            // cout<<"hihi";
            
            if(grid[i--][j++] != 0) costX++;
        }
          i = center + 1;
        while(i<=n-1){
            if(grid[i++][center] != 0 ) costX++;
        }
        
        // now change the remaining squares to either 1 or 2 
        
        int costY = b;
        int costZ = c;
        if(ans > costX + min(costY,costZ) ){
            cout<<costX<<" "<<" + "<<costY<<","<<costZ<<" ";
            ans = costX + min(costY,costZ);
        }
        
        
        
        // change the Y to 1 
          i = j = center;
         costX = 0;
        while(i >= 0 ){
            if(grid[i][i] != 1) costX++;
            i--;
        }
        i = center - 1;
        j = center + 1;
        while(i >=0 && j <= n-1){
            if(grid[i--][j++] != 1) costX++;
        }
          i = center + 1;
        while(i<=n-1){
            if(grid[i++][center] != 1 ) costX++;
        }
        
        // now change the remaining squares to either 1 or 2 
        // cout<<"ELLO";
        
         costY = a;
         costZ = c;
        
        if(ans > costX + min(costY,costZ) ){
            cout<<costX + min(costY,costZ)<<" ";
            ans = costX + min(costY,costZ);
        }
        // change the Y to 2 
         i = j = center;
         costX = 0;
        while(i >= 0 ){
            if(grid[i][i--] != 2) costX++;
        }
        i = center - 1;
        j = center + 1;
        while(i >=0 && j <= n-1){
            if(grid[i--][j++] != 2) costX++;
        }
          i= center + 1;
        
        while(i<=n-1){
            if(grid[i++][center] !=2 ) costX++;
        }
        
        // now change the remaining squares to either 1 or 2 
         costY = a;
         costZ = b;
        
        if(ans > costX + min(costY,costZ) ){
            cout<<costX + min(costY,costZ)<<" ";
            ans = costX + min(costY,costZ);
        }
        return ans;
        
        
    }
};

[05/03/24, 10:41:50 AM] Satvik Saini: I/O Waiting: Processes often have to wait for input/output operations to complete. This could include waiting for data to be read from a disk, received from a network, or written to an output device.

CPU Waiting: Sometimes, processes must wait for access to the CPU. This typically occurs when multiple processes are competing for CPU time, and the operating system scheduler needs to allocate CPU resources fairly.

Semaphore Waiting: In concurrent programming, processes may need to wait for access to a shared resource protected by a semaphore. When a process attempts to acquire a semaphore that is currently held by another process, it must wait until the semaphore becomes available.

Condition Variable Waiting: In multithreaded programming, threads may need to wait for a certain condition to become true before proceeding. Condition variables are often used in conjunction with mutexes to implement thread synchronization.

Event Waiting: Processes or threads may wait for certain events to occur before continuing execution. This could include events such as user input, signals from other processes, or timers.

Barrier Waiting: In parallel computing, processes or threads may need to wait for all other processes or threads to reach a certain point before proceeding. Barriers are synchronization primitives used to coordinate the execution of multiple tasks.

Suspend/Resume Waiting: Processes may be suspended (temporarily halted) by the operating system for various reasons, such as when they are waiting for resources or when higher-priority tasks need to run. Processes in a suspended state are waiting until they are resumed by the operating system.

Sleep Waiting: Processes or threads may voluntarily enter a sleep state for a specified period, during which they are not actively executing but are waiting for a certain amount of time to elapse before resuming execution.
[05/03/24, 10:44:30 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: No, a busy wait cannot probably be avoided altogether. In a uniprocessor system, one could inhibit interrupts during
wait()and

signal()operations in semaphores, but that is not possible in multiprocessor systems. In fact, a busy wait (or

spinlock), can be useful, especially in multiprocessor systems, when the wait is expected to be short (as with

wait()and

signal()), because no context switch is required when a process must wait on the lock

[08/03/24, 6:56:08 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Ruk
[08/03/24, 7:05:55 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Define Computer Organization:
Computer organization refers to the arrangement of the various components of a computer system and how they interact to perform computing tasks. It involves the design and structure of the hardware components such as the central processing unit (CPU), memory, input/output devices, and the interconnection between them. Computer organization also encompasses the instruction set architecture (ISA) and the organization of data within the system. It focuses on the physical aspects of the computer system rather than the software.

Explain Microprogrammed Control Unit:
A microprogrammed control unit is a component of the central processing unit (CPU) responsible for executing instructions. Instead of using hardwired logic circuits to control instruction execution directly, a microprogrammed control unit uses microcode—a sequence of microinstructions stored in a control memory—to control the operation of the CPU.

When an instruction is fetched from memory, the microprogrammed control unit decodes it and generates a sequence of microinstructions required to execute that instruction. These microinstructions are executed in sequence to perform the desired operation. Microprogramming provides flexibility and ease of modification since the control logic is implemented using software-like microinstructions rather than fixed hardware circuits.

Explain How at a Particular Time One Device is Selected for Data Transfer to the Bus:
Data transfer to the bus in a computer system involves multiple devices accessing the system bus to send or receive data. To ensure orderly and efficient data transfer, a mechanism for selecting one device at a time is necessary. This is typically achieved through a process called bus arbitration.

Bus arbitration involves a set of rules or protocols that determine which device has access to the bus at any given time. One common method is the use of a bus arbiter, which is a hardware component responsible for managing bus access requests from different devices. The arbiter prioritizes these requests based on predefined criteria, such as the type of transaction, device priority, or a round-robin scheme.

When a device needs to transfer data to the bus, it asserts a request signal to the bus arbiter. The arbiter evaluates the requests it receives and grants access to the bus to the highest-priority device that has requested it. Once the device completes its data transfer, it releases control of the bus, allowing the arbiter to grant access to another device waiting in the queue.

This process ensures that only one device is selected for data transfer to the bus at a particular time, preventing conflicts and ensuring the orderly operation of the system.

[18/03/24, 10:03:00 AM] Satvik Saini: int Solution::coverPoints(vector<int> &A, vector<int> &B) {
    int min_steps = 0;
    for(int i=0;i<A.size()-1;i++){
        int x1 = A[i];
        int y1 = B[i];
        int x2 = A[i+1];
        int y2 = B[i+1];
        
        int x_diff = abs(x1 - x2);
        int y_diff = abs(y1 - y2);
        int mini = min(x_diff,y_diff);
        min_steps += mini;
        x_diff -= mini;
        y_diff -= mini;
        min_steps += x_diff + y_diff;
    }
    return min_steps;
}
[18/03/24, 10:09:52 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int Solution::coverPoints(vector<int> &x, vector<int> &y) {
    int steps = 0;
    for(int i=0 ; i<x.size()-1 ; i++){
        
        int xdiff = abs(x[i+1] - x[i]);
        int ydiff = abs(y[i+1] - y[i]);
        
        steps += abs(xdiff - ydiff);
        
        steps += min(xdiff,ydiff);
        
    }
    return steps;
    
}

[19/03/24, 9:48:25 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int Solution::maxSubArray(const vector<int> &A) {
    int currsum = 0;
    int maxsum = 0;
    int i=0;
    int maxi = INT_MIN;
    if(A.size() == 1) return A[0];
    while(i<A.size()){
        currsum += A[i];
        if(currsum > maxsum) maxsum = currsum;
        if(currsum < 0) currsum = 0;
        i++;
        maxi = max(maxi,A[i]);

    }
    // cout<<maxi<<endl;
    if(maxi < 0) return maxi;
    return maxsum;
}

[19/03/24, 11:32:42 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int Solution::solve(vector<string> &A) {
    int n = A.size(), m = A[0].size();
    map<char, int> mxr[m], mnr[m], mxc, mnc;

    // Iterate through each element in the vector of strings
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for(int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
            // Update the maximum row index for each character in column j
            mxr[j][A[i][j]] = max(mxr[j][A[i][j]], i);

            // Update the minimum row index for each character in column j
            if(mnr[j].count(A[i][j]))
                mnr[j][A[i][j]] = min(mnr[j][A[i][j]], i);
            else
                mnr[j][A[i][j]] = i;

            // Update the maximum column index for each character
            mxc[A[i][j]] = max(mxc[A[i][j]], j);

            // Update the minimum column index for each character
            if(mnc.count(A[i][j]))
                mnc[A[i][j]] = min(mnc[A[i][j]], j);
            else
                mnc[A[i][j]] = j;
        }
    }

    int ans = 0;

    // Iterate through each column
    for(int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        // Check if the necessary characters exist in the respective maps
        if(mxr[i].count('r') and mxr[i].count('g') and mxc.count('b'))
            ans = max(ans, max(abs(mxr[i]['r'] - mnr[i]['g']) + 1, abs(mxr[i]['g'] - mnr[i]['r']) + 1) * max(abs(mxc['b'] - i) + 1, abs(i - mnc['b']) + 1));
        if(mxr[i].count('g') and mxr[i].count('b') and mxc.count('r'))
            ans = max(ans, max(abs(mxr[i]['g'] - mnr[i]['b']) + 1, abs(mxr[i]['b'] - mnr[i]['g']) + 1) * max(abs(mxc['r'] - i) + 1, abs(i - mnc['r']) + 1));
        if(mxr[i].count('r') and mxr[i].count('b') and mxc.count('g'))
            ans = max(ans, max(abs(mxr[i]['r'] - mnr[i]['b']) + 1, abs(mxr[i]['b'] - mnr[i]['r']) + 1) * max(abs(mxc['g'] - i) + 1, abs(i - mnc['g']) + 1));
    }

    return (ans + 1) / 2;
}

[20/03/24, 10:06:32 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int findMaxLength(vector<int>& nums) {
        // 0 0 1 1 0 0 1 1 0 1 
        int sum = 0;
        vector<int> prefix(nums.size()+1,0);
        for(int i=0 ; i<nums.size() ; i++){
            sum+=nums[i];
            prefix[i+1] = sum;
        }
        int maxi = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<nums.size() ; i++){
            for(int j = i+1 ; j<nums.size() ; j++){
                int oneCount = prefix[j+1] - prefix[i];
                int zeroCount = (j - i + 1 ) - oneCount;
                if(oneCount == zeroCount) maxi = max(maxi , j-i+1);
            }
        }

        return maxi;
        
    }
};

[22/03/24, 9:32:17 AM] Satvik Saini: /**
 * // This is the MountainArray's API interface.
 * // You should not implement it, or speculate about its implementation
 * class MountainArray {
 *   public:
 *     int get(int index);
 *     int length();
 * };
 */

class Solution {
    int BSinc(MountainArray& A, int B, int s, int e) {
        while (s <= e) {
            int mid = (s + e) / 2;
            if (A.get(mid) == B)
                return mid;
            if (A.get(mid) > B) {
                e = mid - 1;
            } else
                s = mid + 1;
        }
        return -1;
    }

    int BSdec(MountainArray& A, int B, int s, int e) {
        while (s <= e) {
            int mid = (s + e) / 2;
            if (A.get(mid) == B)
                return mid;
            if (A.get(mid) > B) {
                s = mid + 1;
            } else
                e = mid - 1;
        }
        return -1;
    }

public:
    int findInMountainArray(int B, MountainArray& A) {
        int n = A.length() - 1;
        int s = 0, e = n;

        int peak;

        while (s <= e) {
            int mid = (s + e) / 2;
            int lb = max(0, mid - 1);
            int ub = min(n, mid + 1);
            if (A.get(mid) >= A.get(lb) && A.get(mid) >= A.get(ub)) {
                peak = mid;
                break;
            }
            if (A.get(ub) >= A.get(mid) && A.get(mid) >= A.get(lb)) {
                s = mid + 1;
            } else {
                e = mid - 1;
            }
        }

        // cout<<"peak : "<<peak;

        int idx1 = BSinc(A, B, 0, peak - 1);
        if(idx1 != -1) return idx1;
        
        int idx2 = BSdec(A, B, peak, n);
        return idx2;

        // cout<<" idx1 : "<<idx1;
        // cout<<" idx2 : "<<idx2;

    }
};

        while(s<=e){

            if(arr[mid] == target) return mid;
            else if(arr[mid] < target){
                s = mid+1;
            }
            else e = mid-1;
        }
        return -1;
    }
        int B_search_dec(int s, int e, int target, vector<int> arr){
        while(s<=e){
            int mid = (s+e)/2;
            if(arr[mid] == target) return mid;
            else if(arr[mid] > target){
                s = mid+1;
            }
            else e = mid-1;
        }
        return -1;
    }
int Solution::solve(vector<int> &arr, int target) {
    
        int s = 0;
        int e = arr.size()-1;
        int ans = -1;
        while(s<e){
            int mid = (s+e)/2;
            if(arr[mid-1] < arr[mid] && arr[mid] > arr[mid+1]){
                if(arr[mid] == target) return mid;
                ans =  B_search_inc(0,mid-1,target,arr);
                if(ans != -1) return ans;
                ans = B_search_dec(mid+1,arr.size()-1,target,arr);
                if(ans != -1) return ans;
            }
            else if(arr[mid-1] < arr[mid] && arr[mid] < arr[mid+1]){
                s = mid+1;
            }
            else{
                e = mid-1;
            }
        }
        return -1;

public:
    int findPeakElement(vector<int>& nums) {
        int lo = 0, hi = nums.size()-1, mid;
        
        while (lo < hi) {
            mid = lo + (hi - lo) / 2;
            if (nums[mid] < nums[mid + 1]) 
                lo = mid + 1;
            else hi = mid;
        }
        
        return lo;
    }
};
[22/03/24, 11:42:31 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: A peak element is an element that is strictly greater than its neighbors.

Given a 0-indexed integer array nums, find a peak element, and return its index. If the array contains multiple peaks, return the index to any of the peaks.

You may imagine that nums[-1] = nums[n] = -∞. In other words, an element is always considered to be strictly greater than a neighbor that is outside the array.

You must write an algorithm that runs in O(log n) time.
[22/03/24, 11:43:13 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int findPeakElement(vector<int>& arr) {
        int s = 0;
        int e = arr.size()-1 ;
        if(s == e)  return s;
        if(arr[s]>arr[s+1]) return s;
        if(arr[e]>arr[e-1]) return e;

        // s++;
        // e--;
        
        while(s<=e){
            int mid = (s+e)/2;
            long int left= mid==0 ? LONG_MIN: arr[mid-1];
            long int right= mid==e ? LONG_MIN: arr[mid+1];


            if(arr[mid]>left and arr[mid]>right){
                return mid;
            }
            else if(arr[mid]<left)  e = mid-1;
            else s = mid+1;
        }
        return -1;

        
    }
};

[22/03/24, 11:54:51 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int findPeakElement(vector<int>& nums) {
        int lo = 0, hi = nums.size()-1, mid;
        
        while (lo < hi-1) {
            mid = lo + (hi - lo) / 2;
            if (nums[mid] < nums[mid - 1]) 
                hi = mid - 1;
            else lo = mid;
        }
        
        if(nums[hi]>nums[lo]) return hi;
        return lo;
    }
};

[22/03/24, 8:05:16 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int Solution::divide(int A, int B) {
    int s = 1;
    if(A == 0) return 0;
    int e = INT_MAX;
    if(A == INT_MIN && B == -1) return INT_MAX; 
    int ans = -1;
    while(s <= e){
        int mid = (s+e)/2;
        if(A - mid*B >= 0){
            ans = mid;
            s = mid+1;
        }
        else{
            e = mid-1;
        }
    }
    return ans;
}
[22/03/24, 8:05:30 PM] Satvik Saini: int Solution::divide(int A, int B) {
    if(A == INT_MIN && B == -1) return INT_MAX;
    bool flag_A = 0;
    bool flag_B = 0;
    if(A > 0 && B < 0){
        flag_A = 0;
        flag_B = 1;
        B = -B;
    }
    else if(A < 0 && B > 0){
        flag_A = 1;
        flag_B = 0;
        A = -A;
    } 
    
    int ans;
    
    int s = 1, e = INT_MAX;
    while(s <= e){
        int mid = (s + e) / 2;
        if(A - mid*B == 0){
            ans = mid;
            break;
        }
        if(A - mid*B > 0){
            s = mid + 1;
        }
        else e = mid - 1;
    }
    if(flag_A == 1 || flag_B == 1) return -ans;
    return ans;
}

[23/03/24, 10:28:36 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool isPossible(int row, int col, vector<vector<int>>& cells, int mid){
        
        vector<vector<int>> grid(row,vector<int>(col,0));
        vector<vector<int>> vis(row,vector<int>(col,0));

        for(int i=0;i<mid;i++){
            grid[cells[i][0]-1][cells[i][1]-1] = 1;
        }

        queue<pair<int,int>> q;
        for(int j=0;j<col;j++){
            if(grid[0][j] == 0) q.push({0,j});
        }

        vector<int> dx = {0,0,1,-1};
        vector<int> dy = {1,-1,0,0};
        bool flag = 0;

        while(!q.empty()){
            int i = q.front().first;
            int j = q.front().second;
            q.pop();

            if(i == row - 1){
                flag = 1;
                break;
            }

            vis[i][j] = 1;

            for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
                int ii = i + dx[k];
                int jj = j + dy[k];

                if(ii >= 0 && ii < row && jj >= 0 && jj < col && grid[ii][jj] == 0 && !vis[ii][jj]){
                    q.push({ii,jj});
                }
            }
        }
        return flag;
    }
public:
    int latestDayToCross(int row, int col, vector<vector<int>>& cells) {
        int s = 0, e = cells.size()-1, day;

        while(s <= e){
            int mid = (s + e) / 2;
            if(isPossible(row, col, cells, mid)){
                day = mid;
                s = mid + 1;
            }
            else e = mid - 1;
        }
        return day;
    }
};

[23/03/24, 10:58:31 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int latestDayToCross(int n, int m, vector<vector<int>>& cells) {
        vector<vector<int>> g(n, vector<int> (m, 0));
        for (int i = 0; i < n * m; i++) g[cells[i][0] - 1][cells[i][1] - 1] = (i + 1);
        int dx[] = {0, 0, 1, -1};
        int dy[] = {-1, 1, 0, 0};
        auto valid = [&](int i, int j) {
            return (i >= 0 && i < n && j >= 0 && j < m);  
        };
        // elements in p are first is the maximum time upto which we can be on that node and other pair is co-ordinate of the node
        priority_queue<pair<int,pair<int,int>>> p;
        int dp[n][m];
        // this dp[i][j] represents maximum time upto which we can use this node as a land
        memset(dp, 0, sizeof(dp));
        for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
            // this is all the source nodes from where we have to find longest time to go the bottom row nodes
            p.push({g[0][j], {0, j}});
            dp[0][j] = g[0][j]; // we can stay on this node only upto the time at which they disappeared
        }
        // this is just dijkstra's step
        while (!p.empty()) {
            auto cur = p.top();
            p.pop();
            int x = cur.second.first, y = cur.second.second, day = cur.first;
            if (x == n - 1) return day - 1; // we reached any node in last row for the first time so return this day - 1 as it wiil be
            // maximum 
            for (int d = 0; d < 4; d++) {
                // going to all adjacent nodes of current node
                int i = x + dx[d], j = y + dy[d];
                if (valid(i, j) && dp[i][j] < min(g[i][j], dp[x][y])) {
                    // upadting only when we get some better ans
                    // if we are coming at this node(i, j) from (x, y) then longest we can take this path is minimum of dp[x][y] and g[i][j]
                    // which is time at which (i, j) disappeared
                    dp[i][j] = min(g[i][j], dp[x][y]);
                    p.push({dp[i][j], {i, j}});
                }
            }
        }   
        return -1;
    }
};
[23/03/24, 10:59:41 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int>dx={-1,0,1,0};
    vector<int>dy={0,-1,0,1};
    bool solve(int n,int m,vector<vector<int>>&c,int k){
        queue<pair<int,int>>q;
        vector<vector<int>>vis(n,vector<int>(m,0));
        for(int i=0;i<k;i++)vis[c[i][0]-1][c[i][1]-1]=1; // marking those cells as visited which have been flooded with water
        for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
            if(vis[0][j]==0){
                vis[0][j]=1;
                q.push({0,j}); // pushing all the top elements to check for possible paths
            }
        }
        // Implementing standard bfs algo
        while(!q.empty()){
            int l=q.size();
            while(l--){
                auto [i,j]=q.front();
                q.pop();
                if(i==n-1)return true; // hurray, we reach the bottom
                for(int p=0;p<4;p++){
                    int x=i+dx[p];
                    int y=j+dy[p];
                    if(x>=0 && y>=0 && x<n && y<m && !vis[x][y]){
                        vis[x][y]=1;
                        q.push({x,y});
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
    int latestDayToCross(int n, int m, vector<vector<int>>&c) {
        int l=0,r=c.size(),ans=0;
        // applying binary search to find the last possible day
        while(l<=r){
            int mid=l+(r-l)/2;
            if(solve(n,m,c,mid)){
                ans=mid;
                l=mid+1; // continue checking for the maximum possible answer
            }
            else r=mid-1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[23/03/24, 11:00:18 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    bool isPossible(int m, int n, int t, vector<vector<int>>& cells) {
        vector<vector<int>> grid(m + 1, vector<int>(n + 1, 0)); // Grid representation
        vector<pair<int, int>> directions {{1, 0}, {-1, 0}, {0, 1}, {0, -1}}; // Possible directions

        for (int i = 0; i < t; i++) {
            grid[cells[i][0]][cells[i][1]] = 1; // Mark cells from the given list as blocked
        }

        queue<pair<int, int>> q;
        
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            if (grid[1][i] == 0) {
                q.push({1, i}); // Start BFS from the top row
                grid[1][i] = 1; // Mark the cell as visited
            }
        }
        while (!q.empty()) {
            pair<int, int> p = q.front();
            q.pop();
            int r = p.first, c = p.second; // Current cell coordinates
            for (auto d : directions) {
                int nr = r + d.first, nc = c + d.second; // Neighbor cell coordinates
                if (nr > 0 && nc > 0 && nr <= m && nc <= n && grid[nr][nc] == 0) {
                    grid[nr][nc] = 1; // Mark the neighbor cell as visited
                    if (nr == m) {
                        return true; // Found a path to the bottom row
                    }
                    q.push({nr, nc}); // Add the neighbor cell to the queue for further exploration
                }
            }
        }
        return false; // Unable to find a path to the bottom row
    }

    int latestDayToCross(int row, int col, vector<vector<int>>& cells) {
        int left = 0, right = row * col, latestPossibleDay = 0;
        while (left < right - 1) {
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2; // Calculate the mid-day
            if (isPossible(row, col, mid, cells)) {
                left = mid; // Update the left pointer to search in the upper half
                latestPossibleDay = mid; // Update the latest possible day
            } else {
                right = mid; // Update the right pointer to search in the lower half
            }
        }
        return latestPossibleDay;
    }
};
[23/03/24, 11:26:38 PM] Satvik Saini: int kthElement(int arr1[], int arr2[], int n, int m, int k)
    {
        if(n > m) return kthElement(arr2, arr1, m, n, k);
        int s = 0, e = n;
        while(s <= e){
            int cut1 = (s + e) / 2;
            int cut2 = k - cut1;
            
            int l1 = cut1 == 0 ? INT_MIN : arr1[cut1-1];
            int l2 = cut2 == 0 ? INT_MIN : arr2[cut2-1];
            
            int r1 = cut1 == n ? INT_MAX : arr1[cut1];
            int r2 = cut2 == m ? INT_MAX : arr2[cut2];
            
            if(l1 <= r2 && l2 <= r1){
                return max(l1,l2);
            }
            if(l1 > r2){
                e = cut1 - 1;
            }
            else s = cut1 + 1;
        }
        return 0;
    }

[24/03/24, 8:50:10 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class compare{
    public:
     bool operator()(pair<int,int>&p1, pair<int,int>&p2){
        return p1.second > p2.second;
    }
};
class Solution {
public:
    
    vector<long long> mostFrequentIDs(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& f) {
        set<pair<int,int>, compare> stt;
        vector<long long> ans;
        for(int i=0 ; i<f.size() ; i++){
                
            int ele = nums[i];
            int freq = f[i];
            auto it = std::find_if(stt.begin(), stt.end(), [ele](const std::pair<int, int>& p) {
                return p.first == ele;
            });
            if(it != stt.end()){
                // found it 
                int curr_freq = it->second;
                stt.erase(it);
                stt.insert({ele, curr_freq-freq});
            }
            else{
                // new wlement
                stt.insert({ele,freq});
            }
            
            auto max_ele = *stt.begin();
            ans.push_back(max_ele.second);
            
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[24/03/24, 9:12:02 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎13 min
[24/03/24, 9:12:06 AM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long

class Compare {
    public:
    bool operator()(const pair<ll,ll>& a, const pair<ll,ll>& b) const {
        return a.second > b.second;
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> mostFrequentIDs(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& freq) {
        set<pair<ll,ll>,Compare> s;    // <num,freq>
        vector<ll> ans;
        
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            auto it = find_if(s.begin(), s.end(), [nums[i]](const pair<ll, ll>& p) {
                return p.first == nums[i];
            });
            if(it == s.end()){
                s.insert({nums[i],freq[i]});
            }
            else{
                ll freq_new = it->second + freq[i];
                s.erase(it);
                s.insert({nums[i],freq_new});
            }
            ans.push_back(*s.begin().second);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

class Compare {
    public:
    bool operator()(const pair<ll,ll>& a, const pair<ll,ll>& b) const {
        return a.second > b.second;
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> mostFrequentIDs(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& freq) {
        set<pair<ll,ll>,Compare> s;    // <num,freq>
        vector<ll> ans;
        
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            auto it = std::find_if(s.begin(), s.end(), [nums[i]](const std::pair<ll, ll>& p) {
                return p.first == nums[i];
            });
            if(it == s.end()){
                s.insert({nums[i],freq[i]});
            }
            else{
                ll freq_new = it->second + freq[i];
                s.erase(it);
                s.insert({nums[i],freq_new});
            }
            ans.push_back(*s.begin().second);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

class compare {
    public:
    bool operator()(const pair<ll,ll>& a, const pair<ll,ll>& b) const {
        return a.second > b.second;
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    
    vector<long long> mostFrequentIDs(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& f) {
        set<pair<ll,ll>, compare> stt;
        vector<long long> ans;
        for(int i=0 ; i<f.size() ; i++){
                
            ll ele = nums[i];
            ll freq = f[i];
            
            auto it = std::find_if(stt.begin(), stt.end(), [ele](const std::pair<int, int>& p) {
                return p.first == ele;
            });
            if(it != stt.end()){
                // found it 
                ll curr_freq = it->second;
                stt.erase(it);
                stt.insert({ele, curr_freq+freq});
            }
            else{
                // new wlement
                stt.insert({ele,freq});
            }
            
            auto max_ele = *stt.begin();
            ans.push_back(max_ele.second);
            
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[25/03/24, 8:10:17 AM] Satvik Saini: int Solution::solve(vector<int> &A, int B) {
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    unordered_set<int> s;
    
    int i = 0, j = 0;
    while(j < B){
        mp[A[j]]++;
        s.insert(A[j]);
        j++;
    }
    int subarray_cnt = 0;
    while(j < A.size()){
        while(i<A.size() &&  s.size() > 2){
            mp[A[i]]--;
            if(mp[A[i]] == 0){
                s.erase(s.find(A[j]));
            }
            i++;
        }
        if(s.size() == 2) subarray_cnt++;
        j++;
        if(j == A.size()) break;
        mp[A[j]]++;
        s.insert(A[j]);
    }
    return subarray_cnt;
}

[25/03/24, 8:43:50 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int Solution::solve(vector<int> &nums, int B) {
        
        int i = 0;
        int j = 0;
        int cnt = 0;
        while(i<nums.size() && j<nums.size()){
        unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
            while(mpp.size() <= 2   && j<nums.size()){
                if(mpp.size() == 2 && mpp.find(nums[j]) == mpp.end()) {
                    j--;
                    break;
                }
                mpp[nums[j]]++;
                j++;
                if(mpp.size() == 2) cnt++;
            }
            // now either map has three elements or array is over 
            mpp[nums[i]]--;
            i++;
            while(mpp.size() <= 2 &&  i < j){
                if(mpp.size() == 2) cnt++;
                mpp[nums[i]]--;
                if(mpp[nums[i]] == 0){
                    mpp.erase(nums[i]);
                }
                i++;
            }
        }
    return cnt;
}

[25/03/24, 9:10:04 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int at_most(vector<int> A,int k){
    int n = A.size(),ans = 0,j = 0,i = 0;
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    while(j < n){
        mp[A[j]]++;
        while(mp.size() > k){
            mp[A[i]]--;
            if(mp[A[i]] == 0) mp.erase(A[i]);
            i++;
        }
        ans += (j-i+1);
        j++;
    }
    return ans;
}

int Solution::solve(vector<int> &A, int B) {
    return at_most(A,B)-at_most(A,B-1);
}
[25/03/24, 9:10:19 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: To directly count the subarrays with exactly B different integers is hard but to find the count of subarrays with at most B different integers is easy.

So the idea is to find the count of subarrays with at most B different integers, let it be C(B), and the count of subarrays with at most (B - 1) different integers, let it be C(B - 1) and finally take their difference, C(B) – C(B – 1) which is the required answer.

Count of subarrays with at most B different elements can be easily calculated through the sliding window technique.

[26/03/24, 8:19:31 AM] Satvik Saini: https://www.interviewbit.com/problems/deserialize/
[26/03/24, 8:20:41 AM] Satvik Saini: vector<string> Solution::deserialize(string A) {
    vector<string> ans;
    for(int i=A.length()-1;i>0;i--){
        i--;
        string num = "";
        while(A[i]>='0' && A[i] <= '9'){
            num += A[i--];
        }
        reverse(num.begin(), num.end());
        int n = stoi(num);
        ans.push_back(A.substr(i-n+1,n));
        i -= n;
    }
    reverse(ans.begin(), ans.end());
    return ans;
}

[26/03/24, 1:15:06 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: //{ Driver Code Starts
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;


// } Driver Code Ends
//User function template for C++
class Solution{
public:
    bool compareMap(unordered_map<char,int> pat_map, unordered_map<char,int> text_map) {
	bool flag = true;
	    for(auto& x : text_map){
	        if(pat_map.find(x.first) == pat_map.end()){
	            flag = false;
	            break;
	        }
	        else{
	            if(pat_map[x.first] != x.second){
	                flag = false;
	                break;
	            }
	        }
	    }
	    return flag;
    }
	int search(string pat, string txt) {
	    // code here
	    int i=0;
	    int j=0;
	    unordered_map<char,int> text_map;
	    unordered_map<char,int> pat_map;
	    for(char &x : txt) text_map[x]++;
	    for(j=0 ; j<txt.size() ; j++){
	        pat_map[pat[j]]++;
	    }
	    bool flag = true;
	    for(auto& x : text_map){
	        if(pat_map.find(x.first) == pat_map.end()){
	            flag = false;
	            break;
	        }
	        else{
	            if(pat_map[x.first] != x.second){
	                flag = false;
	                break;
	            }
	        }
	    }
	    int cnt = 0;
	    if(flag) cnt++;
            
        while(j < pat.size()){
                pat_map[pat[i]]--;
                pat_map[pat[j]]++;
            // calculte for the new window 
            if(flag){
                // previous was an anagram
                if(pat[i] == pat[j]){
                    cnt++;
                }
            }
            else{
                // picla was not an anagram of text
                flag = compareMap(pat_map,text_map);
                if(flag) cnt++;
            }
            i++;
	        j++;
            
        }
        return cnt;
        	    
	}

};

//{ Driver Code Starts.

int main() {
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--) {
        string pat, txt;
        cin >> txt >> pat;
        Solution ob;
        auto ans = ob.search(pat, txt);
        cout << ans << "\n";
    }
    return 0;
}

[26/03/24, 1:15:29 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<iostream>

using namespace std;

bool compareMap(int wFreqMap[], int tFreqMap[]) {
	for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++)
		if (tFreqMap[i] != wFreqMap[i])
			return false;
	return true;
}

int main() {

	string s = "cbaebabacd";
	string t = "abc";

	int n = s.size();
	int k = t.size(); // size of the window

	int count = 0; // to store the count of anagrams of 't' in 's'

	int tFreqMap[26] = {0}; // to store a mapping  b/w characters
	// present in 't' & their frequencies
	for (int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
		tFreqMap[t[i] - 'a']++;
	}

	int i = 0; // to store the start of the window
	int j = 0; // to store the end of the window

	int wFreqMap[26] = {0}; // to store a mapping between characters
	// present in window & their frequencies

	// build the frequency map for the 1st window

	while (j < k) {
		wFreqMap[s[j] - 'a']++;
		j++;
	}

	// check if the window is an anagram of 't'

	if (compareMap(wFreqMap, tFreqMap)) count++;

	// build the frequency map for the remaining window

	while (j < n) {

		// slide the window
		wFreqMap[s[i] - 'a']--;
		i++;
		wFreqMap[s[j] - 'a']++;

		if (compareMap(wFreqMap, tFreqMap)) count++;

		j++;

	}

	cout << count << endl;

	return 0;
}

//User function template for C++
class Solution{
public:
    bool compareMap(unordered_map<char,int> pat_map, unordered_map<char,int> text_map) {
	bool flag = true;
	    for(auto& x : text_map){
	        if(pat_map.find(x.first) == pat_map.end()){
	            flag = false;
	            break;
	        }
	        else{
	            if(pat_map[x.first] != x.second){
	                flag = false;
	                break;
	            }
	        }
	    }
	    return flag;
    }
	int search(string txt, string pat) {
	    // code here
	    int i=0;
	    int j=0;
	    unordered_map<char,int> text_map;
	    unordered_map<char,int> pat_map;
	    for(char &x : txt) text_map[x]++;
	    for(j=0 ; j<txt.size() ; j++){
	        pat_map[pat[j]]++;
	    }
	    bool flag = compareMap(pat_map,text_map)
	    int cnt = 0;
	    if(flag) cnt++;
            
        while(j < pat.size()){
                pat_map[pat[i]]--;
                pat_map[pat[j]]++;
            // calculte for the new window 
            if(flag){
                // previous was an anagram
                if(pat[i] == pat[j]){
                    cnt++;
                }
            }
            else{
                // picla was not an anagram of text
                flag = compareMap(pat_map,text_map);
                if(flag) cnt++;
            }
            i++;
	        j++;
            
        }
        return cnt;
        	    
	}

};

[26/03/24, 2:04:42 PM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> findDuplicates(vector<int>& nums) {
       
        vector<int> ans;
        int n = nums.size();

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            nums[(nums[i]%(n+1))-1]+=n+1;
        }

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i]/(n+1)==2){
                ans.push_back(i+1);
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }

[26/03/24, 6:00:54 PM] Satvik Saini: import React, { useState } from 'react'

const Timer = () => {

    const [hour, setHour] = useState(0);
    const [min, setMin] = useState(0);
    const [sec, setSec] = useState(0);

    const [time, setTime] = useState({
        hours: 0, mins: 0, secs: 0
    });

    // Get hours, minutes, and seconds
    const hours = time.hours;
    const minutes = time.mins;
    const seconds = time.secs;

    // Format hours, minutes, and seconds to add leading zeros if needed
    const formattedHours = (hours < 10 ? '0' : '') + hours;
    const formattedMinutes = (minutes < 10 ? '0' : '') + minutes;
    const formattedSeconds = (seconds < 10 ? '0' : '') + seconds;


    function startTimer(){
        setTime({hours:{hour},mins:{min},secs:{sec}});
    }

    function changeInpHour(e){
        setHour(e.target.value);
    }
    function changeInpMin(e){
        setMin(e.target.value);
    }
    function changeInpSec(e){
        setSec(e.target.value);
    }
    

    return (
        <>
            <input className='w-5' type="number" value={hour} onChange={changeInpHour}/>
            <input className='w-5' type="number" value={min} onChange={changeInpMin}/>
            <input className='w-5' type="number" value={sec} onChange={changeInpSec}/>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-success" onClick={startTimer}>Start</button>
            <h1 style={{ fontSize: 100 }}>{formattedHours}:{formattedMinutes}:{formattedSeconds}</h1>

        </>
    )
}

export default Timer

[26/03/24, 6:11:41 PM] Satvik Saini: import React, { useState } from 'react'

const Timer = () => {

    const [hour, setHour] = useState(0);
    const [min, setMin] = useState(0);
    const [sec, setSec] = useState(0);

    const [time, setTime] = useState({
        hours: 0, mins: 0, secs: 0
    });

    // Format hours, minutes, and seconds to add leading zeros if needed
    let formattedHours;
    let formattedMinutes;
    let formattedSeconds;

    function startTimer() {
        setTime({ hours: { hour }, mins: { min }, secs: { sec } });
        // Get hours, minutes, and seconds
        const hours = time.hours;
        const minutes = time.mins;
        const seconds = time.secs;

        // Format hours, minutes, and seconds to add leading zeros if needed
        formattedHours = (hours < 10 ? '0' : '') + hours;
        formattedMinutes = (minutes < 10 ? '0' : '') + minutes;
        formattedSeconds = (seconds < 10 ? '0' : '') + seconds;
    }

    function changeInpHour(e) {
        setHour(e.target.value);
    }
    function changeInpMin(e) {
        setMin(e.target.value);
    }
    function changeInpSec(e) {
        setSec(e.target.value);
    }


    return (
        <>
            <input className='w-5' type="number" value={hour} onChange={changeInpHour} />
            <input className='w-5' type="number" value={min} onChange={changeInpMin} />
            <input className='w-5' type="number" value={sec} onChange={changeInpSec} />
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-success" onClick={startTimer}>Start</button>
            <h1 style={{ fontSize: 100 }}>{formattedHours}:{formattedMinutes}:{formattedSeconds}</h1>

        </>
    )
}

export default Timer

[26/03/24, 7:24:06 PM] Satvik Saini: x = 1 + ceil(B/A)

[26/03/24, 7:25:58 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution(object):
    def repeatedStringMatch(self, A, B):
        t = -(-len(B) // len(A)) # Equal to ceil(len(b) / len(a))
        return t * (B in A * t) or (t + 1) * (B in A * (t + 1)) or -1

        for (j = 0; j < B.size() && A[(i + j) % A.size()] == B[j]; ++j);
        if (j == B.size()) 
            return (i + j - 1) / A.size() + 1;
    }

[26/03/24, 7:26:54 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int repeatedStringMatch(string a, string b) {
    vector<int> prefTable(b.size() + 1); // 1-based to avoid extra checks.
    for (auto sp = 1, pp = 0; sp < b.size();)
        if (b[pp] == b[sp] || pp == 0)  {
            pp = b[pp] == b[sp] ? pp + 1 : 0;
            prefTable[++sp] = pp;
        }
        else
            pp = prefTable[pp];
    for (auto i = 0, j = 0; i < a.size(); ) {
        while (j < b.size() && a[(i + j) % a.size()] == b[j]) 
            ++j;
        if (j == b.size()) 
            return (i + j - 1) / a.size() + 1;
        j = prefTable[j];
        i += max(1, j - prefTable[j]);
    }
    return -1;
}

public:
    int lengthOfLongestSubstring(string s) {

    int i=0;
    int j=0;
    unordered_map<char,int> mpp;

    while( j < s.size()){

        mpp[s[j]]++;
        if(mpp[s[j]] == 1){
            maxlen = max(maxlen , j-i+1);
        }
        else{
            // s[j] char is now repeated 
            while( mpp[s[j]] == 2){
                mpp[s[i]]--;
                if(mpp[s[i]] == 0) mpp.erase(s[i]);
                i++;  
            }
        }
        
        j++;

    }

[27/03/24, 11:27:22 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<iostream>
#include<unordered_map>

using namespace std;

int main() {

	string s = "aabacbebebe";
	int n = s.size();
	int k = 3;

	int i = 0; // to store the start of the window
	int j = 0; // to store the end of the windw

	int max_len = 0; // to track the length of the longest substring
	// i.e. window that contain k unique characters

	int uniqueCount = 0; // to keep track of no. of unique characters in the window

	unordered_map<char, int> freqMap; // to store a  mapping  between characters
	// present in a window & their frequencies

	// time : O(n)
	// space : O(n) due to freqMap when s has all unique characters

	while (j < n) {

		// expand the window

		// add s[j] to the window

		freqMap[s[j]]++;
		if (freqMap[s[j]] == 1) {
			// s[j] is seen in the window for the 1st time
			uniqueCount++;
		}

		// check for the violation of the window property

		if (uniqueCount > k) {

			// window property is violated, fix it by shrinking the window

			while (uniqueCount > k) {

				// delete s[i] from the window
				freqMap[s[i]]--;
				if (freqMap[s[i]] == 0) {
					uniqueCount--;
				}
				i++;

			}

		}

		// check for the validity of the window, and update the answer

		if (uniqueCount == k) {

			// you've found a valid window

			max_len = max(max_len, j - i + 1);

		}

		// continue expansion of the window
		j++;
	}

	cout << max_len << endl;

	return 0;
}

class Solution{
  public:
    int longestKSubstr(string s, int k) {
        int i=0;
        int j=0;
        int maxlen = -1;
        unordered_map<char,int> mpp;
        for( j=0 ; j<s.size() ; j++){
            mpp[s[j]]++;
            
            if(mpp.size() == k){
                    maxlen = max(maxlen, j-i+1);
            }
            else if(mpp.size() > k){
                
                while(mpp.size() > k){
                    mpp[s[i]]--;
                    if(mpp[s[i]] == 0){
                        mpp.erase(s[i]);
                    }
                    i++;
                }
            }
            
             
        }
        return maxlen;
    // your code here
    }
};

[27/03/24, 11:35:16 AM] Satvik Saini: int numSubarrayProductLessThanK(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        if(k <= 1) return 0;
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        int prod = 1, res = 0;
        while(j < nums.size()){
            prod *= nums[j];
            while(prod >= k){
                prod /= nums[i];
                i++;
            }
            // count all the subarray between i and j, starting with i
            res += j - i + 1;
            j++;
        }
        return res;
    }
[27/03/24, 12:04:45 PM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> lps(string s){
        int n = s.length();
        vector<int> prefix(n, 0);

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            int j = prefix[i-1];
            while(j > 0 && s[i] != s[j]){
                j = prefix[j-1];
            }
            if(s[i] == s[j]){
                j++;
            }
            prefix[i] = j;
        }
        return prefix;
    }

    bool KMP(string str, string pattern, int mid, vector<int> prefix){
        string s = "";
        for(int i=0;i<mid;i++){
            s += str;
        }
        int i = 0, j = 0, pos = -1;

        while(i < s.length()){
            if(s[i] == pattern[j]){
                i++;
                j++;
            }
            else{
                if(j != 0){
                    j = prefix[j-1];
                }
                else i++;
            }
            if(j == pattern.length()){
                pos = i - pattern.length();
            }
        }
        return pos != -1;
    }
    bool KMP(string A, string B, int times){
        for(int i=0;i<times;i++){
            A += A;
        }
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        
    }
  public:
    int minRepeats(string A, string B) {
        vector<int> f1(26,0);
        vector<int> f2(26,0);
        
        for(char ch : A){
            f1[ch-'a']++;
        }
        for(char ch : B){
            f2[ch-'a']++;
            // not possible
            if(f1[ch-'a'] == 0) return -1;
        }
        
        int s = 1, e = 1 + ceil(B.length()/A.length());
        int ans;
        vector<int> prefix = lps(B);
        while(s >= e){
            int mid = (s + e) / 2;
            if(KMP(A,B,mid,prefix)){
                ans = mid;
                e = mid - 1;
            }
            else s = mid + 1;
        }
        return ans;
    }

        sort(tokens.begin(), tokens.end());
        int res = 0, points = 0, i = 0, j = tokens.size() - 1;
        while (i <= j) {
            if (P >= tokens[i]) {
                P -= tokens[i++];
                res = max(res, ++points);
            } else if (points > 0) {
                points--;
                P += tokens[j--];
            } else {
                break;
            }
        }

[27/03/24, 2:43:50 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int bagOfTokensScore(vector<int>& tokens, int power) {
        sort(tokens.begin(), tokens.end());
        int i = 0, j = tokens.size()-1;

        int p = power;
        int score = 0;
        int max_score = 0;

        while(i <= j){
            if(power >= tokens[i]){
                power -= tokens[i];
                score++;
                i++;
                max_score = max(max_score,score);
            }
            else{
                if(score == 0) break;
                score--;
                power += tokens[j];
                j--;
            }
        }
        return max_score;
    }
};

[28/03/24, 8:04:29 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    string minWindow(string s, string t) {

        if (s.length() < t.length())
            return "";

        unordered_map<char, int> mp;

        for (auto ch : t) {
            mp[ch]++;
        }

        int n = s.length(), m = t.length();

        int i = 0, j = 0;
        int cnt = t.length();

        int len = INT_MAX;
        int start;

        while (j < n) {
            if (mp[s[j]] > 0) {
                cnt--;
            }
            mp[s[j]]--;
            j++;

            while (cnt == 0) {
                if (len > j - i) {
                    len = j - i;
                    start = i;
                }
                mp[s[i]]++;
                if (mp[s[i]] > 0)
                    cnt++;
                i++;
            }
        }
        return len == INT_MAX ? "" : s.substr(start, len);
    }
};
[28/03/24, 8:08:25 AM] Satvik Saini: #include<iostream>
#include<unordered_map>

using namespace std;

string minWindow(string s, string t) {

	int m = s.size();
	int n = t.size();

	unordered_map<char, int> tFreqMap; // to store a mapping  b/w characters
	// present in 't' & their frequencies

	int tCount = 0; // to store the no. of unique characters in 't'.

	// to keep track of number of chacters of 't' with the
	// required frequeny NOT present in the current window

	for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
		char ch = t[i];
		tFreqMap[ch]++;
		// if(tFreqMap[ch] == 1) tCount++;
	}

	tCount = tFreqMap.size();

	int i = 0; // to store the start of the window
	int j = 0; // to store the end of the windw

	int min_len = INT_MAX; // to track the length of the minimum window
	int s_index;   // to store the starting index of the minimum window

	while (j < m) {

		// expand the window

		// add s[j] into the window

		char ch = s[j];
		if (tFreqMap.find(ch) != tFreqMap.end()) {
			tFreqMap[ch]--;
			if (tFreqMap[ch] == 0) {
				// window has sufficient occurrences of 'ch'
				tCount--;
			}
		}

		// check for validity of the window
		if (tCount == 0) {
			// found a valid window
			if (j - i + 1 < min_len) {s_index = i; min_len = j - i + 1;}
			// optimise the window length by shrinking it
			while (tCount == 0) {
				char out = s[i];
				if (tFreqMap.find(out) != tFreqMap.end()) {
					// 'out' is present in 't'
					tFreqMap[out]++;
					if (tFreqMap[out] == 1) {
						// window no longer has sufficient occurrences
						// of 'out' therefore it is no longer valid.
						i++;
						tCount++;
					} else {
						// you have sufficient occurrences of 'out'
						// in the  window  hence it is still valid.
						i++;
						if (j - i + 1 < min_len) {s_index = i; min_len = j - i + 1;}
					}
				} else {
					// 'out' was an  unnecessary character in the
					// window therefore the window is still valid.
					i++;
					if (j - i + 1 < min_len) {s_index = i; min_len = j - i + 1;}
				}
			}
		}

		// continue with the expansion of the window
		j++;

	}

	return min_len == INT_MAX ? "" : s.substr(s_index, min_len);
}

int main() {

	string s = "adobecodebanc";
	string t = "abc";

	cout << minWindow(s, t) << endl;

	return 0;
}

[28/03/24, 11:12:34 AM] Satvik Saini: #include<iostream>
#include<queue>

using namespace std;

int main() {

	queue<char> q;

	char ch;

	int freq[26] = {0};

	while (true) {

		cin >> ch;

		freq[ch - 'a']++;
		if (freq[ch - 'a'] == 1) {
			// ch is non-repeating
			q.push(ch);
		}

		while (!q.empty() and freq[q.front() - 'a'] > 1) {
			q.pop();
		}

		if (q.empty()) {
			// after reading 'ch', stream doesn't have a non-repeating character
			cout << -1 << " ";
		} else {
			cout << q.front() << " ";
		}

	}


	return 0;
}

[28/03/24, 12:17:45 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> maxSlidingWindow(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        vector<int> ans;
        deque<int> dq;

        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            if(!dq.empty() && dq.front() == i-k){
                dq.pop_front();
            }

            while(!dq.empty() && nums[dq.back()] < nums[i]){
                dq.pop_back();
            }
            dq.push_back(i);
            if(i >= k-1){
                ans.push_back(nums[dq.front()]);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

        // CODE: update state using A[i]
    }
    ans = max(ans, j - i + 1); // the window [i, j] is the maximum window we've found thus far
}

    //     setInterval(function () {
    //         setTime(time + 1);
    //     }, 1000);
    // }, [time]);

    // -----------right-----------------

    // it runs between 2 renders
    // it removes the previous states
    // NOTE : for every states (at every render) there will be different variable for time
    // it will make a new variable for a new state

    useEffect(() => {
        let id = setInterval(function () {
            setTime(time + 1);
        }, 1000);
        
        // cleanup function
        return ()=>{
            clearInterval(id);
        };
    }, [time]);

    return (
        <div>
            <h1>Timer : {time}</h1>
        </div>
    )
}

[28/03/24, 9:06:20 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int maxProfitBottomUp(vector<int>& prices, int n) {

	vector<vector<int>> dp(n, vector<int>(n));

	for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
		// int j = i;
		// int y = n;
		// dp[i][j] = y * prices[i]; // y * prices[j]
		dp[i][i] = n * prices[i];
	}

	for (int i = n - 2; i >= 0; i--) {
		for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {

			// make a decision for the yth year

			int y = n - j + i;

			// 1. sell the ith bottle of wine

			int x = dp[i + 1][j];

			// 2. sell the jth bottle of wine

			int z = dp[i][j - 1];

			dp[i][j] = max(y * prices[i] + x, y * prices[j] + z);
		}
	}

	return dp[0][n - 1]; // at the (0, n-1)th index, we store f(0, n-1)

} ‎<This message was edited>
[28/03/24, 9:08:13 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int maxProfitTopDown(vector<int> prices, int i, int j, int y, vector<vector<int>>& dp) {

	// lookup

	if (dp[i][j] != -1) {
		// you've already computed result for f(i, j)
		return dp[i][j];
	}

	// base case

	if (i == j) {
		return dp[i][j] = y * prices[i]; // or y * prices[j] // y is equal to n
	}

	// recursive case

	// make a decision for the yth year

	// 1. sell the ith bottle of wine

	int x = maxProfitTopDown(prices, i + 1, j, y + 1, dp);

	// 2. sell the jth bottle of wine

	int z = maxProfitTopDown(prices, i, j - 1, y + 1, dp);

	return dp[i][j] = max(y * prices[i] + x, y * prices[j] + z);

}

[29/03/24, 9:22:04 AM] Satvik Saini: int Solution::trap(const vector<int> &A) {
    int n = A.size();
    int a = 0, b = n-1;
    int leftMax,rightMax;
    leftMax = rightMax = 0;
    int water = 0;
    while(a <= b){
        leftMax = max(leftMax, A[a]);
        rightMax = max(rightMax, A[b]);
        if(leftMax < rightMax){
            water += leftMax - A[a];
            a++;
        }
        else{
            water += rightMax - A[b];
            b--;
        }
    }
    return water;
}

[29/03/24, 10:06:41 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int maximalSquare(vector<vector<char>>& M) {
     
        int m = size(M), n = size(M[0]), ans = 0;
        vector<vector<int>> dp(m+1, vector<int>(n+1));
        for(int i = m-1; ~i; i--)
            for(int j = n-1; ~j; j--) 
                dp[i][j] = (M[i][j] == '1' ? 1 + min({dp[i+1][j], dp[i][j+1], dp[i+1][j+1]}) : 0),
                ans = max(ans, dp[i][j]);

        return ans * ans;
    }
};

‎[29/03/24, 10:25:48 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎image omitted
[29/03/24, 10:29:24 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int maximalSquare(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        return tabulation(matrix);
    }
    
    // 1. Brute force
    int bruteForce(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        int res = 0;
        
        for(int i = 0; i < matrix.size(); ++i) {
            for(int j = 0; j < matrix[0].size(); ++j) {
                if (matrix[i][j] == '0') continue;
                
                int area = 1;
                int right = j + 1, low = i + 1;
                while(right < matrix[0].size() && low < matrix.size()) {
                    bool valid = true;
                    for(int row = i; row <= low; ++row) {
                        if (matrix[row][right] == '0') {
                            valid = false;
                            break;
                        }
                    }
                    
                    for(int col = j; col <= right; ++col) {
                        if (matrix[low][col] == '0') {
                            valid = false;
                            break;
                        }
                    }
                    
                    if (valid) {
                        area = max(area, (low - i + 1) * (right - j + 1));
                    } else {
                        area = max(area, (low - i) * (right - j));
                        break;
                    }
                    
                    ++right;
                    ++low;
                }
                res = max(res, area);
            }
        }
        
        return res;
    }
    
    // 2. Recursive.
    // TLE.
    int recursive(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        if (matrix.empty()) return 0;
        
        int res = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < matrix.size(); ++i) {
            for(int j = 0; j < matrix[0].size(); ++j) {
                res = max(res, helper(matrix, i, j));
            }
        }
        return res * res;
    }
    
    // Return the area of maximum square with (i, j) as upper-left corner.
    int helper(vector<vector<char>>& matrix, int i, int j) {
        if (i >= matrix.size() || j >= matrix[0].size()) return 0;
        if (matrix[i][j] == '0') return 0;
        return min(min(helper(matrix, i, j+1), helper(matrix, i+1, j)), 
                   helper(matrix, i+1, j+1)) + 1;
    }
    
    
    // 3. Memoization
    int memoization(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        if (matrix.empty()) return 0;
        vector<vector<int>> mem(matrix.size(), vector<int>(matrix[0].size(), -1));
        
        int res = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < matrix.size(); ++i) {
            for(int j = 0; j < matrix[0].size(); ++j) {
                res = max(res, solve(matrix, mem, i, j));
            }
        }
        return res * res;
    }
    
    int solve(vector<vector<char>>& matrix, vector<vector<int>>& mem, int i, int j) {
        if (i >= matrix.size() || j >= matrix[0].size()) return 0;
        if (mem[i][j] >= 0) return mem[i][j];
        if (matrix[i][j] == '0') return mem[i][j] = 0;
        mem[i][j] = min(min(solve(matrix, mem, i+1, j), solve(matrix, mem, i, j+1)),
                        solve(matrix, mem, i+1, j+1)) + 1;
        return mem[i][j];
    }
    
    
    // 4. Tabulation
    int tabulation(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        if (matrix.empty()) return 0;
        
        int res = 0;
        vector<vector<int>> tab(matrix.size(), vector<int>(matrix[0].size()));

        for(int row = tab.size() - 1; row >= 0; --row) {
            for(int col = tab[0].size() - 1; col >= 0; --col) {
                if (col == matrix[0].size() - 1) {
                    tab[row][col] = matrix[row][col] == '0' ? 0 : 1;
                } else if (row == matrix.size() - 1) {
                    tab[row][col] = matrix[row][col] == '0' ? 0 : 1;
                } else if (matrix[row][col] == '0') {
                    tab[row][col] = 0;
                } else {
                    tab[row][col] = min(min(tab[row+1][col], tab[row][col+1]),
                                        tab[row+1][col+1]) + 1;
                }
                res = max(res, tab[row][col]);
            }
        }
        
        return res * res;
    }
};

[29/03/24, 1:41:01 PM] Satvik Saini: // APPROACH
// when you are at (i,j), then treat it as the bottom right corner of the
// submatrix find the maxi side of a square submatrix from (i,j-1), (i-1,j) and
// (i-1,j-1) the min of all three will be selected because (i,j) want the
// overlapping of all submatrices and add 1 because of (i,j) itself

// using 2D dp

class Solution {
public:
    int maximalSquare(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        int n = matrix.size();
        int m = matrix[0].size();

        int ans = 0;

        vector<vector<int>> dp(n, vector<int>(m));
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                if (i == 0 || j == 0 || matrix[i][j] == '0') {
                    dp[i][j] = matrix[i][j] - '0';
                }
                else {
                    dp[i][j] =
                        min(dp[i - 1][j - 1], min(dp[i - 1][j], dp[i][j - 1])) + 1;
                }
                ans = max(ans, dp[i][j]);
            }
        }
        return ans * ans; // for the area
    }
};

// space optimised version

class Solution {
public:
    int maximalSquare(vector<vector<char>>& matrix) {
        int n = matrix.size();
        int m = matrix[0].size();

        int ans = 0;

        vector<int> curr(m, 0), prev(m, 0);
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                if (i == 0 || j == 0 || matrix[i][j] == '0') {
                    curr[j] = matrix[i][j] - '0';
                }
                else {
                    curr[j] = min(prev[j - 1], min(prev[j], curr[j - 1])) + 1;
                }
                ans = max(ans, curr[j]);
            }
            prev = curr;
        }
        return ans * ans;
    }
};

[29/03/24, 6:54:34 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    
    int scoreOfParentheses(string s) {
        stack<int> stk;
        for(char c : s){
            int sum = 0;
            if(c == '('){
                stk.push(0);
            }
            else{
                // calculate result
                while(stk.top()!=0){
                    sum+=stk.top();
                    stk.pop();
                }
                sum = max(2*sum , 1);
                stk.pop();
                stk.push(sum);
            }
        }
        int count = 0;
        while(!stk.empty()){
            count+=stk.top();
            stk.pop();
        }
        return count;
    }
    // int scoreOfParentheses(string s) {
