[29/03/24, 6:55:01 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
  int scoreOfParentheses(string S)
{
    stack<int> m_stack;
    m_stack.push(0); // to keep the total score
    for(char c:S){
        if(c=='(')
            m_stack.push(0); //When meets '(', just push a zero to stack
        else{
            int tmp=m_stack.top(); //  balance the last '(', it stored the score of inner parentheses
            m_stack.pop();
            int val=0;
            if(tmp>0) // not zero means inner parentheses exists and double it
                val=tmp*2;
            else // zero means no inner parentheses, just using 1
                val=1;
            m_stack.top()+=val; // pass the score of this level to parent parenthese
        }   
    }
    return m_stack.top();
}
};
[29/03/24, 6:55:01 PM] Satvik Saini: Approach:

When travel through S, only meets ')', we need to calculate the score of this pair of parenthese. If we know the score of inner parentheses, such as 3, we can double it and pass to the outer parenthese. But the question is how do we know the score of inner parentheses? Using stack.

This is example we are using to explain with "( ( ) ( ( ) ) )"

stack: 0->
string_traveled :""
When start only 0 in stack, this int will store the total score

stack: 0->0->0->
string_traveled:"( ("
Meet two '(', push two zeros to the stack

stack: 0->1->
string_traveled: "( ( )"
First time meets ')', it balance the last '(', so pop the stack. But 0 indicates no inner parentheses exists, so just pass 1 to parent parenthese.

stack: 0->1->0->0->
string_traveled: "( ( ) ( ("
Keep pushing zeros

stack 0->1->1->
string_traveled: "( ( ) ( ( )"
Balance one '(', and still no inner parenthese, so pass 1 to parent

stack 0->3->
string_traveled: "( ( ) ( ( ) )"
Balance another '(', but the inner is not zero, so double it and add to parent's score

stack 6->
string_traveled: "( ( ) ( ( ) ) )"
Same as last step, double the inner score and add to parent's

[29/03/24, 7:21:55 PM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎18 min
[29/03/24, 7:22:25 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int sumSubarrayMins(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        vector<int> left_smaller;
        vector<int> right_smaller;

        stack<pair<int, int>> stk; // <idx,val>
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            while (!stk.empty() && stk.top().second >= arr[i]) {
                stk.pop();
            }
            if (stk.empty()) {
                left_smaller.push_back(-1);
            } else
                left_smaller.push_back(stk.top().first);
            stk.push({i, arr[i]});
        }

        while (!stk.empty())
            stk.pop();

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            while (!stk.empty() && stk.top().second > arr[i]) {
                stk.pop();
            }
            if (stk.empty()) {
                right_smaller.push_back(n);
            } else
                right_smaller.push_back(stk.top().first);
            stk.push({i, arr[i]});
        }
        reverse(right_smaller.begin(), right_smaller.end());

        long long sum = 0;
        int MOD = 1e9 + 7;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            sum += (long long)(i - left_smaller[i]) * (right_smaller[i] - i) *
                   arr[i] % MOD;
            sum %= MOD;
        }
        return sum;
    }
};

[30/03/24, 9:05:47 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: Count of SubArrays with K Distinct Elements = Count of SubArrays with At Most K Distinct Elements - Count of SubArrays with At Most K-1 Distinct Elements
[30/03/24, 9:06:44 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int subArray(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        unordered_map<int, int> map;  // create an unordered map to store the count of each number in the current subarray
        int count = 0, start = 0, end = 0;  // initialize variables for count of valid subarrays, start and end index of subarray
        while (end < n) {  // loop through the array from the start to end index
            map[nums[end]]++;  // add the current element to the map and increment its count
            while (map.size() > k) {  // if the number of distinct elements in the map is greater than k, move the start index and remove elements from the map
                map[nums[start]]--;  // decrement the count of the element at the start index
                if (map[nums[start]] == 0) {  // if the count of the element at the start index becomes 0, remove it from the map
                    map.erase(nums[start]);
                }
                start++;  // increment the start index to move the window
            }
            count += end - start + 1;  // add the count of valid subarrays for the current subarray to the total count
            end++;  // increment the end index to move the window
        }
        return count;  // return the total count of valid subarrays
    }
    int subarraysWithKDistinct(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        // return the count of subarrays with exactly k distinct elements minus the count of subarrays with less than k distinct elements
        return subArray(nums, k) - subArray(nums, k - 1);
    }
};

[30/03/24, 10:06:51 AM] Satvik Saini: class MinStack {
public:
    stack<long long> stk;
    long long minEle;
    MinStack() {
    }
    
    void push(int val) {
        if(stk.empty()){
            stk.push(val);
            minEle = val;
        }
        else{
            if(val >= minEle){
                stk.push(val);
            }
            else{
                // this value will be smaller than current min, detection point that min val changes
                stk.push((long long)val+(val-minEle));
                minEle = val;
            }
        }
    }
    
    void pop() {
        if(stk.top() >= minEle){
            stk.pop();
        }
        else{
            minEle = minEle + (minEle - stk.top());
            stk.pop();
        }

    }
    
    int top() {
        if(stk.top() >= minEle) return stk.top();
        return (int)minEle;
    }
    
    int getMin() {
        return (int)minEle;
    }
};

[30/03/24, 1:49:01 PM] Satvik Saini: int Solution::solve(vector<int> &A, int B) {
    
    unordered_set<int> s1;
    set<pair<int,int>> s2;
    
    for(int ele : A){
        if(s1.find(ele^B) != s1.end()){
            s2.insert({ele,ele^B});
        }
        s1.insert(ele);
    }
    return s2.size();
}

[31/03/24, 9:12:37 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int distance(vector<int>& point1, vector<int>& point2) {
        return abs(point1[0] - point2[0]) + abs(point1[1] - point2[1]);
    }
public:
    int minimumDistance(vector<vector<int>>& points) {
        int n = points.size();
        int dist = 0;
        vector<int> x,y;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++){
                if(dist < distance(points[i],points[j])){
                    dist = distance(points[i],points[j]);
                    x = points[i];
                    y = points[j];
                }
            }
        }
        // now you have 2 candidates which we can remove to minimise the maximum distance
        int max_x = 0, max_y = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(points[i] == x || points[i] == y) continue;
            max_x = max(max_x,distance(points[i],x));
            max_y = max(max_y,distance(points[i],y));
        }
        return max_x > max_y ? max_y : max_x;
    }
};

[31/03/24, 9:32:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #define ll long long

class Solution {
public:
    int mod=1e9+7;
    unordered_map<ll,unordered_map<ll,unordered_map<ll,unordered_map<ll,ll>>>> dp;
    ll helper(vector<int> &nums,int n,int k,int ind,int count,ll diff,ll last){
        if(count==k) return (diff%mod);
        if(ind==n) return 0;
        if(dp.count(ind) && dp[ind].count(count) && dp[ind][count].count(diff) && dp[ind][count][diff].count(last)) 
            return dp[ind][count][diff][last];
        
        ll new_diff= (last==-1) ? diff%mod : min(diff , abs(nums[ind]*1LL - nums[last]*1LL)%mod);
        ll take = helper(nums,n,k,ind+1,count+1,new_diff,ind);
        ll notTake = helper(nums,n,k,ind+1,count,diff,last);
        
        return dp[ind][count][diff][last] = (take%mod + notTake%mod)%mod;
    }
    
    int sumOfPowers(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n=nums.size();
        //memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        return helper(nums,n,k,0,0,LONG_MAX,-1);
    }
};
[31/03/24, 9:33:08 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int mod = 1000000007;

    // 4D DP with dimensions: (i, last, size, mindiff)
    // i -> current index we are standing at
    // last -> last index that we included. (can be -1 for empty subsequence)
    // size -> size of the subsequence considered so far
    // mindiff -> current minimum absolute difference so far

    // mindiff will also be a variable attribute, as according to the
    // subsequence considered, (i, last, size) might be same, but due to
    // some different elements being considered, mindiff might be different

    // due to presence of -ve values (last can be -1), 
    // we are using unordered_map, as its complexity is 1 in best case
    // gives TLE in ordered map

    // mindiff can be a very large value, probably >INT_MAX, hence, taking
    // it to be long, and all other dimensions fits into INT
    unordered_map<int, unordered_map<int, unordered_map<int, unordered_map<long, long>>>> dp;

    long recur(vector<int>& nums, int k, int i, int last, int size, long long mindiff) {
      int n = nums.size();
      if(size == k) return mindiff;   // valid subsequence
      if(i >= n) return LONG_MAX; // invalid subsequence, so return invalid diff

      // MEMOIZATION: check if this call is an overlapping call.
      // if all the constraints of current call are present in the dp hash,
      // we return it.
      // NOTE: we are using count() as this will return 1 if the constraint is present in hash, otherwise returns 0
      if(dp.count(i) && dp[i].count(last) && dp[i][last].count(size) && dp[i][last][size].count(mindiff)) 
        return dp[i][last][size][mindiff];

      long ans1 = LONG_MAX, ans2 = LONG_MAX;

      // TAKE call
      // it might be possible that subsequence is empty till now, i.e., last = -1
      long long diff = LONG_MAX;  // it might be possible that
      if(last != -1) diff = abs(nums[i]*1LL - nums[last]) % mod;

      ans2 = recur(nums, k, i+1, i, size+1, min(mindiff, diff));



      // NOT TAKE call
      ans1 = recur(nums, k, i+1, last, size, mindiff);

      // NOTE: if NOT TAKE is executed first, gives TLE in last testcase,
      // as there will be too many useless calls where the size < k

      // if any of the calls return invalid answer, return other one
      if(ans1 == LONG_MAX) return dp[i][last][size][mindiff] = ans2;
      if(ans2 == LONG_MAX) return dp[i][last][size][mindiff] = ans1;

      // return the sum of both calls, and store in dp hash
      return dp[i][last][size][mindiff] = (ans1+ans2) % mod;
    }

    int sumOfPowers(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
      // sort the elements first, so that the min difference is easier to calculate
      // possible min diff always occur in adjacent elements      
      sort(begin(nums), end(nums)); 

      // NOTE: declaring dp array in class, as it might give TLE

      // function signature -> recur(array, k, i, last, size, mindiff)
      return recur(nums, k, 0, -1, 0, LONG_MAX);
    }
};
[31/03/24, 9:34:20 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int dp[50][50][2], mod = 1000000007;
int dfs(int i, int p, int k, int pwr, bool eq, vector<int>& n) {
    if (k == 0)
        return eq ? pwr : 0;
    if (i >= n.size())
        return 0;
    if (dp[p][k][eq] == -1) {
        dp[p][k][eq] = dfs(i + 1, p, k, pwr, eq, n);
        if (abs(n[i] - n[p]) >= pwr)
            dp[p][k][eq] = (dp[p][k][eq] + dfs(i + 1, i, k - 1, pwr, eq | (n[i] - n[p] == pwr), n)) % mod;
    }
    return dp[p][k][eq];
}
int sumOfPowers(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
    long long res = 0;
    sort(begin(nums), end(nums));
    set<int> pwrs;
    for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); ++i)
        for (int j = i + 1; j < nums.size(); ++j)
            if (nums[i] != nums[j] && pwrs.insert(nums[j] - nums[i]).second) {
                memset(dp, 255, sizeof(dp));
                res = (res + dfs(0, nums.size() - 1, k, nums[j] - nums[i], false, nums)) % mod;
            }
    return res;
}

[31/03/24, 11:36:25 AM] Satvik Saini: int LadderBottomUp(int n, int k){
    vector<int> dp(n + 1);

		// dp[i] represents the no of ways of going from ith step to 0

    dp[0] = 1;  // denotes the no of ways of going from step 0 to 0
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++){
        int count = 0;
        for (int j = 1; j <= k; j++){
            if (j <= i){
								// you can reach to the ith step by taking a jump of j
                count += dp[i - j];
            }
        }
        dp[i] = count;
    }
    return dp[n];
}

// time : O(n)
// space : O(n) due to dp[]

int LadderTimeOptimised(int n, int k){
    vector<int> dp(n + 1);

    dp[0] = 1;
    dp[1] = dp[0];

		// first find the values till dp[k]
    for (int i = 2; i <= k; i++){
        dp[i] = 2 * dp[i - 1];
    }

		// applying sliding window approach to find dp[i] in constant time
    for (int i = k + 1; i <= n; i++){
        dp[i] = 2 * dp[i - 1] - dp[i - k - 1]
    }
    return dp[n];
}
[31/03/24, 11:40:05 AM] Satvik Saini: int LadderTopDown(int n, int k, vector<int> dp)
{
    // base case
    if (n == 0){
        // no of ways of going from step 0 to 0 is 1
        return 1;
    }

    // lookup
    if (dp[n] != -1){
        return dp[n];
    }

    // recursive case
    int count = 0;
    for (int i = 1; i <= k; i++){
        if (i <= n){
            // jump only if it is feasible
            // recursively, find the no of ways from step n - i to 0
            count += LadderTopDown(n - i, k, dp);
        }
    }
    return dp[n] = count;
}

[31/03/24, 7:21:00 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int diffSub(string s, string t, int n, int m, int i, int j,
                vector<vector<int>>& dp) {
        // base case
        if (j >= m) {
            return 1;
        }

        if (i >= n) {
            return 0;
        }

        // lookup
        if (dp[i][j] != -1) {
            return dp[i][j];
        }

        // recursive case
        int count = 0;

        // op1 : leave the char
        count += diffSub(s, t, n, m, i + 1, j, dp);

        // op2 : take the char
        if (s[i] == t[j])
            count += diffSub(s, t, n, m, i + 1, j + 1, dp);

        return dp[i][j] = count;
    }

    int diffSubBottomUp(string s, string t) {
        int n = s.length();
        int m = t.length();
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 1, vector<int>(m + 1, 0));

        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {
            dp[i][m] = 1;
        }
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            for (int j = m - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
                int count = 0;
                // op1 : leave the char
                count += dp[i+1][j];

                // op2 : take the char
                if (s[i] == t[j]) count += dp[i+1][j+1];

                dp[i][j] = count;
            }
        }
        return dp[0][0];
    }

    int numDistinct(string s, string t) {

        vector<vector<int>> dp(s.length() + 1, vector<int>(t.length() + 1, -1));

        // return diffSub(s, t, s.length(), t.length(), 0, 0, dp);
        return diffSubBottomUp(s, t);
    }
};

[01/04/24, 9:30:04 AM] Satvik Saini: int BottomUp(vector<vector<char>>& matrix){
        int n = matrix.size();
        int m = matrix[0].size();

        vector<vector<pair<int,int>>> dp(n+1, vector<pair<int,int>>(m+1,{0,0}));
        int area = 0;
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=m;j++){
                if((i==1 && j==1) || matrix[i-1][j-1] == '0'){
                    dp[i][j] = {matrix[i-1][j-1] - '0', matrix[i-1][j-1] - '0'};
                }
                else{
                    pair<int,int> p1 = dp[i-1][j];
                    pair<int,int> p2 = dp[i][j-1];
                    pair<int,int> p3 = dp[i-1][j-1];

                    int a = p1.first, b = p1.second, c = p2.first, d = p2.second, e = p3.first, f = p3.second;
                    int op1 = (1 + min(b,f)) * (1 + min(c,e));
                    // int op4 = (1 + min(a,e)) * (1 + min(d,f));
                    int op2 = 1 + b;
                    int op3 = 1 + c;

                    int max_area = max(op1,max(op2,op3));
                    if(max_area == op1){
                        dp[i][j] = {1 + min(c,e), 1 + min(b,f)};
                    }
                    else if(max_area == op2){
                        dp[i][j] = {1, 1 + b};
                    }
                    else if(max_area == op3){
                        dp[i][j] = {1 + c, 1};
                    }
                    // else dp[i][j] = {1 + min(d,f), 1 + min(a,e)};
                }
                area = max(area, dp[i][j].first * dp[i][j].second);
            }
        }

        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            for(int j=1;j<=m;j++){
                cout<<"("<<dp[i][j].first<<","<<dp[i][j].second<<") ";
            }
            cout<<endl;
        }
        cout<<endl;

        return area;
    }

[01/04/24, 11:44:46 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    // target -> [0... 10000]
    // i -> [0...n]
    int dp[2001][10001];
    bool f(int i , int target , vector<int>& nums){
        // base case
        if(target == 0) return true;
        if(i == nums.size()) return false;

        if(dp[i][target] != -1) return dp[i][target];
        
        // recursive case
        // you need to check if nums[i...n-1] there is a subset with sum = target 
        // for this you need to take a sequence of decision at each step you will deicde wether to include ith object or to exclude it 
        // include the obj if you can 
        int x = false;
        if(target >= nums[i]){
            x = f(i+1, target - nums[i], nums);
        }
        return  dp[i][target] = x || f(i+1, target , nums);

    }

    bool canPartition(vector<int>& nums) {
        int target = 0;
        int n = nums.size();
        for(int x : nums) target += x;
        // vector<vector<int>> dp(nums.size()+1 , vector<int>((target/2)+1,0));
        if(target&1 ) return false;//number is odd  
        // memset(dp, sizeof(dp), -1);
        return f(0,target/2,nums);

[02/04/24, 7:36:33 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    string ans;
    int cnt = 0;
    void KthPath(vector<int>& d, int i, int j, int k, string path) {
        // base case
        if (i > d[0]) return;
        if (j > d[1]) return;
        if (i == d[0] && j == d[1]) {
            cnt++;
            if (cnt == k) {
                // store the ans
                ans = path;
                return;
            }
        }

        // recursive case
        // op1 : go right
        KthPath(d, i, j + 1, k, path + "H");

        // op2 : go down
        KthPath(d, i + 1, j, k, path + "V");
    }

public:
    string kthSmallestPath(vector<int>& destination, int k) {
        KthPath(destination, 0, 0, k, "");
        return ans;
    }
};

[02/04/24, 10:12:22 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {

    int pickup(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int n, int m, int i1, int j1, int i2, vector<vector<vector<int>>>& dp) {
        int j2 = i1 + j1 - i2;
        // base case
        if ((i1 == n || j1 == m || grid[i1][j1] == -1) || (i2 == n || j2 == m || grid[i2][j2] == -1)) {
            return INT_MIN;
        }

        if (i1 == n - 1 && j1 == m - 1) {
            return grid[i1][j1];
        }

        // lookup
        if (dp[i1][i2][j1] != -1) {
            return dp[i1][i2][j1];
        }

        // recursive case
        int cherries = 0;
        if (i1 == i2 && j1 == j2) {
            cherries += grid[i1][j1];
        } else {
            cherries += grid[i1][j1] + grid[i2][j2];
        }
        int op1 = pickup(grid, n, m, i1 + 1, j1, i2 + 1, dp);
        int op2 = pickup(grid, n, m, i1 + 1, j1, i2, dp);
        int op3 = pickup(grid, n, m, i1, j1 + 1, i2 + 1, dp);
        int op4 = pickup(grid, n, m, i1, j1 + 1, i2, dp);

        cherries += max(max(op1, op2), max(op3, op4));
        return dp[i1][i2][j1] = cherries;
    }

public:
    int cherryPickup(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int n = grid.size();
        int m = grid[0].size();

        if (n == 1 && m == 1 && grid[0][0] == 1)
            return 1;

        vector<vector<vector<int>>> dp(n + 1, vector<vector<int>>(n + 1, vector<int>(n + 1, -1)));

        int ans = pickup(grid, m, n, 0, 0, 0, dp);

        return ans < 0 ? 0 : ans;
    }

[02/04/24, 3:18:40 PM] Satvik Saini: The logic you've implemented to find the maximum number of repetitions of string s2 within string s1 is conceptually incorrect. Let's address the issues:

Binary Search Approach: The binary search approach is not suitable for this problem because the number of repetitions of s2 within s1 does not have a monotonic behavior with respect to the number of repetitions of s2. That means, you cannot guarantee that if a certain number of repetitions is feasible, then all greater numbers will also be feasible, and vice versa.

Incorrect Subsequence Checking: The function isSubsequence is meant to check if s2 is a subsequence of s1, but this is not the requirement of the problem. Instead, you need to find out how many times s2 can be repeated within s1.
[02/04/24, 3:21:24 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool isSubsequence(string s1, string s2, int i, int j, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        //base case
        if(j == s2.length()) return true;
        if(i == s1.length()) return false;

        //lookup
        if(dp[i][j] != -1) return dp[i][j];
        
        //recursive case
        //op1 : take the char if possible
        bool ans = false;
        if(s1[i] == s2[j]){
            ans = isSubsequence(s1, s2, i+1, j+1, dp);
        }
        //op2 : do not take the char
        if(!ans){
            ans = isSubsequence(s1, s2, i+1, j, dp);
        }
        return dp[i][j] = ans;
    }
public:
    int getMaxRepetitions(string s1, int n1, string s2, int n2) {
        int s = 1, e = 10000;
        string str1 = "";
        while(n1){
            str1 += s1;
            n1--;
        }
        int ans;
        while(s <= e){
            int mid = s + (e - s) / 2;
            string str2 = "";
            int temp = mid;
            while(temp){
                str2 += s2;
                temp--;
            }
            vector<vector<int>> dp(str1.length()+1, vector<int>(str2.length()+1, -1));
            if(isSubsequence(str1, str2, 0, 0, dp)){
                ans = mid;
                s = mid + 1;
            }
            else e = mid - 1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

            n1--;

                temp--;

            else e = mid - 1;

        return ans;

[02/04/24, 3:30:58 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int solve(int n, vector<int>& dp) {
        // base case
        if (n <= 1) {
            return 1;
        }

        if (dp[n] != -1) {
            return dp[n];
        }

        // reucrsive case
        int ans = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            ans += solve(i - 1, dp) * solve(n - i, dp);
        }

        return dp[n] = ans;
    }

    int numTrees(int n) {

        vector<int> dp(n + 1, -1);
        return solve(n, dp);
    }
};

public:
    int findSubstringInWraproundString(string s) {
        int i = 0, j = 0, cnt = 0;
        while (j < s.length()) {
            if (j == 0 || s[j - 1] + 1 == s[j] || (s[j - 1] == 'z' and s[j] == 'a')) {
            }
            else {
                cnt += (j - i) * (j - i + 1) / 2;
                i = j;
            }
            j++;
        }
        cnt += (j - i) * (j - i + 1) / 2;
        return cnt;
    }

[03/04/24, 7:41:08 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-iii/description/?envType=list&envId=50vlu3z5
[03/04/24, 7:41:24 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int BuySell(vector<int>& prices, int i, int cnt, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        //base case
        if(i == prices.size() || cnt == 2){
            return 0;
        }

        //lookup
        if(dp[i][cnt] != -1) return dp[i][cnt];

        //recursive case
        //op1 : do not buy
        int ans = BuySell(prices, i+1, cnt, dp);

        //op2 : buy and sell
        for(int j=i+1;j<prices.size();j++){
            if(prices[j] > prices[i])
            ans = max(ans, BuySell(prices, j+1, cnt+1, dp) + prices[j] - prices[i]);
        }
        return dp[i][cnt] = ans;
    }
public:
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        vector<vector<int>> dp(prices.size()+1, vector<int>(3,-1));
        return BuySell(prices, 0, 0, dp);
    }
};

[03/04/24, 7:50:07 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:

int f(int num, int currstk, int i, vector<int>& prices){

        // base case
        if(num == 2) return 0;
        if(i == prices.size()){
            return 0;
        }
        // recursive case

        if(currstk == -1){
            return max(f(num, prices[i],i+1,prices) , f(num, -1 , i+1,prices));
        }
        return max(prices[i] - currstk + f(num + 1, -1 , i+1,prices) , f(num,currstk , i+1,prices));
    }
    
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        return max(f(0,prices[0],0,prices) , f(0,-1,0,prices));
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    
    int solve(vector<int>&prices, int day, int transactionsLeft, vector<vector<int>> &Memo){
        
        if(day == prices.size()){
            return 0;
        }
        
        if(transactionsLeft == 0){
            return 0;
        }
        
        int &ans = Memo[day][transactionsLeft]; 
        
        if(ans != -1){ // if problem has already been solved 
            return ans;
        }
        
        // choice 1
        // no transaction today
        int ans1 = solve(prices, day + 1, transactionsLeft, Memo);
        
        
        // choice 2
        // doing the possible transaction today     
        int ans2 = 0;
        bool buy = (transactionsLeft % 2 == 0);
        
        if(buy == true){ // buy
            ans2 = -prices[day] + solve(prices, day + 1, transactionsLeft - 1, Memo);
        }else{ // sell
            ans2 = prices[day] + solve(prices, day + 1, transactionsLeft - 1, Memo);
        }
        
        return ans = max(ans1, ans2); // store ans in memo before returning
        
        
    }
    
    
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {
        
        vector<vector<int>> Memo(prices.size(), vector<int>(5, -1));
        int ans = solve(prices, 0, 4, Memo);
        return ans;
        
    }
};

[03/04/24, 8:30:54 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: // https://leetcode.com/problems/best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-iv/

#define vvvi vector<vector<vector<int>>>

class Solution {
public:

    int helper(vector<int>& prices, int N, int i, int k, bool canBuy) {

        // base case

        if (i == N || k == 0) {

            return 0;

        }

        // recursive case

        // find the maximum profit you can make by completing <=k transactions starting from the ith day

        // make a decision for the ith day

        // 1. don't do anything

        int ans = helper(prices, N, i + 1, k, canBuy);

        // 2. buy a stock on the ith day
        if (canBuy) {
            ans = max(ans, helper(prices, N, i + 1, k, false) - prices[i]);

            // Y - prices[i]
        }

        // 3. sell the stock on the ith day
        if (!canBuy) {
            ans = max(ans, helper(prices, N, i + 1, k - 1, true) + prices[i]);

            // Z + prices[i]
        }

        return ans;



    }

    int helperTopDown(vector<int>& prices, int N, int i, int k, bool canBuy, vvvi& dp) {

        // base case

        if (i == N || k == 0) {

            return 0;

        }

        // lookup

        if (dp[i][k][canBuy] != -1) {
            return dp[i][k][canBuy];
        }

        // recursive case

        // find the maximum profit you can make by completing <=k transactions starting from the ith day

        // make a decision for the ith day

        // 1. don't do anything

        int ans = helperTopDown(prices, N, i + 1, k, canBuy, dp);

        // 2. buy a stock on the ith day
        if (canBuy) {
            ans = max(ans, helperTopDown(prices, N, i + 1, k, false, dp) - prices[i]);

            // Y - prices[i]
        }

        // 3. sell the stock on the ith day
        if (!canBuy) {
            ans = max(ans, helperTopDown(prices, N, i + 1, k - 1, true, dp) + prices[i]);

            // Z + prices[i]
        }

        return dp[i][k][canBuy] = ans;

    }


    int maxProfit(int K, vector<int>& prices) {
        int N = prices.size();
        // return helper(prices, N, 0, K, true);
        vvvi dp(N + 1, vector<vector<int>>(K + 1, vector<int>(2, -1)));
        return helperTopDown(prices, N, 0, K, true, dp);
    }
};

[04/04/24, 7:33:18 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include<iostream>
#include<vector>

using namespace std;

bool isPalindrome(string s) {
	int i = 0;
	int j = s.size() - 1;

	while (i < j) {
		if (s[i] != s[j]) {
			// 's' is not a palindrome
			return false;
		}
		i++;
		j--;
	}

	// 's' is a palindrome
	return true;
}

int helperTopDown(string str, int n, int i, vector<int>& dp) {

	// lookup

	if (dp[i] != -1) {
		return dp[i];
	}


	// base case

	if (i == n) {
		return dp[i] = 1;
	}

	// recursive case

	// count the no. of palindromic partitioning of str[i...n-1]

	int count = 0;

	// decide the next cut

	for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {

		// can you make a cut at the jth index

		string subString = str.substr(i, j - i + 1);
		if (isPalindrome(subString)) {
			// make a cut at the jth index
			count += helperTopDown(str, n, j + 1, dp);
		}

	}

	return dp[i] = count;

}

int main() {

	string str = "abaaa";
	int n = str.size();

	vector<int> dp(n + 1, -1);
	cout << helperTopDown(str, n, 0, dp) << endl;

	return 0;
}

[04/04/24, 10:43:15 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int longestValidParentheses(string s) {
        int n = s.length();
        int max_len = 0;
        stack<int> indices;
        // You can imagine there is a ) at index -1 position
        // i.e. s[-1] = ')'
        indices.push(-1);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            if(s[i] == '(') indices.push(i);
            else{
                // if there is a match (i.e. "()"), then we can pop the stack
                // and update the max length by (i - indices.top())
                // (because the string in (indices.top(), i] is a valid parenthese)
                // else if there isn't a match (i.e. "))"), then we can substitute
                // the top of the stack by the latest one
                // To sum up, no matter "()" or "))", we all need to pop the stack
                indices.pop();
                
                // if the stack is empty, it means a "))" occurs
                if(indices.empty()) indices.push(i);
                // a "()" occurs
                else{
                    max_len = max(max_len, i - indices.top());
                }
            }
        }
        return max_len;
    }
};
[04/04/24, 10:43:28 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-valid-parentheses/?envType=list&envId=50v8wybv
[04/04/24, 10:52:23 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: stack<int> stk;
        for(char c : s){
            int sum = 0;
            if(c == '('){
                stk.push(0);
            }
            else{
                // calculate result
                while(stk.top()!=0){
                    sum+=stk.top();
                    stk.pop();
                }
                sum = max(2*sum , 1);
                stk.pop();
                stk.push(sum);
            }
        }
        int count = 0;
        while(!stk.empty()){
            count+=stk.top();
            stk.pop();
        }
        return count;
    }
[04/04/24, 10:53:38 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int scoreOfParentheses(string S) {
        stack<int> m_stack;
        m_stack.push(0); // to keep the total score
        for (char c : S) {
            if (c == '(') m_stack.push(0); // When meets '(', just push a zero to stack
            else {
                int tmp = m_stack.top(); //  balance the last '(', it stored the score of inner parentheses
                m_stack.pop();
                int val = 0;
                if (tmp > 0) val = tmp * 2; // not zero means inner parentheses exists and double it
                else  val = 1; // zero means no inner parentheses, just using 1
                m_stack.top() += val; // pass the score of this level to parent parenthese
            }
        }
        return m_stack.top();
    }
};
[04/04/24, 10:56:18 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/score-of-parentheses/solutions/1856642/c-solution-with-better-intution/
[04/04/24, 10:56:43 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/score-of-parentheses/solutions/141975/c-solution-using-stack-5ms-detail-explained/
[04/04/24, 11:00:02 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int scoreOfParentheses(string s) {
        int cnt = 0;
        stack<int> stk;
        for(char ch : s){
            if(ch == '('){
                stk.push(cnt);
                cnt = 0; // for new level
            }
            else{
                cnt += stk.top() + max(1,cnt);
                stk.pop();
            }
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};

[08/04/24, 6:46:39 PM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> shortestPath(int n, int m, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n+1];
        
        for(auto it : edges){
            adj[it[0]].push_back({it[1],it[2]});
            adj[it[1]].push_back({it[0],it[2]});
        }
        
        vector<int> distMap(n+1, INT_MAX);
        distMap[1] = 0;
        vector<int> vis(n+1, 0);
        vector<int> parentMap(n+1);
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            parentMap[i] = i;
        }
        priority_queue<pair<int,int>, vector<pair<int,int>>, greater<pair<int,int>>> pq;
        pq.push({0,1});   // <dist,node>
        
        while(!pq.empty()){
            int dist = pq.top().first;
            int node = pq.top().second;
            pq.pop();
            
            for(auto adjP : adj[node]){
                int neighbour = adjP.first;
                int edW = adjP.second;
                if(!vis[neighbour]){
                    vis[neighbour] = 1;
                    if(dist + edW < distMap[neighbour]){
                        distMap[neighbour] = dist + edW;
                        parentMap[neighbour] = node;
                        pq.push({distMap[neighbour], neighbour});
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        if(distMap[n] == INT_MAX) return {-1};
        vector<int> ans;
        int node = n;
        while(node != parentMap[node]){
            ans.push_back(parentMap[node]);
            node = parentMap[node];
        }
        ans.push_back(1);
        ans.push_back(distMap[n]);
        reverse(ans.begin(), ans.end());
        return ans;
    }
[08/04/24, 6:46:47 PM] Satvik Saini: kya glti kr rha hu bataie

[08/04/24, 6:53:22 PM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> dijkstra(int src, int n, const vector<vector<pii>>& adj) {
    vector<int> dist(n + 1, numeric_limits<int>::max());
    vector<bool> visited(n + 1, false);
    priority_queue<pii, vector<pii>, greater<pii>> pq;

    dist[src] = 0;
    pq.push({0, src});

    while (!pq.empty()) {
        int u = pq.top().second;
        pq.pop();

        if (visited[u]) continue;
        visited[u] = true;

        for (const auto& neighbor : adj[u]) {
            int v = neighbor.first;
            int weight = neighbor.second;

            if (!visited[v] && dist[u] + weight < dist[v]) {
                dist[v] = dist[u] + weight;
                pq.push({dist[v], v});
            }
        }
    }

    return dist;
}

[09/04/24, 7:13:05 AM] Satvik Saini: // approach
// you will give chance to each bomb to be the source node for the bfs
// then count the no of bombs detonated by that source
// and keep the track of the max bombs detonated 
// bfs will be called bombs.size()-1 times
// we also have to create an adjacency list
// for that we need to know that how to check where a bomb lies with the the area surrounded by the centre (x, y) with radius r
// if bomb1 can detonate bomb2, then make an edge from bomb1 -> bomb2

#define ll long long

class Solution {
    ll distance_sq(int x, int y, int a, int b){
        return (ll)pow(x-a, 2) + (ll)pow(y-b, 2);
    }
    void dfs(vector<int> adj[], unordered_set<int> &vis, int i){
        vis.insert(i);
        for(int neighbour : adj[i]){
            if(vis.find(neighbour) == vis.end()){
                dfs(adj, vis, neighbour);
            }
        }
    }
public:
    int maximumDetonation(vector<vector<int>>& bombs) {

        vector<int> adj[bombs.size()];

        for(int i=0;i<bombs.size();i++){
            int x = bombs[i][0];
            int y = bombs[i][1];
            int r1 = bombs[i][2];

            for(int j=i+1;j<bombs.size();j++){

                int a = bombs[j][0];
                int b = bombs[j][1];
                int r2 = bombs[j][2];

                if(distance_sq(x,y,a,b) <= (ll)r1*(ll)r1){
                    // ith bomb can detonate jth bomb
                    adj[i].push_back(j);
                }
                if(distance_sq(x,y,a,b) <= (ll)r2*(ll)r2){
                    // jth bomb can detonate ith bomb
                    adj[j].push_back(i);
                }
            }
        }

        for(int i=0;i<bombs.size();i++){
            cout<<i<<" : ";
            for(int j=0;j<adj[i].size();j++){
                cout<<adj[i][j]<<" ";
            }cout<<endl;
        }

        int maxDet = 0;

        //give chance to each bomb to detonate first

        // for(int i=0;i<bombs.size();i++){
        //     int detonate = 1; // ith bomb is already detonated

        //     vector<int> vis(bombs.size(), 0);
        //     vis[i] = 1;
        //     queue<int> q;
        //     q.push(i);

        //     while(!q.empty()){
        //         int front = q.front();
        //         q.pop();

        //         for(auto adjNode : adj[front]){
        //             if(!vis[adjNode]){
        //                 detonate++;
        //                 vis[adjNode] = 1;
        //                 q.push(adjNode);
        //             }
        //         }
        //     }
        //     maxDet = max(maxDet, detonate);
        // }

        unordered_set<int> vis;
        for(int i=0;i<bombs.size();i++){
            int sz = vis.size();
            if(vis.find(i) == vis.end()){
                dfs(adj, vis, i);
                int szz = vis.size();
                maxDet = max(maxDet, szz - sz);
            }
        }

        return maxDet;
    }
};

[09/04/24, 7:27:37 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎Voice call, ‎14 min
[09/04/24, 7:32:55 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    double calcDis(int& x1, int& y1, int& x2, int& y2){
        
        long double dis = sqrtl(1LL * (x1-x2)*(x1-x2) + 1LL * (y1-y2)*(y1-y2));
        
        return dis;
    }
    
    void dfs(int node, vector<int>& visited,int& thisPathBombs, vector<int> canDetonate[]){
        
        visited[node] = 1;
        thisPathBombs++;
        
        for(int i=0;i<canDetonate[node].size();i++){
            
            int cnode = canDetonate[node][i];
            
            if(visited[cnode] == -1){
                dfs(cnode,visited,thisPathBombs,canDetonate);
            }
        }
    }
    
    int maximumDetonation(vector<vector<int>>& bombs) {
        
        int n = bombs.size();
        
        vector<int> canDetonate[n];
        
        int mxBombs = 0;
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++){
                double dis = calcDis(bombs[i][0],bombs[i][1],bombs[j][0],bombs[j][1]);
                double d1 = bombs[i][2] * 1.0;
                double d2 = bombs[j][2] * 1.0;
                
                if(dis <= d1){
                    canDetonate[i].push_back(j);
                }
                
                if(dis <= d2){
                    canDetonate[j].push_back(i);
                }
            }
        }
        
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
            int thisPathBombs = 0;
            vector<int> visited(n,-1);
            dfs(i,visited,thisPathBombs,canDetonate);
            mxBombs = max(mxBombs, thisPathBombs);
        }
        
        return mxBombs;
    }
};

[09/04/24, 6:19:32 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int mod = 1e9 + 7;
    int dp[51][101][51];
    int f(int i, int p, int k, int n, int m) {
        // base case
        if (k == -1) return 0;
        if (dp[i][p][k] != -1) return dp[i][p][k];

        if (i == n) {
            if (k == 0)
                return 1;
            return 0;
        }

        // recursive case
        int ans = 0;
        for (int j = 1; j <= m; j++) {
            ans = (ans + f(i + 1, max(j, p), j > p ? k - 1 : k, n, m)) % mod;
        }

        return dp[i][p][k] = ans;
    }
    int numOfArrays(int n, int m, int k) {

        memset(dp, -1, sizeof(dp));
        return f(0, 0, k, n, m);
    }
};

            if(k == 0) return 1;

        // recursive case
        int ans = 0;
        for(int j=1 ; j<=m ; j++){
            ans = ( ans + f(i+1,max(j,p), j > p ? k-1 : k , n,m) )%mod;
        }

        return dp[i][p][k] = ans;

    }
    int numOfArrays(int n, int m, int k) {
        if(k>n) return 0;
        int maxi = 0;
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        int ans = 0;

        }
        return ans;
        
    }

[10/04/24, 8:33:00 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int orangesRotting(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {

        int m = grid.size();
        int n = grid[0].size();

        // if multiple rotten oranges are given this gives hint towards multi source bfs
        // if there is a component which does not have a rotten orange then ans will be -1 

        // we will have a queue to track the oranges which are rotten but have not made its neighbours rot 
        queue<pair<int , int>> q;
        // we will need a disance map to track the distance or each fresh orange from its nearest neighbour , the maximum distance will
        // the answer
        vector<vector<int>> dist(m , vector<int>(n , INT_MIN));
        // initialisation of queue which stores the rotten oranges which have not made its neighbour rot
        for(int i=0 ; i<m ; i++){
            for(int j=0 ; j<n ; j++){
                if(grid[i][j] == 2){
                    q.push({i,j});
                    dist[i][j] = 0;
                }
            }
        }
        vector<int> dx = {-1 , 1 , 0 , 0};
        vector<int> dy = {0 ,0 , -1 , 1};
        while(!q.empty()){
            pair<int,int> p = q.front();
            int i = p.first;
            int j = p.second;
            q.pop();
            // explore the element popped 
            for(int k=0 ; k<4 ; k++){
                int nx = i + dx[k];
                int ny = j + dy[k];

                if(nx>=0 and ny>=0 and nx<m and ny<n and grid[nx][ny] == 1){
                    // you are at a fresh orange 
                    grid[nx][ny] = 2;
                    dist[nx][ny] = dist[i][j] + 1;
                    q.push({nx,ny});

                }
            }
        }
        int timeelapsed = 0;
        // after this the distance map is ready 
        for(int i=0 ; i<m ; i++){
            for(int j=0 ; j<n ; j++){
                if(grid[i][j] == 1){
                    return -1;
                }
                timeelapsed = max(timeelapsed , dist[i][j]);
            }
        }
        return timeelapsed;

    }
};

[11/04/24, 12:25:28 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /*

	Implementation of the disjoint set union data structure
	by using union by rank and path compression heuristics.

*/

#include<iostream>
#include<unordered_map>

using namespace std;

template <typename T>
class disjointSet {

	unordered_map<T, T> parentMap; // to store a mapping b/w vertices & their parents
	unordered_map<T, int> rankMap;   // to store a mapping b/w vertices & their ranks i.e. sizes

public :

	void createSet(T x) {
		parentMap[x] = x;
		rankMap[x] = 1;
	}

	T findSet(T x) {
		if (parentMap[x] == x) {
			return x;
		}

		return parentMap[x] = findSet(parentMap[x]); // path compression
	}

	void unionSet(T x, T y) {
		T lx = findSet(x);
		T ly = findSet(y);

		if (lx != ly) {

			int rx = rankMap[lx];
			int ry = rankMap[ly];

			if (rx > ry) {
				parentMap[ly] = lx;
				rankMap[lx] += rankMap[ly];
			} else {
				parentMap[lx] = ly;
				rankMap[ly] += rankMap[lx];
			}

		}
	}


};

int main() {

	disjointSet<int> ds;

	ds.createSet(1); // {1}
	ds.createSet(2); // {2}
	ds.createSet(3); // {3}
	ds.createSet(4); // {4}

	ds.unionSet(1, 2); // {1, 2}, {3}, {4}
	ds.unionSet(2, 3); // {1, 2, 3}, {4}

	cout << ds.findSet(2) << endl;

	ds.unionSet(3, 4); // {1, 2, 3, 4}

	cout << ds.findSet(4) << endl;

	return 0;
}
[11/04/24, 12:25:56 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /*

	Cycle detection in an undirection graph using the union-find algorithm.

*/

#include<iostream>
#include<unordered_map>
#include<set>
#include<vector>

using namespace std;

template <typename T>
class disjointSet {

	unordered_map<T, T> parentMap; // to store a mapping b/w vertices & their parents
	unordered_map<T, int> rankMap;   // to store a mapping b/w vertices & their ranks i.e. sizes

public :

	void createSet(T x) {
		parentMap[x] = x;
		rankMap[x] = 1;
	}

	T findSet(T x) {
		if (parentMap[x] == x) {
			return x;
		}

		return parentMap[x] = findSet(parentMap[x]); // path compression
	}

	void unionSet(T x, T y) {
		T l_x = findSet(x);
		T l_y = findSet(y);
		if (l_x != l_y) {
			if (rankMap[l_x] > rankMap[l_y]) { // union by rank (size)
				parentMap[l_y] = l_x;
				rankMap[l_x] += rankMap[l_y];
			} else {
				parentMap[l_x] = l_y;
				rankMap[l_y] += rankMap[l_x];
			}
		}
	}

};


template <typename T>
class edge {
public :

	T u;
	T v;

	edge(T u, T v) {
		this->u = u;
		this->v = v;
	}
};

template <typename T>
class graph {

	set<T>  vertexSet;        // to store the graph representation
	vector<edge<T>> edgeList; // to store the graph representation

public :

	void addEdge(T u, T v) {
		// add an edge of weight 'w' b/w 'u' and 'v'
		edgeList.push_back(edge<T>(u, v));
		vertexSet.insert(u);
		vertexSet.insert(v);
	}

	bool isCyclePresent() {
		disjointSet<T> ds;
		for (T vertex : vertexSet) {
			ds.createSet(vertex);
		}
		for (edge<T> e : edgeList) {
			if (ds.findSet(e.u) != ds.findSet(e.v)) {
				ds.unionSet(e.u, e.v);
			} else {
				return true;
			}
		}
		return false;
	}
};

int main() {

	graph<char> g;

	g.addEdge('A', 'B');
	g.addEdge('A', 'C');
	g.addEdge('B', 'C');

	g.isCyclePresent() ? cout << "cycle found!" << endl :
	                          cout << "cycle not found!" << endl;

	return 0;
}

[12/04/24, 10:16:43 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int MOD = 1e9 + 7;
    void sum(vector<int>& nums, int k, int i, vector<int> &diff, int prev, long long val){
        //base case
        if(i == nums.size()){
            if(k == 0){
                diff.push_back(val % MOD);
            }
            return;
        }
        
        // recursive case
        //op1 : pick
        if(prev == INT_MIN){
            sum(nums, k-1, i+1, diff, nums[i], val);
        }
        else{
            sum(nums, k-1, i+1, diff, nums[i], min(val, (long long)abs(nums[i]-prev)));
        }
        
        //op2 : not pick
        sum(nums, k, i+1, diff, prev, val);
        
    }
public:
    int sumOfPowers(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        vector<int> diff;
        
        sum(nums, k, 0, diff, INT_MIN, LLONG_MAX);
        
        long long ans = 0;
        for(long long ele : diff){
            // cout<< ele << " ";
            ans = (ans + ele) % MOD;
        }
        return ans % MOD;
    }
};
[12/04/24, 10:25:26 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    void addContri(vector<int> &bitV, int n, bool isAdd){
        int idx = 0;
        while(n){
            bitV[idx] = bitV[idx] + (isAdd ? n & 1 : -(n & 1));
            n = n >> 1;
            idx++;
        }
    }
    int val(vector<int> bitV){
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<32;i++){
            ans += bitV[i] != 0 ? 1<<i : 0;
        }
        return ans;
    }
public:
    int minimumSubarrayLength(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        vector<int> bitV(32,0);
        
        int i = 0, j = 0, len = INT_MAX;
        while(j < nums.size()){
            
            addContri(bitV, nums[j], true);
            while(val(bitV) >= k && i <= j){
                len = min(len, j - i + 1);
                addContri(bitV, nums[i], false);
                i++;
            }
            j++;
        }
        
        return len == INT_MAX ? -1 : len;
    }
};
[12/04/24, 10:35:29 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int n, mod = 1e9 + 7;
    unordered_map<long long, int> dp;
private:
    int sim(int i, int prev, int k, int mini, vector<int> &nums) {
        if (!k) return mini;
        if (i == n and k) return 0;
        
        long long key = i + 1e2 * prev + 1e4 * k + 1e6 * mini;
        
        if (dp.find(key) != dp.end()) 
            return dp[key];

        int skip = sim(i+1, prev, k, mini, nums);
        int pick = sim(i+1, i, k-1, min(mini, prev == -1 ? mod : nums[i] - nums[prev]), nums);
        
        return dp[key] = (pick + skip) % mod;
    }
public:
    int sumOfPowers(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        n = nums.size();
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        return sim(0, -1, k, 1e9, nums);
    }
};

[12/04/24, 12:01:35 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int find(int i, vector<int> parent){
        if(parent[i] == i ) return i;
        return parent[i] = find(parent[i],parent);
    }
    long long countPairs(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<int> parent(n);
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++) parent[i] = i;
        for(auto edge : edges ){
            int l_x = find(edge[0], parent);
            int l_y = find(edge[1],parent);
            if(l_x != l_y){
                parent[l_x] = l_y;
            }
        }
        unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
        for(int &x : parent){
            mpp[x]++;
        }
        vector<int> temp;
        for(auto& x : mpp){
            temp.push_back(x.second);
        }
        long long  prod = 1;
        long long sum = 0;
        for(int j=temp.size()-1 ; j>=0 ; j++){
            prod *= temp[j];
            sum += prod;
        }
        return sum;
    }
};

[12/04/24, 12:13:31 PM] Satvik Saini: // Create a vector to store the result
    vector<int> result(n);
    
    // First, calculate the product of all elements before i
    int product = 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        result[i] = product;
        product *= nums[i];
    }
    
    // Then, multiply the product of all elements after i
    product = 1;
    for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
        result[i] *= product;
        product *= nums[i];
    }
    
    return result;
[12/04/24, 12:14:08 PM] Satvik Saini: It first calculates the product of all elements before and after each element in two separate loops, and then combines these products to get the final result.

public:
    int find(int i, vector<int> parent){
        if(parent[i] == i ) return i;
        return parent[i] = find(parent[i],parent);
    }
    long long countPairs(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<int> parent(n);
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++) parent[i] = i;
        for(auto edge : edges ){
            int l_x = find(edge[0], parent);
            int l_y = find(edge[1],parent);
            if(l_x != l_y){
                parent[l_x] = l_y;
            }
        }
        unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
        for(int &x : parent){
            mpp[x]++;
        }
        vector<int> temp;
        for(auto& x : mpp){
            temp.push_back(x.second);
        }
        long long sum = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<temp.size()-1 ; i++){
           long long prod = temp[i];
           for(int j=i+1 ; j<temp.size() ; j++){
               sum += temp[j]*prod;
           }
       }

[12/04/24, 12:21:45 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int find(int i, vector<int> parent){
        if(parent[i] == i ) return i;
        return parent[i] = find(parent[i],parent);
    }
     void Union(int i, int j, vector<int>& parent,vector<int>& rank ){

        int l_i = find(i,parent);
        int l_j = find(j,parent);
        if(l_i == l_j) return ;
        int r_i = rank[l_i];
        int r_j = rank[l_j];
        if(r_i > r_j){
            parent[l_j] = l_i;
            rank[l_i]+=rank[l_j];
        }
        else{
            // cout<<"hihih";
            parent[l_i] = l_j;
            rank[l_j]+=rank[l_i];
        }
    }
    long long countPairs(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<int> parent(n);
        vector<int> rank(26);
        for(int i=0 ; i<26 ; i++){
            parent[i] = i;
            rank[i] = 1;
        }
        for(auto edge : edges ){
            int l_x = find(edge[0], parent);
            int l_y = find(edge[1],parent);
            if(l_x != l_y){
                 Union(edge[0],edge[1],parent,rank);
            }
        }
        unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
        for(int &x : parent){
            cout<<x<<" ";
            mpp[x]++;
        }
        vector<int> temp;
        for(auto& x : mpp){
            temp.push_back(x.second);
        }
        long long sum = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<temp.size()-1 ; i++){
           long long prod = temp[i];
           for(int j=i+1 ; j<temp.size() ; j++){
               sum += temp[j]*prod;
           }
       }
        return sum;
    }

     void Union(int i, int j, vector<int>& parent,vector<int>& rank ){

[12/04/24, 12:36:27 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    typedef long long ll;
    void dfs(int node, unordered_map<int,vector<int>>& m, ll& cnt, vector<int>& vis){
        vis[node] = 1;
        cnt++;
        for(auto& i: m[node]){
            if(vis[i]==0) dfs(i,m,cnt,vis);   
        }
    }
    long long countPairs(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        unordered_map<int,vector<int>> m; // making adjacency list
        for(int i=0;i<edges.size();i++){
            m[edges[i][0]].push_back(edges[i][1]);
            m[edges[i][1]].push_back(edges[i][0]);
        }
        ll ans = ((ll)n*(n-1))/2;
        vector<int> vis(n,0);
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(vis[i]==0){ // as node is not visited, we find the no. of nodes in current component.
                ll cnt = 0;
                dfs(i,m,cnt,vis);
                ans -= (cnt*(cnt-1))/2;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[12/04/24, 12:36:54 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Total no. of ways to pick 2 nodes from n nodes = nC2 = n*(n-1)/2;
Here we should not pick 2 nodes from the same component, so we find the number of nodes in each component. And subtract the no. of ways to pick 2 nodes from that component.
To find no. of nodes in a component, we can just do a DFS traversal and maintain a cnt to maintain no. of nodes visited in that dfs call.
[12/04/24, 12:38:00 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: long long dfs(int i, vector<vector<int>> &al, vector<bool> &visited) {
    if (visited[i])
        return 0;
    visited[i] = true;
    return accumulate(begin(al[i]), end(al[i]), 1, [&](int s, int j){ return s + dfs(j, al, visited); });
}
long long countPairs(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
    long long res = 0;
    vector<vector<int>> al(n);
    vector<bool> visited(n);
    for (auto &e : edges) {
        al[e[0]].push_back(e[1]);
        al[e[1]].push_back(e[0]);
    }
    for (int i = 0; i < al.size(); ++i) {
        auto reached = dfs(i, al, visited);
        res += (n - reached) * reached;
        n -= reached;
    }
    return res;
}
‎[12/04/24, 12:38:44 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎image omitted
[12/04/24, 12:41:54 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
    int[] parent;
    int[] rank;
    int find(int x){
        while(parent[x]!=x){
            x = parent[parent[x]];
        }
        return x;
    }
    void makeUnion(int x, int y){
        int xPar = find(x);
        int yPar = find(y);
        if(xPar == yPar){
            return;
        }
        else if(rank[xPar]<rank[yPar]){
            parent[xPar] = yPar;
        }
        else if(rank[xPar]>rank[yPar]){
            parent[yPar] = xPar;
        }
        else{
            parent[yPar] = xPar;
            rank[xPar]++;
        }
        return;
    }
    public long countPairs(int n, int[][] edges) {
        parent = new int[n];
        rank = new int[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            parent[i] = i;
        }
        for(int[] edge:edges){
            makeUnion(edge[0], edge[1]);
        }
        long[] componentMembers = new long[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            int par = find(i);
            componentMembers[par]++;
        }
        long pairs = 0;
        long remainingMemebers = n;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(componentMembers[i]==0){
                continue;
            }
            long currentComponents = componentMembers[i];
            remainingMemebers -= currentComponents;
            long currentPairs = currentComponents * remainingMemebers;
            pairs+=currentPairs;
        }
        return pairs;
    }
}

    int[] parent;

    int find(int x){

            x = parent[parent[x]];
        }
        return x;
    }
    void makeUnion(int x, int y){
        int xPar = find(x);

            parent[yPar] = xPar;
        }
        else{
            parent[yPar] = xPar;
            rank[xPar]++;
        }
        return;
    }
    public long countPairs(int n, int[][] edges) {
        parent = new int[n];
        rank = new int[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            parent[i] = i;
        }
        for(int[] edge:edges){
            makeUnion(edge[0], edge[1]);
        }
        long[] componentMembers = new long[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            int par = find(i);
            componentMembers[par]++;
        }
        long pairs = 0;
        long remainingMemebers = n;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(componentMembers[i]==0){
                continue;
            }
            long currentComponents = componentMembers[i];
            remainingMemebers -= currentComponents;
            long currentPairs = currentComponents * remainingMemebers;
            pairs+=currentPairs;
        }
        return pairs;
    }
}

    public long countPairs(int n, int[][] edges) {
        parent = new int[n];
        rank = new int[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            parent[i] = i;
        }
        for(int[] edge:edges){
            makeUnion(edge[0], edge[1]);
        }
        long[] componentMembers = new long[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            int par = find(i);
            componentMembers[par]++;
        }
        long pairs = 0;
        long remainingMemebers = n;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(componentMembers[i]==0){
                continue;
            }
            long currentComponents = componentMembers[i];
            remainingMemebers -= currentComponents;
            long currentPairs = currentComponents * remainingMemebers;
            pairs+=currentPairs;
        }
        return pairs;
    }
}

    int[] parent;
    int[] rank;
    int find(int x){
        while(parent[x]!=x){
            x = parent[parent[x]];
        }
        return x;
    }
    void makeUnion(int x, int y){
        int xPar = find(x);
        int yPar = find(y);
        if(xPar == yPar){
            return;
        }
        else if(rank[xPar]<rank[yPar]){
            parent[xPar] = yPar;
        }
        else if(rank[xPar]>rank[yPar]){
            parent[yPar] = xPar;
        }
        else{
            parent[yPar] = xPar;
            rank[xPar]++;
        }
        return;
    }
    public long countPairs(int n, int[][] edges) {
        parent = new int[n];
        rank = new int[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            parent[i] = i;
        }
        for(int[] edge:edges){
            makeUnion(edge[0], edge[1]);
        }
        long[] componentMembers = new long[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            int par = find(i);
            componentMembers[par]++;
        }
        long pairs = 0;
        long remainingMemebers = n;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(componentMembers[i]==0){
                continue;
            }
            long currentComponents = componentMembers[i];
            remainingMemebers -= currentComponents;
            long currentPairs = currentComponents * remainingMemebers;
            pairs+=currentPairs;
        }
        return pairs;
    }
}

[12/04/24, 1:26:15 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: struct Comparator {
        bool operator()(const pair<int, char>& p1, const pair<int, char>& p2) const {
            if (p1.first == p2.first) {
                return p1.second < p2.second;
            }
            return p1.first < p2.first;
        }
    };
class Solution {
public:

    static bool cmp(pair<int,char>& p1, pair<int,char>&p2){
        if(p1.first == p2.first){
            return p1.second > p2.second;
        }
        return p1.first > p2.first;
    }
    string minimizeStringValue(string s) {
        priority_queue<pair<int,char>, vector<pair<int,char>>, greater<pair<int,char>> > min_heap;
        vector<int> freq(26,0);
        for(auto& x: s){
            if(x != '?') freq[x-'a']++;
        }
        for(int i=0 ; i<26 ; i++){
            min_heap.push({freq[i],i+'a'});
        }
        string ans = "";
        for(int i=0 ; i<s.size() ; i++){
            if(s[i] == '?'){

                // you need to place something here
                pair<int , char> temp = min_heap.top();
                // s[i] = temp.second;
                char ch = temp.second;
                cout<<temp.second<<" ";
                ans.push_back(temp.second);
                freq[ch-'a']++;
                min_heap.pop();
                min_heap.push({freq[ch-'a'],ch});

            }
        }
        cout<<endl;
        for(auto& x : ans) cout<<x<<" ";
        sort(ans.begin(),ans.end());
        int idx = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<s.size() ; i++){
            if(s[i] == '?'){
                s[i] = ans[idx++];
            }
        }
        
        return s;

    }
};

[12/04/24, 1:55:41 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    string minimizeStringValue(string s) {
        priority_queue<pair<int,char>, vector<pair<int,char>>, greater<pair<int,char>>> pq;
        vector<int> f(26,0);
        for(char ch : s){
            if(ch != '?') f[ch -'a']++;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<26;i++){
            pq.push({f[i], i + 'a'});
        }
        string str = "";
        for(char ch : s){
            if(ch != '?'){
                str += ch;
            }
            else{
                str += pq.top().second;
                int freq = pq.top().first;
                char chr = pq.top().second;
                pq.pop();
                pq.push({freq+1,chr});
            }
        }
        string t = "";
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            if(s[i] == '?') t += str[i];
        }
        sort(t.begin(), t.end());
        int idx = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
            if(s[i] == '?'){
                str[i] = t[idx];
                idx++;
            }
        }
        return str;
    }
};

[12/04/24, 1:56:36 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int find(int i, vector<int> parent){
        if(parent[i] == i ) return i;
        return parent[i] = find(parent[i],parent);
    }
     void Union(int i, int j, vector<int>& parent,vector<int>& rank ){

        int l_i = find(i,parent);
        int l_j = find(j,parent);
        if(l_i == l_j) return ;
        int r_i = rank[l_i];
        int r_j = rank[l_j];
        if(r_i > r_j){
            parent[l_j] = l_i;
            rank[l_i]+=rank[l_j];
        }
        else{
            parent[l_i] = l_j;
            rank[l_j]+=rank[l_i];
        }
    }
    long long countPairs(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<int> parent(n);
        vector<int> rank(n);
        sort(edges.begin(),edges.end());
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            parent[i] = i;
            rank[i] = 1;
        }
        for(auto edge : edges ){
            int l_x = find(edge[0], parent);
            int l_y = find(edge[1],parent);
            if(l_x != l_y){
                 Union(edge[0],edge[1],parent,rank);
            }
        }
        unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            mpp[find(i,parent)]++;
        }
        vector<int> temp;
        for(auto& x : mpp){
            temp.push_back(x.second);
        }
        long long sum = 0;
        for(int &x : temp){
            sum += x * (n-x);
            n-=x;
        }
        return sum;
    }
};

[12/04/24, 8:33:22 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: vector<int> shortestPath(int n, int m, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        
        vector<vector<pair<int,int>>> adj(n+1);
        for(auto edge : edges){
            adj[edge[0]].push_back({edge[1],edge[2]}); 
            adj[edge[1]].push_back({edge[0],edge[2]});
        }
        unordered_map<int,int> parentMap;
        for(int i=1 ; i<=n ; i++) parentMap[i] = i;
        vector<int> distMap(n+1,INT_MAX);
        distMap[1] = 0;
        set<pair<int,int>> minheap; // <dist , node > 
        vector<int> explored(n+1,false);
        
        for(int i=1 ; i<=n ; i++){
            minheap.insert({distMap[i],i});
        }
        while(!minheap.empty()){
            pair<int,int> front_pair = *minheap.begin();
            minheap.erase(minheap.begin());
            int dist = front_pair.first;
            int vertex = front_pair.second;
            
            for( auto neighbour : adj[vertex]){
                int neighbour_node = neighbour.first;
                int wt = neighbour.second;
                if(!explored[neighbour_node] && distMap[neighbour_node] > dist + wt){
                    // now you need to relax this edge 
                    // deldete it from minheap 
                    auto it = minheap.find({distMap[neighbour_node], neighbour_node});
                    if (it != minheap.end()) {
                        minheap.erase(it);
                    }
                    // Insert the updated pair into minheap
                    minheap.insert({dist + wt, neighbour_node});
                    distMap[neighbour_node] = dist + wt;
                    parentMap[neighbour_node] = vertex;
                
            }
        }
            explored[vertex] = true;
        }
        // Code here
        vector<int> ans;
        int node = n;
        if(parentMap[node] == INT_MAX) return {-1};
        
        while(parentMap[node] != node){
            ans.push_back(node);
            node = parentMap[node];
        }
        // 2147483647 0 2 4 1 5 -2  size = n+1 = 6 
        ans.push_back(1);
        reverse(ans.begin(),ans.end());
        return ans;
    }
[12/04/24, 8:35:02 PM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> shortestPath(int n, int m, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n+1];
        
        for(auto it : edges){
            adj[it[0]].push_back({it[1],it[2]});
            adj[it[1]].push_back({it[0],it[2]});
        }
        
        vector<int> distMap(n+1, INT_MAX);
        distMap[1] = 0;
        vector<int> vis(n+1, 0);
        vector<int> parentMap(n+1);
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
            parentMap[i] = i;
        }
        priority_queue<pair<int,int>, vector<pair<int,int>>, greater<pair<int,int>>> pq;
        pq.push({0,1});   // <dist,node>
        
        while(!pq.empty()){
            int dist = pq.top().first;
            int node = pq.top().second;
            pq.pop();
            
            for(auto adjP : adj[node]){
                int neighbour = adjP.first;
                int edW = adjP.second;
                if(!vis[neighbour]){
                    vis[neighbour] = 1;
                    if(dist + edW < distMap[neighbour]){
                        distMap[neighbour] = dist + edW;
                        parentMap[neighbour] = node;
                        pq.push({distMap[neighbour], neighbour});
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        if(distMap[n] == INT_MAX) return {-1};
        vector<int> ans;
        int node = n;
        while(node != parentMap[node]){
            ans.push_back(parentMap[node]);
            node = parentMap[node];
        }
        ans.push_back(1);
        ans.push_back(distMap[n]);
        reverse(ans.begin(), ans.end());
        return ans;
    }
[12/04/24, 8:35:19 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: vector<int> shortestPath(int n, int m, int S, vector<vector<int>> &edges){
    vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n+1];

    for(auto it : edges){
        int u = it[0];
        int v = it[1];
        int wt = it[2];

        adj[u].push_back({v, wt});
        adj[v].push_back({u, wt});
    }

    vector<int> distMap(n+1, INT_MAX);
    distMap[S] = 0;
    priority_queue<pair<int,int> ,vector<pair<int,int>>, greater<pair<int,int>>> pq;
    pq.push({0,S}); // <dist, node>

    while(!pq.empty()){
        int node = pq.top.first;
        int dist = pq.top.second;
        pq.pop();

        for(auto it : adj[node]){
            int adjNode = it.first;
            int wt = it.second;

            if(dist + wt < distMap[adjNode]){
                distMap[adjNode] = dist + wt;
                pq.push({distMap[adjNode], adjNode});
            }
        }
    }
}
[12/04/24, 8:40:27 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: vector<int> shortestPath(int n, int m, int S, vector<vector<int>> &edges){
    vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n+1];

    for(auto it : edges){
        int u = it[0];
        int v = it[1];
        int wt = it[2];

        adj[u].push_back({v, wt});
        adj[v].push_back({u, wt});
    }

    vector<int> distMap(n+1, INT_MAX);
    distMap[S] = 0;
    priority_queue<pair<int,int> ,vector<pair<int,int>>, greater<pair<int,int>>> pq;
    pq.push({0,S}); // <dist, node>

    while(!pq.empty()){
        int node = pq.top.first;
        int dist = pq.top.second;
        pq.pop();

        for(auto it : adj[node]){
            int adjNode = it.first;
            int wt = it.second;

            if(dist + wt < distMap[adjNode]){
                distMap[adjNode] = dist + wt;
                pq.push({distMap[adjNode], adjNode});
            }
        }
    }
}

[14/04/24, 7:34:39 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

void solve(){
    int n, k;
    cin >> n >> k;

    vector<int> ships(n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++){
        cin >> ships[i];
    }
    
    int i = 0, j = n - 1;
    while (i <= j){
        if(i == j && ships[i] <= k){
            cout<<n<<endl;
            return;
        }
        int dest = min(ships[i], ships[j]);
        if (ships[i] < ships[j]){
            if (dest * 2 - 1 <= k){
                ships[i] = 0;
                ships[j] -= dest - 1;

                i++;
                if (ships[j] == 0) j--;
                k -= dest * 2 - 1;
            }
            else{
                cout << n - (j - i + 1) << endl;
                return;
            }
        }
        else{
            if (dest * 2 <= k){
                ships[i] -= dest;
                ships[j] = 0;

                if (ships[i] == 0) i++;
                j--;
                k -= dest * 2;
            }
            else{
                cout << n - (j - i + 1) << endl;
                return;
            }
        }
    }
    cout << n << endl;
    return;
}

int main(){
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    for (int i = 0; i < t; i++)
    {
        solve();
    }
}
[14/04/24, 7:46:05 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <unordered_map>
#include <climits>
using namespace std;

void solve() {
    int n, c, d, num;
    cin >> n >> c >> d;
    int a11 = INT_MAX;
    unordered_map<int, int> mp;

    for (int i = 0; i < n * n; i++) {
        cin >> num;
        mp[num]++;
        a11 = min(a11, num);
    }
    vector<vector<int> > v(n, vector<int>(n));
    v[0][0] = a11;
    mp[v[0][0]]--;
    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        v[i][0] = v[i - 1][0] + c;
        mp[v[i][0]]--;
        if (mp[v[i][0]] < 0) {
            cout << "NO" << endl;
            return;
        }
    }
    for (int j = 1; j < n; j++) {
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            v[i][j] = v[i][j - 1] + d;
            mp[v[i][j]]--;
            if (mp[v[i][j]] < 0) {
                cout << "NO" << endl;
                return;
            }
        }
    }
    cout<<"YES"<<endl;
}

int main() {
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    for (int i = 0; i < t; i++) {
        solve();
    }
}
[14/04/24, 7:46:16 AM] Satvik Saini: https://codeforces.com/contest/1955/problem/B
[14/04/24, 9:12:12 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int dx[4] = {-1, 1, 0, 0};
    int dy[4] = {0, 0, -1, 1};
    int f(int i, int j, vector<vector<int>>& arr,
          vector<vector<int>>& visited) {
        // base case
        if(i == arr.size()-1 && j == arr[0].size()-1){
            return 0;
        }

        if (i >= arr.size() || j >= arr[0].size() || i <= -1 || j <= -1 )
            return INT_MAX;

        if(visited[i][j] != -1) return visited[i][j];
        // recursive case
        int mini_Eff = INT_MAX;
        visited[i][j] = 1;
        for (int k = 0; k < 4; k++) {
            int nx = i + dx[k];
            int ny = j + dy[k];
            // find effort of this path
            if (nx >= 0 && nx < arr.size() && ny >= 0 && ny < arr[0].size() &&
                visited[nx][ny] == -1) {
                int Eff_temp = f(nx, ny, arr, visited);
                int Effort_curr_path =
                    max(Eff_temp, abs(arr[nx][ny] - arr[i][j]));
                mini_Eff = min(mini_Eff, Effort_curr_path);
            }
        }
        return visited[i][j] = mini_Eff;
    }
    int minimumEffortPath(vector<vector<int>>& heights) {
        vector<vector<int>> visited(heights.size(),
                                    vector<int>(heights[0].size(), -1));
        return f(0, 0, heights, visited);
    }
};
