[14/04/24, 9:21:43 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int minimumEffortPath(vector<vector<int>>& heights) {
        int n = heights.size();
        int m = heights[0].size();

        vector<vector<int>> diffMap(n, vector<int>(m, INT_MAX));
        diffMap[0][0] = 0;

        priority_queue<pair<int,pair<int,int>>, vector<pair<int,pair<int,int>>>, greater<pair<int,pair<int,int>>>> pq;

        pq.push({0,{0,0}});

        while(!pq.empty()){
            auto it = pq.top();
            pq.pop();

            int diff = it.first;
            int i = it.second.first;
            int j = it.second.second;

            vector<int> dx = {1, -1, 0, 0};
            vector<int> dy = {0, 0, 1, -1};

            for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
                int ii = i + dx[k];
                int jj = j + dy[k];

                if(ii>=0 && ii<n && jj>=0 && jj<m && max(diff, abs(heights[ii][jj] - heights[i][j])) < diffMap[ii][jj]){
                    diffMap[ii][jj] = max(diff, abs(heights[ii][jj] - heights[i][j]));
                    pq.push({diffMap[ii][jj],{ii,jj}});
                }
            }
        }

        return diffMap[n-1][m-1];
    }
};
[14/04/24, 9:24:53 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
    vector<vector<int>> dirs = {
                {-1,0},
        {0,-1},         {0,1},
                {1, 0}
    };
    bool isValid(vector<vector<int>>& heights, int mx) {
        queue<pair<int,int>> q;
        int ROWS = heights.size();
        int COLS = heights[0].size();
        
        vector<vector<bool>> seen(ROWS, vector<bool>(COLS, false));
        q.push({0,0});
        seen[0][0] = true;
        while(!q.empty()) {
            auto node = q.front();
            q.pop();
            int r = node.first;
            int c = node.second;
            if(r == ROWS - 1 && c == COLS - 1) return true;
            for(auto& dir : dirs) {
                int dr = dir[0] + r;
                int dc = dir[1] + c;
                if(dr < 0 || dr >= ROWS) continue;
                if(dc < 0 || dc >= COLS) continue;
                if(seen[dr][dc]) continue;
                if(abs(heights[r][c] - heights[dr][dc]) > mx) continue;
                seen[dr][dc] = true;
                q.push({dr, dc});
            }
        }
        
        return false;
    }
    
public:
    int minimumEffortPath(vector<vector<int>>& heights) {

        int L = 0;
        int R = INT_MAX;
        int best = INT_MAX;
        while(L <= R) {
            int M = L + (R-L) / 2;
            
            if(isValid(heights, M)) {
                R = M - 1;
                best = min(best, M);
            } else {
                L = M + 1;
            }
        }
        
        return best;
    }
};
[14/04/24, 9:32:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution
{
public:
    int dx[4] = {0, 0, -1, 1};
    int dy[4] = {1, -1, 0, 0};
    // we have defined the change in coordinate if they move in specific directions 

    bool isvalid(int x, int y, int n, int mid)
    {
        return (x >= 0 && x < n && y >= 0 && y < mid);
        // to check whether on which path we are moving is valid or not 
    }


    bool bfs(vector<vector<int>> heights, int k)
    {
        queue<pair<int, int>> q;
        // queue to perform the BFS logic 
        q.push({0, 0});
        // initially push the first cell of matrix 
        vector<vector<bool>> visited(101, vector<bool>(101, false));
        // make a visisted array initially with all the value false initially 
        visited[0][0] = 1;
        // since it visited , makr it a true  

        while (!q.empty())
        {
            pair<int, int> curr = q.front();
            // pick out the front 
            q.pop();
            int cx = curr.first;
            int cy = curr.second;
            // get the current x and y 
            if (cx == heights.size() - 1 && cy == heights[0].size() - 1)
                return true;
            // if we are reached the last index we are done
            // else just go in all 4 direction and check conditions  
            for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
            {
                int x = dx[i] + cx;
                int y = dy[i] + cy;
                // each time make new x , y 
                if (isvalid(x, y, heights.size(), heights[0].size()) && !visited[x][y])
                {
                    // if that x,y is valid , just check tah absolute difference is less tha tha mid or not 
                    if (abs(heights[cx][cy] - heights[x][y]) <= k)
                    {
                        visited[x][y] = true;
                        // if yes visit that node 
                        q.push({x, y});
                        // push it in queue 
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

    int minimumEffortPath(vector<vector<int>> &heights)
    {
        // we have similar binary search template  

        int low = 0;
        int high = 1e6;
        int ans = -1;

        // set high and low  

        while (low <= high)
        {
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
            // get a mid 
            // apply bfs over that mid value 
            if (bfs(heights, mid))
            {
                // if that bfs on that value return true , it might be our answer , so store it 
                ans = mid;
                high = mid - 1;
                // since we want want min value , high=mid-1
            }
            else
            {
                low = mid + 1;
                // else increase the value and check for it 
            }
        }
        return ans;
        //  return the ans 
    }
};

[15/04/24, 8:41:18 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
//the minimum possible sum of the values of the m subarrays nums is divided into. If it is not possible to divide nums into m subarrays satisfying these conditions, return -1.
    int f(int i,vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& andValues, int m ){
        //base case
        if(i == nums.size() && m == 0) {
            // you have finished elements but no ans 
            return 0;
        }
        if(i == nums.size() && m>0) return INT_MAX;
        if(m == 0) return INT_MAX;

        // recursive case
        // start to divide from i 
        int bit_ans = nums[i];
        cout<<"i:"<<i<<" ";
        int mini = INT_MAX;// sum of the values of the m subarrays nums is divided into
        for(int j = i ; j<nums.size() ; j++){
            cout<<j<<",";
            bit_ans = bit_ans & nums[j]; 
            if(bit_ans == andValues[i]){
                int x = f(j+1,nums,andValues, m-1);
                if(x != INT_MAX){
                mini = min(mini,nums[j] + x); // this is sum of the values of the m-1 subarrays nums is divided into
                }
            }
        }       
        return  mini;
    }
    int minimumValueSum(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& andValues) {
        return f(0,nums,andValues,andValues.size());
    }
}; ‎<This message was edited>

// solve function starts here

void solve(){
    string s;
    cin>>s;

    int cnt_A = 0, cnt_B = 0;
    int cnt_sub = 0, cnt_sub_B = 0;
    char prev = 'C';
    int len = 0;
    int f_len = INT_MAX;

    for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++){
        if(prev == 'A' && s[i] == 'B') cnt_sub++;
        if(prev == 'B' && s[i] == 'A') cnt_sub_B++;
        if(s[i] == 'A'){
            len++;
            cnt_A++;
            prev = 'A';
        }
        else{
            cnt_B++;
            f_len = min(f_len, len);
            prev = 'B';
            len = 0;
        }
    }
    if(s[s.length()-1] != 'B') cnt_sub++;
    if(s[s.length()-1] != 'A') cnt_sub_B++;
    if(s[0] == 'B' || s[s.length()-1] == 'B'){
        cout<<cnt_A<<endl;
        return;
    }
    if(cnt_B == 0){
        cout<<0<<endl;
        return;
    }
    if(cnt_sub != cnt_sub_B + 1){
        cout<<cnt_A<<endl;
    }
    else{
        cout<<cnt_A - f_len<<endl;
    }
}

// solve function ends here



// Main()  function
int main()
{
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    for(int i=0 ; i<t ; i++){
        solve();
    }
    
    return 0;
}

[16/04/24, 6:30:40 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎Voice call, ‎21 min
[16/04/24, 6:30:56 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left),
 * right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    TreeNode* addOneRow(TreeNode* root, int val, int depth) {
        if (depth == 1) {
            TreeNode* new_root = new TreeNode(val);
            new_root->left = root;
            return new_root;
        }
        // 46213
        queue<TreeNode*> q;
        q.push(root);
        int cnt = 0;
        bool flag = false;
        while (!q.empty()) {
            int n = q.size();
            while (n--) {
                TreeNode* front = q.front();
                q.pop();
                if (cnt == depth - 1) {
                    TreeNode* new_node_left = new TreeNode(val);
                    TreeNode* new_node_right = new TreeNode(val);
                    new_node_left->left = front->left;
                    new_node_right->right = front->right;
                    front->left = new_node_left;
                    front->right = new_node_right;
                    flag = true;

                } else {
                    if (front->right)
                        q.push(front->right);
                    if (front->left)
                        q.push(front->left);
                }
            }
            if(flag) break;
            cnt++;
        }
        return root;
        // go to depth - 1 node
    }
}; ‎<This message was edited>

[18/04/24, 6:28:41 PM] Satvik Saini: // approach : based on LIS
// first sort the envelopes in the order of increasing width and if the width is same, then sort the height in decreasing order
// eg : [2,3], [5,4], [6,7], [6,4]
// because we will be applying LIS code in the height of the envelopes
// if the width is same, then we want to pick the envelope with greater height bec there is a chance that an envelope with smaller height could not fit inside the prev envelope
// eg : [2,3], [5,4], [6,4], [6,7] here, [6,4] could not fit inside [5,4]

// time : O(nlogn)

class Solution {
public:
    static bool comparator(vector<int> &a, vector<int> &b){
        if(a[0] == b[0]){
            return a[1] > b[1];
        }
        return a[0] < b[0];
    }
    int maxEnvelopes(vector<vector<int>>& envelopes) {
        sort(envelopes.begin(), envelopes.end(), comparator);

        vector<int> ans;
        ans.push_back(envelopes[0][1]);

        for(int i=1;i<envelopes.size();i++){
            if(envelopes[i][1] > ans.back()){
                ans.push_back(envelopes[i][1]);
            }
            else{
                int idx = lower_bound(ans.begin(), ans.end(), envelopes[i][1]) - ans.begin();
                ans[idx] = envelopes[i][1];
            }
        }
        return ans.size();
    }
};
[18/04/24, 6:29:02 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: vector<int> lis;

            if(idx >= lis.size()) lis.push_back(ele);
            else lis[idx] = ele;
        }
        
        return lis.size();
    }

#pragma GCC optimization("Ofast")
#define ll long long
#define ld long double
#define nl '\n'
#define pill pair<ll, ll>
#define fs first
#define sc second
#define pb push_back
#define db(xx) cout<<#xx<<": "<<xx<<nl
#define dl(xx) cout<<#xx<<": "<<xx<<' '
#define rv return void
using namespace std;
//============================

void run(){
    ll k;
    cin>>k;
    vector<vector<ll>> v(k);
    ll cn = 0;
    map<ll,vector<pill>> mp;

    while(k--){
        cn++;
        ll n;
        cin>>n;
        ll sm = 0;
        ll a[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            cin>>a[i];

            sm+=a[i];
        }
        set<ll> st;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            if(st.count(a[i])) continue;
            st.insert(a[i]);
            mp[sm-a[i]].pb({cn,i+1});
        }
    }
    for(auto [sm,p]:mp){
        if(p.size()>1){
            cout<<"YES"<<nl;
            cout<<p[0].fs<<' '<<p[0].sc<<nl;
            cout<<p[1].fs<<' '<<p[1].sc<<nl;
            rv();
        }
    }
    cout<<"NO"<<nl;
}

//============================
int main()
{
#ifdef ONLINE_JUDGE
    cin.tie(0)->sync_with_stdio(0);
#endif
    run();
}

[19/04/24, 1:52:30 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int mod = (int)1e9 + 7;
    int f(int n, int k, int target, int j, vector<vector<int>> dp){
        // base case
        if(j == n){
            return !target;
        }
        if(target == 0) return 0;
        if(dp[j][target] != -1){
            return dp[j][target];
        }
        // recursive case
        int count = 0;
        for(int i=1 ; i<=k ; i++){      
            if(target - i >= 0 ){
                int x = f(n,k,target-i,j+1,dp); 
                count = (count + x)%mod;
                // cout<<x<<" ";
            }
        }
        return dp[j][target] = count%mod;
    }
    int numRollsToTarget(int n, int k, int target) {
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1,vector<int>(target+1 , -1));
        return f(n,k,target,0,dp)%mod;
        
    }
};

using namespace std;

/* TYPES  */
#define ll long long
#define pii pair<int, int>
#define pll pair<long long, long long>
#define vi vector<int>
#define vll vector<long long>

/* FUNCTIONS */
#define f(i,s,e) for(long long int i=s;i<e;i++)
#define cf(i,s,e) for(long long int i=s;i<=e;i++)
#define rf(i,e,s) for(long long int i=e-1;i>=s;i--)
#define pb push_back
#define eb emplace_back

#define NO cout<<"NO"<<endl

/* UTILS */
#define MOD 1000000007
#define PI 3.1415926535897932384626433832795
#define read(type) readInt<type>()
ll min(ll a,int b) { if (a<b) return a; return b; }
ll min(int a,ll b) { if (a<b) return a; return b; }
ll max(ll a,int b) { if (a>b) return a; return b; }
ll max(int a,ll b) { if (a>b) return a; return b; }
ll gcd(ll a,ll b) { if (b==0) return a; return gcd(b, a%b); }
ll lcm(ll a,ll b) { return a/gcd(a,b)*b; }
string to_upper(string a) { for (int i=0;i<(int)a.size();++i) if (a[i]>='a' && a[i]<='z') a[i]-='a'-'A'; return a; }
string to_lower(string a) { for (int i=0;i<(int)a.size();++i) if (a[i]>='A' && a[i]<='Z') a[i]+='a'-'A'; return a; }
bool prime(ll a) { if (a==1) return 0; for (int i=2;i<=round(sqrt(a));++i) if (a%i==0) return 0; return 1; }

void solve(){
    int n,k;
    cin>>n>>k;
    int temp[n];
    f(i,0,n){
        cin>>temp[i];
    }
    long double res = INT_MIN;
    f(z,k,n){
        long double sum = 0;
        f(i,0,z){
            sum += temp[i];
        }
        int i = 1, j = z;
        long double ans = sum/z;
        while(j < n){
            sum += temp[j];
            j++;
            sum -= temp[i];
            i++;
            ans = max(ans, sum/z);
        }
        res = max(res, ans);
    }
    cout<<res<<endl;
}

// Main()  function
int main() {

        solve();
    // }
    return 0;
}

[21/04/24, 9:03:34 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int longestEqualSubarray(vector<int>& A, int k) {
        int maxf = 0, i = 0, n = A.size();
        unordered_map<int, int> count;
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            maxf = max(maxf, ++count[A[j]]);
            if (j - i + 1 - maxf > k)
                --count[A[i++]];
        }
        return maxf;
    }
[21/04/24, 9:12:28 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-longest-equal-subarray/solutions/3933994/cpp-sliding-window-solution-with-explanation-notes/
[21/04/24, 9:13:14 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int helper(int mid,int k,vector<int>&nums)
    {
         int i=0,j=0;
          unordered_map<int ,int>check;
        while(j<nums.size()){
            if(check[nums[j]]+1>=mid)return true;
            check[nums[j]]+=1;
            if(j>= k+mid-1){
                check[nums[i]]-=1;
                i+=1;
            }
            j++;
        }
        return false;
    }
    int longestEqualSubarray(vector<int>& nums, int k) 
    {
        int s= 1 ,e = nums.size(),ans=0;
        while(s<=e)
        {
            int mid = (e-s)/2+s;
            if(helper(mid,k,nums))
            {
                ans=mid,s = mid+1;
            }
            else e=mid-1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

void solve(){
    int n;cin>>n;
    int a[n];
    int cnt = 0;
    int andd = 2^31 - 1;
    f(i,0,n){
        cin>>a[i];
        andd &= a[i];
        if(andd == 0){
            cout<<i<<" ";
            cnt++;
            andd = 2^31 - 1;
        }
    }cout<<endl;
    if(!cnt){
        cout<<1<<endl;
    }
    else cout<<cnt<<endl;
}

// Main()  function
int main() {
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    for(int i=0 ; i<t ; i++){
        solve();
    }
    return 0;
}

[23/04/24, 11:03:07 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ListNode* mergeSortedLinkedList(ListNode* head1, ListNode* head2) {

	// base case

	if (head1 == NULL) {
		// first LL is empty
		return head2;
	}

	if (head2 == NULL) {
		// second LL is empty
		return head1;
	}

	// recursive case

	ListNode* head;

	if (head1->val < head2->val) {

		head = head1;
		ListNode* headFromMyFriend = mergeSortedLinkedList(head1->next, head2);
		head->next = headFromMyFriend;

	} else {

		head = head2;
		ListNode* headFromMyFriend = mergeSortedLinkedList(head1, head2->next);
		head->next = headFromMyFriend;

	}


	return head;

}

[24/04/24, 6:33:56 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int minLengthAfterRemovals(vector<int>& nums) {
        int i=0;
        int j=0;
        int cnt = 0;
        while( j < nums.size()){
            if(nums[j] == nums[i]) cnt ++;
            else if(nums[j] > nums[i]) cnt --;
            j++;
            if(cnt == 0) i = j;
        }
        return j-i;
    }
};

[03/05/24, 11:35:32 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int maxSum(vector<int>& nums) {
        int arr[10][2];
        int maxi_sum = -1;
        for(int x : nums){
            int temp_num = x;
            int maxi_digit = 0;
            while(temp_num){
                int digit = temp_num%10;
                temp_num /=10;
                maxi_digit = max(maxi_digit, digit);
            }

            int a1 = arr[maxi_digit][0];
            int a2 = arr[maxi_digit][1];

            if(a1 < a2){
                if(a1 < x){
                    arr[maxi_digit][0] = x;
                }
            }
            else{
                if(a2 < x){
                    arr[maxi_digit][1] = x;
                }
            }
            
        }
        
        for(int i=0 ; i<=9 ; i++){
            if(arr[i][0] == 0 || arr[i][1] == 0) continue;
            maxi_sum = max(maxi_sum, arr[i][0] + arr[i][1]);
            cout<<arr[i][0]<<" "<<arr[i][1]<<endl;
        }
        return maxi_sum;
    }
};

[04/05/24, 8:33:48 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-possible-stable-binary-arrays-ii/description/
[04/05/24, 8:34:14 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int mod = 1000000007;
    int solve(int zero, int one, int limit, int prev, vector<vector<vector<int>>>& dp) {
        
        // Base case
        if (zero == 0 && one == 0) {
            return 1;
        }

        // Lookup
        if (dp[zero][one][prev+1] != -1) {
            return dp[zero][one][prev+1];
        }

        // Recursive case
        int ans = 0;
        
        if (prev != 0) {
            for (int i = 1; i <= limit; i++) {
                if(i > zero) break;
                ans = (ans + solve(zero - i, one, limit, 0, dp)) % mod;
            }
        }
        if (prev != 1) {
            for (int i = 1; i <= limit; i++) {
                if(i > one) break;
                ans = (ans + solve(zero, one - i, limit, 1, dp)) % mod;
            }
        }
        return dp[zero][one][prev+1] = ans % mod;
    } 

    
    int numberOfStableArrays(int zero, int one, int limit) {
      
        vector<vector<vector<int>>> dp(zero + 1, vector<vector<int>>(one + 1, vector<int>(3, -1)));
        return solve(zero, one, limit, -1, dp);
    }
};
[04/05/24, 8:37:15 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int mod = (int)1e9 + 7;
    int dp[201][201][201][2];
    int f(int zeros, int ones, int prev_cnt, int prev, int limit){
        
        if(!ones && !zeros) return 1;
        
        if(prev != -1 && dp[zeros][ones][prev_cnt][prev] != -1) return dp[zeros][ones][prev_cnt][prev];
            
        // recursive case
        int cnt = 0;
        if(prev == -1){
            if(zeros){
                // can place zero
                cnt = (cnt + f(zeros-1, ones, 1, 0, limit))%mod;
            }
            if(ones){
                // can place zero
                cnt = (cnt + f(zeros, ones-1, 1, 1, limit))%mod;
            }
            return cnt;
        }
        
        // now prev == 0
        if(prev == 0){
            
            // place 0 given previous is zero and you can place zero here 
            if(zeros && prev_cnt!=limit){
                cnt = (cnt + f(zeros-1, ones, prev_cnt+1, 0, limit))%mod;
            }
            // place 1 given previous is zero
            if(ones) cnt = (cnt + f(zeros, ones-1, 1, 1, limit))%mod;
            
            return dp[zeros][ones][prev_cnt][prev] = cnt;
            
        }
        
        // now prev == 1
        // place 1 given previous is one and you can place one here 
            if(ones && prev_cnt!=limit){
                cnt = (cnt + f(zeros, ones-1, prev_cnt+1, 1, limit))%mod;
            }
            // place zero given previous is one
            if(zeros) cnt = (cnt + f(zeros-1, ones, 1, 0, limit))%mod;
            
            return dp[zeros][ones][prev_cnt][prev] = cnt;
        
    }
    int numberOfStableArrays(int zero, int one, int limit) {
        memset(dp, -1, sizeof(dp));
        return (f(zero,one,0,-1,limit))%mod;
    }
};

[08/05/24, 10:48:49 AM] Satvik Saini: Disjoint –
The requirement of this constraint is that an entity should not belong to no more than one lower-level entity set. For example, the entity of student entity satisfy only one condition for student type attribute i.e. Either an entity can be a graduate or an undergraduate student, but cannot be both at the same time.
Overlapping –
In this category of generalizations, within a single generalization, the same entity may belong to more than one lower-level entity set. For example, in the employee work-team assume that certain employees participate in more than one work team. Thus, it offers a given employee that he may appear in more than one of the team entity sets that are lower-level entity sets of employee. Thus, generalization is overlapping.

[08/05/24, 7:51:10 PM] Satvik Saini: class cmp {
public:
    bool operator()(vector<int> &v1, vector<int> &v2){
        return v1[1] < v2[1];
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    int findMinArrowShots(vector<vector<int>>& points) {
        sort(points.begin(), points.end(), cmp());

        int endTime = points[0][1];
        int cnt = 1;

        for(int i=1;i<points.size();i++){
            if(points[i][0] > endTime){
                cnt++;
                endTime = points[i][1];
            }
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};
‎[08/05/24, 7:53:08 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎image omitted
[08/05/24, 7:54:46 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int findMinArrowShots(vector<vector<int>>& points) {
        sort(points.begin(), points.end(), [](vector<int>&i, vector<int>&j){
            if(i[0] == j[0]) return i[1] > j[1];
            return i[0] > j[0];
        });
        stack<pair<int, int> > stk;
        for(auto point : points ){
            stk.push({point[0], point[1]});
        }
        int cnt = 0;
        while(!stk.empty()){

            pair<int, int> curr_balloon = stk.top();
            int end = curr_balloon.second;
            cout<<curr_balloon.first<<" "<<end<<endl;
            stk.pop();
            while(!stk.empty() && stk.top().first <= end){
                stk.pop();
            }
            cnt++;
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};

[08/05/24, 8:17:26 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int findMinArrowShots(vector<pair<int, int>>& points) {
        int count = 0, minEnd = INT_MAX;
        sort(points.begin(), points.end());
        for(auto& p: points) {
            if(p.first > minEnd) {count++; minEnd = p.second;}
            else minEnd = min(minEnd, p.second);
        }
        return count + !points.empty();
    }
[08/05/24, 8:17:48 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: wefwfe
[08/05/24, 8:17:49 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: efrvear

[08/05/24, 8:20:43 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: int eraseOverlapIntervals(vector<Interval>& intervals) {
        int total = 0, minEnd = INT_MIN, overNb = 1;
        sort(intervals.begin(), intervals.end(), [&](Interval& inter1, Interval& inter2) {return inter1.start < inter2.start;});
        for(auto& p: intervals) {
            if(p.start >= minEnd) {
                total += overNb-1;
                overNb = 1;
                minEnd = p.end;
            }
            else {
                overNb++;
                minEnd = min(minEnd, p.end);
            }
        }
        return total + overNb-1;
    }
[08/05/24, 8:21:55 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: For example, for the problem Minimum "Number of Arrows to Burst Balloons", we have

Sort balloons in increasing order of the start position.
Scan the sorted pairs, and maintain a pointer for the minimum end position for current "active balloons", whose diameters are overlapping.
When the next balloon starts after all active balloons, shoot an arrow to burst all active balloons, and start to record next active balloons.

[12/06/24, 11:05:24 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/integer-replacement/description/
[12/06/24, 11:07:02 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int integerReplacement(int n) {
        int cnt = 0;
        while(n != 1){
            cout<<n<<" ";
            cnt++;
            if(n % 2 == 0){
                n /= 2;
                continue;
            }
            int m = n - 1;
            if((m & (m-1)) == 0){
                n--;
                continue;
            }
            m = n + 1;
            if((m & (m-1)) == 0) n++;
            else n--;
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};

[12/06/24, 11:16:47 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int integerReplacement(int num) {
        int cnt = 0;
        long long n = num;
        while(n!=1){
            if(n&1){
                int p = __builtin_popcountll(n);
                int np = __builtin_popcountll(n+1);
                if(np<p and n!=3){
                    n++;
                }else{
                    n--;
                }
            }else{
                n/=2;
            }
            cnt++;
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};
[12/06/24, 11:24:38 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    // We have to reach to 1 so most favourable thing will be divide by 2.
    // But we can perform it only when n is even.

    int integerReplacement(int n) {
        if(n==INT_MAX)// Here if (n+1) becomes(2^31) then need to return 32.
            return 32;
        
        int ans=0;
        while(n>1){
            if(n%2==0){// If even then directly divide by 2.
                ans++;
                n/=2;
            }
            else if(n==3){
                // We have to specially handle this as 3->2->1 is good 
                // than 3->4->2->1.
                ans+=2;
                break;
            }
            else{
                ans+=2;
                // Here two operation will be done first add/sub and then divide.

                // need to check whether who among these will be divisible of 2.

                // ex - for 23 need to check whether (23+1)/2 == 12 or
                // (23-1)/2 == 11 is divisible by 2.
                
                if(((n+1)/2)%2 == 0)
                    n = (n+1)/2;
                else if(((n-1)/2)%2 == 0)
                    n = (n-1)/2;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[12/06/24, 11:26:26 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/integer-replacement/solutions/87948/python-o-log-n-time-o-1-space-with-explanation-and-proof/
[12/06/24, 11:29:24 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int integerReplacement(int n) {
        int dp[n + 1]; memset(dp, 0, sizeof(dp));
        for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
            dp[i] = 1 + (i & 1 == 0 ? dp[i / 2] : min(dp[i - 1], 1 + dp[i / 2 + 1]));
        }
        return dp[n];
}
[12/06/24, 11:30:41 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/find-a-value-of-a-mysterious-function-closest-to-target/description/
[12/06/24, 11:33:02 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/find-subarray-with-bitwise-and-closest-to-k/description/
[12/06/24, 11:40:10 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int closestToTarget(vector<int>& arr, int target) {
        int best = INT_MAX, runner = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < arr.size(); ++i) {
            runner &= arr[i];
            best = min(best, abs(runner-target));
            if (runner < target){
                runner = arr[i];
                best = min(best, abs(runner-target));
            }
        }
        runner = -1;
        for (int i = arr.size()-1; i >= 0; --i) {
            runner &= arr[i];
            best = min(best, abs(runner-target));
            if (runner < target){
                runner = arr[i];
                best = min(best, abs(runner-target));
            }
        }
        return best;
    }
};
[12/06/24, 11:40:17 AM] Satvik Saini: ye badiya soln n us q ka
[12/06/24, 11:40:33 AM] Satvik Saini: sliding window approach
[12/06/24, 11:46:12 AM] Satvik Saini: // Sliding window approach
// time : O(n)
// space : O(1)

// Move through the array with a runner that gets subsequently ANDed with each element (and reset at times).
// Realize that as you do this:

// the sequence of values runner takes is non-increasing (until reset)
// thus, once runner < target, you can not get closer to target by moving forward more. So reset and slide the window.

// But note that the above description results in edge cases where you want to 'reset' your runner without having gone below target. 
// However, it turns out that running the same algorithm from the other end captures those cases.

class Solution {
public:
    int closestToTarget(vector<int>& arr, int target) {
        int ans = INT_MAX, runner = -1; // 1111111111
        for(int i=0;i<arr.size();i++){
            runner &= arr[i];
            ans = min(ans, abs(target - runner));

            if(runner < target){
                runner = arr[i];
                ans = min(ans, abs(target - runner));
            }
        }

        runner = -1;

        for(int i=arr.size()-1;i>=0;i--){
            runner &= arr[i];
            ans = min(ans, abs(target - runner));

            if(runner < target){
                runner = arr[i];
                ans = min(ans, abs(target - runner));
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

‎[12/06/24, 12:03:49 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎image omitted
[12/06/24, 10:58:05 PM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎5 sec
[13/06/24, 7:54:19 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/can-i-win/
[13/06/24, 7:54:24 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int dp[1<<20];
    bool win(int M, int total, int K){
        // base case
        if(total <= 0) return 0;

        // lookup
        if(dp[K] != -1) return dp[K];

        // recursive case
        for(int i=0;i<M;i++){
            if(!(K & (1<<i)) && !win(M, total-(i+1), K | (1<<i))){
                return dp[K] = 1;
            }
        }
        return dp[K] = 0;
    }
public:
    bool canIWin(int maxInt, int total) {
        if(total == 0) return 1;
        int t = maxInt*(maxInt+1)/2;
        if(t < total) return 0;
        if(t == total) return maxInt%2;
        memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
        return win(maxInt, total, 0);
    }
};

[16/06/24, 5:51:15 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-total-reward-using-operations-i/
[16/06/24, 5:52:41 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int dp[2001][4000];
    int reward(vector<int>& rewardValues, int i, int rew){
        //base case
        if(i == rewardValues.size()) return rew;
        
        //lookup
        if(dp[i][rew] != -1) return dp[i][rew];
        
        //recursive case
        int pick = 0;
        if(rew < rewardValues[i]){
            pick = reward(rewardValues, i+1, rew+rewardValues[i]);
        }
        int notPick = reward(rewardValues, i+1, rew);
        
        return dp[i][rew] = max(pick, notPick);
    }
public:
    int maxTotalReward(vector<int>& rewardValues) {
        sort(rewardValues.begin(), rewardValues.end());
        memset(dp, -1, sizeof(dp));
        return reward(rewardValues, 0, 0);
    }
};
[16/06/24, 5:54:10 PM] Satvik Saini: Lets say the last element we picked is X.
The max possible value of reward before that is X-1.
This implies max possible reward is X + (X-1) = 2*X-1.
Since max value of X is 2000, so the max value of reward is 3999.
[16/06/24, 5:54:45 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int maxi = 0;
    void f(int i, int x, vector<int>& arr ){
        if(i == arr.size() ){
            maxi = max(maxi,x);
            return ;
        }
        if(arr[i] > x){
            f(i+1,x+arr[i],arr);
        }
        f(i+1,x,arr);
    }
    int maxTotalReward(vector<int>& a) {
        sort(a.begin(),a.end());
        f(0,0,a);
        return maxi;
    }
};
[16/06/24, 5:58:56 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int maxi = 0;
    int dp[2001][4000];
    void f(int i, int x, vector<int>& arr ){
        if(i == arr.size() ){
            maxi = max(maxi,x);
            return ;
        }
        if(dp[i][x] != -1) return;
        if(arr[i] > x){
            f(i+1,x+arr[i],arr);
        }
        f(i+1,x,arr);
        dp[i][x] = 1;
    }
    int maxTotalReward(vector<int>& a) {
        sort(a.begin(),a.end());
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        f(0,0,a);
        return maxi;
    }
};
[16/06/24, 5:59:48 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int maxTotalReward(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size(), m;
        bitset<2000> a, b;
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        if(n==1 || nums[0]==nums[n-1])
            return nums[0];
        a.set(0);
        b.set(nums[0]);
        for(int i=1, j=0; i<n; ++i) {
            if(nums[i-1]==nums[i])
                continue;
            for(; j<nums[i]; ++j) {
                if(b.test(j))
                    a.set(j);
            }
            b|=a<<nums[i];
        }
        for(m=nums[n-1]-1; !a.test(m); --m) {}
        return m+nums[n-1];
    }
};

[17/06/24, 9:28:55 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-total-damage-with-spell-casting/description/
[17/06/24, 9:29:10 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    long long damage(vector<int>& power, unordered_map<int,long long> &mp, int i, int prev, vector<long long> &dp){
        //base case
        if(i == power.size()) return 0;

        //lookup
        if(dp[prev+1] != -1) return dp[prev+1];

        //recursive case
        //pick
        long long pick = 0;
        if(prev == -1 || power[i] > power[prev] + 2){
            pick = power[i]*mp[power[i]] + damage(power, mp, i+1, i, dp);
        }
        long long notPick = damage(power, mp, i+1, prev, dp);

        return dp[prev+1] = max(pick, notPick);
    }
public:
    long long maximumTotalDamage(vector<int>& power) {
        unordered_map<int,long long> mp;
        for(int p : power){
            mp[p]++;
        }
        vector<int> upower;
        for(auto p : mp){
            upower.push_back(p.first);
        }
        int n = upower.size();
        sort(upower.begin(), upower.end());
        vector<long long> dp(n+1,-1);

        return damage(upower, mp, 0, -1, dp);
    }
};
[17/06/24, 9:40:03 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
#define ll long long 
private:
    ll getMaxDamage(vector<ll>& dp, map<int, int>& frequencyMap, vector<int>& uniquePowers, int index) {
        if (index == uniquePowers.size()) return 0;
        if (dp[index] != -1) return dp[index];
        // Option 1: Skip the current element
        ll skip = getMaxDamage(dp, frequencyMap, uniquePowers, index + 1);
        // Option 2: Take the current element
        ll take = 0;
        int nextIndex = index + 1;
        while (nextIndex < uniquePowers.size() && uniquePowers[nextIndex] - uniquePowers[index] <= 2) {
            nextIndex++;
        }
        take = ((1ll)*frequencyMap[uniquePowers[index]] * uniquePowers[index]) + getMaxDamage(dp, frequencyMap, uniquePowers, nextIndex);
        return dp[index] = max(take, skip);
    }
public:
    long long maximumTotalDamage(vector<int>& power) {
        map<int, int> frequencyMap;
        vector<int> uniquePowers;
        // Create frequency map and unique powers list
        for (auto p : power) {
            frequencyMap[p]++;
        }
        for (auto it : frequencyMap) {
            uniquePowers.push_back(it.first);
        }
        // Initialize DP array with -1
        vector<ll> dp(frequencyMap.size(), -1);
        // Start the recursive function
        return getMaxDamage(dp, frequencyMap, uniquePowers, 0);
    }
};
[17/06/24, 9:47:51 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: long long maximumTotalDamage(vector<int>& power) {
    long long dp[100001] = {0}, max_dp = 0;
    sort(begin(power), end(power));
    for (int i = 0, j = 0; i < power.size(); ++i)        
        if (power[i] == power[max(0, i - 1)])
            dp[i + 1] = power[i] + dp[i];
        else {
            while(power[j] + 2 < power[i])
                max_dp = max(max_dp, dp[++j]);
            dp[i + 1] = power[i] + max_dp;
        }
    return *max_element(begin(dp), begin(dp) + power.size() + 1);
}
[17/06/24, 9:49:55 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: long long maximumTotalDamage(vector<int>& power) {
    deque<array<long long, 2>> dp{{0, 0}};
    long long max_dp = 0;
    sort(begin(power), end(power));
    for (int p : power)
        if (p == dp.back()[1])
            dp.back() = {p + dp.back()[0], p};
        else {
            while(!dp.empty() && dp.front()[1] + 2 < p) {
                max_dp = max(max_dp, dp.front()[0]);
                dp.pop_front();
            }
            dp.push_back({p + max_dp, p});
        }
    return (*max_element(begin(dp), end(dp)))[0];
}

[19/06/24, 4:59:16 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    bool increasingTriplet(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> sm_left(n);
        vector<int> lg_right(n);
        sm_left[0] = lg_right[n-1] = -1;

        int mini = nums[0];
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i] > mini) sm_left[i] = mini;
            else sm_left[i] = -1;
            mini = min(mini, nums[i]);
        }
        int maxi = nums[n-1];
        for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){
            if(nums[i] < maxi) lg_right[i] = mini;
            else lg_right[i] = -1;
            maxi = max(maxi, nums[i]);
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            cout<<sm_left[i]<<" ";
        }cout<<endl;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            cout<<lg_right[i]<<" ";
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(sm_left[i] != -1 && lg_right[i] != -1) return 1; 
        }
        return 0;
    }
};
[19/06/24, 5:00:26 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    bool increasingTriplet(std::vector<int>& nums) {
        if (nums.size() < 3) {
            return false;
        }
        int a = INT_MAX;
        int b = INT_MAX;

        for (int num : nums) {
            if (num <= a) {
                a = num;
            } else if (num <= b) {
                b = num;
            } else {
                return true;
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
};
[19/06/24, 5:06:53 PM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long
class Solution {
public:
    bool increasingTriplet(vector<int>& nums) {
        ll n=nums.size();
        vector<int>pre(n),suff(n);
        pre[0]=nums[0];
        suff[n-1]=nums[n-1];
        for(ll i=1;i<n;i++)
        {
            pre[i]=min(pre[i-1],nums[i]);
        }
        for(ll i=n-2;i>=0;i--)
        {
            suff[i]=max(suff[i+1],nums[i]);
        }
        for(ll i=1;i<n-1;i++)
        {
            if(pre[i-1]<nums[i] && nums[i]<suff[i+1])
           {
               return 1;
           }
        }
        return 0;
    }
};

[22/06/24, 8:53:19 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int numberOfSubarrays(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        vector<int> OddIdx;
        for(int i=0 ; i < nums.size() ; i++) {
            if(nums[i]%2) OddIdx.push_back(i);
        }
        int cnt = 0;
        int i=0;
        for(int j=0 ; j < nums.size() ; j++){

            if(nums[j]%2) k--;

            while(k < 0){
                if(nums[i]%2) k++;
                i++;
            }

            if(k == 0){
                auto x = lower_bound(OddIdx.begin(), OddIdx.end(), i);
                if(x != OddIdx.end()) cnt += *x - i + 1;
            }
        }
        return cnt;

    }
};

        for(int ele : nums){
            sum += ele;
            ans = max(ans, sum);
            if(sum < 0) sum = 0;
        }
[22/06/24, 8:59:23 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/sliding-window-maximum/
[22/06/24, 9:00:01 AM] Satvik Saini: // Brute Force : O(n^2)
// go on each window (O(n)) and find the max element (O(n))

// Using priority queue : O(nlogk)
// firstly, push k elements into the pq, then pop the first element of the
// window (O(logk)) and add the last element of the new window (O(logk))

// Optimal Approach
// using deque

// dq is storing the inidices and not the value

// whenever we expand our window, then if nums[i] is greater than the elements present in the dq from the back, then pop_back till we get a greater element
// this is becuase the smaller elements before it is of no use since we got a greater element in the right
// now, there maybe a case that no element is smaller than nums[i], then the window size will be k+1
// at this point, dq.front() = i - k, thus we need to pop_front since this element is from the prev window
// now add the front element which is always the max element in the window to the ans vector only when once i has reached k-1,
// because before the we have not traversed the whole window only

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> maxSlidingWindow(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        vector<int> ans;
        deque<int> dq;

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            while (!dq.empty() && nums[dq.back()] <= nums[i]) {
                dq.pop_back();
            }
            dq.push_back(i);
            if (dq.front() == i - k) {
                dq.pop_front();
            }
            if (i >= k - 1) {
                ans.push_back(nums[dq.front()]);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[22/06/24, 9:07:43 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: 1 2 3 4 5 -1 -2
[22/06/24, 9:08:11 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: k = 3
[22/06/24, 10:46:45 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/multiply-strings/
[22/06/24, 10:46:57 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎12 sec
[22/06/24, 10:47:17 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    string multiply(string num1, string num2) {
        int carry = 0;
        int idx = num1.length()-1;
        vector<string> v(num2.length());
        int v_idx = 0;
        while(num2.length() != 0){
            if(idx == -1){
                idx = num1.length()-1;
                v_idx++;
                num2.pop_back();
            }
            int n1 = num1[idx]-'0';
            int n2 = num2.back()-'0';
            int num = (n1*n2) + carry;
            v[v_idx] += to_string(num%10);
            carry = num/10;
            idx--;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<num2.length();i++){
            reverse(v[i].begin(), v[i].end());
            cout<<v[i]<<endl;
        }
        return "";
    }
};

[23/06/24, 10:39:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int uniquePaths(int m, int n) {
        long ans = 1;
        for(int i = m+n-2, j = 1; i >= max(m, n); i--, j++) 
            ans = (ans * i) / j;
        return ans;
    }
};
[23/06/24, 10:39:19 AM] Satvik Saini: void printNcR(int n, int r)
{
    long long p = 1, k = 1;
    if (n - r < r)
        r = n - r;
 
    if (r != 0) {
        while (r) {
            p *= n;
            k *= r;
            long long m = __gcd(p, k);
            p /= m;
            k /= m;
 
            n--;
            r--;
        }
    }
    else p = 1;
    cout << p << endl;
}

[23/06/24, 1:40:33 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: You are given an integer array nums with length n.

The cost of a 
subarray
 nums[l..r], where 0 <= l <= r < n, is defined as:

cost(l, r) = nums[l] - nums[l + 1] + ... + nums[r] * (−1)r − l

Your task is to split nums into subarrays such that the total cost of the subarrays is maximized, ensuring each element belongs to exactly one subarray.

Formally, if nums is split into k subarrays, where k > 1, at indices i1, i2, ..., ik − 1, where 0 <= i1 < i2 < ... < ik - 1 < n - 1, then the total cost will be:

cost(0, i1) + cost(i1 + 1, i2) + ... + cost(ik − 1 + 1, n − 1)

Return an integer denoting the maximum total cost of the subarrays after splitting the array optimally.

Note: If nums is not split into subarrays, i.e. k = 1, the total cost is simply cost(0, n - 1).
[23/06/24, 1:40:44 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Example 1:

Input: nums = [1,-2,3,4]

Output: 10

Explanation:

One way to maximize the total cost is by splitting [1, -2, 3, 4] into subarrays [1, -2, 3] and [4]. The total cost will be (1 + 2 + 3) + 4 = 10.

Example 2:

Input: nums = [1,-1,1,-1]

Output: 4

Explanation:

One way to maximize the total cost is by splitting [1, -1, 1, -1] into subarrays [1, -1] and [1, -1]. The total cost will be (1 + 1) + (1 + 1) = 4.

Example 3:

Input: nums = [0]

Output: 0

Explanation:

We cannot split the array further, so the answer is 0.

Example 4:

Input: nums = [1,-1]

Output: 2

Explanation:

Selecting the whole array gives a total cost of 1 + 1 = 2, which is the maximum.

 

Constraints:

1 <= nums.length <= 105
-109 <= nums[i] <= 109

[23/06/24, 1:59:23 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: -> This problem is similar to take not take dp the only twist
it that we have to take all the elements but we can change their sign based on the previous element.
-> Here we are using f variable to check if we can change the sign of the current element or not (i.e if the previous element was changed than the current element cannot be changed).
-> We cannot change the first element therefore we have just added it to the answer.

Approach
Complexity
Time complexity:
Space complexity:
Code
class Solution {
    private:
    typedef long long ll;
    vector<vector<ll>> dp;
    ll n;
    ll func(vector<int>&nums,int id,int f){
        if(id>=n) return 0;
        if(dp[id][f]!=-1) return dp[id][f];
         ll take = -1e15,ntake = -1e15;
        if(f==1){
            ntake = (-nums[id])+func(nums,id+1,0);
        }
        take = nums[id]+func(nums,id+1,1);
        return dp[id][f] = max(take,ntake);
    }
public:
    long long maximumTotalCost(vector<int>& nums) {
        n = nums.size();
        dp.resize(n+1,vector<ll>(3,-1));
        return nums[0]+func(nums,1,1);
        
    }
};

        long long pos = -1e15, neg = 0, tmp;
        for (int a : A) {
            tmp = neg;
            neg = pos - a;
            pos = max(pos, tmp) + a;
        }
        return max(pos, neg);
    }

[23/06/24, 5:54:11 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    typedef long long ll;
    vector<vector<ll>> dp;
    long long maximumTotalCost(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        dp.resize(n+1,vector<ll>(2,0));
        // ll ans = -1e15;
        int dpI0 = 0;
        int dpI1 = 0;
        for(int i = nums.size()-1 ; i>=0 ; i--){
            // sign = 1 : you take -ve now : prev was +ve 
            // sign = 0 : you take positive : prev was -ve 
            // continue the prev 
            for(int sign = 0 ; sign <= 1 ; sign++){
                ll continue_sub = -1e15;
                if(sign == 1){
                    continue_sub =  -nums[i] + dpI0;
                }
                // start a new subarray 
                ll start_new = nums[i] + dpI1;

                if(sign == 0) dpI0 = max(continue_sub , start_new);
                else dpI1 = max(continue_sub , start_new);
            }
        }
        return dpI0;
    }
};
[23/06/24, 5:54:23 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    typedef long long ll;
    vector<vector<ll>> dp;
    long long maximumTotalCost(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        dp.resize(n+1,vector<ll>(2,0));
        // ll ans = -1e15;
        for(int i = nums.size()-1 ; i>=0 ; i--){
            // sign = 1 : you take -ve now : prev was +ve 
            // sign = 0 : you take positive : prev was -ve 
            // continue the prev 
            for(int sign = 0 ; sign <= 1 ; sign++){
                ll continue_sub = -1e15;
                if(sign == 1){
                    continue_sub =  -nums[i] + dp[i+1][0];
                }
                // start a new subarray 
                ll start_new = nums[i] + dp[i+1][1];

                dp[i][sign] = max(continue_sub , start_new);
            }
        }
        return dp[0][0];
    }
};

[24/06/24, 10:31:00 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector<int>& nums) {
        queue<int> q;
        int flips = 0;
        
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            while(!q.empty() && q.front() + 2 < i){
                q.pop();
            }
            int num = (nums[i] + q.size()) % 2;
            if(num == 0){
                if(i + 3 > nums.size()) return -1;
                flips++;
                q.push(i);
            }
        }
        return flips;
    }
};
[24/06/24, 10:32:00 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector<int>& nums) {
        int cnt = 0;
        int j=0;
        while(j <= nums.size()-3){
            if(nums[j] == 0){
                cnt++;
                for(int i = j ; i <= j+2 ; i++){
                    if(i < nums.size()){
                        nums[i] = nums[i] ? 0 : 1;
                    }
                }
            }
            j++;
        }
        for(int i=nums.size()-1 ; i>=0 ; i--)if(nums[i] == 0) return -1;
        return cnt;
    }
};
[24/06/24, 10:33:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector<int>& nums) {
        int fc = 0;
        int j=0;
        while(j < nums.size()){
            if(fc % 2 && nums[j] == 1){
                fc++;
            }
            else if(fc % 2 == 0 && nums[j] == 0){
                fc++;
            }
            j++;
        }
        return fc;
    }
};

[25/06/24, 9:42:51 AM] Satvik Saini: int maxi(vector<vector<int>> mat, int i, int j){
    return max(mat[i-1][j],max(mat[i][j-1],max(mat[i+1][j],mat[i][j+1])));
}

void solve(){
    int n,m;
    cin>>n>>m;
    vector<vector<int>> mat(n+2, vector<int>(m+2, INT_MIN));
    f(i,1,n+1){
        f(j,1,m+1){
            cin>>mat[i][j];
        }
    }
    set<pair<int,int>> st;
    // vector<int> dx = {0,0,1,-1};
    // vector<int> dy = {1,-1,0,0};

    f(i,1,n+1){
        f(j,1,m+1){
            if(mat[i][j] > maxi(mat,i,j)){
                st.insert({i,j});
            }
        }
    }

    while(!st.empty()){
        pair<int,int> p = *st.begin();
        st.erase(p);
        int i = p.first, j = p.second;
        mat[i][j] -= maxi(mat,i,j);

}

void solve(){
    int n,m;
    cin>>n>>m;
    vector<vector<int>> mat(n+2, vector<int>(m+2, INT_MIN));
    f(i,1,n+1){
        f(j,1,m+1){
            cin>>mat[i][j];
        }
    }

    f(i,1,n+1){
        f(j,1,m+1){
            if(mat[i][j] > maxi(mat,i,j)){
                mat[i][j] = maxi(mat,i,j);
            }
        }
    }

    f(i,1,n+1){
        f(j,1,m+1){
            cout<<mat[i][j]<<" ";
        }
        cout<<endl;
    }
    cout<<endl;
}

[26/06/24, 10:36:04 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <climits>
double avg = INT_MIN;

int calc_avg(TreeNode<int> *root, int &count) {
    // base case
    if (root == NULL) return 0;

    // recursive case
    int lcount = 0, rcount = 0;

    int lsum = calc_avg(root->left, lcount);
    int rsum = calc_avg(root->right, rcount);
    double sum = lsum + rsum + root->data;
    count = lcount + rcount + 1;
    avg = max(avg, sum/count);
    return sum;
}
double maxSubtreeAverage(TreeNode<int> *root) {
    int count = 0;
    calc_avg(root, count);
    return avg;
}
[26/06/24, 10:38:10 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: pair<int,int> f(TreeNode<int> *root){
    if(root == NULL) return {0,0};
    // recursive case
    pair<int,int> l = f(root->left);
    pair<int,int> r = f(root->right);
    // sum , no of nodes
    int sum = l.first + r.first + root -> data;
    int n = l.second + r.second + 1;
    if(l.second != 0) maxi = (double)max(l.first/l.second*1.0,maxi);
    if(r.second != 0) maxi = (double)max(r.first*1.0/r.second,maxi);
    maxi = (double)max(maxi, sum*1.0/n );
    return {sum,n};


}

[26/06/24, 10:50:58 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <climits>
#include <queue>

vector<int> shortestAlternateColoredPath(int n, vector<vector<int>>& redEdges, vector<vector<int>>& blueEdges) 
{
    vector<vector<int>> Radj(n);
    vector<vector<int>> Badj(n);

    for(auto v : redEdges){
        Radj[v[0]].push_back(v[1]);
    }
    for(auto v : blueEdges){
        Badj[v[0]].push_back(v[1]);
    }

    vector<int> redDist(n, INT_MAX);
    vector<int> blueDist(n, INT_MAX);

    redDist[0] = 0;
    blueDist[0] = 0;

    queue<pair<int, char>> q;    // {node,color}
    q.push({0, 'R'});
    q.push({0, 'B'});

    while(!q.empty()){
        int node = q.front().first;
        char color = q.front().second;
        q.pop();

        if(color == 'R'){
            for(auto adjNode : Badj[node]){
                if(redDist[node] + 1 < blueDist[adjNode]){
                    blueDist[adjNode] = redDist[node] + 1;
                    q.push({adjNode, 'B'});
                }
            }
        }
        else {
            for(auto adjNode : Radj[node]){
                if(blueDist[node] + 1 < redDist[adjNode]){
                    redDist[adjNode] = blueDist[node] + 1;
                    q.push({adjNode, 'R'});
                }
            }
        }
    }

    vector<int> distMap(n);
    for(int i = 0; i < n; ++i){
        distMap[i] = min(redDist[i], blueDist[i]);
        if(distMap[i] == INT_MAX) distMap[i] = -1;
    }

    return distMap;
}

int LIS(vector<int> &arr, int i, int n, int prev, int last_idx, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
    // base case
    if(i%n == last_idx) return 0;

    // lookup
    if(dp[i%n][(prev+1)%n] != -1) return dp[i%n][(prev+1)%n];

    // recursive case
    // pick if possible
    int pick = 0;
    if(prev == -1 || arr[i%n] > arr[prev%n]){
        if(prev == -1) pick = 1 + LIS(arr, i+1, n, i, i, dp);
        else pick = 1 + LIS(arr, i+1, n, i, last_idx, dp);
    }
    int notPick = LIS(arr, i+1, n, prev, last_idx, dp);
    return dp[i%n][(prev+1)%n] = max(pick, notPick);
}

int lisInCircularManner(int n, vector<int> &arr) {

    vector<vector<int>> dp(n,vector<int>(n+1,-1));
    return LIS(arr,0,n,-1,n,dp);

}

[30/06/24, 1:25:49 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Ninja is fond of sequences. He has a set of numbers and wants to make minimum decreasing subsequences such that all numbers are part of exactly one subsequence. Can you help Ninja with this challenge?

You are given an array ‘ARR’ having ‘N’ elements.Your task is to divide all ‘N’ elements of the array into a minimum number of strictly decreasing subsequences. Each number can be in one subsequence only. Find the minimum number of such strictly decreasing subsequences.

For Example
If 'ARR' is [4,2,1,3] ,it can be splitted into two subsequences as [4,2,1] , [3] or [4,3],[2,1].
[30/06/24, 1:28:17 PM] Satvik Saini: int decreasingSubsequences(int n, vector<int> &arr) {
    vector<int> used(n, 0); // to track whether we can add any element next to arr[i] or not
    int ans = 0; // to store the number of subsequences

    // Set USED[i] as 1 for each index ‘i’ in range 0 to ‘N-1’
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        used[i] = 1;
    }

    // Process each index ‘i’ in range 0 to ‘N-1’
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        int index = -1;

        // For each index ‘j’ in range 0 to ‘i-1’
        for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
            if (used[j] == 1 && arr[j] > arr[i]) {
                if (index == -1) {
                    index = j;
                } else if (arr[i] - arr[j] < arr[i] - arr[index]) {
                    index = j;
                }
            }
        }

        if (index == -1) {
            // No suitable element found. We will put arr[i] into a new subsequence
            ans++;
        } else {
            used[index] = 0;
        }
    }

    return ans;
}

    if(dp[i%n][(prev+1)%n] != -1) return dp[i%n][(prev+1)%n];

[30/06/24, 1:50:41 PM] Satvik Saini: /*
    Time Complexity : O(N^2 * log(N))
    Space Complexity : O(N)

    Where, N is the size of the array.
*/

// Binary search function to find the lower bound.
int binarySearch(vector<int> &minElement, int n, int x)
{
    int l = 0, r = n, mid, ans = n;
    while (l <= r) {
        mid = (l + r) / 2;

        /*
            If the mid element is greater than x, update
            ans and search in the left half of the array.
        */
        if (minElement[mid] >= x) {
            ans = mid;
            r = mid - 1;
        }

        /*
            If the mid element is less than x,
            search in the right half of the array.
        */
        else {
            l = mid + 1;
        }
    }
    return ans;
}

int lisUsingBS(vector<int> &newArr, int index) {

    // take an integer len to store LIS for current element.
    int len = 0, n = newArr.size();
    vector<int> minElement(n);
    minElement[0] = newArr[0];

    // Iterate through the newArr vector.
    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {

        // If a greater value is found increment length.
        if (newArr[i] > minElement[len]) {
            len++;
            minElement[len] = newArr[i];
        }

        // Else update the small element into the minElement vector.
        else {

            // Find the lower bound of current element using binary search.
            int index = binarySearch(minElement, len, newArr[i]);

            // Update minElement array.
            minElement[index] = newArr[i];
        }
    }

    // Return the length of longest increasing sequence.
    return len + 1;
}

int lisInCircularManner(int n, vector<int> &arr) {

    // Take an integer to store the final answer.
    int answer = 0;

    // Iterate through the array to calculate LIS for every index.
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

        // Take a vector to store the elements from ith index.
        vector<int> newArr(n);
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            newArr[j] = arr[(i + j) % n];
        }

        // Function call.
        int lis = lisUsingBS(newArr, n);

        // Update the value of answer.
        answer = max(answer, lis);
    }
    return answer;
}
[01/07/24, 8:40:21 AM] Satvik Saini: https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/delete-and-score_2436719?leftPanelTabValue=PROBLEM
[01/07/24, 8:40:25 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <unordered_map>
#include <algorithm>

int score(vector<int> &arr, int i, int prev, unordered_map<int,int> &freq, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
    // base case
    if(i == arr.size()) return 0;

    // lookup
    if(dp[i][prev+1] != -1) return dp[i][prev+1]; 

    // recursive case
    // pick if possible
    int pick = 0;
    if(prev == -1 || arr[i] > arr[prev]+1){
        pick = freq[arr[i]]*arr[i] + score(arr,i+1,i,freq,dp);
    }
    int notPick = score(arr,i+1,prev,freq,dp);

    return dp[i][prev+1] = max(pick, notPick);
}

int findScore(int n, vector<int> &arr) 
{
    vector<int> v;
    unordered_map<int,int> freq;
    for(int ele : arr) freq[ele]++;

    for(auto p : freq) v.push_back(p.first);
    sort(v.begin(), v.end());
    int m = v.size();

    vector<vector<int>> dp(m, vector<int>(m+1,-1));

    return score(v,0,-1,freq,dp);
}
[01/07/24, 8:40:30 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎4 min
[01/07/24, 8:45:02 AM] Satvik Saini: int findScore(int n, vector<int> &arr) 
{
    // Intialize a variable maxN with a value 10001
    int maxN = 10001;
    
    // Initialize an integer array count of size maxN
    vector<int> dp(maxN, 0);

    // Iterate i in 0 to arr.length
    for (int i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++) 
    {
        dp[arr[i]] += arr[i];
    }

    // Iterate i in 2 to maxN
    for (int i = 2; i <= maxN; i++) 
    {
        dp[i] = max(dp[i - 1], dp[i - 2] + dp[i]);
    }

    // return dp[maxN - 1]
    return dp[maxN - 1];
}

[01/07/24, 11:22:44 AM] Satvik Saini: // If GCD(a, K) * GCD(b, K) is divisible by key, 
// then a * b should also be divisible by key.

#include <math.h>

long long pairProductDivByK(int n, int k, vector<int> &nums) {
    long long cnt = 0;
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    for(int ele : nums){
        int gcd = __gcd(ele,k);
        int x = k / gcd;
        for(auto p : mp){
            if(p.first % x == 0) cnt += p.second;
        }
        mp[gcd]++;
    }
    return cnt;
}

[01/07/24, 5:14:29 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Input:  s = "00110101"
Output: 3 
Explanation:

Here is one way to reverse the string in 3 operations:
    
          
00110101 - 00101011 (index 3 was appended at the end)

          
00101011 - 01010110 (index 0 was appended at the end)

          
01010110 - 10101100 (index 0 was appended at the end)

     
So the answer here is 3 operations.

[01/07/24, 5:26:54 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: public int reverseBinaryString(String s) {
    // write your code here
  StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(s);
  String t = sb.reverse().toString();
  int l = 0;
  int r = 0;
  int res = 0;
  while (l < s.length()) {
    if (s.charAt(l) != t.charAt(r)) {
      l++;
      res++;
    } else {
      l++;
      r++;
    }
  }
  return res;
}

[02/07/24, 10:28:40 AM] Satvik Saini: int maxSumRectangle(vector<vector<int>> arr) {
    int n = arr.size();
    int m = arr[0].size();
    int maxSum = 0;

    // Iterate over all pairs of rows
    for (int r1 = 0; r1 < n; r1++) {
        vector<int> temp(m, 0);

        for (int r2 = r1; r2 < n; r2++) {
            // Calculate the sum of elements between r1 and r2 rows for each column
            for (int c = 0; c < m; c++) {
                temp[c] += arr[r2][c];
            }

            // Apply Kadane's algorithm to find the maximum sum subarray in temp
            int currentMax = 0, currentSum = 0;
            for (int c = 0; c < m; c++) {
                currentSum += temp[c];
                currentMax = max(currentMax, currentSum);
                if (currentSum < 0) currentSum = 0;
            }
            maxSum = max(maxSum, currentMax);
        }
    }

    return maxSum;
}
[02/07/24, 10:37:54 AM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> nextPermutation(vector<int> &a, int n)
{
    priority_queue<int,vector<int>,greater<int>> pq;
    for(int i=n-1;i>0;i--){
        if(a[i-1] > a[i]) pq.push(i);
        else{
            pq.push(i);
            while(a[pq.top()] < a[i-1]) pq.pop();
            int j = pq.top();
            swap(a[i-1],a[j]);
            sort(a.begin()+i,a.end());
            return a;
        }
    }
    sort(a.begin(),a.end());
    return a;
}
[02/07/24, 10:47:53 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <bits/stdc++.h> 
vector<int> nextPermutation(vector<int> &a, int n)
{
    priority_queue<int,vector<int>,greater<int>> pq;
    for(int i=n-1;i>0;i--){
        pq.push(a[i]);
        if(a[i-1] < a[i]){
            while(a[pq.top()] < a[i-1])pq.pop();
            int j = pq.top();
            swap(a[i-1],a[j]);
            sort(a.begin()+i,a.end());
            return a;
        }
    }
    sort(a.begin(),a.end());
    return a;
}
[02/07/24, 10:49:54 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    void nextPermutation(vector<int>& arr) {
        int mini_idx = INT_MIN;
        for(int i=arr.size()-1 ; i>0 ;i--){
            if(arr[i]>arr[i-1]){
                mini_idx = i - 1;
                break;
            }
        }
        if(mini_idx == INT_MIN){
            reverse(arr.begin(),arr.end());
            return;
        }
        int i = mini_idx + 1;
        int curr_grt = arr[i];
        int just_grt = INT_MAX;
        int just_grt_idx = i;
        while(i<arr.size()){
            if(arr[i] > arr[mini_idx]){
                curr_grt = arr[i];
                if(curr_grt < just_grt){
                    just_grt = curr_grt;
                    just_grt_idx = i;
                }
            }  
            i++;
        }
        swap(arr[mini_idx],arr[just_grt_idx]);
        sort(arr.begin() + mini_idx +1 , arr.end());        
    }
};

[03/07/24, 8:23:18 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimize-the-maximum-difference-of-pairs/
[03/07/24, 8:23:30 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int minimizeMaxDiff(vector<int> &diff, int i, int p){
        // base case
        if(i >= diff.size() || p == 0) return INT_MIN;

        // recursive case
        int pick = max(diff[i], minimizeMaxDiff(diff, i+2, p-1));
        int notPick = minimizeMaxDiff(diff, i+1, p);

        return min(pick, notPick);
    }
public:
    int minimizeMax(vector<int>& nums, int p) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        vector<int> diff;
        for(int i=1;i<nums.size();i++){
            diff.push_back(nums[i] - nums[i-1]);
        }
        return minimizeMaxDiff(diff, 0, p);
    }
};

[03/07/24, 10:27:56 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: There are some processes that need to be executed. Amount of a load that process causes on a server that runs it, is being represented by a single integer. Total load caused on a server is the sum of the loads of all the processes that run on that server. You have at your disposal two servers, on which mentioned processes can be run. Your goal is to distribute given processes between those two servers in the way that, absolute difference of their loads will be minimized.

Given an array of n integers, of which represents loads caused by successive processes, return the minimum absolute difference of server loads.
[03/07/24, 10:28:20 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: Input:  loads = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
Output: 1 
Explanation:

We can distribute the processes with loads [1, 2, 4] to the first server and [3, 5] to the second one, so that their total loads will be 7 and 8, respectively, and the difference of their loads will be equal to 1.
[03/07/24, 11:03:34 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎Missed voice call, ‎Tap to call back
[03/07/24, 11:29:41 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎9 min
[03/07/24, 11:30:14 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <algorithm>

int sum(vector<int> &loads, int i, int t, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
    // base case
    if(t <= 0) return 0;
    if(i == loads.size()) return 1e7;

    // lookup
    if(dp[i][t] != -1) return dp[i][t];

    // recursive case
    int pick = loads[i] + sum(loads, i+1, t-loads[i], dp);
    int notPick = sum(loads, i+1, t, dp);

    return dp[i][t] = min(pick, notPick);
}

int minAbsDiff(int n, vector<int> &loads) {
    int total = accumulate(loads.begin(), loads.end(), 0);
    int target = total/2;
    vector<vector<int>> dp(loads.size()+1, vector<int>(target+1,-1));
    int closest = sum(loads, 0, target, dp);
    return abs(total - 2*closest);
}

[06/07/24, 10:54:45 AM] Satvik Saini: int complementary(int prefix, int B){
    int num = 0;
    for(int i=0;i<32;i++){
        if((prefix & (i << 1)) != (B & (i << i))) num += i << 1;
    }
    return num;
}

int Solution::solve(vector<int> &A, int B) {
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    mp[0] = 1;
    int prefix = 0;
    int cnt = 0;
    
    for(int i=0;i<A.size();i++){
        prefix ^= A[i];
        int req = complementary(prefix,B);
        if(mp.find(req) != mp.end()) cnt += mp[req];
        mp[prefix]++;
    }
    
    return cnt;
}

[06/07/24, 12:33:32 PM] Satvik Saini: https://www.interviewbit.com/problems/water-flow/
[06/07/24, 12:33:41 PM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> dx = {1,-1,0,0};
vector<int> dy = {0,0,1,-1};

bool reach(vector<vector<int> > &A, int n, int m, int i, int j, char col){
    // base case
    if(col == 'R' && (i == n-1 || j == m-1)) return 1;
    if(col == 'B' && (i == 0 || j == 0)) return 1;
    
    // recursive case
    int temp = A[i][j];
    A[i][j] = 1e9 + 7;
    
    
    for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
        int ii = i + dx[k];
        int jj = j + dy[k];
        if(ii >= 0 && ii < n && jj >= 0 && jj < m && A[ii][jj] <= A[i][j] && reach(A,n,m,ii,jj,col)) return 1;
    }
    A[i][j] = temp;
    return 0;
}

int Solution::solve(vector<vector<int> > &A) {
    int n = A.size();
    int m = A[0].size();
    
    int count = 0;
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
            if(i == 0 || j == 0) count += reach(A,n,m,i,j,'R');
            if(i == n-1 || j == m-1) count += reach(A,n,m,i,j,'B');
            else count += reach(A,n,m,i,j,'R') && reach(A,n,m,i,j,'B');
        }
    }
    return count;
}
[06/07/24, 12:39:51 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> bfs(vector<vector<int>> heights, bool pacific){

        vector<vector<int>> grid(heights.size(), vector<int>(heights[0].size(), -1));
        queue<pair<int, int> > q;
        if(pacific){
            for(int i=0 ; i<heights.size() ; i++){
                q.push({i,0});
                grid[i][0] = 1;
            }
            for(int i=0 ; i<heights[0].size() ; i++){
                q.push({0,i});
                grid[0][i] = 1;
            }
        }
        else{
            for(int i=0 ; i<heights.size() ; i++){
                q.push({i,heights[0].size()-1});
                grid[i][heights[0].size()-1] = 1;
            }
            for(int i=0 ; i<heights[0].size() ; i++){
                q.push({heights.size()-1,i});
                grid[heights.size()-1][i] = 1;
            }
        }
        int dx[4] = {-1, 1, 0, 0};
        int dy[4] = {0, 0, -1, 1};
        while( !q.empty()){
            pair<int, int> p = q.front();
            int i = p.first;
            int j = p.second;
            q.pop();
            for(int k=0 ; k<4 ; k++){
                int nx = i + dx[k];
                int ny = j + dy[k];
                if(nx>=0 && nx<heights.size() && ny>=0 && ny<heights[0].size() && heights[nx][ny] >= heights[i][j] && grid[nx][ny] == -1){
                    grid[nx][ny] = 1;
                    q.push({nx,ny}); 
                }
            }
        }
        return grid;
    }
    vector<vector<int>> pacificAtlantic(vector<vector<int>>& heights) {
        vector<vector<int>> res1 = bfs(heights, 1);
        vector<vector<int>> res2 = bfs(heights, 0);
        vector<vector<int>> ans;
        for(int i=0 ; i<heights.size() ; i++){
            for(int j=0 ; j<heights[0].size() ; j++){
                // if(res1[i][j] == res2[i][j] && res1[i][j]) ans.push_back({i,j});
                cout<<res1[i][j]<<"   ";
            }
            cout<<endl;
        }
        cout<<endl;
        for(int i=0 ; i<heights.size() ; i++){
            for(int j=0 ; j<heights[0].size() ; j++){
                if(res1[i][j] == res2[i][j] && res1[i][j] == 1) ans.push_back({i,j});
                cout<<res2[i][j]<<"   ";
            }
            cout<<endl;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[09/07/24, 10:14:04 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <unordered_map>

int Solution::solve(vector<vector<int> > &A) {
    int n = A.size();
    int m = A[0].size();
    int cnt = 0;
    
    for(int r1=0;r1<n;r1++){
        vector<int> temp(m,0);
        for(int r2=r1;r2<n;r2++){
            for(int c=0;c<m;c++){
                temp[c] += A[r2][c];
            }
            unordered_map<int,int> mp;
            mp[0] = 1;
            int prefix = 0;
            for(int c=0;c<m;c++){
                prefix += temp[c];
                if(mp.find(prefix) != mp.end()) cnt += mp[prefix];
                mp[prefix]++;
            }
        }
    }
    return cnt;
}

[09/07/24, 10:25:35 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int Solution::solve(vector<vector<int> > &A) {
	int r = A.size();
	if(!r) return 0;
	int c = A[0].size();
	if(!c) return 0;

	vector<vector<int> > pre;

	pre.resize(r, vector<int>(c, 0));

	for(int i = 0; i < r; ++i) {
		for(int j = 0; j < c; ++j) {
			pre[i][j] = A[i][j];
			if(i) pre[i][j] += pre[i - 1][j];
			if(j) pre[i][j] += pre[i][j - 1];
			if(i && j) pre[i][j] -= pre[i - 1][j - 1];
		}
	}
	int ans = 0;
	for(int r1 = 0; r1 < r; ++r1) {
		for(int r2 = r1; r2 < r; ++r2) {
			unordered_map<int, int> count;
			count[0] = 1;
			for(int j = 0; j < c; ++j) {
				int val = pre[r2][j];
				if(r1) val -= pre[r1 - 1][j];
				ans += count[val];
				count[val]++;
			}
		}
	}

	return ans;
}

[09/07/24, 10:31:52 AM] Satvik Saini: // Approach
// sort the array in order of increasing height
// if height is same, then sort the order of increasing no. of person
// lets take [5,1] and [5,0], then we will keep [5,0] in front of [5,1]
// sorted in inc height bec we will place the elements according to the no of person ahead of them
// [[7,0],[4,4],[7,1],[5,0],[6,1],[5,2]]
// after sorting -> [4,4], [5,0], [5,2], [6,1], [7,0], [7,1]
// take [4,4], we can see that 4 will be placed after 4 person of greater height in front of it
// thus, we init cnt = 4 (people[i][1]) and if there is -1 (empty) we decrement the cnt as a greater no will come at this place
// if a person of greater height is already placed, then also we will decrement cnt
[09/07/24, 10:33:11 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    static bool cmp(vector<int> &v1, vector<int> &v2){
        if(v1[0] == v2[0]){
            return v1[1] < v2[1];
        }
        return v1[0] < v2[0];
    }
public:
    vector<vector<int>> reconstructQueue(vector<vector<int>>& people) {
        sort(people.begin(), people.end(), cmp);

        vector<vector<int>> ans;
        for(int i=0;i<people.size();i++){
            ans.push_back({-1,-1});
        }
        for(int i=0;i<people.size();i++){
            int cnt = people[i][1];
            for(int j=0;j<ans.size();j++){
                if(ans[j][0] == -1 && cnt == 0){
                    ans[j] = {people[i][0],people[i][1]};
                    break;
                }
                if(ans[j][0] == -1 || ans[j][0] >= people[i][0]) cnt--;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[09/07/24, 10:38:26 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    static bool comp(vector<int>& a, vector<int>& b){ //Comparator function for the logic of sort
        if(a[0] == b[0]) return a[1] < b[1];
        return a[0] > b[0];
    }
    vector<vector<int>> reconstructQueue(vector<vector<int>>& people) {   
        sort(people.begin(), people.end(), comp);  //Sorting the array according to comp function.
        vector<vector<int>> ans;                   //to store the final array to be returned
        for(auto man : people){
            ans.insert(ans.begin()+man[1], man);   //Inserting the element at desired position.
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[10/07/24, 3:09:03 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int canCompleteCircuit(vector<int>& gas, vector<int>& cost) {
        if(accumulate(gas.begin(), gas.end(),0) < accumulate(cost.begin(), cost.end(),0)) return -1;

        int remaining_fuel = 0;
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<gas.size();i++){
            remaining_fuel += gas[i] - cost[i];
            if(remaining_fuel < 0){
                ans = i+1;
                remaining_fuel = 0;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
