[10/07/24, 7:12:09 PM] Satvik Saini: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
    unordered_map<string,TreeNode*> hm;
    set<TreeNode*> st;
public:
    string dfs(TreeNode* root){
        //base case
        if(root == NULL){
            return "X";
        }
        //recursive case
        string left = dfs(root->left);
        string right = dfs(root->right);

        string uniquestr = to_string(root->val) + "." + left + "." + right;
        if(hm.find(uniquestr) != hm.end()){
            // duplicate is found
            st.insert(hm[uniquestr]);
        }
        else{
            hm[uniquestr] = root;
        }
        return uniquestr;
    }

    vector<TreeNode*> findDuplicateSubtrees(TreeNode* root) {
        string x = dfs(root);

        return vector<TreeNode*> (st.begin(), st.end());
    }
};
[10/07/24, 7:15:10 PM] Satvik Saini: string smallestInteger(string &num, int n, int k) {
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        // currently finding the best fit for ith bit by doing at most k swaps
        char ch = num[i];
        int idx;
        for(int j=i+1;j<min(n,i+k+1);j++){
            if(ch > num[j]){
                ch = num[j];
                idx = j;
            }
        }
        if(ch == num[i]){
            // no need to swap, go on to (i+1)th index for best fit
            continue;
        }
        else{
            // we have to shift the digits clockwise from i to idx
            char temp = num[idx];
            for(int j=idx;j>i;j--){
                num[j] = num[j-1];
            }
            num[i] = temp;
            k -= idx - i;
            if(!k) return num;
        }
    }
    return num;
}
[10/07/24, 7:17:37 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Time : О(n^2), In the worst case, k will be very large, and it becomes bubble sort.
[10/07/24, 7:21:20 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /** <Greedy Approach>
We take 10 queues for digits 0 to 9 and store their occurence(index in the original string) in the queues (clearly all the queues are sorted by default) 
Now we want the most significant digit to be the smallest so we try all the 0-9 digits at position i .
Suppose we want to place any digit j in range [0,9] at a position i we do a binay search on all the 10 queues to find the number of digits 
with index smaller than the current chosen digits index then we will check if the swaps are less than or equal to the current k value if yes
we put the current digit in new string and go for the (i+1)th place else we will continue to check for digit j+1 .
Below is the implementation
*/
int bs(vector<int> &v,int l,int r,int key){

        if(l>r) return l;
        int mid=l+(r-l)/2;

        if(v[mid]>key) return bs(v,l,mid-1,key);
        return bs(v,mid+1,r,key);
}
string minInteger(string num, int k) {
     int n=num.size();
	 //trivial case
     if(k>=(n*(n-1))/2){
        sort(num.begin(),num.end());
        return num;
     }
	 //queues
     vector<vector<int> >v(10);
     for(int i=0;i<n;++i){
        v[num[i]-'0'].push_back(i);
     }
	 //head for every queue to store the queue state
     vector<int> head(10);
     string ans="";
      vector<bool> visit(n);
     for(int i=0;i<n && k>0;++i){
        for(int j=0;j<10;++j){

            if(head[j]<v[j].size()){

				// total count of digits with smaller index than the current chosen digit
                int idx=0;
				//binary search on all the 10 queues
                for(int l=0;l<10;++l){
                    if(l!=j){
                        idx+=bs(v[l],0,head[l]-1,v[j][head[j]]);
                    }
                    else
                        idx+=head[l];
                }
//                cout<<k<<" "<<idx<<" "<<j<<"\n";
                if(k>=(v[j][head[j]]-idx)){

                    ans.push_back((char)(j+'0'));
                    visit[v[j][head[j]]]=true;
                    k-=(v[j][head[j]]-idx);
                    ++head[j];
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
     }
	// appending the remaining string
     for(int i=0;i<n;++i) if(!visit[i]) ans.push_back(num[i]);
    
     return ans;

}
[11/07/24, 8:06:14 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎1 min
[11/07/24, 9:08:26 AM] Satvik Saini: unordered_set<string> hm;

pair<string, bool> dfs(BinaryTreeNode<char>* root) {
    // base case
    if (root == NULL) {
        return {"X", false};
    }

    // recursive case
    pair<string, bool> left = dfs(root->left);
    pair<string, bool> right = dfs(root->right);

    string uniquestr = to_string(root->data) + "." + left.first + "." + right.first;
    if (hm.find(uniquestr) != hm.end()) {
        // duplicate is found
        return {uniquestr, true};
    } else {
        hm.insert(uniquestr);
    }

    return {uniquestr, left.second || right.second};
}

bool similarSubtree(BinaryTreeNode<char>* root) {
    pair<string, bool> x = dfs(root);
    return x.second;
}

[11/07/24, 9:27:13 AM] Satvik Saini: Ninja is assigned a task to reach the last stone by his master. These stones are numbered with some value and in the form of an array. He is allowed to jump either odd-numbered jumps or even-numbered jumps and has to reach the last stone.

So your task is to find the number of starting index from which he may start jumping so he reaches the last stones. You are provided with the given array and you have to find the number of starting index of the array from which Ninja can reach the end of the array by jumping some number of times.

For jumping you have to follow below instructions:

You may jump forward from index ‘i’ to index ‘j’ (with i < j) in the following way:

During odd-numbered jumps (i.e., jumps 1, 3, 5, ...), you jump to the index ‘j’ such that ‘arr[i] <= arr[j]’ and ‘arr[j]’ is the smallest possible value. If there are multiple such indices ‘j’, you can only jump to the smallest such index j.

During even-numbered jumps (i.e., jumps 2, 4, 6, ...), you jump to the index ‘j’ such that ‘arr[i] >= arr[j]’ and ‘arr[j]’ is the largest possible value. If there are multiple such indices ‘j’, you can only jump to the smallest such index ‘j’.

It may be the case that for some index ‘i’, there are no legal jumps.

[11/07/24, 12:20:11 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /*
  Time Complexity:O(n*log(n))
  Space Complexity:O(1)

   where n is the number of points.
*/

// Sorting According to comparator.
class cmp
{
public:
	bool operator()(vector<int>a, vector<int>b)
	{

		int dist = a[0] * a[0] + a[1] * a[1];
		int dist1 = b[0] * b[0] + b[1] * b[1];

		if (dist == dist1)
		{
			return a[0] < b[0];
		}

		return dist < dist1;
	}
};

vector<vector<int>>KnearestPoints(int n, int k, vector<vector<int>>points)
{
    // Sorting the array
	sort(points.begin(), points.end(), cmp());

	vector<vector<int>>ans;
    
    // First k points are the k nearest points.
	for (int i = 0; i < k; i++)
	{
		ans.push_back(points[i]);
	}

    // Return the array ans
	return ans;
}
[11/07/24, 12:22:07 PM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎21 sec
[11/07/24, 1:20:42 PM] Satvik Saini: /*
    Time complexity: O(N)
    Space complexity: O(N)
    
    Where 'N' is the number of nodes in the tree.
*/

// Helper function.
int helper(TreeNode<int> *root, int &res){
    
    // Base case.
    if(root == NULL){
        return 0;
    }
    
    // Call subtrees recursively.
    int lMax = helper(root -> left, res);
    int rMax = helper(root -> right, res);
    
    // For storing left and right answers.
    int lTemp = 0;
    int rTemp = 0;
    
    // Check conditions.
    if(root -> left && root -> left -> weight == root -> weight){
        lTemp += 1 + lMax;
    }

    if(root -> right && root -> right -> weight == root -> weight){
        rTemp += 1 + rMax;
    }
    
    // Update res.
    res = max(res, lTemp + rTemp);
    
    return max(lTemp, rTemp);
}

int longestPath(TreeNode<int> *root){
    
    // To store the longest path.
    int res = 0;
    
    helper(root, res);
    
    return res;
}

// vector<int> incDecArray(int n, string s) {

//    buildArray(n,s,0,vis,temp);

vector<int> incDecArray(int n, string s) {
   vector<int> ans;
   vector<int> vis(n+1,0);
   int cnt_n = 0;
   for(char ch : s) if(ch == 'N') cnt_n++;
   ans.push_back(cnt_n+1);
   vis[cnt_n+1] = 1;

   for(char ch : s){
      if(ch == 'P'){
         int ele = ans.back();
         for(int i=ele+1;i<=n;i++){
            if(vis[i] == 0){ ans.push_back(i); vis[i] = 1; break;}
         }
      }
      else{
         int ele = ans.back();
         for(int i=ele-1;i>0;i--){
            if(vis[i] == 0){ ans.push_back(i); vis[i] = 1; break;}
         }
      }
   }
   return ans;
}
[12/07/24, 9:23:49 AM] Satvik Saini: bool used[100]={false};  // this array checks for the digit used till now in num

bool flag = false;  // we have not got the smallest number yet, this variable is used so that we could stop after printing the first no as it the lexographically smallest number.

void solve(string inp, string &num, int i){

  //base case

  if(num.size() == inp.size() + 1){
    flag = true;
    cout << num << endl;
    return;
  }

  //recursive case

	// intially there is no element in num
  if(num.size() == 0){
    for(int d = 1; d <= 9; d++){
      num.push_back(d + '0');
      used[d] = true;
      solve(inp, num, i); // we not use i+1, bec we haven't used the inp string yet for the 0th digit
      if(flag) return;
      num.pop_back();     // backtracking
      used[d] = false;
    }
    return;
  }

  int x = num[num.size() - 1] - '0';  // converting char to int

  if(inp[i] == 'I'){
    for(int d = x+1;d <= 9;d++){   // since we have to search for a greater no.
      if(used[d] == false){.       // ensuring that the number is not used yet
        num.push_back(d + '0');    // converting int to char
        used[d] = true;
        solve(inp, num, i + 1);
        if(flag) return;
        num.pop_back();
        used[d] = false;
      }
    }
  }

  else{
    for(int d=1;d>=1;d--){      // since we have to search for a smaller no.
      if(used[d] == false){
        num.push_back(d+'0');
        used[d] = true;
        solve(inp, num, i+1);
	      if(flag) return;
        num.pop_back();
        used[d] = false;
      }
    }
  }
}

int main(){
  string inp = "IID";
  string num = "";
  solve(inp,num,0);
  return 0;
}

bool flag = 0;

void buildArray(int n, string s, int i, vector<int> &vis, vector<int> &temp){
   // base case
   if(i == n-1){
      if(temp.size() == n) {res = temp; flag = 1}
      return;
   }

   // recursive case
   if(temp.size() == 0){
      for(int j=1;j<=n;j++){
         temp.push_back(j);
         vis[j] = 1;
         buildArray(n,s,0,vis,temp);
         vis[j] = 0;
         temp.pop_back();
      }
   }
   else{
      if(s[i] == 'P'){
         int ele = temp.back();
         for(int j=ele+1;j<=n;j++){
            if(!vis[j]){
               temp.push_back(j);
               vis[j] = 1;
               buildArray(n,s,i+1,vis,temp);
               if(flag) return;
               vis[j] = 0;
               temp.pop_back();
            }
         }
      }
      else{
         int ele = temp.back();
         for(int j=1;j<ele;j++){
            if(!vis[j]){
               temp.push_back(j);
               vis[j] = 1;
               buildArray(n,s,i+1,vis,temp);
               if(flag) return;
               vis[j] = 0;
               temp.pop_back();
            }
         }
      }
   }
}

vector<int> incDecArray(int n, string s) {
   vector<int> vis(n+1,0);
   vector<int> temp;
   buildArray(n,s,0,vis,temp);
   return res;
}
[12/07/24, 9:54:42 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
    boolean[] flag;
    char[] ans;
    boolean found;
    char[] a;

    public String smallestNumber(String pattern) {
        a = pattern.toCharArray();
        ans = new char[a.length + 1];
        flag = new boolean[140];
        found = false;
        backtracking(0);
        return new String(ans);
    }

    private void backtracking(int po) {
        if (po == ans.length) {
            found = true;
            return;
        }
        for (int i = '1'; i <= '9' && !found; i++) {
            if (po == 0 || (!flag[i] && ((a[po - 1] == 'I' && i > ans[po - 1]) || (a[po - 1] == 'D' && i < ans[po - 1])))) {
                flag[i] = true;
                ans[po] = (char) i;
                backtracking(po + 1);
                flag[i] = false;
            }
        }
    }
}

        vis[cnt_n+1] = 1;

        for(char ch : s){

                int ele = ans.back();
                for(int i=ele+1;i<=n;i++){
                    if(vis[i] == 0){ ans.push_back(i); vis[i] = 1; break;}
                }
            }
            else{
                int ele = ans.back();
                for(int i=ele-1;i>0;i--){
                    if(vis[i] == 0){ ans.push_back(i); vis[i] = 1; break;}
                }
            }
        }
        string ansStr = "";
        for(int ele : ans){
            ansStr += to_string(ele);
        }
        return ansStr;
    }

[13/07/24, 9:56:43 AM] Satvik Saini: static bool cmp(vector<int> &a, vector<int> &b){
    if(a[0] == b[0]){
        return a[1]>b[1];
    }
    return a[0] > b[0];
    // if(a[1] == b[1]){
    //     return a[0]>b[0];
    // }
    // return a[1] > b[1];
}

int maxHeight(vector<vector<int>> &arr, int n, int i, int prev){
    // base case
    if(i == arr.size()) return 0;

    // recursive case
    // pick
    int pick = 0;
    if(prev == -1 || (arr[i][0] < arr[prev][0] && arr[i][1] < arr[prev][1])){
        pick = 1 + maxHeight(arr, n, i+1, i);
    }
    int notPick = maxHeight(arr, n, i+1, prev);
    return max(pick, notPick);
}

int maxTowerHeight(vector<vector<int>> &arr, int n)
{
    sort(arr.begin(),arr.end(),cmp);
    return maxHeight(arr, n, 0, -1);
}
[13/07/24, 9:58:42 AM] Satvik Saini: https://www.naukri.com/code360/problems/thomas-and-friends_2420288
[13/07/24, 10:14:09 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <unordered_map>

int cnt = 0;
unordered_map<pair<int,int>,int> mp;

void dfs(vector<int> adj[], int a, int b, vector<int> &vis, vector<pair<int,int>> &path){
    // base case
    if(a == b){
        cnt++;
        for(auto p : path) mp[p]++;
        return;
    }

    // recursive case
    for(int neighbour : adj[a]){
        if(!vis[neighbour]){
            vis[neighbour] = 1;
            path.push_back({a,neighbour});
            dfs(adj,neighbour,b,vis,path);
            vis[neighbour] = 0;
            path.pop_back();
        }
    }
}

int getMinDistance(int v, int e, vector<int> &v1, vector<int> &v2, int a, int b) {
    vector<int> adj[v];

    for(int i=0;i<v;i++){
        adj[v1[i]].push_back(v2[i]);
        adj[v2[i]].push_back(v1[i]);
    }
    vector<int> vis(v,0);
    vector<pair<int,int>> path;

    dfs(adj,a,b,vis,path);

    int ans = 0;
    for(auto p : mp){
        if(p.second == cnt) ans++;
    }
    return ans;

}

[13/07/24, 2:57:59 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    static bool cmp(pair<int,int> &p1, pair<int,int> &p2){
        return p1.first < p2.first;
    }
public:
    vector<int> survivedRobotsHealths(vector<int>& positions, vector<int>& healths, string directions) {
        vector<vector<int>> v;
        for(int i=0;i<positions.size();i++){
            if(directions[i] == 'R') v.push_back({positions[i],-healths[i],i});
            else v.push_back({positions[i],healths[i],i});
        }
        sort(v.begin(),v.end());

        stack<pair<int,int>> stk;

        vector<pair<int,int>> ans;

        for(int i=0;i<v.size();i++){
            if(stk.empty() && v[i][1] < 0) ans.push_back({v[i][2],abs(v[i][1])});
            else{
                if(v[i][1] > 0) stk.push({v[i][2],v[i][1]});
                else{
                    bool flag = 0;
                    while(!stk.empty() && stk.top().second > 0){
                        if(stk.top().second == abs(v[i][1])){                          
                            stk.pop();
                            flag = 1;
                            break;
                        }
                        else if(stk.top().second > abs(v[i][1])){
                            pair<int,int> top = stk.top();
                            stk.pop();
                            stk.push({top.first,top.second-1});
                            flag = 1;
                            break;
                        }
                        else{
                            stk.pop();
                            v[i][1]--;
                        }
                    }
                    if(!flag) ans.push_back({v[i][2],abs(v[i][1])});
                }
            }
        }

        while(!stk.empty()){
            ans.push_back({stk.top().first, abs(stk.top().second)});
            stk.pop();
        }

        sort(ans.begin(), ans.end(), cmp);

        vector<int> res;
        for(auto p : ans){
            res.push_back(p.second);
        }
        return res;
    }
};

[13/07/24, 3:44:42 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    bool areOpp(int a, int b){
        if(a<0 && b>0) return true;
        if(a>0 && b<0) return true;
        return false;
    }
    vector<int> survivedRobotsHealths(vector<int>& pos, vector<int>& healths, string str) {
       vector<pair<int,pair<int,int>>> robots;

       for(int i=0 ; i<pos.size() ; i++){
        if(str[i] == 'L'){
          robots.push_back({pos[i],{-1*healths[i],i}});  
        }
        else{
        robots.push_back({pos[i],{healths[i],i}});
        }
       } 
       sort(robots.begin(),robots.end(),[](pair<int,pair<int,int>>&a, pair<int,pair<int,int>>&b){
            return a.first < b.first;
       });
       vector<pair<int,int>> stk;
       for(auto robot : robots){
            int health = robot.second.first;
            bool flag = false;
            while(!stk.empty() && abs(stk[stk.size()-1].first) <= abs(health) && areOpp(stk[stk.size()-1].first,health)){
                if(stk[stk.size()-1].first == health){
                    stk.pop_back();
                    flag = true;
                    break;
                }
                else{
                    stk.pop_back();
                    health--;
                }
            }
            if(!flag && health > 0){
                // if the robot is not destroyed 
                stk.push_back({health,robot.second.second});
            }
       }
       sort(stk.begin(),stk.end(),[](pair<int,int>&a, pair<int,int>&b){
            return a.second<b.second;
       });
       vector<int> ans;
       for(auto a : stk) ans.push_back(a.first);
       return ans;
    }
};

            stk.pop();

            res.push_back(p.second);
        }
        return res;
    }

public:
    bool areOpp(int a, int b){

        cout << "false" << endl;
        return false;
    }
    vector<int> survivedRobotsHealths(vector<int>& pos, vector<int>& healths, string str) {
       vector<pair<int,pair<int,int>>> robots;

       for(int i=0 ; i<pos.size() ; i++){
        if(str[i] == 'L'){
          robots.push_back({pos[i],{-1*healths[i],i}});  
        }
        else{
        robots.push_back({pos[i],{healths[i],i}});
        }
       } 
       sort(robots.begin(),robots.end(),[](pair<int,pair<int,int>>&a, pair<int,pair<int,int>>&b){
            return a.first < b.first;
       });
       vector<pair<int,int>> stk;
       for(auto robot : robots){
            int health = robot.second.first;
            bool flag = false;
            while(!stk.empty() && areOpp(stk[stk.size()-1].first,health) && abs(stk[stk.size()-1].first) <= abs(health)){
                if(abs(stk[stk.size()-1].first) == abs(health)){
                    stk.pop_back();
                    flag = true;
                    break;

                else{
                    stk.pop_back();
                    if(health > 0) health--;
                    else health++;
                }
            }

            if( !flag && health > 0){
                stk.push_back({health,robot.second.second});
            }
       }
       sort(stk.begin(),stk.end(),[](pair<int,int>&a, pair<int,int>&b){
            return a.second<b.second;
       });
       vector<int> ans;
       for(auto a : stk) ans.push_back(a.first);
       return ans;
    }

[14/07/24, 9:21:26 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <string>

class Solution {
    string repeat(int n, string s) { 
    string s1 = s; 
    for (int i=1; i<n;i++) s += s1;
    return s; 
} 
public:
    string countOfAtoms(string formula) {
        stack<string> stk;
        string prev = "";
        for(char ch : formula){
            if(ch >= 'a' && ch <= 'z'){
                string top = stk.top();
                stk.pop();
                top += ch;
                prev += ch;
                stk.push(top);
            }
            else if(ch >= '0' && ch <= '9'){
                string top = stk.top();
                stk.pop();
                top += repeat(ch-'0'-1,prev);
                stk.push(top);
                // if(prev == ")"){
                //     string top1 = stk.top();
                //     stk.pop();
                //     string top2 = stk.top();
                //     stk.pop();
                //     stk.push(top1 + top2);
                // }
                prev = "";
            }
            else if(ch >= 'A' && ch <= 'Z'){
                if(prev == "(" || prev == ""){
                    // stk.push(to_string(ch));
                    // stk.push(string(ch));
                    stk.push(string(1, ch));
                }
                else{
                    string top = stk.top();
                    stk.pop();
                    top += ch;
                    stk.push(top);
                }
                prev = string(1,ch);
            }
            else if(ch == '('){
                prev = string(1,ch);
            }
            else{
                // ch == ')'
                prev = stk.top();
            }
        }
        map<string,int> mp;
        while(!stk.empty()){
            string top = stk.top();
            cout<<stk.top()<<endl;
            for(int i=0;i<top.length()-1;i++){
                if(top[i] >= 'A' && top[i] <= 'Z'){
                    if(top[i+1] >= 'a' && top[i+1] <= 'z'){
                        mp[top.substr(i,2)]++;
                        i++;
                    }
                    else mp[string(1,top[i])]++;
                }
            }
            if(top.back() >= 'A' && top.back() <= 'Z') mp[string(1,top.back())]++;
            stk.pop();
        }
        string ans = "";
        for(auto p : mp){
            string s = p.first;
            int cnt = p.second;
            if(cnt > 1) ans += s + to_string(cnt);
            else ans += s;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[16/07/24, 9:21:36 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/step-by-step-directions-from-a-binary-tree-node-to-another/
[16/07/24, 9:25:13 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    pair<string, bool> getPath(TreeNode* root, int target) {
        // base case
        if (!root) return {"", false};
        if (root->val == target) return {"", true};

        // recursive case
        pair<string, bool> left = getPath(root->left, target);
        if (left.second) {
            return {left.first + "L", true};
        }

        pair<string, bool> right = getPath(root->right, target);
        if (right.second) {
            return {right.first + "R", true};
        }

        return {"", false};
    }
public:
    string getDirections(TreeNode* root, int startValue, int destValue) {
        string root_to_start = getPath(root, startValue).first;
        string root_to_dest = getPath(root, destValue).first;

        cout<<root_to_start<<" "<<root_to_dest<<endl;

        int n = root_to_start.length(), m = root_to_dest.length();

        int i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < n && j < m && root_to_start[i] == root_to_dest[j]) {
            i++;
            j++;
        }

        string up_moves = string(n - i, 'U');
        string down_moves = root_to_dest.substr(j);

        return up_moves + down_moves;
    }
};

[16/07/24, 5:19:41 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <vector>
#include <cmath>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

vector<vector<int>> solution(int t, vector<vector<int>>& testCases) {
    vector<vector<int>> results;
    
    for (const auto& test : testCases) {
        int uSpeed = test[0], uAlpha = test[1], uBeta = test[2], uDelta = test[3];
        
     
        for (int time = 1; time <= 10000; ++time) {
            int distance = time * uSpeed;
            
            // Check if this combination satisfies all conditions
            if (distance + time == uAlpha &&
                distance * time == uBeta &&
                distance - time == uDelta &&
                abs(distance) > abs(time)) {
                
                results.push_back({distance, time});
                break;
            }
        }
        
    
        if (results.size() < testCases.size()) {
            results.push_back({-1, -1});
        }
    }
    
    return results;
}
[16/07/24, 5:26:24 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <unordered_set>
using namespace std;

void dfs(int node, vector<vector<int>> &graph, vector<bool> &visited) {
    visited[node] = true;
    for (int neighbor : graph[node]) {
        if (!visited[neighbor]) {
            dfs(neighbor, graph, visited);
        }
    }
}

int solution(int n, vector<string> otp_list) {
    vector<vector<int>> graph(n);
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        unordered_set<char> set1(otp_list[i].begin(), otp_list[i].end());
        for (int j = i + 1; j < n; ++j) {
            unordered_set<char> set2(otp_list[j].begin(), otp_list[j].end());
            for (char c : set1) {
                if (set2.find(c) != set2.end()) {
                    graph[i].push_back(j);
                    graph[j].push_back(i);
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
    }
    vector<bool> visited(n, false);
    int components = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        if (!visited[i]) {
            dfs(i, graph, visited);
            components++;
        }
    }
    return components;
}
[16/07/24, 5:40:57 PM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎5 min
[16/07/24, 5:41:32 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
#include <climits>

using namespace std;

long long solution(int n, vector<vector<int>> s) {
    int subsets = 1 << n; // total number of subsets
    vector<long long> dp(subsets, 0);

    for (int mask = 1; mask < subsets; ++mask) {
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            if (mask & (1 << i)) {
                for (int j = i + 1; j < n; ++j) {
                    if (mask & (1 << j)) {
                        dp[mask] += s[i][j];
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }

    vector<long long> result(subsets, LLONG_MIN);
    result[0] = 0;

    for (int mask = 1; mask < subsets; ++mask) {
        for (int subset = mask; subset > 0; subset = (subset - 1) & mask) {
            result[mask] = max(result[mask], result[mask ^ subset] + dp[subset]);
        }
    }

    return result[subsets - 1];
}

[16/07/24, 5:49:58 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <cmath>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

vector<vector<int>> solution(int t, vector<vector<int>> testCases) {
    vector<vector<int>> results;

    for (int i = 0; i < t; ++i) {
        int A = testCases[i][0];
        int B = testCases[i][1];
        int C = testCases[i][2];
        int D = testCases[i][3];
        
        vector<int> values = {A, B, C, D};
        sort(values.begin(), values.end());
        
        int distance = -1;
        int time = -1;

        do {
            int uSpeed = values[0];
            int uAlpha = values[1];
            int uBeta = values[2];
            int uDelta = values[3];

            for (int d = 1; d <= 1000000; ++d) {
                int t = d / uSpeed;
                if (uAlpha == d + t && uBeta == d * t && uDelta == d - t) {
                    distance = d;
                    time = t;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (distance != -1) break;

        } while (next_permutation(values.begin(), values.end()));

        if (distance == -1 && time == -1) {
            results.push_back({-1, -1});
        } else {
            results.push_back({distance, time});
        }
    }
    return results;
}

#include <vector>
#include <cmath>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

vector<vector<int>> solution(int t, vector<vector<int>> testCases) {
    vector<vector<int>> results;

    for (int i = 0; i < t; ++i) {
        int A = testCases[i][0];
        int B = testCases[i][1];
        int C = testCases[i][2];
        int D = testCases[i][3];
        
        vector<int> values = {A, B, C, D};
        sort(values.begin(), values.end());
        
        int distance = -1;
        int time = -1;

        do {
            int uDelta = values[0];
            int uSpeed = values[1];
            int uAlpha = values[2];
            int uBeta = values[3];

            for (int t = 1; t <= 1000000; ++t) {
                int d = uSpeed * t;
                if (uAlpha == d + t && uBeta == d * t && uDelta == t - d) {
                    distance = d;
                    time = t;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (distance != -1) break;

        } while (next_permutation(values.begin(), values.end()));

        if (distance == -1 && time == -1) {
            results.push_back({-1, -1});
        } else {
            results.push_back({time, distance});
        }
    }
    return results;
}

int main() {
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    vector<vector<int>> testCases(t, vector<int>(4));

    for (int i = 0; i < t; ++i) {
        for (int j = 0; j < 4; ++j) {
            cin >> testCases[i][j];
        }
    }

    vector<vector<int>> results = solution(t, testCases);

    for (const auto& result : results) {
        cout << result[0] << " " << result[1] << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}
[16/07/24, 6:03:38 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <cmath>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

vector<int> solveSingleCase(vector<int> values) {
    sort(values.begin(), values.end());
    do {
        int uSpeed = values[0];
        int uAlpha = values[1];
        int uBeta = values[2];
        int uDelta = values[3];
        
     
        if (uSpeed == 0) continue;
        
        // d = Distance, t = Time
        int d = (uAlpha + uDelta) / 2;
        int t = (uAlpha - uDelta) / 2;
        
        
        if (uSpeed == floor(d / t) && uAlpha == d + t && uBeta == d * t && uDelta == d - t) {
            return {d, t};
        }
    } while (next_permutation(values.begin(), values.end()));
    
    return {-1, -1};
}

vector<vector<int>> solution(int t, vector<vector<int>> testCases) {
    vector<vector<int>> results;
    for (int i = 0; i < t; ++i) {
        results.push_back(solveSingleCase(testCases[i]));
    }
    return results;
}

[17/07/24, 4:04:00 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

// Function to determine the optimal path to minimize traversal distance
string optimalPath(string &path) {
    int north_count = 0;  // Counter for northward steps
    int east_count = 0;   // Counter for eastward steps
    int left_limit = 0;   // Left boundary during traversal
    int right_limit = 0;  // Right boundary during traversal

    // Traverse the given path to update boundaries and counters
    for(char direction : path) {
        if (direction == 'N') {
            north_count++;
        } else if (direction == 'E') {
            east_count++;
            right_limit = max(right_limit, east_count);
        } else {  // Assuming the only other option is 'W' for west
            east_count--;
            left_limit = min(left_limit, east_count);
        }
    }

    // Adjusting margins to include boundary limits
    right_limit++;
    left_limit--;

    // Calculating the distance to traverse towards the right and left boundaries
    int right_traverse_distance = 2 * right_limit - east_count;
    int left_traverse_distance = east_count - 2 * left_limit;

    string result = "";  // Resultant path

    // Determine the optimal direction to traverse
    if (right_traverse_distance < left_traverse_distance) {
        // Traverse towards the right limit
        for (int i = east_count; i < right_limit; i++) {
            result += 'E';
        }
        // Move south to return to origin
        for (int i = north_count; i > 0; i--) {
            result += 'S';
        }
        // Traverse towards the left to complete the path
        for (int i = right_limit; i > 0; i--) {
            result += 'W';
        }
    } else {
        // Traverse towards the left limit
        for (int i = east_count; i > left_limit; i--) {
            result += 'W';
        }
        // Move south to return to origin
        for (int i = north_count; i > 0; i--) {
            result += 'S';
        }
        // Traverse towards the right to complete the path
        for (int i = left_limit; i < 0; i++) {
            result += 'E';
        }
    }
    return result;  // Return the constructed optimal path
}

[17/07/24, 5:28:00 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: // you can use includes, for example:
// #include <algorithm>

// you can write to stdout for debugging purposes, e.g.
// cout << "this is a debug message" << endl;
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
int dp[100000][2];
int f(int i,bool ch, vector<int> &A, vector<int> &B, int X, int Y){

    if(i == A.size()) return 0;

    if(dp[i][ch] != -1 ) return dp[i][ch];

    // recursive case
    // you are at ith point in the assembly line in 'ch' line
    if(ch == true){
        // go to the next position in same line 
        int same = A[i] + f(i+1,true,A,B,X,Y);

        // go to the next position in diff line 
        int switch_line = A[i] + X + f(i+1,false,A,B,X,Y);
        return  dp[i][ch] = min(same,switch_line);
    }
    // go to the next position in same line 
        int same = B[i] + f(i+1,false,A,B,X,Y);

        // go to the next position in diff line 
        int switch_line = B[i] + Y + f(i+1,true,A,B,X,Y);
        return  dp[i][ch] = min(same,switch_line);

}
int solution(vector<int> &A, vector<int> &B, int X, int Y) {
    // Implement your solution here
    memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
    return min(f(0,true,A,B,X,Y),f(0,false,A,B,X,Y));
}
[17/07/24, 5:32:07 PM] Satvik Saini: // you can use includes, for example:
// #include <algorithm>

// you can write to stdout for debugging purposes, e.g.
// cout << "this is a debug message" << endl;

int minTime(vector<int> &A, vector<int> &B, int X, int Y, int i, char ch){
    // base case
    if(i == A.size()) return 0;

    // recursive case
    // op1 : pick ith compartment from A
    int op1 = 0;
    if(ch == 'A') op1 = minTime(A,B,X,Y,i+1,'A');
    else op1 = Y + minTime(A,B,X,Y,i+1,'A');

    // op2 : pick ith compartment from B
    int op2 = 0;
    if(ch == 'B') op2 = minTime(A,B,X,Y,i+1,'B');
    else op2 = X + minTime(A,B,X,Y,i+1,'B');

    return min(op1, op2);
}

int solution(vector<int> &A, vector<int> &B, int X, int Y) {
    return min(minTime(A,B,X,Y,1,'A'), minTime(A,B,X,Y,1,'B'));
}

int solution(vector<int> &A, vector<int> &B, int X, int Y) {
    // Implement your solution here
    int n = A.size();
    vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1, vector<int>(2,0));
    // return min(f(0,true,A,B,X,Y),f(0,false,A,B,X,Y));
    for(int ch=0 ; ch<=1 ; ch++){
        for(int i = n-1 ; i>=0 ; i--){
            if(ch == true){
                // go to the next position in same line 
                int same = A[i] + dp[i+1][true];
                // go to the next position in diff line 
                int switch_line = A[i] + X + dp[i+1][false];
                dp[i][ch] = min(same,switch_line);
            
            }else{
                // go to the next position in same line 
                int same = B[i] + dp[i+1][false];
                // go to the next position in diff line 
                int switch_line = B[i] + Y + dp[i+1][true];
                dp[i][ch] = min(same,switch_line);
            }

        }

    }
    return min(dp[0][1],dp[0][0]);
}
[17/07/24, 5:42:12 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <vector>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

int solution(vector<int> &A, vector<int> &B, int X, int Y) {
    int n = A.size();
    vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 1, vector<int>(2, 0));

    for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        // Case when we are on line A (ch == 0)
        int sameA = A[i] + dp[i + 1][0];
        int switchToB = A[i] + X + dp[i + 1][1];
        dp[i][0] = min(sameA, switchToB);
        
        // Case when we are on line B (ch == 1)
        int sameB = B[i] + dp[i + 1][1];
        int switchToA = B[i] + Y + dp[i + 1][0];
        dp[i][1] = min(sameB, switchToA);
    }

    return min(dp[0][0], dp[0][1]);
}

int solution(vector<int> &A, vector<int> &B, int X, int Y) {
    // Implement your solution here
    int n = A.size();
    // return min(f(0,true,A,B,X,Y),f(0,false,A,B,X,Y));
    int dp_1 = 0;
    int dp_0 = 0;
    int curr_1 = 0;
    int curr_0 = 0;
        for(int i = n-1 ; i>=0 ; i--){
                // claculate dp[i][1]
                // go to the next position in same line 
                int same_1 = A[i] + dp_1;
                // go to the next position in diff line 
                int switch_line_1 = A[i] + X + dp_0;
                curr_1 = min(same_1,switch_line_1);
            
                // go to the next position in same line 
                int same_2 = B[i] + dp_0;
                // go to the next position in diff line 
                int switch_line_2 = B[i] + Y + dp_1;
                curr_0 = min(same_2,switch_line_2);

                dp_0 = curr_0;
                dp_1 = curr_1;

        }
    return min(curr_1,curr_0);
}

[22/07/24, 6:42:19 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: LOTR:
def findMinimumPrice(n, price, m):
    import heapq
    
    pq = []
    for p in price:
        heapq.heappush(pq, (-p, p, 0))
    
    while m > 0 and pq:
        neg_curr_price, original_price, coupons_used = heapq.heappop(pq)
        curr_price = -neg_curr_price
        if coupons_used < m:
            new_price = original_price // (2 ** (coupons_used + 1))
            heapq.heappush(pq, (-new_price, original_price, coupons_used + 1))
        m -= 1
    
    return sum([-item[0] for item in pq])

[22/07/24, 6:43:22 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: LOTR:
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
#include <iostream>

using namespace std;

long findSum(long cum[], int l, int r, int n) {
    if (l == 0) {
        return cum[r];
    }
    return cum[r] - cum[l - 1];
}

long getThreeNonOverLappingIntervals(vector<int> starting, vector<int> ending) {
    vector<pair<int, int>> vp;
    int n = starting.size();
    
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        vp.push_back({starting[i], ending[i]});
    }
    
    sort(vp.begin(), vp.end());
    
    long dp[n];
    dp[n - 1] = 0;
    
    for (int i = n - 2; i >= 0; i--) {
        int l = i + 1;
        int r = n - 1;
        int pos = n;
        
        while (l <= r) {
            int mid = l + (r - l) / 2;
            if (vp[mid].first > vp[i].second) {
                pos = min(pos, mid);
                r = mid - 1;
            } else {
                l = mid + 1;
            }
        }
        
        dp[i] = n - pos;
    }
    
    long dp1[n];
    dp1[n - 1] = 0;
    dp1[n - 2] = 0;
    long ans = 0;

    long cum[n];
    cum[0] = dp[0];
    
    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        cum[i] = cum[i - 1] + dp[i];
    }
    
    for (int i = n - 3; i >= 0; i--) {
        int l = i + 1;
        int r = n - 1;
        int pos = n;
        
        while (l <= r) {
            int mid = l + (r - l) / 2;
            if (vp[mid].first > vp[i].second) {
                pos = min(pos, mid);
                r = mid - 1;
            } else {
                l = mid + 1;
            }
        }
        
        if (pos == n) {
            continue;
        }
        
        ans += findSum(cum, pos, n - 1, n);
    }
    
    return ans;
}

#include <iostream>
#include <vector>


struct SinglyLinkedListNode {
    int data;
    SinglyLinkedListNode* next;
    SinglyLinkedListNode(int x) : data(x), next(nullptr) {}
};

SinglyLinkedListNode* mergeInBetween(SinglyLinkedListNode* list1, SinglyLinkedListNode* list2, int a, int b) {
    SinglyLinkedListNode* prevA = nullptr;
    SinglyLinkedListNode* curr = list1;
    for (int i = 0; i < a - 1; ++i) {
        prevA = curr;
        curr = curr->next;
    }
    SinglyLinkedListNode* afterB = curr;
    for (int i = a; i <= b; ++i) {
        afterB = afterB->next;
    }

    if (prevA != nullptr) {
        prevA->next = list2;
    } else {
        list1 = list2;
    }

    SinglyLinkedListNode* tailList2 = list2;
    while (tailList2->next != nullptr) {
        tailList2 = tailList2->next;
    }

    tailList2->next = afterB;

    return list1;
}


void printList(SinglyLinkedListNode* head) {
    SinglyLinkedListNode* curr = head;
    while (curr != nullptr) {
        std::cout << curr->data << " -> ";
        curr = curr->next;
    }
    std::cout << "nullptr" << std::endl;
}


SinglyLinkedListNode* createList(const std::vector<int>& arr) {
    if (arr.empty()) return nullptr;
    SinglyLinkedListNode* head = new SinglyLinkedListNode(arr[0]);
    SinglyLinkedListNode* tail = head;
    for (size_t i = 1; i < arr.size(); ++i) {
        tail->next = new SinglyLinkedListNode(arr[i]);
        tail = tail->next;
    }
    return head;
}

[22/07/24, 7:01:46 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <vector>
#include <queue>
#include <cmath>

using namespace std;

long findMinimumPrice(vector<int> price, int m) {
    priority_queue<tuple<long, int, int>> pq;
    
    // Populate the priority queue with initial prices
    for (int p : price) {
        pq.push(make_tuple(-p, p, 0));
    }
    
 
    while (m > 0 && !pq.empty()) {
        auto [neg_curr_price, original_price, coupons_used] = pq.top();
        pq.pop();
        
        long curr_price = -neg_curr_price;
        if (coupons_used < m) {
            long new_price = original_price / pow(2, coupons_used + 1);
            pq.push(make_tuple(-new_price, original_price, coupons_used + 1));
        }
        m--;
    }
    
  
    long total_price = 0;
    while (!pq.empty()) {
        total_price += -get<0>(pq.top());
        pq.pop();
    }
    
    return total_price;
}

#include <vector>
#include <queue>
#include <cmath>
using namespace std;

long long findMinimumPrice(vector<int>& price, int m) {
    priority_queue<int> pq;

    for (int p : price) {
        pq.push(p);
    }

    while (m > 0 && !pq.empty()) {
        int currentPrice = pq.top();
        pq.pop();
        int newPrice = currentPrice / 2;
        pq.push(newPrice);

        m--;
    }

    long long totalPrice = 0;
    while (!pq.empty()) {
        totalPrice += pq.top();
        pq.pop();
    }

    return totalPrice;
}

[23/07/24, 9:17:46 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumOperations(vector<int>& nums, vector<int>& target) {
        long long ops = 0;
        int n = nums.size();

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i] == target[i]) continue;
            if(nums[i] > target[i]){
                int j = i;
                int diff = nums[i]-target[i];
                while(j < n && nums[j] > target[i]){
                    nums[j] -= diff;
                    j++;
                }
                if(j != i) ops++;
            } 
            else{
                int j = i;
                int diff = target[i]-nums[i];
                while(j < n && nums[j] < target[i]){
                    nums[j] += diff;
                    j++;
                }
                if(j != i) ops++;
            }
        }
        return ops;
    }
};

[27/07/24, 4:42:43 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: public static String maskSensitiveInfo(String data) {
        if (isEmail(data)) {
            return maskEmail(data);
        } else if (isPhoneNumber(data)) {
            return maskPhoneNumber(data);
        }
        return data; 
    }

    private static boolean isEmail(String data) {
        return data.matches("^[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$");
    }

    private static boolean isPhoneNumber(String data) {
        return data.matches("^[0-9().\\-+ ]{10,20}$");
    }

    private static String maskEmail(String email) {
        email = email.toLowerCase();
        String[] parts = email.split("@");
        String local = parts[0];
        String domain = parts[1];

        if (local.length() > 2) {
            local = local.charAt(0) + "*" + local.charAt(local.length() - 1);
        } else {
            local = local.charAt(0) + "*";
        }
        return local + "@" + domain;
    }

    private static String maskPhoneNumber(String phone) {
        phone = phone.replaceAll("[^0-9]", "");
        int len = phone.length();
        String maskedPhone = "";

        if (len == 10) {
            maskedPhone = "###-###-" + phone.substring(6);
        } else if (len == 11) {
            maskedPhone = "+#-###-###-" + phone.substring(7);
        } else if (len == 12) {
            maskedPhone = "+##-###-###-" + phone.substring(8);
        } else if (len == 13) {
            maskedPhone = "+###-###-###-" + phone.substring(9);
        }

        return maskedPhone;
    }
[27/07/24, 4:43:34 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Bhej rha h c++ me
[27/07/24, 4:43:38 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Copy Mt krio abhi
[27/07/24, 4:44:38 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <regex>
#include <string>

bool isEmail(const std::string& data) {
    const std::regex emailPattern("^[A-Za-z0-9._%+-]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$");
    return std::regex_match(data, emailPattern);
}

bool isPhoneNumber(const std::string& data) {
    const std::regex phonePattern("^[0-9().\\-+ ]{10,20}$");
    return std::regex_match(data, phonePattern);
}

std::string maskEmail(const std::string& email) {
    std::string lowerEmail = email;
    std::transform(lowerEmail.begin(), lowerEmail.end(), lowerEmail.begin(), ::tolower);
    size_t atIndex = lowerEmail.find('@');
    std::string local = lowerEmail.substr(0, atIndex);
    std::string domain = lowerEmail.substr(atIndex + 1);

    if (local.length() > 2) {
        local = local.front() + std::string(5, '*') + local.back();
    } else {
        local = local.front() + std::string(5, '*');
    }

    return local + "@" + domain;
}

std::string maskPhoneNumber(const std::string& phone) {
    std::string digits;
    for (char c : phone) {
        if (isdigit(c)) {
            digits += c;
        }
    }

    size_t len = digits.length();
    std::string maskedPhone;

    if (len == 10) {
        maskedPhone = "###-###-" + digits.substr(6);
    } else if (len == 11) {
        maskedPhone = "+#-###-###-" + digits.substr(7);
    } else if (len == 12) {
        maskedPhone = "+##-###-###-" + digits.substr(8);
    } else if (len == 13) {
        maskedPhone = "+###-###-###-" + digits.substr(9);
    } else {
        maskedPhone = phone;  // Return the original phone number if it doesn't match any of the above conditions
    }

    return maskedPhone;
}

std::string maskSensitiveInfo(const std::string& data) {
    if (isEmail(data)) {
        return maskEmail(data);
    } else if (isPhoneNumber(data)) {
        return maskPhoneNumber(data);
    }
    return data;
}

int main() {
    std::string data1 = "john.doe@example.com";
    std::string data2 = "+1 (234) 567-8901";

    std::cout << "Masked Email: " << maskSensitiveInfo(data1) << std::endl;
    std::cout << "Masked Phone Number: " << maskSensitiveInfo(data2) << std::endl;

    return 0;
}

        if(st.size() == 0) return 0;

[29/07/24, 9:52:00 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
int larger(int num, set<int>& stt){
        auto it = stt.lower_bound( num);
        if(it == stt.end()) return 0;
        int small = distance(stt.begin(),it);
        return stt.size() - small;
    }
    int smaller(int num, set<int>& stt){
        auto it = stt.lower_bound( num);
        if( it == stt.end()) {
            return stt.size();
        }
        return (distance(stt.begin(),it));
    }
    
    int numTeams(vector<int>& rating) {
        int n = rating.size();

        vector<int> left_smaller(n);
        vector<int> right_smaller(n);
        vector<int> left_larger(n);
        vector<int> right_larger(n);
        set<int> stt_1;
        set<int> stt_2;
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            // calc left smaller and larger 
            left_smaller[i] = (smaller(rating[i], stt_1));
            left_larger[i] = (larger(rating[i], stt_1));
            stt_1.insert(rating[i]);
            cout << left_larger[i] << ' ';
        }
        cout << endl;
        for(int i=n-1 ; i>=0 ; i--){
            // calc right smaller and larger 
            right_smaller[i] = (smaller(rating[i], stt_2));
            right_larger[i] = (larger(rating[i], stt_2));
            stt_2.insert(rating[i]);
            cout << right_smaller[i] << " ";
        }
        int ans = 0;
        reverse(right_larger.begin(), right_larger.end());
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            ans += left_smaller[i]*right_larger[i];
            ans += left_larger[i]*right_smaller[i];
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[30/07/24, 4:48:57 PM] Satvik Saini: long maximumSum(vector<long> a, long m) {
    int n = a.size();
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        a[i] = a[i]%m;
    }
    long long sum = 0, ans = 0;
    int i = 0, j = 0;
    while(j < n){
        sum += a[j];
        while(sum >= m){
            sum -= a[i];
            i++;
        }
        ans = max(ans, sum);
        j++;
    }
    return ans;
}
[30/07/24, 4:51:23 PM] Satvik Saini: void solve()
{
    ll N,M;
    ll x,prefix=0,maxim=0;
    cin>>N>>M;
    set<ll> S;
    S.insert(0);
    for(int i=1;i<=N;i++){
        cin>>x;
        prefix = (prefix + x)%M;
        maxim = max(maxim,prefix);
        set<ll>::iterator  it = S.lower_bound(prefix+1);
        if( it != S.end() ){
            maxim = max(maxim,prefix - (*it) + M );
        }
        S.insert(prefix);
    }
    cout<<maxim<<endl;
}

[31/07/24, 9:06:43 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int optimalHeight(vector<vector<int>>& books, int shelfWidth, int i, int w, int h){
        // base case
        if(i == books.size()) return h;

        // recursive case
        // op1 : add it in the current shelf if possible
        int op1 = INT_MAX;
        if(books[i][0] + w <= shelfWidth){
            op1 = optimalHeight(books, shelfWidth, i+1, w+books[i][0], max(h, books[i][1]));
            if(books[i][1] <= h) return op1;
        }
        // op2 : add it in the new shelf
        int op2 = h + optimalHeight(books, shelfWidth, i+1, books[i][0], books[i][1]);

        return min(op1, op2);
    }
public:
    int minHeightShelves(vector<vector<int>>& books, int shelfWidth) {
        return optimalHeight(books, shelfWidth, 0, 0, 0);
    }
};

[31/07/24, 9:23:22 AM] Satvik Saini: vector<vector<int>> memo;
int dp(int i,vector<vector<int>>& books,int shelfwidth,int width,int h)
{
    if(i>=books.size())
        return h;
    if(memo[i][width]!=-1)
        return memo[i][width];
    int q=h+dp(i+1,books,shelfwidth,books[i][0],books[i][1]);
    if(width+books[i][0]<=shelfwidth)
        q=min(q,dp(i+1,books,shelfwidth,width+books[i][0],max(h,books[i][1])));
    return memo[i][width]=q;
}
int minHeightShelves(vector<vector<int>>& books, int shelf_width) 
{
    memo.resize(books.size(),vector<int>(shelf_width+1,-1));
    return dp(0,books,shelf_width,0,0);
}

[31/07/24, 10:08:42 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/alphabet-board-path/
[31/07/24, 10:08:49 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    string alphabetBoardPath(string target) {
        vector<string> board = {"abcde", "fghij", "klmno", "pqrst", "uvwxy", "z"};
        queue<pair<string,pair<int,int>>> q;
        q.push({"",{0,0}});

        int idx = 0;

        vector<int> dx = {1, -1, 0, 0};
        vector<int> dy = {0, 0, 1, -1};
        vector<string> dir = {"D","U","R","L"};

        while(!q.empty()){
            string path = q.front().first;
            int i = q.front().second.first;
            int j = q.front().second.second;
            q.pop();

            if(idx == target.size()) return path;

            for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
                int ii = i + dx[k];
                int jj = j + dy[k];

                if((ii == 5 && jj == 0) || (ii >= 0 && ii < 5 && jj >= 0 && jj < 5)){
                    string new_path = path + dir[k];
                    if(board[ii][jj] == target[idx]){
                        new_path += "!";
                        idx++;
                    }
                    q.push({new_path,{ii,jj}});
                }
            }
        }
        return "";
    }
};

[07/08/24, 9:42:10 AM] Satvik Saini: void dfs1(int node, vector<vector<int>> adj, vector<int> &vis, stack<int> &stk){
        vis[node] = 1;
        for(auto it : adj[node]){
            if(!vis[it]){
                dfs1(it, adj, vis, stk);
            }
        }
        stk.push(node);
    }
    
    void dfs2(int node, vector<int> radj[], vector<int> &vis){
        vis[node] = 1;
        for(auto it : radj[node]){
            if(!vis[it]){
                dfs2(it, radj, vis);
            }
        }
    }
    
	public:
	//Function to find number of strongly connected components in the graph.
    int kosaraju(int n, vector<vector<int>>& adj)
    {
        vector<int> radj[n];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j : adj[i]){
                radj[j].push_back(i);
            }
        }
        
        stack<int> stk;
        vector<int> vis(n,0);
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(!vis[i]){
                dfs1(i, adj, vis, stk);
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) vis[i] = 0;
        
        int comp = 0;
        
        while(!stk.empty()){
            int top = stk.top();
            stk.pop();
            if(!vis[top]){
                dfs2(top, radj, vis);
                comp++;
            }
        }
        return comp;
    }

[07/08/24, 10:13:17 AM] Satvik Saini: void APUtil(vector<int> adj[], int u, bool visited[],
            int disc[], int low[], int& time, int parent,
            bool isAP[])
{
    // Count of children in DFS Tree
    int children = 0;

    // Mark the current node as visited
    visited[u] = true;

    // Initialize discovery time and low value
    disc[u] = low[u] = ++time;

    // Go through all vertices adjacent to this
    for (auto v : adj[u]) {
        // If v is not visited yet, then make it a child of u
        // in DFS tree and recur for it
        if (!visited[v]) {
            children++;
            APUtil(adj, v, visited, disc, low, time, u, isAP);

            // Check if the subtree rooted with v has
            // a connection to one of the ancestors of u
            low[u] = min(low[u], low[v]);

            // If u is not root and low value of one of
            // its child is more than discovery value of u.
            if (parent != -1 && low[v] >= disc[u])
                isAP[u] = true;
        }

        // Update low value of u for parent function calls.
        else if (v != parent)
            low[u] = min(low[u], disc[v]);
    }

    // If u is root of DFS tree and has two or more children.
    if (parent == -1 && children > 1)
        isAP[u] = true;
}

[08/08/24, 9:46:35 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool AliceWins(vector<int>& piles, int i, int j, int a, int b, bool Alice){
        // base case
        if(i > j) return a > b;

        // recursive case
        if(Alice){
            return AliceWins(piles, i+1, j, a+piles[i], b, 0) || AliceWins(piles, i, j-1, a+piles[j], b, 0);
        }
        return AliceWins(piles, i+1, j, a, b+piles[i], 1) || AliceWins(piles, i, j-1, a, b+piles[j], 1);
    }
public:
    bool stoneGame(vector<int>& piles) {
        return AliceWins(piles, 0, piles.size()-1, 0, 0, 1);
    }
};

[08/08/24, 9:51:20 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool AliceWins(vector<int>& piles, int i, int j, int a, bool Alice){
        // base case
        if(i > j){
            int b = accumulate(piles.begin(), piles.end(), 0) - a;
            return a > b;
        }

        // recursive case
        if(Alice){
            return AliceWins(piles, i+1, j, a+piles[i], 0) || AliceWins(piles, i, j-1, a+piles[j], 0);
        }
        return AliceWins(piles, i+1, j, a, 1) || AliceWins(piles, i, j-1, a, 1);
    }
public:
    bool stoneGame(vector<int>& piles) {
        return AliceWins(piles, 0, piles.size()-1, 0, 1);
    }
};

[08/08/24, 9:58:13 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    bool stoneGame(vector<int>& piles) {
        int n = piles.size();
        vector<vector<int>>dp(n, vector<int>(n));
        
        for(int gap = 0; gap < n; gap++)
            for(int i = 0, j = gap; j < n; i++, j++){
                if(gap == 0) dp[i][j] = piles[i];
                else if(gap == 1) dp[i][j] = max(piles[i], piles[j]);
                else{
                    int case1 = piles[i] + min(dp[i+2][j], dp[i+1][j-1]);
                    int case2 = piles[j] + min(dp[i+1][j-1], dp[i][j-2]);
                    dp[i][j] = max(case1, case2); // maximum of these 2 cases
                }
            }
        return dp[0][n-1];
    }
};
[08/08/24, 9:58:16 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int dp[1005][1005];
    
    int f(int l, int r, vector <int> &piles) {
        if(l == r-1) return max(piles[l], piles[r]);
        
        if(dp[l][r] != -1) return dp[l][r];
        
        int ifleft = piles[l] + max(f(l+2, r, piles), f(l+1, r-1, piles));
        int ifright = piles[r] + max(f(l+1, r-1, piles), f(l, r-2, piles));
        
        return dp[l][r] = max(ifleft, ifright);
    }
    bool stoneGame(vector<int>& piles) {
        int l = 0, r = piles.size()-1;
        memset(dp, -1, sizeof(dp));
        int alex = f(l, r, piles);
        int sum = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<piles.size();i++) sum += piles[i];

        return alex > (sum - alex);
    }
};
[08/08/24, 9:59:22 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/stone-game/solutions/298170/c-very-intuitive-solution/
[08/08/24, 10:02:09 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ** Just return true**

Alex is first to pick pile.
piles.length is even, and this lead to an interesting fact:
Alex can always pick odd piles or always pick even piles!

For example,
If Alex wants to pick even indexed piles piles[0], piles[2], ....., piles[n-2],
he picks first piles[0], then Lee can pick either piles[1] or piles[n - 1].
Every turn, Alex can always pick even indexed piles and Lee can only pick odd indexed piles.

In the description, we know that sum(piles) is odd.
If sum(piles[even]) > sum(piles[odd]), Alex just picks all evens and wins.
If sum(piles[even]) < sum(piles[odd]), Alex just picks all odds and wins.

So, Alex always defeats Lee in this game.

[08/08/24, 10:07:30 AM] Satvik Saini: // class Solution {
// public:

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> shortestDistanceAfterQueries(int n, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {
        // vector<int> ans;
        // vector<int> adj[n];
        // vector<int> distMap(n);
        // for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
        //     adj[i].push_back(i+1);
        //     distMap[i] = n-i-1;
        // }
        // for(auto qu : queries){
        //     adj[qu[0]].push_back(qu[1]);
        //     queue<pair<int,int>> q;
        //     q.push({0,0});

        //     while(!q.empty()){
        //         int node = q.front().first;
        //         int dist = q.front().second;
        //         q.pop();

        //         if(node == n-1){
        //             ans.push_back(dist);
        //             break;
        //         }

        //         for(auto it : adj[node]){
        //             q.push({it,dist+1});
        //         }
        //     }
        // }
        // return ans;

        vector<int> ans;
        vector<vector<pair<int, int>>> adj(n);

        // Initialize the adjacency list with the initial roads
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; ++i) {
            adj[i].push_back({i + 1, 1});
        }
        
        // Function to find the shortest path using Dijkstra's algorithm
        auto dijkstra = [&](int start) {
            vector<int> dist(n, INT_MAX);
            // priority_queue<pair<int, int>, vector<pair<int, int>>, greater<pair<int, int>>> q;
            queue<pair<int,int>> q;
            dist[start] = 0;
            q.push({0, start});
            
            while (!q.empty()) {
                int d = q.front().first;
                int node = q.front().second;
                q.pop();
                
                if (d > dist[node]) continue;
                
                for (const auto& neighbor : adj[node]) {
                    int nextNode = neighbor.first;
                    int weight = neighbor.second;
                    if (dist[node] + weight < dist[nextNode]) {
                        dist[nextNode] = dist[node] + weight;
                        q.push({dist[nextNode], nextNode});
                    }
                }
            }
            
            return dist;
        };
        
        // Compute initial shortest path distances from node 0
        vector<int> dist = dijkstra(0);

        // Process each query and update the adjacency list
        for (const auto& query : queries) {
            int u = query[0];
            int v = query[1];
            adj[u].push_back({v, 1});
            // Recompute shortest path distances from node 0 after adding new road
            dist = dijkstra(0);
            ans.push_back(dist[n - 1]);
        }
        
        return ans;
    }
};

public:
    void print(vector<vector<int>>& dist){
        for(int i=0 ; i<dist[0].size() ; i++) cout << dist[0][i] << " ";
        cout << endl;
    }
    vector<int> shortestDistanceAfterQueries(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<int> res;
        vector<vector<int>> dist(n, vector<int>(n, 0));
        for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
            int cnt = 0;
            for(int j=i ; j<n ; j++){
                dist[i][j] = cnt;
                cnt++;
            }
        }
        for(auto edge : edges){
            int u = edge[0];
            int v = edge[1];
            dist[u][v] = 1;
            for(int i=0 ; i<u ; i++){
                for(int j=v ; j<n ; j++){
                    if(dist[i][j] > dist[i][u] + 1 + dist[v][j]){
                        dist[i][j] = dist[i][u] + 1 + dist[v][j];
                    }
                }
            }
            int new_dist = dist[0][u] + dist[v][n-1] + 1;
            dist[0][n-1] = min(dist[0][n-1], new_dist);
            print(dist);
            res.push_back(dist[0][n-1]);
        }

        return res;

    }
};

[09/08/24, 10:06:06 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int maxSumSubmatrix(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int k) {
        int n = matrix.size();
        int m = matrix[0].size();

        int ans = INT_MIN;
        
        for(int r1=0;r1<n;r1++){
            vector<int> temp(m,0);
            for(int r2=0;r2<n;r2++){
                for(int c=0;c<m;c++){
                    temp[c] += matrix[r2][c];
                }
                int sum = 0, maxSum = INT_MIN;
                for(int c=0;c<m;c++){
                    sum += temp[c];
                    if(sum <= k && sum > ans) ans = sum;
                    if(sum < 0) sum = 0;
                }
                if(sum <= k && sum > ans) ans = sum;

            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};

[09/08/24, 10:14:21 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int findMaxLength(vector<int>& nums) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mpp;
        mpp[0] = -1;
        int cnt = 0;
        int maxi = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<nums.size() ; i++){
            if(nums[i] == 0) cnt ++;
            else if(nums[i] == 1) cnt--;
            if(mpp.find(cnt) == mpp.end()) mpp[cnt] = i;
            else{
                maxi = max(maxi,i-mpp[cnt]);
            }
        }
        if(cnt == 0) return nums.size();
        
        return maxi;
        
    }
};

[09/08/24, 2:23:42 PM] Satvik Saini: class unionfind{        //most optimised way of implementing disjoint sets
    public: 
    int count;
    vector <int> root;
    vector <int> rank;
    unionfind(int n){
        count = n;
        root = vector <int> (n);
        rank = vector <int> (n);
        
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            root[i]=i;
            rank[i]=1;
        }
    }
    
    void unionset(int x, int y){        
        int rootx=find(x), rooty=find(y);
        if(rootx!=rooty){
            if(rank[rootx]>rank[rooty])
                root[rooty]=rootx;
            else if(rank[rooty]>rank[rootx])
                root[rootx]=rooty;
            else{
                root[rooty]=rootx;
                rank[rootx]++;
            }
            count--;
        }
    }
    
    int find(int x){
        if(x==root[x])
            return root[x];
        return root[x]=find(root[x]);
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    string smallestStringWithSwaps(string s, vector<vector<int>>& pairs) {
        int n = s.length();
        
        if(pairs.size()==0)          //if there are no edges at all, we simply return back the string
            return s;
        
        unionfind uf(n);             //to create n-sized arrays(root, rank)
        
        for(auto pair: pairs)        //make the union of elements
            uf.unionset(pair[0], pair[1]);
        
        map<int, string> m;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){      //adding the char one by one in map corresponding to root
            int root = uf.find(i);
            uf.root[i] = root;
            m[root] += s[i];
        }
        
        if(uf.count==1){             //if the whole graph is connected, simply return string after sorting
            sort(s.begin(), s.end());
            return s;
        }
        
        for(auto pairs:m){           //if whole graph is not completely connected, sort the char in disconnected graphs
            int i=pairs.first;
            string s=pairs.second;
            sort(s.begin(), s.end(), greater<char>());
            m[i]=s;
        }
        
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){     //storing the back into the string
            int root=uf.find(i);
            s[i]=m[root].back();
            m[root].pop_back();
        }
        return s;                   //return the resultant string
    }
};
[09/08/24, 2:23:49 PM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/smallest-string-with-swaps/description/

[09/08/24, 4:23:36 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: You are given a array A of N integers. You will have to pick 3 subarrays form the array l1, l2, and l3. The subarray l1 must be a prefix and l3 must be suffix. [09/08/24, 7:29:10 PM] Satvik Saini: vector<int> solution(int a, int b, vector<int> c){
    vector<int> res(a, 0);
    int curr = 0;
    int it = 0;
    while(true){
        curr += b;
        if(curr > a) return res;
        if(it < c.size()){
            int temp = curr + c[it] - 1;
            for(curr:curr<=min(a,temp);curr++){
                res[curr-1] = it+1;
            }
            curr--;
            it++;
        }
        else return vector<int>(-1);
    }
    return res;
}
[09/08/24, 7:33:56 PM] Satvik Saini: int cntSubsequence(string s, string t, int i, int j, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
    // base case
    if(j == t.length()) return 1;
    if(i == s.length()) return 0;

    // lookup
    if(dp[i][j] != -1) return dp[i][j];

    // recursive case
    int cnt = 0;
    if(s[i] == t[j]){
        cnt += cntSubsequence(s, t, i+1, j+1, dp);
    }
    cnt += cntSubsequence(s, t, i+1, j, dp);
    return dp[i][j] = cnt;

}

int solution(string s, string t){
    int n = s.length();
    int m = t.length();
    if(m > n) return 0;

    vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1, vector<int>(m+1, -1));

    return cntSubsequence(s, t, 0, 0, dp);
}

#include<vector>
#include<algorithm> 
using namespace std;
int max(vector<int>&profits, ){

    int n = profist.size();
    int m = vec.size();
    int maxProfit = 0;

    if(n == 0 || m == 0){
        return 0;
    }
    vector<int> dp(1 << m, 0);
    for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
        vector<int> new_dp = dp;
        for(int mask = 0; mask < (1 << m) ; mask--){
            for(int j=0 ; j<m ; j++){
                if((mask & (1 << j)) == 0){
                    bool is_Hired = true;
                    for(int k = 0 ; k < vec[i].size() ; k++){
                        if(vec[i][k] && !vec[j][k]){
                            is_Hired = false;
                            break;
                        }
                    }
                    if(is_hired){
                        new_dp[mask | (1 << j)] = max(new_dp[mask | (1 << j)], dp[mask] + profits[i]);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        dp = new_dp;
    }
    for(int i=0 ; i < (1 << m) ; i++){
        maxProfit = max(maxProfit, dp[i]);
    }

}

[09/08/24, 9:08:08 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

bool chkValid(const vector<string>& eq, unordered_map<char, int>& l2d) {
    vector<long long> nums;
    for (const string& p : eq) {
        long long num = 0;
        for (char c : p) {
            num = num * 10 + l2d[c];
        }
        nums.push_back(num);
    }
    return nums[0] + nums[1] == nums[2];
}

int dfs(vector<string>& eq, unordered_map<char, int>& l2d, unordered_set<int>& tD, vector<char>& let, int pos) {
    if (pos == let.size()) {
        return chkValid(eq, l2d) ? 1 : 0;
    }
    
    char l = let[pos];
    int count = 0;
    for (int d = 0; d < 10; ++d) {
        if (tD.count(d)) continue;
        if (d == 0 && find_if(eq.begin(), eq.end(), [&](string& p) { return p[0] == l; }) != eq.end()) continue;
        
        tD.insert(d);
        l2d[l] = d;
        
        count += dfs(eq, l2d, tD, let, pos + 1);
        
        tD.erase(d);
        l2d.erase(l);
    }
    
    return count;
}

int cntCryptarithmSolutions(vector<string> eq) {
    unordered_set<char> allLet;
    for (const string& p : eq) {
        for (char c : p) {
            allLet.insert(c);
        }
    }
    
    vector<char> let(allLet.begin(), allLet.end());
    unordered_map<char, int> l2d;
    unordered_set<int> tD;
    
    return dfs(eq, l2d, tD, let, 0);
}

[09/08/24, 9:20:03 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: bool isValidMapping(const vector<string>& crypt, const int mapping[26]) {
    long long nums[3] = {0, 0, 0};

    for (int i = 0; i < 3; ++i) {
        const string& word = crypt[i];
        if (mapping[word[0] - 'A'] == 0 && word.length() > 1) {
            return false; // Leading zeros are not allowed for multi-digit numbers
        }
        for (char c : word) {
            nums[i] = nums[i] * 10 + mapping[c - 'A'];
        }
    }
    
    return nums[0] + nums[1] == nums[2];
}

int countValidSolutions(const vector<string>& crypt, const vector<char>& uniqueLetters, int idx, int usedDigits, int mapping[26]) {
    if (idx == uniqueLetters.size()) {
        return isValidMapping(crypt, mapping) ? 1 : 0;
    }
    
    int count = 0;
    for (int digit = 0; digit <= 9; ++digit) {
        if (!(usedDigits & (1 << digit))) {
            mapping[uniqueLetters[idx] - 'A'] = digit;
            count += countValidSolutions(crypt, uniqueLetters, idx + 1, usedDigits | (1 << digit), mapping);
        }
    }
    
    return count;
}

int solution(vector<string> crypt) {
    bool seen[26] = {false};
    for (const string& word : crypt) {
        for (char c : word) {
            seen[c - 'A'] = true;
        }
    }
    
    vector<char> uniqueLetters;
    for (int i = 0; i < 26; ++i) {
        if (seen[i]) uniqueLetters.push_back('A' + i);
    }
    
    int mapping[26] = {0}; // Fixed-size array for mapping characters to digits
    return countValidSolutions(crypt, uniqueLetters, 0, 0, mapping);
}

[10/08/24, 10:50:23 AM] Satvik Saini: class DisjointSet{
    unordered_map<int,int> parent, rank;
    public:
    DisjointSet(int n){
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            parent[i] = i;
            rank[i] = 1;
        }
    }
    int findParent(int x){
        if(parent[x] == x) return x;
        return parent[x] = findParent(parent[x]);
    }
    void unionSet(int x, int y){
        int lx = findParent(x);
        int ly = findParent(y);

        if(lx != ly){
            int rx = rank[x];
            int ry = rank[y];

            if(rx > ry){
                parent[ly] = lx;
                rank[lx] += ry;
            }
            else{
                parent[lx] = ly;
                rank[ly] += rx;
            }
        }
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    int containVirus(vector<vector<int>>& isInfected) {
        int n = isInfected.size();
        int m = isInfected[0].size();

        DisjointSet ds(n*m);

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(isInfected[i][j] == 1){
                    int cellIdx = i*m + j;
                    while(j < m){
                        if(isInfected[i][j] == 1){
                            int neighbourIdx = i*m + j;
                            ds.unionSet(cellIdx, neighbourIdx);
                        }
                        j++;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                if(isInfected[i][j] == 1){
                    int cellIdx = i*m + j;
                    while(i < n){
                        if(isInfected[i][j] == 1){
                            int neighbourIdx = i*m + j;
                            ds.unionSet(cellIdx, neighbourIdx);
                        }
                        i++;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
};

    unordered_map<int,int> parent, rank;
    public:
    DisjointSet(int n){
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            parent[i] = i;
            rank[i] = 1;
        }
    }
    int findParent(int x){
        if(parent[x] == x) return x;
        return parent[x] = findParent(parent[x]);
    }
    void unionSet(int x, int y){
        int lx = findParent(x);
        int ly = findParent(y);

        if(lx != ly){
            int rx = rank[x];
            int ry = rank[y];

            if(rx > ry){
                parent[ly] = lx;
                rank[lx] += ry;
            }
            else{
                parent[lx] = ly;
                rank[ly] += rx;
            }
        }
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    int containVirus(vector<vector<int>>& isInfected) {
        int n = isInfected.size();
        int m = isInfected[0].size();

        DisjointSet ds(n*m);

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(isInfected[i][j] == 1){
                    int cellIdx = i*m + j;
                    while(j < m && isInfected[i][j] == 1){
                        int neighbourIdx = i*m + j;
                        ds.unionSet(cellIdx, neighbourIdx);
                        j++;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                if(isInfected[i][j] == 1){
                    int cellIdx = i*m + j;
                    while(i < n && isInfected[i][j] == 1){
                        int neighbourIdx = i*m + j;
                        ds.unionSet(cellIdx, neighbourIdx);
                        i++;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
};

[11/08/24, 9:57:31 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int MOD = 1e9 + 7;
    int splitPairs(vector<int>& nums, int i, int prevA, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        int prevB = (i > 0) ? nums[i-1]-prevA : 2001;
        // base case
        if(i == nums.size()) return 1;

        // lookup
        if(dp[i][prevA] != -1) return dp[i][prevA];
        if(nums[i] < prevA) return dp[i][prevA] = 0;

        // recursive case
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int j=0;j<=nums[i];j++){
            int num1 = j;
            int num2 = nums[i] - j;
            if(num1 >= prevA && num2 <= prevB){
                cnt = (cnt + splitPairs(nums, i+1, num1, dp)) % MOD;
            }
        }
        return dp[i][prevA] = cnt;
    }
public:
    int countOfPairs(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1, vector<int>(2001,-1));
        return splitPairs(nums, 0, 0, dp);
    }
};
[11/08/24, 10:05:01 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int MOD = 1e9 + 7;
    int splitPairs(vector<int>& nums, int i, int prevA, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        int prevB = (i > 0) ? nums[i-1]-prevA : 1001;
        // base case
        if(i == nums.size()) return 1;

        // lookup
        if(dp[i][prevA] != -1) return dp[i][prevA];

        // recursive case
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int j=prevA;j<=nums[i];j++){
            int num1 = j;
            int num2 = nums[i] - j;
            if(num1 >= prevA && num2 <= prevB){
                cnt = (cnt + splitPairs(nums, i+1, num1, dp)) % MOD;
            }
        }
        return dp[i][prevA] = cnt;
    }
public:
    int countOfPairs(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int maxi = *max_element(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n+1, vector<int>(maxi+1,-1));
        return splitPairs(nums, 0, 0, dp);
    }
};
[11/08/24, 10:06:29 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎You deleted this message.
[11/08/24, 10:11:57 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
    public static long modulo = (long) 1e9 + 7;
    public static Long[][] dp;
    public int countOfPairs(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        dp = new Long[n + 1][51];
        return (int) solve(0, nums, 0, 50);
    }
    public static long solve(int i, int[] nums, int el1, int el2) {
        if(i >= nums.length) {
            return 1;
        }
        if(dp[i][el1] != null) return dp[i][el1];
        long ans = 0;
        int l = nums[i];
        for(int j = 0; j <= l; j++){
            int u = j;
            int v = l - j;
            if(v > el2 || u < el1) continue; 
            ans = (ans + solve(i + 1, nums, u, v)) % modulo;
        }
        return dp[i][el1] = ans;
    }
}
[11/08/24, 10:13:48 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int dp[2001][2001],sp[2001][2001],mod=1e9+7;
    int countOfPairs(vector<int>& nums) {
        memset(dp,0,sizeof(dp));
        int n=nums.size();
        for(int i=0;i<=1000;i++) dp[n][i]=1;
        for(int i=1000;i>=0;i--) sp[n][i]=(dp[n][i]+sp[n][i+1])%mod;
        for(int ind=n-1;ind>=0;ind--) {
            for(int prev=1000;prev>=0;prev--) {
                int sum=0,mx=0;
                if(ind!=0) mx=max(nums[ind]-nums[ind-1]+prev,prev);
                if(ind==0 && prev<=nums[ind]) 
                    sum=(sum+sp[ind+1][prev]-sp[ind+1][nums[ind]+1])%mod;
                else if(ind!=0 && mx<=nums[ind]) 
                    sum=(sum+sp[ind+1][mx]-sp[ind+1][nums[ind]+1])%mod;
                dp[ind][prev]=sum;
                sp[ind][prev]=(dp[ind][prev]+sp[ind][prev+1])%mod;
            }
        }
        return dp[0][0];
    }
};
