[12/08/24, 8:36:33 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int count, n;
    vector<int> f;
    int regionsBySlashes(vector<string>& grid) {
        n = grid.size();
        count = n * n * 4;
        for (int i = 0; i < n * n * 4; ++i) f.push_back(i);

        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            for (int j = 0; j < n; ++j) {
                if (grid[i][j] != '/') {
                    uni(g(i, j, 0), g(i, j, 1));
                    uni(g(i, j, 2), g(i, j, 3));
                }
                else if (grid[i][j] != '\\') {
                    uni(g(i, j, 0), g(i, j, 3));
                    uni(g(i, j, 2), g(i, j, 1));
                }

                if (i > 0) uni(g(i - 1, j, 2), g(i, j, 0));
                if (j > 0) uni(g(i, j - 1, 1), g(i, j, 3));
            }
        }
        return count;
    }

    int find(int x) {
        if (x != f[x]) {
            f[x] = find(f[x]);
        }
        return f[x];
    }
    void uni(int x, int y) {
        x = find(x);
        y = find(y);
        if (x != y) {
            f[x] = y;
            count--;
        }
    }
    int g(int i, int j, int k) {
        return (i * n + j) * 4 + k;
    }
};
[12/08/24, 8:52:01 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    class comparasion {
        public:
        bool operator()(pair<int, int>& a, pair<int, int>& b) {//always put the smallest and shortest sequence on the top of the heap
            if(a.first == b.first) return a.second > b.second;
            return a.first > b.first;
        };
    };
    bool isPossible(vector<int>& nums) {
        priority_queue<pair<int, int>, vector<pair<int, int>>, comparasion> qe;
        int i = 0;
        while(i < nums.size()) {
            if(qe.empty()) {
                qe.push({nums[i], 1});
                i++;
            }
            else {
                pair<int, int> tmp = qe.top();
                if(nums[i] == tmp.first) {
                    qe.push({nums[i], 1});//add a new sequence
                    i++;
                }
                else if(nums[i] == tmp.first + 1) {
                    qe.pop();
                    qe.push({nums[i], tmp.second + 1});//update the top of the heap
                    i++;
                }
                else {
                    if(tmp.second < 3) {//false
                        return false;
                    }
                    qe.pop();
                }
            }
        }
        while(!qe.empty()) {
            if(qe.top().second < 3) {
                return false;
            }
            qe.pop();
        }
        return true;
    }
};

[12/08/24, 2:13:14 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> res;
    void dfs(int i,vector<vector<int>> adj, vector<int>& visited, vector<int>&dfs_visited ){

        visited[i] = 1;
        dfs_visited[i] = 1;

        for(auto neighbour : adj[i]){
            if(dfs_visited[neighbour] == 1 && visited[neighbour] == 0){
                    res =  {i,neighbour};
                    return;
            }
            if(visited[neighbour] == 1 && dfs_visited[neighbour] == 0){
                res =  {i,neighbour};
                return;
            }
            if(visited[neighbour] == 0){
                 dfs(neighbour,adj,visited,dfs_visited);
            }
        }
        dfs_visited[i] = 0;
    }
    vector<int> findRedundantDirectedConnection(vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        int n = edges.size();
        vector<int> visited(n,0);
        vector<int> dfs_visited(n,0);
        vector<vector<int>> adj;
        for(auto it : edges){
            adj[it[0]].push_back(it[1]);
        }
        dfs(0,adj,visited,dfs_visited);
        return res;
        
    }
};

[13/08/24, 9:07:25 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    void solve(vector<int>& arr, int target,vector<vector<int>> &ans,vector<int> out,int i){
        //base case
        if(target == 0){
            ans.push_back(out);
            return;
        }

        //recursive case
        for(int j=i;j<arr.size();j++){
            if(j > i && arr[j] == arr[j-1]) continue;

            if(arr[j] <= target){
                out.push_back(arr[j]);
                solve(arr, target - arr[j], ans, out, j+1);
                out.pop_back();
            }    
        }
    }

    vector<vector<int>> combinationSum2(vector<int>& candidates, int target) {
        sort(candidates.begin(),candidates.end());
        vector<vector<int>> ans;
        vector<int> output;
        solve(candidates,target,ans,output,0);
        return ans;
    }
};
[13/08/24, 9:10:43 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    void combisum(vector<int> arr, int target,int i,vector<int> combination,vector<vector<int>>& ans){
        // base case
       
            if(target == 0){
            ans.push_back(combination);
            return;
            }     
        //recursive case

        for(int j=i ; j<arr.size() ; j++){

            if(i!=j and arr[j] == arr[j-1] )  continue;
            if(target - arr[j] >= 0){
            combination.push_back(arr[j]);
            combisum(arr,target-arr[j],j+1,combination,ans);
            combination.pop_back();
            }

        }
            
    }
    vector<vector<int>> combinationSum2(vector<int>& candidates, int target) {

        vector<vector<int>>  ans;
        vector<int> combination;
        sort(candidates.begin(),candidates.end());

        combisum(candidates,target,0,combination,ans);

        return ans;


        
    }
};

public:
    vector<int> res;
    void dfs(int i,vector<vector<int>>& adj, vector<int>& visited, vector<int>&dfs_visited ){

                cout << "indgeree";
                res =  {i,neighbour};
                return;

                 dfs(neighbour,adj,visited,dfs_visited);

[13/08/24, 9:31:37 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int find(int u,vector<int> &parent)
    {
        if(parent[u]<0)
            return u;
        
        parent[u]=find(parent[u],parent);
        return parent[u];
    }
    
    bool union_by_weight(int u,int v,vector<int> &parent)
    {
        int pu=find(u,parent);
        int pv=find(v,parent);
        
        if(pu==pv)
            return 0;
        
        if(parent[pu]<parent[pv])
        {
            parent[pu]+=parent[pv];
            parent[pv]=pu;   
        }
        else
        {
            parent[pv]+=parent[pu];
            parent[pu]=pv;
        }
        return 1;
    }
    
    vector<int> findRedundantDirectedConnection(vector<vector<int>>& e) {
        
        int i,n=e.size();
        vector<int> parent(n+1,-1);
        vector<int> in(n+1,-1);
        int e1=-1,e2=-1;
        
        for(i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(in[e[i][1]]!=-1)         // indegree 2
            {
                e2=in[e[i][1]];         // first edge causing indegree 2
                e1=i;                   // second edge causing indegree 2
                break;
            }
            in[e[i][1]]=i;    
        }
    
        for(i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            if(i==e1)                                        //ignore edge causing indegree
                continue;
            
            if(!union_by_weight(e[i][0],e[i][1],parent))     //cycle is present
            {
                if(e1!=-1)                                   //indegree 2 , wrong edge ignored
                    return e[e2];
                else                                         //indegree 1 , remove edge causing cycle
                    return e[i];
            }
        }
        return e[e1];
    }
};

[13/08/24, 7:09:40 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: def remove_duplicates(numbers):
    seen = set()  # To keep track of the numbers we've already encountered
    unique_numbers = []
    
    for num in numbers:
        if num >= 0 and num not in seen:  # Check if the number is positive and not already seen
            unique_numbers.append(num)
            seen.add(num)
    
    return unique_numbers

def main():
    # Prompt the user to input a list of numbers
    input_numbers = input("").strip()
    if input_numbers:  # Check if the input is not empty
        numbers_list = list(map(int, input_numbers.split()))

        # Process the list to remove duplicates
        result = remove_duplicates(numbers_list)

        # Print the unique numbers in the order they first appeared
        print(" ".join(map(str, result)))

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

    ans = []
    
    for i in range(len(org)):
        if i % 2 == 0:
            ans.append(org[i])
        else:
            ans.append(org[i] + rev[i])
    
    return ans

ip = input()
orgL = list(map(int, ip.split()))

[15/08/24, 8:35:43 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool isPossible(vector<int>& nums, int k, int mid){
        // count the no of pairs having dist <= mid
        // return count >= k;
        int n = nums.size();
        int cnt = 0, j = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            while(j < n && nums[j] - nums[i] <= mid) j++;
            cnt += (j-i-1);
        }
        return cnt >= k;
    }
public:
    int smallestDistancePair(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int n = nums.size();
        int s = INT_MAX,e=nums[n-1]-nums[0];
        for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
            s = min(s, nums[i+1]-nums[i]);
        }

        int ans;
        while(s <= e){
            int mid = (s+e)/2;
            if(isPossible(nums, k, mid)){
                ans = mid;
                e = mid-1;
            }
            else s = mid+1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[16/08/24, 10:47:55 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> size;
    pair<int, int> dfs1(vector<vector<int>>& adj, int src,
                        vector<int>& visited) {
        // this is called to calculate the sum of dist. of all nodes to root

        // then this values is ued to calculate sum of distances of root->left
        // ie root->child

        // all the nodes in the subtree of root->child 's distance will decrease
        // by one when we are calculating sum of distances of root->child

        // and distaces of al the other nodes other than the childs subtree,
        // will increase by one

        // sumOfDist_child = sumOfDist_parent - size of subtree of _child + ( N
        // - size of subtree of _child)

        visited[src] = true;
        pair<int, int> p = {
            1, 0}; // size of subtree at src , sumOfDist of all nodes to root
        for (int x : adj[src]) {
            if (visited[x] == false) {
                pair<int, int> p_c = dfs1(adj, x, visited);
                p.second += p_c.second + p_c.first;
                p.first += p_c.first;
                size[x] = p_c.first;
            }
        }
        return p;
    }
    vector<int> ans;
    void dfs2(vector<vector<int>>& adj, int src, int sumOfDistfromSrc,
              vector<int>& visited, int n) {

        cout << src << " : ";
        ans[src] = sumOfDistfromSrc;
        visited[src] = 1;
        for (int x : adj[src]) {
            cout << x << ",";
            if (visited[x] == 0) {
                int sumOfDistToChild =
                    sumOfDistfromSrc - size[x] + (n - size[x]);
                cout << sumOfDistToChild << " ";
                dfs2(adj, x, sumOfDistToChild, visited, n);
            }
        }
        cout << endl;
    }
    vector<int> sumOfDistancesInTree(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<vector<int>> adj(n);
        for (auto& it : edges) {
            adj[it[0]].push_back(it[1]);
            adj[it[1]].push_back(it[0]);
        }
        vector<int> visited(n, 0);
        size.resize(n);
        ans.resize(n);
        pair<int, int> p = dfs1(adj, 0, visited);
        cout << p.second;
        fill(visited.begin(),visited.end(), 0);
        dfs2(adj, 0, p.second, visited, n);
        return ans;
    }
};

class Solution {
    vector<vector<TreeNode*>> t;
    void buildTree(string s, int i, int depth){
        // base case
        if(i == s.length()) return;

        // recursive case
        int n = 0;
        while(i < s.length() && s[i]>='0' && s[i]<='9'){
            n = n * 10 + (s[i]-'0');
            i++;
        }
        TreeNode* root = new TreeNode(n);
        t[depth].push_back(root);
        if (depth > 0) {
            TreeNode* parent = t[depth - 1].back();
            if (!parent->left) parent->left = root;
            else parent->right = root;
        }
        int d = 0;
        while(i < s.length() && s[i] == '-'){d++;i++;}
        buildTree(s, i, d);
    }
public:
    TreeNode* recoverFromPreorder(string traversal) {
        int maxDepth = 0, cnt = 0;
        for(char ch : traversal){
            if(ch) cnt++;
            else{
                maxDepth = max(maxDepth, cnt);
                cnt = 0;
            }
        }
        t.resize(maxDepth+1);
        buildTree(traversal, 0, 0);
        return t[0][0];
    }
};

// d    nodes
// 0 -> 1
// 1 -> 2 5
// 2 -> 3 4 6 7

        string longestPalindrome(string s) {
            string t = transform(s);
            int l = 0, r = 0, n = t.length();
            int maxLen = 0, centre;
            vector<int> p(n);
            p[0] = 0;

            for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
                int k;
                if(i > r){
                    k = 0;
                }
                else{
                    int j = l + (r - i);
                    if(j - p[j] > l){
                        p[i] = p[j];
                        continue;
                    }
                    else{
                        k = r-i;
                    }
                }

                while(i-k >= 0 && i+k < n && t[i-k] == t[i+k]){
                    k++;
                }
                k--;
                p[i] = k;
                if(p[i] > maxLen){
                    maxLen = p[i];
                    centre = i/2;
                }
                if(k+i > r){
                    l = i - k;
                    r = i + k;
                }
            }
            return s.substr(centre - (maxLen / 2),maxLen);
        }
[17/08/24, 10:57:26 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
#define lli long long

using namespace std;

vector <lli> palindromes;

lli cal(string p)
{
    string p1 = p;
    reverse(p1.begin(), p1.end());
    p += p1;
    lli ans = 0;
    for ( int i = p.size() - 1; i >= 0; i-- ) {
        if ( p[i] == '1' ) ans += (1LL << ((int)p.size() - 1 - i));
    }
    return ans;
}

lli cal1(string p)
{
    string p1 = p;
    reverse(p1.begin(), p1.end());
    p1.erase(p1.begin());
    p += p1;
    int ans = 0;
    for ( int i = p.size() - 1; i >= 0; i-- ) {
        if ( p[i] == '1' ) ans += (1LL << ((int)p.size() - 1 - i));
    }
    return ans;
}

void f(int idx, string p, int flag)
{
    if ( idx == 16 ) {
        palindromes.push_back(cal(p));
        if ( !p.empty() ) palindromes.push_back(cal1(p));
        return;
    }
    if ( flag == 0 ) {
        f(idx + 1, p, 0);
        f(idx + 1, p + "1", 1);
    }
    else {
        f(idx + 1, p + "0", 1);
        f(idx + 1, p + "1", 1);
    }
}

int main()
{
    int t;
    lli idx, ans, n;
    cin >> t;
    assert(t >= 1 && t <= 100000);

    f(0, "", 0);
    sort(palindromes.begin(), palindromes.end());
    
    while ( t-- ) {
        cin >> n;
        assert(n >= 0 && n <= 2000000000);
        idx = lower_bound(palindromes.begin(), palindromes.end(), n) - palindromes.begin();
        ans = palindromes[idx] - n;
        if ( idx > 0 ) ans = min(ans, n - palindromes[idx - 1]);
        cout << ans << endl;
    }
    
    return 0;
}
[17/08/24, 10:57:26 AM] Satvik Saini: void dfs(int node, vector<vector<int>> &adj, vector<int> &outDeg, vector<int> &path) {
    while (outDeg[node] > 0) {
        int nextNode = adj[node].back();
        adj[node].pop_back();
        outDeg[node]--;
        dfs(nextNode, adj, outDeg, path);
    }
    path.push_back(node);
}

vector<int> eulerPathInDirectedGraph(int n, vector<vector<int>> edges) {
    vector<vector<int>> adj(n);
    vector<int> inDeg(n, 0), outDeg(n, 0);
    
    for (auto e : edges) {
        adj[e[0]].push_back(e[1]);
        outDeg[e[0]]++;
        inDeg[e[1]]++;
    }

    int startNode = 0, endNode = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (outDeg[i] > inDeg[i] + 1 || inDeg[i] > outDeg[i] + 1) return {};
        else if (outDeg[i] == inDeg[i] + 1) startNode++;
        else if (inDeg[i] == outDeg[i] + 1) endNode++;
    }

    if (!((startNode == 1 && endNode == 1) || (startNode == 0 && endNode == 0))) return {};

    
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (outDeg[i] > 0) {
            startNode = i;
            break;
        }
    }
    vector<int> path;
    dfs(startNode, adj, outDeg, path);
    reverse(path.begin(), path.end());
    return path;
}
[17/08/24, 10:57:26 AM] Satvik Saini: // Approach
// we cannot directly sort the array because i < j condition will not be maintained
// thus we use divide and conquer apporach, in which while conqouring, 
// we will maintain i at starting of the left array and right at starting of the right array

class Solution {

    int merge(vector<int> &arr, int low, int mid, int high) {

        int right = mid + 1;
        int cnt = 0;
        for (int i = low; i <= mid; i++) {
            while (right <= high && arr[i] > 2 * (long long)arr[right]){
                cnt += mid - i + 1;
                right++;
            }
        }

        vector<int> temp; 
        int left = low;      
        right = mid + 1; 

        while (left <= mid && right <= high) {
            if (arr[left] <= arr[right]) {
                temp.push_back(arr[left]);
                left++;
            }
            else {
                temp.push_back(arr[right]);
                right++;
            }
        }

        while (left <= mid) {
            temp.push_back(arr[left]);
            left++;
        }

        while (right <= high) {
            temp.push_back(arr[right]);
            right++;
        }

        for (int i = low; i <= high; i++) {
            arr[i] = temp[i - low];
        }
        return cnt;
    }

    int mergeSort(vector<int> &arr, int low, int high) {
        // base case
        if (low >= high) return 0;

        // recursive case
        int cnt = 0;
        int mid = (low + high) / 2 ;
        cnt += mergeSort(arr, low, mid); 
        cnt += mergeSort(arr, mid + 1, high); 
        cnt += merge(arr, low, mid, high); 
        return cnt;
    }

public:
    int reversePairs(vector<int>& nums) {
        return mergeSort(nums, 0, nums.size()-1);
    }
};
[17/08/24, 10:57:26 AM] Satvik Saini: void printCircuit(vector< vector<int> > adj) {
    unordered_map<int,int> edge_count;
 
    for (int i=0; i<adj.size(); i++) {
        edge_count[i] = adj[i].size();
    }
 
    if (!adj.size()) return;
    stack<int> curr_path;
    vector<int> circuit;
    curr_path.push(0);
    int curr_v = 0; 
 
    while (!curr_path.empty()) {
        if (edge_count[curr_v]) {
            curr_path.push(curr_v);
            int next_v = adj[curr_v].back();
            edge_count[curr_v]--;
            adj[curr_v].pop_back();
            curr_v = next_v;
        }
        else {
            circuit.push_back(curr_v);
            curr_v = curr_path.top();
            curr_path.pop();
        }
    }
    for (int i=circuit.size()-1; i>=0; i--) {
        cout << circuit[i];
    }
}
[17/08/24, 10:57:26 AM] Satvik Saini: printing EULER CIRCUIT in DIRECTED GRAPH 👆
[17/08/24, 10:57:26 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int MOD = 1e9 + 7;
    int cntPerm(int n, int lastIdx, int inversions, unordered_map<int,int> &mp, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        // base case
        if(n == lastIdx) return 1;

        // lookup
        if(dp[n][inversions] != -1) return dp[n][inversions];

        // recursive case
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<=n+1;i++){
            int temp = inversions + (n-i+1);
            if(temp < dp[0].size() && (mp.find(n+1) == mp.end() || temp == mp[n+1])){
                ans = (ans + cntPerm(n+1, lastIdx, temp, mp, dp)) % MOD;
            }
        }
        return dp[n][inversions] = ans;
    }
public:
    int numberOfPermutations(int n, vector<vector<int>>& requirements) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        int maxR = 0;
        for(auto r : requirements){
            mp[r[0]] = r[1];
            maxR = max(maxR, r[1]);
        }
        if(mp.find(0) != mp.end() && mp[0]>0) return 0;
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n, vector<int>(maxR+1,-1));
        return cntPerm(0, n-1, 0, mp, dp);
    }
};

[17/08/24, 11:32:19 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <cmath>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

int solve(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2, int xc, int yc, int R) {
    int count = 0;
    int R_squared = R * R;

    for (int x = max(x1, xc - R); x <= min(x2, xc + R); ++x) {
        int dx_squared = (x - xc) * (x - xc);
        if (dx_squared > R_squared) continue;

        int dy_max = sqrt(R_squared - dx_squared);
        int y_min = max(y1, yc - dy_max);
        int y_max = min(y2, yc + dy_max);

        count += (y_max - y_min + 1);
    }

    return count;
}

int main() {
    int x1 = -100000, y1 = -100000, x2 = 100000, y2 = 100000;
    int xc = 0, yc = 0, R = 100000;

    cout << "Count of points: " << solve(x1, y1, x2, y2, xc, yc, R) << endl;

    return 0;
}

[17/08/24, 12:15:57 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <bitset>
#include <algorithm>

const int MOD = 1000000007;

// Function to count the number of set bits in an integer
int countSetBits(int x) {
    return std::bitset<32>(x).count();  // Using bitset to count set bits
}

int countPossibleDecryptions(int N, int k) {
    std::vector<std::vector<int>> dp(k + 1, std::vector<int>(N + 1, 0));

    // Initial condition: In 0 steps, we can only be at number 1
    dp[0][1] = 1;

    for (int step = 0; step < k; ++step) {
        for (int num = 1; num <= N; ++num) {
            if (dp[step][num] > 0) {
                int nextNum = countSetBits(num);
                if (nextNum <= N) {
                    dp[step + 1][nextNum] = (dp[step + 1][nextNum] + dp[step][num]) % MOD;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    int result = 0;
    for (int i = 1; i <= N; ++i) {
        result = (result + dp[k][i]) % MOD;
    }

    return result;
}

int main() {
    int N, k;
    std::cin >> N >> k;

    int result = countPossibleDecryptions(N, k);
    std::cout << result << std::endl;

    return 0;
}

[17/08/24, 12:17:41 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <bitset>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>

const int MOD = 1000000007;

// Function to count the number of set bits in an integer
int countSetBits(int x) {
    return std::bitset<32>(x).count();  // Using bitset to count set bits
}

// Function to convert a binary string to a decimal number
unsigned long long binaryStringToDecimal(const std::string& binaryStr) {
    unsigned long long decimalValue = 0;
    for (char bit : binaryStr) {
        decimalValue = (decimalValue << 1) | (bit - '0');
    }
    return decimalValue;
}

int countPossibleDecryptions(const std::string& binaryStr, int k) {
    unsigned long long N = binaryStringToDecimal(binaryStr);
    if (N == 0) return 0;

    std::vector<std::vector<int>> dp(k + 1, std::vector<int>(N + 1, 0));

    // Initial condition: In 0 steps, we can only be at number 1
    dp[0][1] = 1;

    for (int step = 0; step < k; ++step) {
        for (unsigned long long num = 1; num <= N; ++num) {
            if (dp[step][num] > 0) {
                int nextNum = countSetBits(num);
                if (nextNum <= N) {
                    dp[step + 1][nextNum] = (dp[step + 1][nextNum] + dp[step][num]) % MOD;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    int result = 0;
    for (unsigned long long i = 1; i <= N; ++i) {
        result = (result + dp[k][i]) % MOD;
    }

    return result;
}

int main() {
    std::string binaryStr;
    int k;
    std::cin >> binaryStr >> k;

    int result = countPossibleDecryptions(binaryStr, k);
    std::cout << result << std::endl;

    return 0;
}

[17/08/24, 5:54:29 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <climits>
using namespace std;

int dfs(int node, vector<pair<int,int>> adj[], vector<int> &vis, bool visC, int C, int dest){
    // base case
    if(node == dest){
        return visC ? 0 : 1e7;
    }

    // recursive case
    vis[node]++;
    cout<<node<<" "<<vis[node]<<endl;
    int ans = INT_MAX;
    for(pair<int,int> it : adj[node]){
        int neighbour = it.first;
        int dist = it.second;
        if(vis[neighbour] == 0){
            if(neighbour == C) ans = min(ans, dist + dfs(neighbour, adj, vis, 1, C, dest));
            else ans = min(ans, dist + dfs(neighbour, adj, vis, visC, C, dest));
        }
        else if(vis[neighbour] == 1){
            if(neighbour == C) ans = min(ans, dfs(neighbour, adj, vis, 1, C, dest));
            else ans = min(ans, dfs(neighbour, adj, vis, visC, C, dest));
        }
    }
    vis[node]--;
    return ans;
}

int minDistVia(int n, vector<vector<int> > edges, int A, int B, int C){
    vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n];
    for(auto e : edges){
        adj[e[0]].push_back({e[1],e[2]});
        adj[e[1]].push_back({e[0],e[2]});
    }
    vector<int> vis(n,0);
    return dfs(A, adj, vis, 0, C, B);
}

int main(){
    vector<vector<int> > edges;
    edges.push_back({0,1,2});
    edges.push_back({0,2,1});
    edges.push_back({0,3,3});

    cout<<minDistVia(4, edges, 1, 3, 2)<<endl;
}

[18/08/24, 8:48:26 AM] Satvik Saini: class Node{
    public:
    unordered_map<char,Node*> childMap;
    char ch;
    int idx;
    Node(char c){
        ch = c;
    }
}

class Trie{
    Node* root;
    public:
    Trie(){
        root = new Node('#');
    }
    int insert(string s, int i){
        Node* curr = root;
        int ans = i;
        for(char c : s){
            if(curr->childMap.find(c) == curr->childMap.end()){
                Node* temp = new Node(c);
                curr->childMap[c] = temp;
            }
            else ans = curr->childMap[c]->idx;
            curr = curr->childMap[c];
            curr->idx = i;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[20/08/24, 9:00:24 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: // This solution will give TLE.
class Solution {
public:
    int rec(int idx, int M, vector<int> &piles, int turn){
        if(idx >= piles.size()) return 0;
        
        if(turn){
            int alexStones = INT_MAX;
            for(int i = 0; i < 2 * M && idx + i < piles.size(); i++){
                alexStones = min(alexStones, rec(idx + i + 1, max(M, i + 1), piles, !turn));
            }
            return alexStones;
        }else{
            int alexStones = 0, temp = 0;
            for(int i = 0; i < 2 * M && idx + i < piles.size(); i++){
                temp += piles[idx + i];
                alexStones = max(alexStones, temp + rec(idx + i + 1, max(M, i + 1), piles, !turn));
            }
            return alexStones;
        }
    }
    
    int stoneGameII(vector<int>& piles) {
        // vector<vector<int> > 
        // int pilesLength = piles.size();
        return rec(0, 1, piles, 0);        
    }
};// This solution will give TLE.
class Solution {
public:
    int rec(int idx, int M, vector<int> &piles, int turn){
        if(idx >= piles.size()) return 0;
        
        if(turn){
            int alexStones = INT_MAX;
            for(int i = 0; i < 2 * M && idx + i < piles.size(); i++){
                alexStones = min(alexStones, rec(idx + i + 1, max(M, i + 1), piles, !turn));
            }
            return alexStones;
        }else{
            int alexStones = 0, temp = 0;
            for(int i = 0; i < 2 * M && idx + i < piles.size(); i++){
                temp += piles[idx + i];
                alexStones = max(alexStones, temp + rec(idx + i + 1, max(M, i + 1), piles, !turn));
            }
            return alexStones;
        }
    }
    
    int stoneGameII(vector<int>& piles) {
        // vector<vector<int> > 
        // int pilesLength = piles.size();
        return rec(0, 1, piles, 0);        
    }
};v

[21/08/24, 6:52:41 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

// Function to rank songs
vector<int> rankSongs(int n, int m, const vector<vector<int>>& pref) {
    // Step 1: Initialize the comparison matrix
    vector<vector<int>> wins(m, vector<int>(m, 0));

    // Step 2: Compare each pair of songs
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for (int a = 0; a < m; a++) {
            for (int b = a + 1; b < m; b++) {
                int song_a = pref[i][a];
                int song_b = pref[i][b];
                wins[song_a][song_b]++;
            }
        }
    }

    // Step 3: Calculate the number of wins for each song
    vector<pair<int, int>> rank(m);
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
            if (i != j) {
                if (wins[i][j] > n / 2 || (wins[i][j] == n / 2 && i < j)) {
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }
        rank[i] = {count, i};
    }

    // Step 4: Sort the songs by the number of wins, and then by id
    sort(rank.rbegin(), rank.rend());

    // Extract the ranking order
    vector<int> result;
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        result.push_back(rank[i].second);
    }

    return result;
}

int main() {
    int n = 3, m = 3;
    vector<vector<int>> pref = {
        {0, 1, 2},
        {0, 2, 1},
        {1, 2, 0}
    };

    vector<int> result = rankSongs(n, m, pref);

    cout << "Song ranking order: ";
    for (int song : result) {
        cout << "Song " << song << " ";
    }
    cout << endl;

    return 0;
}

[21/08/24, 7:05:27 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

// Function to rank songs
vector<int> rankSongs(int n, int m, const vector<vector<int>>& pref) {
    vector<pair<int, int>> rank(m);  // Pair of (number of wins, song ID)
    
    // Initialize the rank with song IDs
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        rank[i] = {0, i};  // Initially, each song has 0 wins
    }

    // Compare each pair of songs
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        for (int j = i + 1; j < m; j++) {
            int count_i_over_j = 0;
            int count_j_over_i = 0;
            
            for (int k = 0; k < n; k++) {
                if (find(pref[k].begin(), pref[k].end(), i) < find(pref[k].begin(), pref[k].end(), j)) {
                    count_i_over_j++;
                } else {
                    count_j_over_i++;
                }
            }
            
            // Determine which song wins over the other
            if (count_i_over_j > count_j_over_i || (count_i_over_j == count_j_over_i && i < j)) {
                rank[i].first++;  // Song i beats song j
            } else {
                rank[j].first++;  // Song j beats song i
            }
        }
    }

    // Sort the songs by the number of wins, and in case of a tie, by song ID
    sort(rank.begin(), rank.end(), [](const pair<int, int>& a, const pair<int, int>& b) {
        return (a.first > b.first) || (a.first == b.first && a.second < b.second);
    });

    // Extract the ranking order
    vector<int> result;
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        result.push_back(rank[i].second);
    }

    return result;
}

[21/08/24, 10:31:53 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>
#include <unordered_map>

using namespace std;

// Helper function to sort characters of a string
string sortString(const string &s) {
    string sorted = s;
    sort(sorted.begin(), sorted.end());
    return sorted;
}

vector<vector<string>> findAnagrams(const vector<string> &words, const vector<string> &queries) {
    unordered_map<string, vector<string>> anagramGroups;

    // Group words by their sorted character sequence
    for (const string &word : words) {
        string sortedWord = sortString(word);
        anagramGroups[sortedWord].push_back(word);
    }

    vector<vector<string>> result;

    // For each query, find and store the corresponding anagrams
    for (const string &query : queries) {
        string sortedQuery = sortString(query);
        vector<string> anagrams = anagramGroups[sortedQuery];

        // Sort the anagrams alphabetically
        sort(anagrams.begin(), anagrams.end());
        result.push_back(anagrams);
    }

    return result;
}

int main() {
    int n = 4, q = 2;
    vector<string> words = {"duel", "speed", "dule", "cars"};
    vector<string> queries = {"spede", "deul"};

    vector<vector<string>> result = findAnagrams(words, queries);

    // Print the result
    for (const auto &anagramList : result) {
        for (const string &anagram : anagramList) {
            cout << anagram << " ";
        }
        cout << endl;
    }

    return 0;
}

[21/08/24, 10:41:17 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>
#include <unordered_map>

using namespace std;

// Helper function to sort characters of a string
string sortString(const string &s) {
    string sorted = s;
    sort(sorted.begin(), sorted.end());
    return sorted;
}

vector<vector<string>> findAnagrams(const vector<string> &words, const vector<string> &queries) {
    unordered_map<string, vector<string>> anagramGroups;

    // Group words by their sorted character sequence
    for (const string &word : words) {
        string sortedWord = sortString(word);
        anagramGroups[sortedWord].push_back(word);
    }

    vector<vector<string>> result;

    // For each query, find and store the corresponding anagrams
    for (const string &query : queries) {
        string sortedQuery = sortString(query);
        
        // Check if the sorted query exists in the anagram groups
        if (anagramGroups.find(sortedQuery) != anagramGroups.end()) {
            vector<string> anagrams = anagramGroups[sortedQuery];

            // Sort the anagrams alphabetically
            sort(anagrams.begin(), anagrams.end());
            result.push_back(anagrams);
        } else {
            // If no anagrams found, return an empty list
            result.push_back({});
        }
    }

    return result;
}

int main() {
    int n = 4, q = 2;
    vector<string> words = {"duel", "speed", "dule", "cars"};
    vector<string> queries = {"spede", "deul"};

    vector<vector<string>> result = findAnagrams(words, queries);

    // Print the result
    for (const auto &anagramList : result) {
        if (!anagramList.empty()) {
            for (const string &anagram : anagramList) {
                cout << anagram << " ";
            }
            cout << endl;
        } else {
            cout << "No anagrams found" << endl;
        }
    }

    return 0;
}

[21/08/24, 10:52:39 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <algorithm>

using namespace std;

int longestSubsequenceSubstring(string x, string y) {
    int n = x.size();
    int m = y.size();
    
    // DP table to store the length of the longest subsequence
    vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 1, vector<int>(m + 1, 0));
    
    int maxLength = 0;

    // Build the DP table
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        for (int j = 1; j <= m; j++) {
            if (x[i - 1] == y[j - 1]) {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1;
                maxLength = max(maxLength, dp[i][j]);
            } else {
                dp[i][j] = 0; // Reset if characters don't match for substring condition
            }
        }
    }

    return maxLength;
}

int main() {
    string x = "abcd";
    string y = "abdc";
    
    int result = longestSubsequenceSubstring(x, y);
    
    cout << "Length of the longest subsequence of x that is also a substring of y: " << result << endl;
    
    return 0;
}

[22/08/24, 9:02:03 AM] Satvik Saini: void countSort(int arr[], int n, int exp)
{

    // Output array
    int output[n];
    int i, count[10] = { 0 };

    // Store count of occurrences
    // in count[]
    for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
        count[(arr[i] / exp) % 10]++;

    // Change count[i] so that count[i]
    // now contains actual position
    // of this digit in output[]
    for (i = 1; i < 10; i++)
        count[i] += count[i - 1];

    // Build the output array
    for (i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        output[count[(arr[i] / exp) % 10] - 1] = arr[i];
        count[(arr[i] / exp) % 10]--;
    }

    // Copy the output array to arr[],
    // so that arr[] now contains sorted
    // numbers according to current digit
    for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
        arr[i] = output[i];
}

// The main function to that sorts arr[]
// of size n using Radix Sort
void radixsort(int arr[], int n)
{

    // Find the maximum number to
    // know number of digits
    int m = getMax(arr, n);

    // Do counting sort for every digit.
    // Note that instead of passing digit
    // number, exp is passed. exp is 10^i
    // where i is current digit number
    for (int exp = 1; m / exp > 0; exp *= 10)
        countSort(arr, n, exp);
}
[22/08/24, 9:03:40 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int maximumGap(vector<int>& nums) {
        if (nums.size() < 2) return 0;
        int hi = 0, lo = INT_MAX, ans = 0;
        for (auto& n : nums)
            hi = max(hi, n), lo = min(lo, n);
        int bsize = max(int((hi - lo) / (nums.size() - 1)), 1);
        vector<vector<int>> buckets((hi - lo) / bsize + 1, vector<int>());
        for (auto& n : nums)
            buckets[(n - lo) / bsize].push_back(n);
        int currhi = 0;
        for (auto& b : buckets) {
            if (b.empty()) continue;
            int prevhi = currhi ? currhi : b[0], currlo = b[0];
            for (auto& n : b)
                currhi = max(currhi, n), currlo = min(currlo, n);
            ans = max(ans, currlo - prevhi);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[23/08/24, 8:37:40 AM] Satvik Saini: // step 1: take the LCM of all the denominators
// step 2: multiply each numerator with LCM/denominator and add all numerators
// step 3: take the GCD of numerator and denominator and divide both of them by GCD

class Solution {
public:
    string fractionAddition(string s) {
        int LCM = 1;
        int n = s.length();

        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            if(s[i-1] == '/') LCM = lcm(LCM, s[i]-'0');
        }

        int num;
        bool neg = 0;
        int fNum = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(s[i] == '-') neg = 1;
            else if(i>0 && s[i-1] == '/'){
                int den = s[i]-'0';
                fNum += (neg?-1:1)*num*(LCM/den);
                neg = 0;
            }
            else if(s[i] != '/'){
                num = s[i]-'0';
            }
        }
        int fDen = LCM;
        int gcd = __gcd(fNum,fDen);
        return to_string(fNum/gcd) + "/" + to_string(fDen/gcd);
    }
};

[24/08/24, 3:00:56 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    string nearestPalindromic(string numberStr) {
        long long number = stoll(numberStr);
        
        // Edge cases for small numbers
        if (number <= 10) return to_string(number - 1);
        if (number == 11) return "9";
        
        // Special case for 18-digit number with all 9s, thanks to dcodeDV for pointing this out
        if (numberStr == "999999999999999999") {
            return "1000000000000000001";
        }
        
        int length = numberStr.length();
        long long leftHalf = stoll(numberStr.substr(0, (length + 1) / 2));
        
        vector<long long> palindromeCandidates(5);
        palindromeCandidates[0] = generatePalindromeFromLeft(leftHalf - 1, length % 2 == 0);
        palindromeCandidates[1] = generatePalindromeFromLeft(leftHalf, length % 2 == 0);
        
        // Handle potential overflow for leftHalf + 1
        if (leftHalf < 999999999) {
            palindromeCandidates[2] = generatePalindromeFromLeft(leftHalf + 1, length % 2 == 0);
        } else {
            palindromeCandidates[2] = stoll("1" + string(length - 1, '0') + "1");
        }
        
        palindromeCandidates[3] = pow(10, length - 1) - 1;
        palindromeCandidates[4] = pow(10, length) + 1;
        
        long long nearestPalindrome = 0;
        long long minDifference = LLONG_MAX;
        
        for (long long candidate : palindromeCandidates) {
            if (candidate == number) continue;
            long long difference = abs(candidate - number);
            if (difference < minDifference || (difference == minDifference && candidate < nearestPalindrome)) {
                minDifference = difference;
                nearestPalindrome = candidate;
            }
        }
        
        return to_string(nearestPalindrome);
    }

private:
    long long generatePalindromeFromLeft(long long leftHalf, bool isEvenLength) {
        long long palindrome = leftHalf;
        if (!isEvenLength) leftHalf /= 10;
        while (leftHalf > 0) {
            palindrome = palindrome * 10 + leftHalf % 10;
            leftHalf /= 10;
        }
        return palindrome;
    }
};

[26/08/24, 8:26:43 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-possible-integer-after-at-most-k-adjacent-swaps-on-digits/description/
[26/08/24, 8:27:40 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    string minInteger(string num, int k) {
        int n = num.length();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            // currently finding the best fit for ith bit by doing at most k swaps
            char ch = num[i];
            int idx;
            for(int j=i+1;j<min(n,i+k+1);j++){
                if(ch > num[j]){
                    ch = num[j];
                    idx = j;
                }
            }
            if(ch == num[i]){
                // no need to swap, go on to (i+1)th index for best fit
                continue;
            }
            else{
                // we have to shift the digits clockwise from i to idx
                char temp = num[idx];
                for(int j=idx;j>i;j--){
                    num[j] = num[j-1];
                }
                num[i] = temp;
                k -= idx - i;
                if(!k) return num;
            }
        }
        return num;
    }
};

[28/08/24, 9:23:08 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    double dfs(int node, vector<vector<pair<int,double>>>& adj, vector<int>& visited, int end){
        if(node == end) return 1;
        visited[node] = true;
        double ans = -1;
        for(auto neighbour : adj[node]){
            if(visited[neighbour.first] == false){
                int val = dfs(neighbour.first, adj, visited, end);
                if(val != -1){
                    ans = max(ans, (double)neighbour.second*val);
                    cout<<node << " " << ans<<endl;
                }
            }
        }
        visited[node] = false;
        return ans;
    }
    double maxProbability(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges, vector<double>& succProb, int start, int end) {
        vector<vector<pair<int,double>>> adj(n);
        for(int i=0 ; i<edges.size() ;i++){
            adj[edges[i][0]].push_back({edges[i][1],succProb[i]});
            adj[edges[i][1]].push_back({edges[i][0],succProb[i]});
        }
        vector<int>visited(n,0);
        return dfs(start, adj, visited, end);
    }
};

[28/08/24, 9:26:44 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: DFS needs some special handling here for it to submit. Still not a good solution from interview point of view.
Code
class Solution {

    vector<list<pair<int,double>>> graph;
    vector<bool> stack;
    int end;
    double maxProb = 0.0;

    void DFS(int node, double prob)
    {
        // this
        if(prob < 1e-5)
            return;

        if(node == end)
        {
            maxProb = prob;
            return;
        }
        
        stack[node] = true;

        for(auto [next, currProb] : graph[node])
        {   
                                // this
            if(!stack[next] && prob * currProb > maxProb)
                DFS(next, prob * currProb);
        }

        stack[node] = false;

        return;
    }

public:
    double maxProbability(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges, vector<double>& succProb, int start, int end) {
        
        this->end = end;
        stack.resize(n, false);
        graph.resize(n);
        for(int i = 0; i < edges.size(); i++)
        {
            graph[edges[i][0]].push_back({edges[i][1], succProb[i]});
            graph[edges[i][1]].push_back({edges[i][0], succProb[i]});
        }

        DFS(start, 1.0);
        
        return maxProb;
    }
};
[28/08/24, 9:28:41 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    double maxProbability(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges, vector<double>& succProb, int start_node, int end_node) {
        vector<pair<int,double>> adj[n];
        for(int i=0;i<edges.size();i++){
            adj[edges[i][0]].push_back({edges[i][1],succProb[i]});
            adj[edges[i][1]].push_back({edges[i][0],succProb[i]});
        }

        priority_queue<pair<double,int>,vector<pair<double,int>>> pq;   // maxHeap
        vector<double> probMap(n,0);

        probMap[start_node] = 1.0;
        pq.push({1,start_node});
        while(!pq.empty()){
            double prob = pq.top().first;
            int node = pq.top().second;
            pq.pop();

            for(auto it : adj[node]){
                int neighbour = it.first;
                double edW = it.second;
                if(edW * prob > probMap[neighbour]){
                    probMap[neighbour] = edW * prob;
                    pq.push({probMap[neighbour], neighbour});
                }
            }
        }
        return probMap[end_node];
    }
};

[28/08/24, 4:22:55 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> verticalTraversal(TreeNode* root) {
        vector<vector<pair<int,int>>> ans(2001);
        queue<pair<TreeNode*,pair<int,int>>> q;
        q.push({root,{0,0}});

        while(!q.empty()){
            TreeNode* node = q.front().first;
            int h = q.front().second.first;
            int v = q.front().second.second;
            q.pop();

            if(ans[h+1001].size() == 0 || ans[h+1001].back().second != v || ans[h+1001].back().first < node->val) ans[h+1001].push_back({node->val,v});
            else{
                pair<int,int> temp = ans[h+1001].back();
                ans[h+1001].pop_back();
                ans[h+1001].push_back({node->val,v});
                ans[h+1001].push_back(temp);
            }
            if(node->left) q.push({node->left, {h-1, v+1}});
            if(node->right) q.push({node->right, {h+1, v+1}});
        }
        vector<vector<int>> res;
        for(auto v : ans){
            if(v.size()){
                vector<int> r;
                for(auto p : v){
                    r.push_back(p.first);
                }
                res.push_back(r);
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};

[28/08/24, 4:25:51 PM] Satvik Saini: Given the root of a binary tree, calculate the vertical order traversal of the binary tree.

For each node at position (row, col), its left and right children will be at positions (row + 1, col - 1) and (row + 1, col + 1) respectively. The root of the tree is at (0, 0).

The vertical order traversal of a binary tree is a list of top-to-bottom orderings for each column index starting from the leftmost column and ending on the rightmost column. There may be multiple nodes in the same row and same column. In such a case, sort these nodes by their values.

Return the vertical order traversal of the binary tree.

[28/08/24, 4:51:54 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    map<int, vector<int>> mpp;
    vector<vector<int>> verticalTraversal(TreeNode* root) {
        if(!root) return {};
        vector<vector<int>> ans;
        queue<pair<TreeNode *, int>> visited;
        visited.push({root, 0});
        visited.push({nullptr, 0});
        recurse(visited);
        for(auto ar: mpp) {
            ans.push_back(ar.second);
        }
        return ans;
    }

    void recurse(queue<pair<TreeNode *, int>> &visited) {
        vector<pair<int,int>> currArr; 
        while(!visited.empty()) {
            pair<TreeNode *, int> curr = visited.front(); visited.pop();
            if(curr.first) {
                currArr.push_back({curr.first->val, curr.second});
                if(curr.first->left) visited.push({curr.first->left, curr.second-1});
                if(curr.first->right) visited.push({curr.first->right, curr.second+1});
            } else {
                if(!visited.empty()) visited.push({nullptr, 0});
                sort(currArr.begin(), currArr.end());
                for(auto k: currArr) {
                    mpp[k.second].push_back(k.first);
                }
                currArr.clear();
            }
        }
        return;
    }
};
[28/08/24, 4:55:09 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎Voice call, ‎8 min
[28/08/24, 4:56:32 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: Intuition
AS GIVEN ITS IN THE EXPLANATION OF PROBELEM TRY TO GIVE INDEXING(X,Y) TO EACH OF THE NODE FOR REPRESENTING THE NODE IN THE 2-D COORDINATE SYSTEM.

Approach
JUST AFTER GIVING THE COORDINATE TO THE NODES IN TREES (BY USING THE MAP) , THEN ITERATE OVER ALL THE PAIRS AND IF NODES ARE IN THE SAME POSITION SORT THE NODES DEPENDING UPON ITS VALUE.

THEN AGAIN TAKE A MAP OF <INT , VECTOR> FOR STORING THE ELEMENT ACCORDING TO THE COLUMN NUMBER.

THEN ITERATE IN THIS MAP ANS STORE THE VECTOR INTO THE FINAL ANS

RETURN THE ANS

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(N * LOG(N))

Space complexity:

O(N)

Code
C++
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */


class Solution {
public:
void solve(TreeNode *root, map<pair<int,int>,vector<int>>&mp,int i,int j){
    if(root==NULL){
        return ;
    }
    mp[{i,j}].push_back(root->val);
    solve(root->left,mp,i+1,j-1);
    solve(root->right,mp,i+1,j+1);
}
    vector<vector<int>> verticalTraversal(TreeNode* root) {
    map<pair<int,int>,vector<int>>mp;
    vector<vector<int>>ans;
    int i=0;
    int j=0;
    solve(root,mp,0,0);
map<int,vector<int>>mp2;
    for(auto &it:mp){
        pair<int,int>p = it.first;
        sort(it.second.begin(),it.second.end());
        }

        for(auto &it:mp){
            pair<int,int>p =it.first;
            vector<int>v =it.second;
            int xx = p.first;
            int yy = p.second;
        for(int i=0;i<v.size();i++){
            mp2[yy].push_back(v[i]);
   }
                  }
                for(auto &it:mp2){
                    vector<int>vv = it.second;
                    ans.push_back(vv);
                }
                return ans;
    }
};

[28/08/24, 6:51:44 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> verticalTraversal(TreeNode* root) {
        map<int,vector<pair<int,int>>> ans;  // vectical,node val, horizontal
        queue<pair<TreeNode*,pair<int,int>>> q;  // node,verical,horizontal
        q.push({root,{0,0}});

        while(!q.empty()){
            TreeNode* node = q.front().first;
            int v = q.front().second.first;
            int h = q.front().second.second;
            q.pop();

            if(ans[v].size() == 0 || ans[v].back().second != h || ans[v].back().first <= node->val) ans[v].push_back({node->val,h});
            else{
                vector<pair<int,int>> vec;
                while(ans[v].size() && ans[v].back().second == h){
                    vec.push_back(ans[v].back());
                    ans[v].pop_back();
                }
                vec.push_back({node->val,h});
                sort(vec.begin(), vec.end());
                for(auto p : vec){
                    ans[v].push_back(p);
                }
            }
            if(node->left) q.push({node->left, {v-1, h+1}});
            if(node->right) q.push({node->right, {v+1, h+1}});
        }
        vector<vector<int>> res;
        for(auto p : ans){
            if(p.second.size()){
                vector<int> r;
                for(auto pr : p.second){
                    r.push_back(pr.first);
                }
                res.push_back(r);
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};

[28/08/24, 7:56:16 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
int dx[4] = {-1,1,0,0};
int dy[4] = {0,0,-1,1};
    bool dfs(int i, int j,vector<vector<int>>& grid1, vector<vector<int>>& grid2, vector<vector<int>>& visited ){
        visited[i][j] = 1;
        if(grid1[i][j] == 0 && grid2[i][j] == 1) return false;
        bool ans = true;
        for(int k=0 ; k<4 ; k++){
            int nx = i + dx[k];
            int ny = j + dy[k];
            if(nx >= 0 && nx<grid1.size() && ny >=0 && ny<grid1[0].size() && visited[nx][ny] == 0 && grid2[nx][ny] == 1){
                if(grid1[nx][ny] == 0) return false;
                else{
                    ans = ans & dfs(nx,ny,grid1,grid2,visited);
                    if(ans == false ) return false;
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
    void print(vector<vector<int>>& grid1){
        for(int i=0 ; i<grid1.size() ; i++){
            for(int j=0 ; j<grid1[0].size() ; j++){
            }
            cout << endl;
        }
        cout << endl;
    }
    int countSubIslands(vector<vector<int>>& grid1, vector<vector<int>>& grid2) {
        int cnt = 0;
        vector<vector<int>> visited(grid1.size(), vector<int>(grid1[0].size(),0));
        for(int i=0 ; i<grid1.size() ; i++){
            for(int j=0 ; j<grid1[0].size() ; j++){
                if(grid2[i][j] == 1 && visited[i][j] == 0){ 
                    if(dfs(i,j,grid1,grid2,visited)){ cnt++; print(visited);}
                    
                }
            }
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};

[28/08/24, 7:59:40 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    vector<int> dx = {1, -1, 0, 0};
    vector<int> dy = {0, 0, 1, -1};
    void dfs(vector<vector<int>>& grid1, vector<vector<int>>& grid2, int i, int j, vector<vector<int>> &vis, bool &flag){
        int n = grid1.size();
        int m = grid1[0].size();
        vis[i][j] = 1;

        for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
            int ii = i + dx[k];
            int jj = j + dy[k];
            if(ii >= 0 && ii < n && jj >= 0 && jj < m && !vis[ii][jj] && grid2[ii][jj]){
                if(!grid1[ii][jj]) flag = 0;
                dfs(grid1, grid2, ii, jj, vis, flag);
            }
        }
    }
public:
    int countSubIslands(vector<vector<int>>& grid1, vector<vector<int>>& grid2) {
        int n = grid1.size();
        int m = grid1[0].size();
        int island = 0;

        vector<vector<int>> vis(n, vector<int>(m,0));
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                if(grid2[i][j] && grid1[i][j] && !vis[i][j]){
                    bool flag = 1;
                    dfs(grid1, grid2, i, j, vis, flag);
                    if(flag) island++;
                }
            }
        }
        return island;
    }
};

[29/08/24, 11:40:36 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int dfs(int n, int i, int j, unordered_map<int,vector<int>>& row_map, unordered_map<int,vector<int>>& col_map, set<pair<int,int>>& visited){
        visited.insert({i,j});
        int ans = 1;
        for(int col : row_map[i]){
            if(col != j && visited.find({i,col}) == visited.end()){
                ans += dfs(n,i,col,row_map,col_map,visited);
            }
        }
        for(int row : col_map[j]){
            if(row != i && visited.find({row,j}) == visited.end()){
                ans += dfs(n,row,j,row_map,col_map,visited);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
    int removeStones(vector<vector<int>>& stones) {
        unordered_map<int,vector<int>> row_map;
        unordered_map<int,vector<int>> col_map;
        set<pair<int,int>> visited;
        int ans = 0;
        int n = stones.size();
        for(auto& stone : stones){
            row_map[stone[0]].push_back(stone[1]);
            row_map[stone[1]].push_back(stone[0]);
        }
        for(auto& stone : stones){
            if(visited.find({stone[0],stone[1]}) == visited.end()){
                ans += dfs(n,stone[0],stone[1],row_map,col_map,visited)-1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[29/08/24, 2:55:45 PM] Satvik Saini: class DisjointSet {
private:
    unordered_map<int, int> parentMap, rankMap;
public:
    void insert(int x) {
        parentMap[x] = x;
        rankMap[x] = 1;
    }
    int findSet(int x) {
        if (parentMap[x] == x) {
            return x;
        }

        return parentMap[x] = findSet(parentMap[x]);
    }
    void unionSet(int x, int y) {
        int x_l = findSet(x);
        int y_l = findSet(y);

        if (x_l != y_l) {
            int r_x = rankMap[x_l];
            int r_y = rankMap[y_l];
            if (r_x > r_y) {
                parentMap[y_l] = x_l;
                rankMap[x_l] += rankMap[y_l];
            } else {
                parentMap[x_l] = y_l;
                rankMap[y_l] += rankMap[x_l];
            }
        }
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    int removeStones(vector<vector<int>>& stones) {
        int maxRow = 0;
        int maxCol = 0;

        for (auto it : stones) {
            maxRow = max(maxRow, it[0]);
            maxCol = max(maxCol, it[1]);
        }

        DisjointSet ds;

        for (int i = 0; i <= maxRow + maxCol + 1; i++) {
            // inserting all the possible value of row and col
            ds.insert(i);
        }

        unordered_map<int, int> stoneNodes;
        for (auto it : stones) {
            int row = it[0];
            // not inserting col directly because row = 2 and col = 2 will be treated as same
            // but they are different
            // thus, we add maxRow + 1 due to which they dont overlap 
            int col = it[1] + maxRow + 1;

            ds.unionSet(row, col);
            stoneNodes[row] = 1;
            stoneNodes[col] = 1;
        }

        int cnt = 0;

        for (auto it : stoneNodes) {
            if (ds.findSet(it.first) == it.first) {
                cnt++;
            }
        }

        return stones.size() - cnt;
    }
};

[30/08/24, 10:38:26 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    void dfs(int node, int dest, vector<pair<int,int>> adj[], vector<int> &vis, vector<int> &path, vector<pair<int,int>> &v, int sum, int cntNeg, int target){
        // base case
        if(node == dest){
            if(sum < target && cntNeg){path.push_back(dest); v.push_back({sum,cntNeg});}
            else if(sum == target && !cntNeg){path.push_back(dest); v.push_back({sum,0});}
            return;
        }

        // recursive case
        if(v.size() == 1) return;
        path.push_back(node);
        vis[node] = 1;
        for(auto it : adj[node]){
            if(v.size() == 1) return;
            int neighbour = it.first;
            int edW = it.second;
            if(!vis[neighbour]){
                dfs(neighbour, dest, adj, vis, path, v, sum + ((edW == -1) ? 0 : edW), cntNeg + (edW == -1), target);
            }
        }
        if(v.size() == 1) return;
        vis[node] = 0;
        path.pop_back();
    }
public:
    vector<vector<int>> modifiedGraphEdges(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges, int source, int destination, int target) {
        vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n];
        for(auto e : edges){
            adj[e[0]].push_back({e[1],e[2]});
            adj[e[1]].push_back({e[0],e[2]});
        }
        vector<pair<int,int>> v;   // {sum except -1, no of -1}
        vector<int> path, vis(n,0);
        // vector<vector<int>> paths;

        dfs(source, destination, adj, vis, path, v, 0, 0, target);
        if(v.size() == 0) return {{}};

        int sum = target - v[0].first;
        int cntNeg = v[0].second;
        cout<<"sum : "<<sum<<endl;
        cout<<"cntNeg : "<<cntNeg<<endl;
        for(int i=0;i<path.size();i++){
            cout<<path[i]<<" ";
        }
        for(int i=0;i<path.size()-1;i++){
            // cout<<path[i]<<" ";
            int u = path[i];
            int v = path[i+1];
            for(auto &e : edges){
                if((e[0] == u && e[1] == v) || (e[0] == v && e[1] == u)){
                    if(e[2] == -1){
                        if(cntNeg == 1){
                            e[2] = sum;
                            cntNeg--;
                            sum = 0;
                        }
                        else if(cntNeg > 1){
                            e[2] = 1;
                            cntNeg--;
                            sum--;
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        // cout<<path.back();
        for(auto &e : edges){
            if(e[2] == 1) e[2] = 2000000000;
        }
        return edges;
    }
};

[30/08/24, 7:22:12 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    long long countFairPairs(vector<int>& nums, int lower, int upper) {
       long long cnt =0 ;
       sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
       for(int i=0 ; i<nums.size() ; i++){
            int max_limit = 0;
            int min_limit = 0;
            auto upperbound = lower_bound(nums.begin()+i+1,nums.end(),upper - nums[i]);
            if(upperbound != nums.end()){
                max_limit =   upperbound - nums.begin();
            }
            auto lowerbound = lower_bound(nums.begin()+i+1,nums.end(),lower - nums[i]);
            if(lowerbound != nums.end()){
                if(*lowerbound == nums[i]){
                    min_limit = lowerbound - nums.begin();
                }
                else{
                    if(lowerbound != nums.begin()){
                        lowerbound--;
                        min_limit = lowerbound - nums.begin();
                    }
                }
            }
            if(min_limit - max_limit > 0 ) cnt += min_limit - max_limit;
       }
        return cnt;
    }
};
[30/08/24, 7:48:30 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    long long countFairPairs(vector<int>& nums, int lower, int upper) {
        long long cnt = 0;
        int n = nums.size();
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            int l = lower_bound(nums.begin(), nums.end(), lower-nums[i]) - nums.begin();
            int r = lower_bound(nums.begin(), nums.end(), upper-nums[i]+1) - nums.begin() - 1;

            if(l != n && r != -1){
                if(l <= i && i <= r) cnt += r - l;
                else cnt += r - l + 1;
            }
        }
        return cnt/2;
    }
};

[31/08/24, 10:42:06 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int maximumScore(vector<int>& scores, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        int n = scores.size();
        vector<int> graph[n];
        for(auto e : edges){
            graph[e[0]].push_back(e[1]);
            graph[e[1]].push_back(e[0]);
        }

        int ans = -1;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(auto j : graph[i]){
                // now we have fixed two nodes, i and j
                // now we need to take all possible combinations of a-i-j-b
                // make sure that a and b should not be i or j
                for(auto neighbour_i : graph[i]){
                    if(neighbour_i != j){
                        for(auto neighbour_j : graph[j]){
                            if((neighbour_j != i) && (neighbour_j != neighbour_i)){
                                int score = scores[i] + scores[j] + scores[neighbour_i] + scores[neighbour_j];
                                ans = max(ans, score);
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[31/08/24, 1:48:51 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    vector<int> topoSort(vector<int> graph[], int k){
        vector<int> topo;
        vector<int> inDegMap(k,0);
        for(int i=0;i<k;i++){
            for(auto neighbour : graph[i]){
                inDegMap[neighbour]++;
            }
        }
        queue<int> q;
        for(int i=0;i<k;i++){
            if(inDegMap[i] == 0) q.push(i);
        }

        while(!q.empty()){
            int node = q.front();
            q.pop();

            topo.push_back(node);

            for(int it : graph[node]){
                inDegMap[it]--;
                if(!inDegMap[it]) q.push(it);
            }
        }
        return topo;
    }
public:
    vector<vector<int>> buildMatrix(int k, vector<vector<int>>& rowConditions, vector<vector<int>>& colConditions) {
        int n = rowConditions.size();
        int m = colConditions.size();

        vector<int> graphR[k], graphC[k];

        for(auto c : rowConditions){
            graphR[c[0]-1].push_back(c[1]-1);
        }
        for(auto c : colConditions){
            graphC[c[0]-1].push_back(c[1]-1);
        }

        vector<int> topoR = topoSort(graphR, k);
        vector<int> topoC = topoSort(graphC, k);

        if(topoR.size() != k || topoC.size() != k) return {};

        vector<vector<int>> ans(k, vector<int>(k,0));
        for(int i=0;i<k;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<k;j++){
                if(topoC[j] == topoR[i]){
                    ans[i][j] = topoR[i]+1;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

    vector<int> topo(vector<vector<int>>&arr, int k,bool row){

        vector<int> IndegreeMap(k+1,0);
        for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size() ; i++){
            adj[arr[i][0]].push_back(arr[i][1]);
            IndegreeMap[arr[i][1]]++;
        }

        for(int i=1 ; i<=k ; i++){
            if(IndegreeMap[i] == 0) q.push(i);
        }

        vector<int> visited(k+1,0);
        while( !q.empty()){
            int x = q.front();
            q.pop();
            res.push_back(x);
            visited[x]++;
            for(int neighbour : adj[x]){
                IndegreeMap[neighbour]--;
                if(!visited[neighbour] && IndegreeMap[neighbour] == 0){
                    q.push(neighbour);
                }
            }

        }
        // if(row) reverse(res.begin(),res.end());
        if(res.size() != k) res = {};
        for(int x : res) cout << x << " ";
        cout << endl;
        return res;
    }

[31/08/24, 2:44:00 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int countRangeSum(vector<int>& nums, int lower, int upper) {
        multiset<int> st;
        st.insert(0);
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            auto lower_it = st.lower_bound(lower-nums[i]);
            auto upper_it = st.lower_bound(upper-nums[i]+1);

            int l = distance(st.begin(), lower_it);
            int u = distance(st.begin(), upper_it) - 1;

            if(l != st.size() && u != -1){
                cnt += u - l + 1;
            }
            multiset<int> newSt;
            newSt.insert(0);
            for(auto it : st){
                newSt.insert(it + nums[i]);
                st.erase(it);
            }
            st = newSt;
        } 
        return cnt;
    }
};

[31/08/24, 2:47:02 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int countRangeSum(vector<int>& nums, int lower, int upper) {
        set<int> st;
        st.insert(0);
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            auto lower_it = st.lower_bound(lower-nums[i]);
            auto upper_it = st.lower_bound(upper-nums[i]+1);

            int l = distance(st.begin(), lower_it);
            int u = distance(st.begin(), upper_it) - 1;

            if(l != st.size() && u != -1){
                cnt += u - l + 1;
            }
            set<int> newSt;
            newSt.insert(0);
            auto it = st.begin();
            while(it != st.end()){
                newSt.insert(*it + nums[i]);
                st.erase(it);
                it++;
            }
            st = newSt;
        } 
        return cnt;
    }
};
[31/08/24, 2:51:58 PM] Satvik Saini: // Method 1
// time : O(n^2logn)

#define ll long long
class Solution {
public:
    int countRangeSum(vector<int>& nums, int lower, int upper) {
        multiset<ll> st;
        st.insert(0);
        int cnt = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            auto lower_it = st.lower_bound((ll)lower - nums[i]);
            auto upper_it = st.lower_bound((ll)upper - nums[i] + 1);

            int l = distance(st.begin(), lower_it);
            int u = distance(st.begin(), upper_it) - 1;

            if(l != st.size() && u != -1) cnt += u - l + 1;
        
            multiset<ll> newSt;
            newSt.insert(0);
            auto it = st.begin();
            while(it != st.end()){
                newSt.insert(*it + nums[i]);
                st.erase(it);
                it++;
            }
            st = newSt;
        } 
        return cnt;
    }
};

[31/08/24, 5:40:45 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int countRangeSum(vector<int>& nums, int lower, int upper) {
        multiset<long long> pSum;
        int res = 0,  i; 
        long long left, right, sum=0;
        for(i=0,pSum.insert(0); i<nums.size(); ++i)
        {
            sum +=nums[i];
            res += std::distance(pSum.lower_bound(sum-upper), pSum.upper_bound(sum-lower));
            pSum.insert(sum);
        }
        return res;
    }

‎[31/08/24, 5:41:49 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎image omitted
[31/08/24, 5:43:34 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: The basic idea is to use a multiset to save sum, where sum at i = nums[0]+...+ nums[i]. At each i, only those sum[j] that satisfies lower=< sum[i]-sum[j]<= upper can generate a valid range[j,i]. so we only need to calculate how many j (0=< j< i) satisfy sum[i]-upper=< sum[j]<=-sum[i]-lower. The STL multiset can take care of sort and find upper_bound, lower_bound j. Since the multiset is usually implemented with Red-black tree, so those operations should have complexity of O(logN). So in total, the complexity is O(NlogN) (except the distance part). At least it looks neat

[31/08/24, 5:59:33 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool isPossible(vector<int>& jobs, int k, int mid){
        // tell whether the maximum time taken by a worker is <= mid
        // now we need to explore all the 
    }
public:
    int minimumTimeRequired(vector<int>& jobs, int k) {
        int s = 0, e = 0;
        for(int time : jobs){
            s = max(s, time);
            e += time;
        }
        int minTime;
        while(s <= e){
            int mid = (s+e)/2;
            if(isPossible(jobs, k, mid)){
                minTime = mid;
                e = mid-1;
            }
            else s = mid+1;
        }
        return minTime
    }
};

[31/08/24, 9:10:20 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int generateKey(int num1, int num2, int num3) {
        string s1 = to_string(num1);
        string s2 = to_string(num2);
        string s3 = to_string(num3);

        while(s1.length() != 4) s1 = "0" + s1;
        while(s2.length() != 4) s2 = "0" + s2;
        while(s3.length() != 4) s3 = "0" + s3;

        string ans = "";
        for(int i=0;i<4;i++){
            char ch = min(s1[i],min(s2[i],s3[i]));
            ans += ch;
        }
        return stoi(ans);
    }
};

    char hash(string s){
        int n = 0;
        for(char ch : s){
            n += ch - 'a';
        }
        return n%26 + 'a';
    }
public:
    string stringHash(string s, int k) {
        string res = "";
        int i = 0, n = s.length();
        while(i<n){
            string str = s.substr(i,k);
            res += hash(str);
            i += k;
        }
        return res;
    }

[31/08/24, 9:45:22 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    bool isKPalindromic(int i, int k) {
        string str = to_string(i);
        if(i % k != 0) return 0;
        int n = str.length();
        for(int i=0;i<n/2;i++){
            if(str[i] != str[n-i-1]) return 0;
        }
        return 1;
    }

    bool canBePalindrome(string s){
        vector<int> mp(10,0);
        for(char ch : s){
            mp[ch-'0']++;
        }
        int odd = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<10;i++){
            if(mp[i] % 2) odd++;
        }
        int n = s.length();
        if((n%2 && odd == 1) || (!n%2 && !odd)) return 1;
        return 0;
    }

    long long countGoodIntegers(int n, int k) {
        set<int> st;
        
        int s = pow(10, n - 1), e = pow(10, n);
        
        for (int i = s; i < e; i++) {
            string str = to_string(i);
            if(canBePalindrome(str)){
                sort(str.begin(), str.end());
                do {
                    int permutedNum = stoi(str);
                    if (permutedNum >= s && isKPalindromic(permutedNum, k)) {
                        st.insert(i); 
                        break;
                    }
                } while (next_permutation(str.begin(), str.end()));
            }
        } 
        return st.size();
    }
};
[01/09/24, 8:52:41 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎11 min
[01/09/24, 8:54:17 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int maxSum(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int &n, int &m, int i, string &vis, unordered_map<string,int> &mp){
        // base case
        if(i == n) return 0;

        // lookup
        string s = vis + to_string(i);
        if(mp.find(s) != mp.end()) return mp[s];

        // recursive case
        int ans = 0;
        for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
            if(vis[grid[i][j]] == '0'){
                vis[grid[i][j]] = '1';
                ans = max(ans, grid[i][j] + maxSum(grid, n, m, i+1, vis, mp));
                vis[grid[i][j]] = '0';
            }
        }
        return mp[s] = max(ans, maxSum(grid, n, m, i+1, vis, mp));
    }
public:
    int maxScore(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        ios::sync_with_stdio(0);
        cin.tie(0);
        int n = grid.size();
        int m = grid[0].size();

        unordered_map<string,int> mp;
        string vis = string(101,'0');
        return maxSum(grid, n, m, 0, vis, mp);
    }
};

[01/09/24, 9:32:20 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int maxScore(vector<vector<int>>& a) {
        using pii = pair<int, int>;
        int n = a.size(), m = a[0].size();
        vector<pii> ord;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < m; j++){
                ord.emplace_back(a[i][j], i);
            }
        }
        sort(ord.rbegin(), ord.rend());
        const int inf = 1<<30;
        vector<int> dp((1<<n), -inf);
        dp[0] = 0;
        for(int i = 0, j = 0; i < n * m; i = j){
            while(j < n * m && ord[i].first == ord[j].first) j++;
            vector<int> ndp = dp;
            for(int msk = 0; msk < (1<<n); msk++){
                for(int k = i; k < j; k++){
                    auto [val, p] = ord[k];
                    if((msk>>p)&1);
                    else ndp[msk | (1<<p)] = max(ndp[msk | (1<<p)], dp[msk] + val);
                }
            }
            dp = ndp;
        }
        return *max_element(dp.begin(), dp.end());
    }
};

[01/09/24, 10:10:45 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int dp[105][1030];
    int solve_dp(int ind,int mask,map<int,vector<int> >&index_){
        if(ind==0){
            return 0;
        }
        
        if(dp[ind][mask] != -1){
            return dp[ind][mask];
        }
        
        int res=solve_dp(ind-1,mask,index_);
        
        for(auto i:index_[ind]){
            if((mask & (1<<i))==0){
                res=max(res,ind+solve_dp(ind-1,mask|(1<<i),index_));
            }
        }
        
        return dp[ind][mask]=res;
    }
    int maxScore(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        memset(dp,-1,sizeof(dp));
        map<int,vector<int> > index_;
        int n=grid.size(),m=grid[0].size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m;j++){
                index_[grid[i][j]].push_back(i);
            }
        }
        
        return solve_dp(100,0,index_);
    }
};
[01/09/24, 10:12:39 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/select-cells-in-grid-with-maximum-score/solutions/5718075/focus-on-uniqueness-in-values-first-then-uniqueness-in-rows-full-explanation/
[01/09/24, 10:19:56 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> dp;
    vector<vector<int>> nums;
    int maxScore(vector<vector<int>>& g) {
        nums.resize(101);
        for (int i = 0; i < g.size(); ++i)
            for (int y = 0; y < g[0].size(); ++y)
                nums[g[i][y]].push_back(i);
        dp = vector<vector<int>>(101, vector<int>(1025, -1));
        return dfs(0, 0);
    }

    int dfs(int i, int bitMask){
        if (i == nums.size()) return 0;
        if (dp[i][bitMask] != -1)
            return dp[i][bitMask];
        // do not take
        int ans = dfs(i + 1, bitMask);
        // iterate row options
        for (int x = 0; x < nums[i].size(); ++x){
            int bit = 1 << nums[i][x];
            if ((bitMask & bit) == 0){
                int nextBit = bitMask | bit;
                ans = max(ans, dfs(i + 1, nextBit) + i);
            }
        }
        return dp[i][bitMask] = ans;
    }
};

[02/09/24, 7:58:59 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int chalkReplacer(vector<int>& chalk, int k) {
        long long sum = accumulate(chalk.begin(), chalk.end(), 0);
        k = k % sum;

        for(int i=0;i<chalk.size();i++){
            if(chalk[i] > k) return i;
            k -= chalk[i];
        }
        return 0;
    }
};
