[02/09/24, 4:05:19 PM] Satvik Saini: class DisjointSet{
private:
    unordered_map<int,int> parentMap;
    unordered_map<int,int> rankMap;
public:
    void insertSet(int x){
        parentMap[x] = x;
        rankMap[x] = 1;
    }
    int findSet(int x){
        if(parentMap[x] == x){
            return x;
        }

        return parentMap[x] = findSet(parentMap[x]);
    }
    int sizeSet(int x){
        int l_x = findSet(x);
        return rankMap[l_x];
    }
    void unionSet(int x, int y){
        int l_x = findSet(x);
        int l_y = findSet(y);

        if(l_x != l_y){
            int r_x = rankMap[l_x];
            int r_y = rankMap[l_y];

            if(r_x > r_y){
                parentMap[l_y] = l_x;
                rankMap[l_x] += rankMap[l_y];
            }
            else{
                parentMap[l_x] = l_y;
                rankMap[l_y] += rankMap[l_x];
            }
        }
    }
};

class Solution {
public:
    int minMalwareSpread(vector<vector<int>>& graph, vector<int>& initial) {
        int n = graph.size();

        DisjointSet ds;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            ds.insertSet(i);
        }

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                if(graph[i][j] == 1){
                    ds.unionSet(i, j);
                }
            }
        }

        unordered_map<int,int> MalwareMp; // <leader, count_malware>
        for(int i=0;i<initial.size();i++){
            MalwareMp[ds.findSet(initial[i])]++;
        }

        int bestMalware = INT_MAX;
        int maxSize = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<initial.size();i++){
            int leader = ds.findSet(initial[i]);

            if(MalwareMp[leader] == 1){
                int size = ds.sizeSet(leader);
                if(size > maxSize){
                    bestMalware = initial[i];
                    maxSize = ds.sizeSet(leader);
                }
                else if(size == maxSize){
                    bestMalware = min(bestMalware, initial[i]);
                }
            }
        }
        return bestMalware == INT_MAX ? *min_element(initial.begin(), initial.end()): bestMalware;
    }
};

[03/09/24, 3:18:29 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> dx = {1, -1, 0, 0}, dy = {0 , 0, 1, -1};
    bool isValid(int i, int j, int m, int n){
        return ((i >= 0 && i < m) && (j >= 0 && j < n));
    }

    int minimumObstacles(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {
        int m = grid.size(), n = grid[0].size();
        using p = pair<int, pair<int, int>>;
        priority_queue<p, vector<p>, greater<p>> pq;
        pq.push({0, {0, 0}});
        vector<vector<int>> distance(m, vector<int>(n, 1e6));
        distance[0][0] = 0;
        while(pq.size()){
            auto[weight, tmp] = pq.top();
            auto[curr_r, curr_c] = tmp;
            pq.pop();
            if(curr_r == m - 1 && curr_c == n - 1)
                return weight;
            for(int k = 0 ; k < 4 ; k++){
                int adj_r = dx[k] + curr_r, adj_c = dy[k] + curr_c;
                if(isValid(adj_r, adj_c, m, n)){
                    if(weight + grid[adj_r][adj_c] < distance[adj_r][adj_c]){
                        distance[adj_r][adj_c] = weight + grid[adj_r][adj_c];
                        pq.push({distance[adj_r][adj_c],{adj_r, adj_c}});
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
};

[05/09/24, 8:30:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> getDistances(vector<int>& arr) {
        using ll = long long;
        unordered_map<ll,vector<ll>> mpp;
        for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size() ; i++){
            mpp[arr[i]].push_back(i);
        }
        vector<ll > ans(arr.size());
        for(auto p : mpp){
            int ele = p.first;
            int n = p.second.size();
            vector<ll> prefix(n,0);
            for(int i=1 ; i<=n-1 ; i++){
                prefix[i] = prefix[i-1] + arr[i-1];
            }
            vector<ll> suffix(n,0);
            for(int i=n-2 ; i>=0 ; i--){
                suffix[i] = suffix[i+1] + arr[i+1];
            }
            for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
                ans[p.second[i]] += ( suffix[i]-prefix[i] - p.second[i]*(-n+2*i+1) );
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[05/09/24, 8:34:02 AM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long

class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> getDistances(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        vector<long long> v(n);
        unordered_map<ll,vector<ll>> mp;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            mp[arr[i]].push_back(i);
        }

        for(auto p : mp){
            int ele = p.first;
            vector<ll> occ = p.second;
            int n = occ.size();
            vector<ll> prefix(n), suffix(n);
            prefix[0] = 0, suffix[n-1] = 0;
            for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
                prefix[i+1] = prefix[i] + occ[i];
            }
            for(int i=n-2;i>=0;i--){
                suffix[i] = suffix[i+1] + occ[i+1];
            }
            for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
                v[occ[i]] = occ[i]*(2*i + 1 - n) - prefix[i] + suffix[i];
            }
        }
        return v;
    }
};
[05/09/24, 8:34:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> getDistances(vector<int>& arr) {
        using ll = long long;
        unordered_map<ll,vector<ll>> mpp;
        for(int i=0 ; i<arr.size() ; i++){
            mpp[arr[i]].push_back(i);
        }
        vector<ll > ans(arr.size());
        for(auto p : mpp){
            int ele = p.first;
            int n = p.second.size();
            vector<ll> prefix(n,0);
            for(int i=1 ; i<=n-1 ; i++){
                prefix[i] = prefix[i-1] + arr[i-1];
            }
            vector<ll> suffix(n,0);
            for(int i=n-2 ; i>=0 ; i--){
                suffix[i] = suffix[i+1] + arr[i+1];
            }
            for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
                ans[p.second[i]] += ( suffix[i]-prefix[i] + p.second[i]*(-n+2*i+1) );
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[06/09/24, 8:18:00 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int findMinHeight(int n, vector<vector<int>>& graph, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<int> indegree(n, 0); 
        for(auto &e : edges){   
            indegree[e[0]]++;
            indegree[e[1]]++;
        }

        // bfs
        queue<int> q;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(indegree[i] == 1) {
                q.push(i); 
            }
        } 
        
        int cnt = 0;
        while(!q.empty()){
            int sz = q.size();
            cnt++; 
            for(int i=0;i<sz;i++){
                int curr = q.front(); 
                q.pop();
                
                for(auto child : graph[curr]){ 
                    indegree[child]--;
                    if(indegree[child] == 1){
                        q.push(child); 
                    }   
                }
            }
        }
        return cnt; 
    }

    int diameter(int n, vector<vector<int>>& graph){
        queue<int> q;
        q.push(0);

        vector<int> vis(n,0), ans;

        while(!q.empty()){
            int sz = q.size();
            ans.clear();
            while(sz--){
                int node = q.front();
                q.pop();
                vis[node] = 1;
                ans.push_back(node);

                for(auto neighbour : graph[node]){
                    if(!vis[neighbour]) q.push(neighbour);
                }
            }
        }
        int node1 = ans[0];
        q.push(node1);
        int dist = 0;
        fill(vis.begin(), vis.end(), 0);
        while(!q.empty()){
            int sz = q.size();
            dist++;
            while(sz--){
                int node = q.front();
                q.pop();
                vis[node] = 1;
        
                for(auto neighbour : graph[node]){
                    if(!vis[neighbour]) q.push(neighbour);
                }
            }
        }
        return dist;
    }

public:
    int minimumDiameterAfterMerge(vector<vector<int>>& edges1, vector<vector<int>>& edges2) {
        int n = 0, m = 0;
        for(auto e : edges1){
            n = max(n, max(e[0],e[1]));
        }
        for(auto e : edges2){
            m = max(m, max(e[0],e[1]));
        }
        n++;m++;

        vector<vector<int>> graph1(n), graph2(m);
        for(auto &e : edges1){   
            graph1[e[0]].push_back(e[1]);
            graph1[e[1]].push_back(e[0]);
        }

        for(auto &e : edges2){   
            graph2[e[0]].push_back(e[1]);
            graph2[e[1]].push_back(e[0]);
        }

        int h1 = findMinHeight(n, graph1, edges1);
        int h2 = findMinHeight(m, graph2, edges2);

        return max(h1+h2+1, max(diameter(n, graph1), diameter(m, graph2)));
    }
};

[06/09/24, 9:13:33 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: int findMinHeightTrees(int total, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<int> adj[total];
        vector<int> degree(total,0);
        if(edges.size() == 0) return {0};
        for(auto it :  edges){
            adj[it[0]].push_back(it[1]);
            adj[it[1]].push_back(it[0]);
            degree[it[0]]++;
            degree[it[1]]++;
        }
        queue<int> q;
        for(int i=0 ; i<total ; i++){
            if(degree[i] == 1) q.push(i);
        }
        int h = 1;
        while(total > 2){
            h++;
            int n = q.size();
            total -= n;
            while(n--){
                int front = q.front();
                q.pop();
                for(int neighbour : adj[front]){
                    degree[neighbour]--;
                    if(degree[neighbour] == 1){
                        q.push(neighbour);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        vector<int> res;
        while(!q.empty()){
            res.push_back(q.front());
            q.pop();
        }
        return h;
        
    }

[07/09/24, 8:31:43 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/linked-list-in-binary-tree/description/?envType=daily-question&envId=2024-09-07
[07/09/24, 8:32:51 AM] Satvik Saini: /**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * struct ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode *next;
 *     ListNode() : val(0), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x, ListNode *next) : val(x), next(next) {}
 * };
 */
/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    bool isSubPath(ListNode* head, TreeNode* root) {
        // base case
        if(!head) return 1;
        if(!root) return 0;

        // recursive case
        bool ans = 0;
        if(root->val == head->val){
            ans = isSubPath(head->next, root->left) || isSubPath(head->next, root->right);
        }
        if(!ans) ans = isSubPath(head, root->left) || isSubPath(head, root->right);
        return ans;
    }
};

[07/09/24, 8:48:24 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    bool subPath(ListNode* head, TreeNode* root) {
        if (!head) return true;
        if (!root) return false;
        
        // Check if current nodes match and recursively check the next list node with the children of the tree node
        if (root->val == head->val) {
            return subPath(head->next, root->left) || subPath(head->next, root->right);
        }
        return false;
    }
    
public:
    bool isSubPath(ListNode* head, TreeNode* root) {
        if (!root) return false;  // If the tree is empty, there is no subpath

        // Check if the list starts at the current node or somewhere down the left or right subtrees
        return subPath(head, root) || isSubPath(head, root->left) || isSubPath(head, root->right);
    }
};

[07/09/24, 12:52:21 PM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-number-of-refueling-stops/description/
[07/09/24, 12:53:47 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int minStops(int target, int fuel, vector<vector<int>>& stations, int i){
        // base case
        if(fuel >= target - ((i > 0) ? stations[i-1][0] : 0)) return 0;
        if(i == stations.size()){
            // if(fuel >= target - stations[i-1][1]) return 0;
            return 1e8;
        }
        if(fuel < stations[i][0]) return 1e8;

        // recursive case
        int distToNext = stations[i][0] - ((i>0) ? stations[i-1][0] : 0);
        // refuel 
        int refuel = 1 + minStops(target, fuel - distToNext + stations[i][1], stations, i+1);
        // dont refuel
        int dont_refuel = minStops(target, fuel - distToNext, stations, i+1);
        return min(refuel, dont_refuel);
    }
public:
    int minRefuelStops(int target, int startFuel, vector<vector<int>>& stations) {
        if(stations.size() == 0){
            if(startFuel >= target) return 0;
            return -1;
        }
        int ans = minStops(target, startFuel, stations, 0);
        return ans >= 1e8 ? -1 : ans;
    }
};

[07/09/24, 2:06:17 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: if we can't reach target, I will first use the largestfuel Station
			(which can take me farthest) and move ahead and keep doing this.
[07/09/24, 2:09:45 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: //Approach-3 : O(nlog(n)) using max-heap
//Similar Problem : Leetcode 1642. Furthest Building You Can Reach
class Solution {
public:
    int minRefuelStops(int target, int startFuel, vector<vector<int>>& stations) {
        int n = stations.size();
        
        priority_queue<int> pq; //max heap
        /*
			if we can't reach target, I will first use the largestfuel Station
			(which can take me farthest) and move ahead and keep doing this.
        */
        int curr = startFuel; //my current position
        int i = 0; //station index
        int result = 0;
        while(curr < target) { //until I reach my target
            while(i < n && curr >= stations[i][0]) {
                /*
					  Sice, I am already ahead of or at this station
					  (i.e. curr >= stations[i][0])  we don't use this
					  station and try to move ahead but I store this
					  station in maxheap to use in future
				*/
                pq.push(stations[i][1]);
				//Keep the station at top which can take me farthest (maximum gas)
                i++;
            }
            
            if(pq.empty()) //we can't move further now
                return -1;
            
            int dist = pq.top();
            pq.pop();
            
            curr += dist;
            result++;
        }
        
        return result;
        
    }
};
[07/09/24, 2:16:27 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
int minRefuelStops(int target, int startFuel, vector<vector>& stations)
{
priority_queue<pair<int,int>>pq,temp;//fuel,position
pair<int,int>p;
int num_refuel=0;
int total_fuel=startFuel;
int i=0;
for(i=0;i<stations.size();i++)
{
p.first=stations[i][1];
p.second=stations[i][0];
pq.push(p);
}
while(total_fuel<target)
{
int cur_fuel=total_fuel;
while(!pq.empty()&&cur_fuel==total_fuel)
{
p=pq.top();
pq.pop();
if(p.second<=total_fuel)//We can refuel or not, since total_fuel tells us max distance we can go at present
{
total_fuel+=p.first;
num_refuel++;
}
else
{
temp.push(p);
}
}
if(pq.empty()&&cur_fuel==total_fuel){return -1;}//We cant reach target
while(!temp.empty())
{
p=temp.top();
temp.pop();
pq.push(p);
}
}
return num_refuel;
}

[07/09/24, 2:18:37 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int minRefuelStops(int target, int startFuel, vector<vector>& stations) {
        priority_queue<pair<int, int>> pq, temp; // fuel,position
        pair<int, int> p;
        int num_refuel = 0;
        int total_fuel = startFuel;
        int i = 0;
        for (i = 0; i < stations.size(); i++) {
            p.first = stations[i][1];
            p.second = stations[i][0];
            pq.push(p);
        }
        while (total_fuel < target) {
            int cur_fuel = total_fuel;
            while (!pq.empty() && cur_fuel == total_fuel) {
                p = pq.top();
                pq.pop();
                if (p.second <=
                    total_fuel) // We can refuel or not, since total_fuel tells
                                // us max distance we can go at present
                {
                    total_fuel += p.first;
                    num_refuel++;
                } else {
                    temp.push(p);
                }
            }
            if (pq.empty() && cur_fuel == total_fuel) {
                return -1;
            } // We cant reach target
            while (!temp.empty()) {
                p = temp.top();
                temp.pop();
                pq.push(p);
            }
        }
        return num_refuel;
    }
};

[08/09/24, 10:45:24 AM] Satvik Saini: char slowestKey(vector<vector<int>>& keyTimes){
    int maxTime = keyTimes[0][1];
    char ch = keyTimes[0][0] + 'a';
    for(int i=0;i<keyTimes.size()-1;i++){
        if(keyTimes[i+1][1] - keyTimes[i][1] > maxTime){
            maxTime = keyTimes[i+1][1] - keyTimes[i][1];
            ch = keyTimes[i+1][0] + 'a';
        }
    }
    return ch;
}

[08/09/24, 10:50:17 AM] Satvik Saini: char slowestKey(vector<vector<int>>& keyTimes) {
    int maxTime = 0;
    char resultKey = 'a';
    
    // Calculate the time to press each key and find the maximum time
    for (int i = 0; i < keyTimes.size(); ++i) {
        int key = keyTimes[i][0];        // Key (encoded as 0 for 'a', 1 for 'b', etc.)
        int pressTime = keyTimes[i][1];  // Time the key was pressed

        // Calculate the difference in time between consecutive key presses
        int timeDiff = pressTime - (i == 0 ? 0 : keyTimes[i - 1][1]);

        // Update maxTime and resultKey if a longer time is found
        if (timeDiff > maxTime) {
            maxTime = timeDiff;
            resultKey = 'a' + key;  // Convert key index to corresponding character
        }
    }
    
    return resultKey;
}
[08/09/24, 10:52:16 AM] Satvik Saini: int getMinOperations(int k) {
    // DP array to store the minimum number of operations to reach each value
    vector<int> dp(k + 1, 0);

    // Base case: 0 operations needed to reach 0
    dp[0] = 0;

    // Fill the DP table from 1 to k
    for (int i = 1; i <= k; ++i) {
        // Option 1: Add 1 to reach i
        dp[i] = dp[i - 1] + 1;

        // Option 2: If i is even, we can reach i by multiplying (i / 2) by 2
        if (i % 2 == 0) {
            dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[i / 2] + 1);
        }
    }

    // The value dp[k] contains the minimum number of operations to reach k
    return dp[k];
}

[09/09/24, 2:51:47 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int largestCombination(vector<int>& candidates) {
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<32;i++){
            int cnt_1 = 0;
            for(int ele : candidates){
                cnt_1 += (ele>>i) & 1;
            }
            ans = max(ans, cnt_1);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[09/09/24, 6:26:12 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> getSkyline(vector<vector<int>>& buildings) {
        int n = buildings.size();
        vector<vector<int>> ans;

        ans.push_back({buildings[0][0],buildings[0][2]});
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            // compare building i and i-1
            if(buildings[i-1][1] < buildings[i][0]){
                // new segment
                ans.push_back({buildings[i-1][1],0});  // bottom point of previous segment
                ans.push_back({buildings[i][0],buildings[i][2]});
            }
            else{
                // same segment
                if(buildings[i-1][2] < buildings[i][2]){
                    ans.push_back({buildings[i][0],buildings[i][2]});
                }
                else if(buildings[i-1][2] > buildings[i][2]){
                    ans.push_back({buildings[i-1][1],buildings[i][2]});
                }
            }
        }
        ans.push_back({buildings[n-1][1],0});
        return ans;
    }
};

[10/09/24, 8:05:10 PM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int element_size;
    cin >> element_size;
    
    vector<int> elements(element_size);
    for (int i = 0; i < element_size; i++) {
        cin >> elements[i];
    }

    int lowerBand, upperBand;
    cin >> lowerBand >> upperBand;

    int count = 0;

    // Check every pair of distinct elements
    for (int i = 0; i < element_size; i++) {
        for (int j = i + 1; j < element_size; j++) {
            int sum = elements[i] + elements[j];
            if (sum >= lowerBand && sum <= upperBand) {
                count++;
            }
        }
    }

    // Output the result
    cout << count << endl;

    return 0;
}

[16/09/24, 8:55:15 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    unordered_map<int,int> mp;
    int sz;
public:
    Solution(ListNode* head) {
        int idx = 0;
        while(head){
            mp[idx] = head->val;
            head = head->next;
            idx++;
        }
        sz = idx;
    }
    
    int getRandom() {
        return mp[rand()%sz];
    }
};
[16/09/24, 9:01:16 AM] Satvik Saini: // sort the time
// either the ans will be the difference of consecutive times or diff btw first and last

class Solution {
    int calcMinutes(string t1, string t2){
        int h1 = stoi(t1.substr(0,2));
        int h2 = stoi(t2.substr(0,2));
        int m1 = stoi(t1.substr(3,2));
        int m2 = stoi(t2.substr(3,2));
        int hDiff1 = (h2 - h1)*60;
        int mDiff1 = m2 - m1;

        int hDiff2 = (23 - h2 + h1)*60;
        int mDiff2 = abs(60 - m2 + m1);

        return min(hDiff1 + mDiff1, hDiff2 + mDiff2);
    }
public:
    int findMinDifference(vector<string>& timePoints) {
        sort(timePoints.begin(), timePoints.end());
        int minTime = INT_MAX;
        for(int i=0;i<timePoints.size()-1;i++){
            minTime = min(minTime, calcMinutes(timePoints[i],timePoints[i+1]));
        }
        return min(minTime, calcMinutes(timePoints[0],timePoints.back()));
    }
};
[16/09/24, 9:04:29 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    int findMinDifference(vector<string>& times) {
        int n = times.size();
        sort(times.begin(), times.end());
        int mindiff = INT_MAX;
        for (int i = 0; i < times.size(); i++) {
            int diff = abs(timeDiff(times[(i - 1 + n) % n], times[i]));
            diff = min(diff, 1440 - diff);
            mindiff = min(mindiff, diff);
        }
        return mindiff;
    }

private:
    int timeDiff(string t1, string t2) {
        int h1 = stoi(t1.substr(0, 2));
        int m1 = stoi(t1.substr(3, 2));
        int h2 = stoi(t2.substr(0, 2));
        int m2 = stoi(t2.substr(3, 2));
        return (h2 - h1) * 60 + (m2 - m1);
    }
};
[16/09/24, 9:07:46 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:

    int convertToMinutes(const string& time) {
        int hours = stoi(time.substr(0, 2));  // Extract hours
        int minutes = stoi(time.substr(3, 2)); // Extract minutes
        return hours * 60 + minutes;
    }

    int findMinDifference(vector<string>& timePoints) {
      // Step 1: Convert all time points to minutes
    vector<int> minutes;
    for (const string& time : timePoints) {
        minutes.push_back(convertToMinutes(time));
    }
    
    // Step 2: Sort the time points in minutes
    sort(minutes.begin(), minutes.end());

    // Step 3: Calculate minimum difference between consecutive time points
    int minDiff = INT_MAX;
    for (int i = 1; i < minutes.size(); ++i) {
        minDiff = min(minDiff, minutes[i] - minutes[i - 1]);
    }
    
    // Step 4: Handle circular case (difference between the last and first time points)
    int circularDiff = (1440 - minutes.back() + minutes[0]);
    minDiff = min(minDiff, circularDiff);

    return minDiff;  
    }
};
[16/09/24, 9:08:58 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:

    int convertToMinutes(const string& time) {
        int hours = stoi(time.substr(0, 2));  // Extract hours
        int minutes = stoi(time.substr(3, 2)); // Extract minutes
        return hours * 60 + minutes;
    }

    int findMinDifference(vector<string>& timePoints) {
      // Step 1: Convert all time points to minutes
    vector<int> minutes;
    for (const string& time : timePoints) {
        minutes.push_back(convertToMinutes(time));
    }
    
    // Step 2: Sort the time points in minutes
    sort(minutes.begin(), minutes.end());

    // Step 3: Calculate minimum difference between consecutive time points
    int minDiff = INT_MAX;
    for (int i = 1; i < minutes.size(); ++i) {
        minDiff = min(minDiff, minutes[i] - minutes[i - 1]);
    }
    
    // Step 4: Handle circular case (difference between the last and first time points)
    int circularDiff = (1440 - minutes.back() + minutes[0]);
    minDiff = min(minDiff, circularDiff);

    return minDiff;  
    }
};

[18/09/24, 8:05:07 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class cmp{
    public:
    bool operator()(int& a , int &b){
        string s1 = to_string(a);
        string s2 = to_string(b);
        int n = s1.size();
        int m = s2.size();
        for(int i=0 ; i<min(n,m) ;i++){
            if(s1[i] < s2[i]) return false;
            else if(s2[i] > s1[i]) return true;
        }
        return s1.size() > s2.size();
    }
};
class Solution {
public:
    string largestNumber(vector<int>& nums) {
        string res;
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end(),cmp());
        for(int i=0 ; i<nums.size() ; i++){
            res += to_string(nums[i]);
        }
        return res;
    }
};
[18/09/24, 8:20:28 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    long long smallestNumber(long long num) {
        string s = to_string(abs(num));
        if(num < 0){
            sort(s.rbegin(),s.rend());
            long long a = stoll(s);
            return -1*a;
        }
        else{
            sort(s.begin(),s.end());
            for(int i=0 ; i<n ; i++){
                if(s[i] == 0) continue;
                else{
                    swap(s[i],s[0]);
                    break;
                }
            }
            long long a = stoll(s);
            return a;
        }
        return 1;
    }
};
[18/09/24, 9:04:27 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎9 min
[18/09/24, 9:04:52 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int nextValidIdx(vector<int>& nums, int k, vector<int> &prefSum, int idx, vector<int> &ans){
        int i = idx, n = nums.size();
        while(i <= n-k){
            long long actual_sum = prefSum[i+k] - prefSum[i];
            long long expected_sum = (long long)(nums[i]+k-1)*(nums[i]+k)/2 - (long long)(nums[i]-1)*nums[i]/2;
            if(actual_sum == expected_sum){
                int j = i+1;
                bool flag = 1;
                while(j < i+k){
                    if(nums[j]-nums[j-1] != 1){
                        flag = 0;
                        break;
                    }
                    j++;
                }
                if(flag){
                    ans.push_back(nums[i]+k-1);
                    break;
                }
                else ans.push_back(-1);
            }
            else ans.push_back(-1);
            i++;
        }
        return i;
    }
public:
    vector<int> resultsArray(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> ans;
        vector<int> prefSum(n+1, 0);
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            prefSum[i+1] = prefSum[i] + nums[i];
        }
        
        int i = nextValidIdx(nums, k, prefSum, 0, ans);
        int j = i+k;
        while(j<n){
            if(nums[j] - nums[j-1] == 1) ans.push_back(nums[j]);
            else{
                for(int l=j;l<min(j+k-1,n);l++) ans.push_back(-1);
                i = nextValidIdx(nums, k, prefSum, j, ans);
                j = i+k-1;
            }
            j++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

[19/09/24, 8:31:59 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    bool isOperator(string exp, int i){
        if (exp[i] == '+' || exp[i] == '-' || exp[i] == '*') return true;
        return false;
    }
    int doOperator(string exp,int i, int x, int y){
        if(exp[i] == '+') return x+y;
        if(exp[i] == '-') return x-y;
        return x*y;
    }
    int f(int i, int j, string& exp, vector<int> & res, vector<int> Opcount){
        // base case
        if( Opcount[j] - (i>0) ? Opcount[i-1] : 0 == 1){
            int k = i+1;
            int num1 = exp[i]-'0';
            while(!isOperator(exp,k)){
                num1 = num1*10 + exp[k]-'0';
                k++;
            }
            int op = k++;
            int num2 = exp[k]-'0';
            while(k<=j){
                num2 = num2*10 + exp[k++]-'0';
            }  
            return doOperator(exp,op,num1,num2);         
        }
        
        // recursive case
        int k = i+1;
        vector<int> temp;
        while(exp[k]>='0' && exp[k]<='9') k++;
        for( ; k<j ; k++){
            if(isOperator(exp,k)){
                // i,k-1 , k+1,j
                int num1 = f(i,k-1,exp,res,Opcount);
                int num2 = f(k+1,j,exp,res,Opcount);
                temp.push_back(doOperator(exp,k,num1,num2));
            }
        }
        res = temp;
        return 
    }
    vector<int> diffWaysToCompute(string exp) {
        vector<int> res;
        vector<int> Opcount(exp.size()+1,0);
        for(int i=1 ; i<exp.size() ; i++){
            if(isOperator(exp,i)){
                Opcount[i]++;
            }
            Opcount[i] += Opcount[i-1]
        }
        f(exp,0,exp.size()-1,res,Opcount);
        return res;

    }
};

// interface

// An Interface is defined as an abstract type used to specify the behavior of a class
// an interface could only have abstract methods and it can't be intantiated
// a class can implement multiple interfaces
// an interface can extend another interface just like classes
/* interface A{
    int age = 100; // variables in interface asre final and static;
    public void show();
    public void detail();
    
}
// if class B does not completely override all the abstract methods in A, then B will e treated as an abstract class
class B implements A{
    public void show(){
        System.out.println("hii in B");
    }
    public void detail(){
        System.out.println("hii in B");
    }
}


class myjava{
    public static void main(String arg[]){
        B obj = new B();
        obj.show();
        System.out.println(A.age);
    }
} */

// Abstract Class

// abstract keyword is used to define methods in the abstract class that needs to be override by the inherited
// sub classes,  we can't create an object of the abstract class
/* abstract class A{
    public void model(){
        System.out.println("in A");
    }
    abstract public void drive();
}

class B extends A{
    public void drive(){
        System.out.println("overriding abstract method");
    }
}

class myjava{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        B obj = new B();
        obj.drive();
    }

// see upcasting and downcasting if required, it is easy

// if final keyword is used with a method of a class then it cannot be overrided again by any subclass
// or we can say that method overriding will not take place

// runtime polymorphism - dynamic method dispatch

// here which show method is executed will be decided on the run time
/* class A{
    public void show(){
        System.out.println("in A");
    }
}

        System.out.println("in B");
    }
}

        A obj = new A();
        obj.show();

        obj.show();
    }
} */

// rum time - method overriding
// compile time - method overloading

// constructor inheritance

// the constructor of both super class and child class is called
// there is a super method inside each constructor that is called by the compiler itself if not mentioned explicitly
// the super method calls the constructor of the parent class 
/* class A{
    public A(){
        super();
        System.out.println("in A");
    }
    public A(int a){
        System.out.println("in A param");
    }
}
class B extends A{
    public B(){
        super(); // since the super don't have any parameter so it calls the default constructor of A
        super(1); // this have a parameter so it calls the parameterised constructor of A
        System.out.println("in B");
    }
}

class myjava{
    public static void main(String[] args) {

[22/09/24, 9:01:35 AM] Satvik Saini: ng long

class Solution {
    vector<vector<ll>> dp;

    ll minSeconds(int h, int i, vector<int>& work) {
        // base cases
        if (h == 0) return 0;
        if (i == work.size()) return 1e15;

        // lookup
        if (dp[h][i] != -1) return dp[h][i];

        ll ans = LLONG_MAX;
        for (int k = 0; k <= h; ++k) {
            ans = min(ans, (ll)work[i] * k * (k + 1) / 2 + minSeconds(h - k,
            i + 1, work));
        }
        return dp[h][i] = ans;
    }

public:
    long long minNumberOfSeconds(int mountainHeight, vector<int>&
    workerTimes) {
        dp = vector<vector<ll>>(mountainHeight + 1,
        vector<ll>(workerTimes.size() + 1, -1)); return
        minSeconds(mountainHeight, 0, workerTimes);
    }
};

[22/09/24, 9:07:14 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    vector<vector<ll>> dp;

    ll minSeconds(int h, int i, vector<int>& work) {
        // base cases
        if (h == 0) return 0;
        if (i == work.size()) return 1e15;

        // lookup
        if (dp[h][i] != -1) return dp[h][i];

        ll ans = LLONG_MAX;
        for (int k = 0; k <= h; ++k) {
            ans = min(ans, max((ll)work[i] * k * (k + 1) / 2, minSeconds(h - k,i + 1, work)));
        }
        return dp[h][i] = ans;
    }

public:
    long long minNumberOfSeconds(int mountainHeight, vector<int>&
    workerTimes) {
        dp = vector<vector<ll>>(mountainHeight + 1,
        vector<ll>(workerTimes.size() + 1, -1)); return
        minSeconds(mountainHeight, 0, workerTimes);
    }
};
[22/09/24, 9:18:31 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎4 min
[22/09/24, 9:18:20 AM] Satvik Saini: #define ll long long

class Solution {
    bool isPossible(int mountainHeight, vector<int>& workerTimes, ll mid) {
        for (int time : workerTimes) {
            ll a = 1, b = 1, c = -2*mid/time;
            ll d = 1 - 4*a*c;
            if (d < 0) continue;
            ll x = (-1+sqrt(d))/2;

            mountainHeight -= x;
            if(mountainHeight <= 0) return 1;
        }
        return mountainHeight <= 0;
    }

public:
    ll minNumberOfSeconds(int mountainHeight, vector<int>& workerTimes) {
        ll s = 0, e = 1e14;

        while (s < e) {
            ll mid = (s + e) / 2;
            if (isPossible(mountainHeight, workerTimes, mid)) e = mid;
            else s = mid + 1;
        }
        return s;
    }
};

[02/10/24, 2:14:41 PM] Satvik Saini: import java.sql.*;

public class Java_Assignment1 {
    private static final String url = "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/practice";
    private static final String user = "root";
    private static final String password = "Muneeb@123";
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try{
            Class.forName("com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver");
            Connection conn = DriverManager.getConnection(url, user, password);
            // Statements
            Statement statement = conn.createStatement();
            // select query
            String query = "SELECT * FROM employee";
            ResultSet resultSet = statement.executeQuery(query);
            
            while (resultSet.next()) {
                String name = resultSet.getString("name");
                int age = resultSet.getInt("age");
                int salary = resultSet.getInt("salary");
                System.out.println("Name: "+name);
                System.out.println("Age: "+age);
                System.out.println("Salary: "+salary);
            }
            
            // update query
            String query2 = "INSERT INTO employee (name, age, salary) VALUES ('Suryansh', 21, 150000), ('Aksh', 20, 150000)";
            int affect = statement.executeUpdate(query2);

            if(affect > 0){
                System.out.println("Data Inserted Successfully");
            }
            else{
                System.out.println("Data Insertion Failed");
            }

            conn.close();
            statement.close();
            resultSet.close();
        }
        catch (Exception e){
            System.out.println(e);
        }
    }
}

[04/10/24, 8:23:31 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int minSubarray(vector<int>& A, int p) {
        int n = A.size(), res = n, need = 0, cur = 0;
        for (auto a : A)
            need = (need + a) % p;
        unordered_map<int, int> last = {{0, -1}};
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            cur = (cur + A[i]) % p;
            last[cur] = i;
            int want = (cur - need + p) % p;
            if (last.count(want))
                res = min(res, i - last[want]);
        }
        return res < n ? res : -1;
    }
};
‎[04/10/24, 8:26:27 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎image omitted
‎[04/10/24, 8:29:04 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎image omitted
[04/10/24, 8:30:43 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <vector>
#include <unordered_map>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    int minSubarray(vector<int>& nums, int p) {
        long totalSum = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            totalSum += num;
        }

        // Find the remainder when total sum is divided by p
        int rem = totalSum % p;
        if (rem == 0) return 0; // If the remainder is 0, no subarray needs to be removed

        unordered_map<int, int> prefixMod;
        prefixMod[0] = -1;  // Initialize for handling full prefix
        long prefixSum = 0;
        int minLength = nums.size();

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); ++i) {
            prefixSum += nums[i];
            int currentMod = prefixSum % p;
            int targetMod = (currentMod - rem + p) % p;

            if (prefixMod.find(targetMod) != prefixMod.end()) {
                minLength = min(minLength, i - prefixMod[targetMod]);
            }

            prefixMod[currentMod] = i;
        }

        return minLength == nums.size() ? -1 : minLength;
    }
};
[04/10/24, 9:14:02 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎Voice call, ‎6 min
[04/10/24, 9:14:36 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/circular-array-loop/
[04/10/24, 9:19:26 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    bool circularArrayLoop(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        vector<int> vis(n, 0);
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (vis[i]) continue;
            
            int idx = i;
            bool isCycle = true; 
            while (!vis[idx]) {
                vis[idx] = 1;
                int nxt_idx = ((idx + nums[idx]) % n + n) % n;

                if (nums[idx] * nums[nxt_idx] < 0 || nxt_idx == idx) {
                    isCycle = 0;
                    break;
                }
                
                idx = nxt_idx; 
            }
            if (isCycle) return 1;
        }
        return 0; 
    }
};

[05/10/24, 8:50:03 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    void populate(vector<int> parent[], vector<set<int>> &ancestor, int i, int idx){
        // base case
        if(parent[i].size() == 0) return;

        // recursive case
        for(int j=0;j<parent[i].size();j++){
            if(ancestor[idx].find(parent[i][j]) == ancestor[idx].end()){
                ancestor[idx].insert(parent[i][j]);
                populate(parent, ancestor, parent[i][j], idx);
            }
        }
    }
public:
    vector<vector<int>> getAncestors(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<set<int>> ancestor(n);
        vector<int> parent[n];
        for(auto e : edges){
            parent[e[1]].push_back(e[0]);
        }

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            populate(parent,ancestor,i,i);
        }
        vector<vector<int>> ans(n);
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(ancestor[i].size()){
                for(int ele : ancestor[i]){
                    ans[i].push_back(ele);
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
[05/10/24, 9:04:13 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
  public:
    int rotateDelete(vector<int> &arr) {
        int i = 1;
        int n = arr.size();
        while (i < (n / 2) + 1) {
            // rotating the array
            rotate(arr.begin(), arr.end() - 1, arr.end());
            // delete (z-k+1)th element
            arr.erase(arr.begin() + (arr.size() - i));
            i++;
        }
        return arr[0];
    }
};

  public:
    int rotateDelete(vector<int> &arr) {

    }

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
int main() {
	int n;
	cin>>n;
	vector<vector<int>> circle(n,vector<int>(2));
	for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		cin>>circle[i][0]>>circle[i][1];
	}
	sort(circle.begin(), circle.end());
	int rb = circle[0][0] + circle[0][1];
	int ans1 = 0;
	for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
		if(circle[i][0]-circle[i][1] < rb){
			// remove ith circle
			ans1++;
		}
		else rb = max(rb, circle[i][0]+circle[i][1]);
	}
	sort(circle.rbegin(), circle.rend());
	int lb = circle[0][0] - circle[0][1];
	int ans2 = 0;
	for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
		if(circle[i][0]+circle[i][1] > lb){
			ans2++;
		}
		else lb = min(lb, circle[i][0]-circle[i][1]);
	}
	cout<<min(ans1, ans2)<<endl;
}

[05/10/24, 11:20:32 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

bool comp(vector<int> &a, vector<int> &b) {
    if((a[0] + a[1]) == (b[0] + b[1])) {
        return (a[0] - a[1]) < (b[0] - b[1]);
    }
    return (a[0] + a[1]) < (b[0] + b[1]);
}

int main() {
    int ans = 1;
    int n;
    cin >> n;

    vector<vector<int>> v(n, vector<int>(2));

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> v[i][0] >> v[i][1];
    }

    sort(v.begin(), v.end(), comp);

    int val = v[0][0] + v[0][1];

    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        if (val <= v[i][0] - v[i][1]) {
            ans++;
            val = v[i][0] + v[i][1];
        }
    }

    cout << n - ans << endl;
}

[06/10/24, 11:26:41 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: long long minimumWeeklyInput(vector<int> costs, int weeks) 
{ 
    int n = costs.size(); 
    vector<vector<long long>> dp(n + 1, vector<long long>(weeks + 1, 1e18)); 

    dp[0][0] = 0; 

    for (int w = 1; w <= weeks; ++w) 
    { 
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) 
        { 
            long long max_cost_in_week = 0; 
            for (int k = i; k > 0; --k) 
            { 
                max_cost_in_week = max(max_cost_in_week, (long long)costs[k - 1]); 
                if (dp[k - 1][w - 1] != 1e18) 
                { 
                    dp[i][w] = min(dp[i][w], dp[k - 1][w - 1] + max_cost_in_week); 
                } 
            } 
        } 
    } 
    return dp[n][weeks]; 
}
[06/10/24, 11:30:03 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #!/bin/python3

import math
import os
import random
import re
import sys



def efficientTrek(trails, record):
    n = len(trails)
        dp = [[float('inf')] * (record + 1) for _ in range(n + 1)]
    dp[0][0] = 0 

    for j in range(1, record + 1):  
        for i in range(1, n + 1): 
            max_length = 0  
            for k in range(i, 0, -1): 
                max_length = max(max_length, trails[k - 1]) 
                dp[i][j] = min(dp[i][j], dp[k - 1][j - 1] + max_length)
                
    return dp[n][record]

[06/10/24, 11:33:46 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
#include <climits>

using namespace std;

int efficientTrek(const vector<int>& trails, int record) {
    int n = trails.size();
    vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 1, vector<int>(record + 1, INT_MAX));
    dp[0][0] = 0;

    for (int j = 1; j <= record; ++j) {
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
            int max_length = 0;
            for (int k = i; k > 0; --k) {
                max_length = max(max_length, trails[k - 1]);
                dp[i][j] = min(dp[i][j], dp[k - 1][j - 1] + max_length);
            }
        }
    }

    return dp[n][record];
}

[06/10/24, 11:41:29 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;

// Function to calculate the minimum sum of the maximum trail length for each day
int minimizeMaxTrail(const vector<int>& trails, int record) {
    int n = trails.size();
    
    // DP table to store minimum sum of maximum trails
    vector<vector<int>> dp(n + 1, vector<int>(record + 1, INT_MAX));
    
    // Base case: dp[0][0] = 0, no trails, no days
    dp[0][0] = 0;

    // Fill DP table
    for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
        for (int k = 1; k <= record; ++k) {
            int maxTrail = 0;
            // Try partitioning the trails at every possible position
            for (int j = i; j > 0; --j) {
                maxTrail = max(maxTrail, trails[j - 1]);  // Track the maximum trail in the current partition
                if (dp[j - 1][k - 1] != INT_MAX) {
                    dp[i][k] = min(dp[i][k], dp[j - 1][k - 1] + maxTrail);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    return dp[n][record];
}

int main() {
    // Example usage
    vector<int> trails = {10, 5, 9, 3, 8, 15};
    int record = 2;
    
    cout << "Minimum sum of maximum trail lengths: " << minimizeMaxTrail(trails, record) << endl;
    return 0;
}

[06/10/24, 11:47:19 AM] Satvik Saini: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

long calculateTotalRegion(const vector<int>& h) {
    int n = h.size();
    vector<long> l(n, 1);
    vector<long> r(n, 1);

    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        int j = i - 1;
        while (j >= 0 && h[j] <= h[i]) {
            l[i] += l[j];
            j -= l[j];
        }
    }

    for (int i = n - 2; i >= 0; i--) {
        int j = i + 1;
        while (j < n && h[j] <= h[i]) {
            r[i] += r[j];
            j += r[j];
        }
    }

    long t = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        t += l[i] + r[i] - 1;
    }

    return t;
}

int main() {
    vector<int> heights = {2, 1, 4, 5, 1, 3, 3};
    cout << "Total Region: " << calculateTotalRegion(heights) << endl;
    
    return 0;
}

[06/10/24, 11:58:35 AM] Satvik Saini: pair<int, int> assignProcesses(vector<int>& times) {
    int n = times.size();
    vector<vector<pair<int, int>>> dp(n, vector<pair<int, int>>(2, {0, 0}));

    // Initial assignment when the latch is with core 1
    dp[0][0] = {times[0], 0}; // Core 1 gets the 1st process
    dp[0][1] = {0, times[0]}; // Core 2 gets the 1st process

    for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
        // Assigning process i to core 1
        dp[i][0].first = max(dp[i - 1][0].first + times[i], dp[i - 1][1].first);
        dp[i][0].second = max(dp[i - 1][0].second, dp[i - 1][1].second + times[i]);

        // Assigning process i to core 2
        dp[i][1].first = max(dp[i - 1][0].first, dp[i - 1][1].first + times[i]);
        dp[i][1].second = max(dp[i - 1][0].second + times[i], dp[i - 1][1].second);
    }

    // Find the optimal solution considering both cores
    pair<int, int> result = {
        max(dp[n - 1][0].first, dp[n - 1][1].first),
        max(dp[n - 1][0].second, dp[n - 1][1].second)
    };

    return result;
}

[07/10/24, 8:33:03 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int shortestPathLength(vector<vector<int>>& graph) {
        int n = graph.size();
        vector<int> inDegMap(n,0);
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            inDegMap[i]++;
            for(int it : graph[i]){
                inDegMap[it]++;
            }
        }
        int ele, indeg = INT_MAX;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(indeg < inDegMap[i]){
                indeg = inDegMap[i];
                ele = i;
            }
        }

        queue<vector<int>> q;
        q.push({ele, 0, ele == 0 ? 1 : (1<<ele)});

        while(!q.empty()){
            int node = q.front()[0];
            int dist = q.front()[1];
            int vis_mask = q.front()[2];
            q.pop();

            if(vis_mask == (1<<n)-1) return dist;

            for(int it : graph[node]){
                q.push({it, dist + 1, vis_mask | (1<<it)});
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
};

[09/10/24, 8:25:36 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/number-of-restricted-paths-from-first-to-last-node/
[09/10/24, 8:27:16 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    int dfs_helper(int s, vector<pair<int,int>> adj[], vector<int> &distMap, vector<int> &vis, int n){
        // base case 
        if(s == n) return 1;

        // recursive case
        vis[s] = 1;
        int path = 0;
        for(auto it : adj[s]){
            int neigh = it.first;
            if(!vis[neigh] && distMap[neigh] < distMap[s]){
                path += dfs_helper(neigh, adj, distMap, vis, n);
            }
        }
        vis[s] = 0;
        return path;
    }
public:
    int countRestrictedPaths(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges) {
        vector<pair<int,int>> adj[n+1];
        for(auto e : edges){
            adj[e[0]].push_back({e[1],e[2]});
            adj[e[1]].push_back({e[0],e[2]});
        }

        vector<int> distMap(n+1, INT_MAX);
        distMap[n] = 0;

        priority_queue<pair<int,int>,vector<pair<int,int>>,greater<pair<int,int>>> pq;
        pq.push({0, n});

        while(!pq.empty()){
            int dist = pq.top().first;
            int node = pq.top().second;
            pq.pop();

            for(auto it : adj[node]){
                int neighbour = it.first;
                int edW = it.second;

                if(edW + dist < distMap[neighbour]){
                    distMap[neighbour] = dist + edW;
                    pq.push({distMap[neighbour], neighbour});
                }
            }
        }
        
        vector<int> vis(n+1, 0);
        return dfs_helper(1, adj, distMap, vis, n);
    }
};

[13/10/24, 6:06:00 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int snakesAndLadders(vector<vector<int>>& board) {
        int n = board.size();

        queue<pair<int,int>> q;
        q.push({0,1});

        while(!q.empty()){
            int moves = q.front().first;
            int pos = q.front().second;
            q.pop();

            if(pos == n*n) return moves;

            for(int dest = pos+1 ; dest <= min(pos+6, n*n); dest++){
                int row = n - dest/n - 1;
                int col = (row & 1) == 0 ? n - dest%n : dest%n;
                // if the new position has a snake or ladder, consider it
                if(board[row][col] != -1) dest = board[row][col];
                q.push({moves+1, dest});
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
};

[15/10/24, 1:47:41 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Trie{
    public:
    struct trienode{
        bool isEnd;
        trienode* arr[26];
    };
    trienode* newnode(){
        trienode* temp = new trienode();
        for(int i=0 ; i<26 ; i++){
            temp->arr[i] = NULL;
        }
        temp->isEnd = false;
        return temp;
    }
    trienode* root;
    Trie(){
        root = new trienode();
    }

    void insert(string word){

        trienode* crawler = root;
        for(int idx=0 ; idx<word.size() ; idx++){
            int i = word[idx]-'a';
            if(!crawler->arr[i]){
                crawler->arr[i] = newnode();
            }
            crawler = crawler->arr[i];
        }
        crawler->isEnd = true;
    }

    bool hasPre(string word){
    trienode* crawler = root;
        for(int idx=0 ; idx<word.size() ; idx++){
            int i = word[idx]-'a';
            if(crawler->arr[i] == NULL) return false;
            crawler = crawler->arr[i];
        }
        return (crawler != NULL);
    }

};
class Solution {
public:
    int f(Trie& t, string target, int i){
        if(i == target.size()) return 0;
        // if(dp[i] != -1) return dp[i];
        // recursive case
        int ans = 1e7;
        for(int j=target.size()-1 ; j>=i ; j--){
            if(t.hasPre(target.substr(i,j-i+1))){
                ans =  min(ans,f(t,target,j+1));
            }
        }
        return  1 + ans;
    }
    int minValidStrings(vector<string>& words, string target) {
        Trie t;
        for(string word : words){
            t.insert(word);
        }
        // vector<int> dp(target.size()+1,-1);
        int temp =  f(t,target,0);
        if(temp >= 1e7) return -1;
        return temp;

    }
};
[15/10/24, 1:47:55 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-number-of-valid-strings-to-form-target-i/
[15/10/24, 1:53:02 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    class Trie {
        vector<vector<int>> trieNodes; // Each node contains an array of 26 children (a-z)
    public:
        Trie() {
            trieNodes.push_back(vector<int>(26, 0)); // Initialize the root node
        }

        void addWord(const string& word) {
            int curr = 0; // Start from the root node
            for (char c : word) {
                int idx = c - 'a';
                if (trieNodes[curr][idx] == 0) {
                    trieNodes.push_back(vector<int>(26, 0)); // Add a new node
                    trieNodes[curr][idx] = trieNodes.size() - 1; // Point to the new node
                }
                curr = trieNodes[curr][idx];
            }
        }

        void findPrefix(const string& target, int startIdx, vector<int>& dpArray) {
            int curr = 0; // Start from the root node
            for (int i = startIdx; i < target.length(); i++) {
                int idx = target[i] - 'a';
                if (trieNodes[curr][idx] == 0) {
                    return; // No valid prefix from this position
                }
                curr = trieNodes[curr][idx];
                dpArray[i + 1] = min(dpArray[i + 1], dpArray[startIdx] + 1);
            }
        }
    };

    int minValidStrings(vector<string>& words, string target) {
        Trie t;

        for (const string& w : words) {
            t.addWord(w);
        }

        int len = target.length();
        vector<int> dpArray(len + 1, INT_MAX); 
        dpArray[0] = 0; 

        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
            if (dpArray[i] != INT_MAX) { 
                t.findPrefix(target, i, dpArray);
            }
        }

        return dpArray[len] == INT_MAX ? -1 : dpArray[len];
    }
};

[16/10/24, 9:36:33 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    string longestDiverseString(int a, int b, int c) {
        string res;
        priority_queue<pair<int,char>> pq;
        pq.push({a,'a'});
        pq.push({b,'b'});
        pq.push({c,'c'});
        while(!pq.empty()){
            pair<int,char> top1 = pq.top();
            pq.pop();
            if(pq.empty()){
                res += top1.second;
                res += top1.second;
                break;
            }
            pair<int,char> top2 = pq.top();
            pq.pop();
            if(top1.first >= 2 && top2.first >=1){
                res += top1.second;
                res += top1.second;
                res += top2.second;
            } 
            top1.first -= 2;   
            top2.first -= 1;   
            if(top1.first - top2.first <= 1 && top2.first >=1){ 
                res += top2.second;
                top2.first -= 1;   
            }
            pq.push({});
            pq.push(top2);
        }
        return res;
    }
};

[16/10/24, 9:39:07 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    string longestDiverseString(int a, int b, int c) {
        priority_queue<pair<int,char>,vector<pair<int,char>>> pq;

        if (a > 0) pq.push({a, 'a'});
        if (b > 0) pq.push({b, 'b'});
        if (c > 0) pq.push({c, 'c'});

        string s = "";
        while(pq.size() >= 2){
            pair<int,char> top1 = pq.top();
            pq.pop();
            pair<int,char> top2 = pq.top();
            pq.pop();

            int cnt1 = min(top1.first, 2);
            int cnt2 = min(top2.first, 2);

            if(top1.first - top2.first > 1){
                top1.first -= cnt1;
                top2.first -= 1;
                s += string(cnt1, top1.second) + top2.second;
            }
            else{
                top1.first -= min({cnt1, cnt2, 2});
                top2.first -= min({cnt1, cnt2, 2});
                s += string(min({cnt1, cnt2, 2}), top1.second) + string(min({cnt1, cnt2, 2}), top2.second);
            }

            if(top1.first) pq.push(top1);
            if(top2.first) pq.push(top2); 
        }

        if(!pq.empty()){
            pair<int,char> top1 = pq.top();
            int cnt1 = min(top1.first,2);
            s += string(cnt1,top1.second);
        }

        return s;
    }
};

[16/10/24, 9:42:23 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    string longestDiverseString(int a, int b, int c) {
        string res;
        priority_queue<pair<int,char>> pq;
        pq.push({a,'a'});
        pq.push({b,'b'});
        pq.push({c,'c'});
        while(!pq.empty() || !(pq.size() == 1 && pq.top().second == res[res.size()-1])){
            pair<int,char> top1 = pq.top();
            pq.pop();
            pair<int,char> top2 = pq.top();
            pq.pop();
            if(top1.first >= 2 && top2.first >=1){
                res += top1.second;
                res += top1.second;
                res += top2.second;
            } 
            top1.first -= 2;   
            top2.first -= 1;   
            if(top1.first - top2.first <= 1 && top2.first >=1){ 
                res += top2.second;
                top2.first -= 1;   
            }
            if(top1.first>0)
                pq.push(top1);
            if(top2.first>0)
                pq.push(top2);
        }
        return res;
    }
};

[16/10/24, 9:50:53 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    string longestDiverseString(int a, int b, int c) {
        //using max heap
        priority_queue<pair<int,char>>pq;
        if(a)
        pq.push({a,'a'});
        if(b)
        pq.push({b,'b'});
        if(c)
        pq.push({c,'c'});
        string ans="";
        while(pq.size()>1){
            pair<int,char>one = pq.top();pq.pop();
            pair<int,char>two = pq.top();pq.pop();
            if(one.first>=2){
                ans+=one.second;
                ans+=one.second;
                one.first-=2;
            }
            else{
                ans+=one.second;
                one.first-=1;
            }
            if(two.first>=2 && two.first>=one.first){
                ans+=two.second;
                ans+=two.second;
                two.first-=2;
            }
            else{
                ans+=two.second;
                two.first-=1;
            }
            if(one.first>0)
                pq.push(one);
            if(two.first>0)
                pq.push(two);
        }
        if(pq.empty())
            return ans;
        if(pq.top().first>=2){
            ans+=pq.top().second;
            ans+=pq.top().second;
        }
        else{
            ans+=pq.top().second;
        }
        return ans;
        
    }
};
[16/10/24, 9:51:06 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: class Solution {
public:
    string longestDiverseString(int a, int b, int c) {
        string res="";
        int size = a + b + c;
        int A = 0, B = 0, C = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < size; i++) {
            if ((a >= b && a >= c && A != 2) || (B == 2 && a > 0) || (C == 2 && a > 0)){
                res+="a";
                a--,A++,B = 0,C = 0;  
            }else if ((b >= a && b >= c && B != 2) || (A == 2 && b > 0) || (C == 2 && b > 0)){
                res+="b";
                b--,B++,A = 0,C = 0;
            }else if ((c >= a && c >= b && C != 2) || (B == 2 && c > 0) || (A == 2 && c > 0)){
                res+="c";
                c--,C++,A = 0,B = 0;  
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
[16/10/24, 9:51:32 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: string longestDiverseString(int a, int b, int c, char aa = 'a', char bb = 'b', char cc = 'c') {
    if (a < b)
        return longestDiverseString(b, a, c, bb, aa, cc);
    if (b < c)
        return longestDiverseString(a, c, b, aa, cc, bb);
    if (b == 0)
        return string(min(2, a), aa);
    auto use_a = min(2, a), use_b = a - use_a >= b ? 1 : 0; 
    return string(use_a, aa) +  string(use_b, bb) + 
		longestDiverseString(a - use_a, b - use_b, c, aa, bb, cc);
}

[18/10/24, 2:38:41 PM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/nearest-exit-from-entrance-in-maze/description/?envType=study-plan-v2&envId=leetcode-75
[18/10/24, 2:40:57 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int nearestExit(vector<vector<char>>& maze, vector<int>& entrance) {
        int n = maze.size();
        int m = maze[0].size();

        queue<pair<int,int>> q;
        q.push({entrance[0],entrance[1]});

        vector<int> dx = {1,-1,0,0};
        vector<int> dy = {0,0,1,-1};

        vector<vector<int>> vis(n, vector<int>(m,0));

        int dist = 0;

        while(!q.empty()){
            int sz = q.size();
            for(int t=0;t<sz;t++){
                int i = q.front().first;
                int j = q.front().second;
                q.pop();

                vis[i][j] = 1;

                if((i == 0 || j == 0 || i == n-1 || j == m-1) && !(i == entrance[0] && j == entrance[1])) return dist; 
                maze[i][j] = '+';

                for(int k=0;k<4;k++){
                    int ii = i + dx[k];
                    int jj = j + dy[k];

                    if(ii >= 0 && ii < n && jj >= 0 && jj < m && maze[ii][jj] == '.' && !vis[ii][jj]){
                        q.push({ii,jj});
                    }
                }
            }
            dist++;
        }
        return -1;
    }
};

[18/10/24, 2:49:34 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution
{
	queue<pair<int, int>> q1;
	vector<vector<int>> visited;
	int bfs(vector<vector<char>> &grid, int i, int j, vector<vector<int>> visi)
	{
		int xn[] = {1, -1, 0, 0};
		int yn[] = {0, 0, -1, 1};
		queue<pair<int, int>> q;
		visited[i][j] = 1;
		q.push({i, j});
		q1.push({i, j});
		int ans = INT_MAX;
		while (!q.empty())
		{
			int x = q.front().first;
			int y = q.front().second;
			q.pop();

			for (int i1 = 0; i1 < 4; i1++)
			{
				i = x + xn[i1];
				j = y + yn[i1];
				if (i >= grid.size() || j >= grid[0].size() || grid[i][j] == '+' || visited[i][j] == 1)
					continue;
				visi[i][j] = visi[x][y] + 1;
				visited[i][j] = 1;
				q.push({i, j});
				q1.push({i, j});
				if (i == 0 || i == grid.size() - 1 || j == 0 || j == grid[0].size() - 1)
					ans = min(visi[i][j], ans);
						}
		}
		if (ans == INT_MAX)
			return -1;
		else
			return ans - 1;
	}

public:
	int nearestExit(vector<vector<char>> &maze, vector<int> &e)
	{
		int i = e[0];
		int j = e[1];

		vector<vector<int>> visi;

		int xn[] = {1, -1, 0, 0};
		int yn[] = {0, 0, -1, 1};

		int n = maze.size();
		int m = maze[0].size();
		visited.resize(n + 1, vector<int>(m + 1, 0));

		visi.resize(n + 1, vector<int>(m + 1, 0));
		visi[i][j] = 1;
		return bfs(maze, i, j, visi);
	}
};
[18/10/24, 2:52:10 PM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
public:
    int dirx[4] = { -1, 0, 0, 1 };
    int diry[4] = { 0, 1, -1, 0 };
    int nearestExit(vector<vector<char>>& maze, vector<int>& entrance) {
        int m = maze.size(), n = maze[0].size();
        queue<array<int, 3>> q; // {i, j, steps}
        // push the starting point (i, j) with initial step 0
        q.push({entrance[0], entrance[1], 0});
        // BFS
        while (!q.empty()) {
            auto [i, j, steps] = q.front(); q.pop();
            // handle exit condition, we can exit if
            // 1. the current position is not the entrance 
            bool isAtTheEntrance = i == entrance[0] && j == entrance[1];
            // 2. and the current position is at the border
            bool isAtTheBorder = i == 0 || j == 0 || i == m - 1 || j == n - 1;
            if (!isAtTheEntrance && isAtTheBorder) return steps;
            // try for 4 directions
            for (int d = 0; d < 4; d++) {
                int next_i = i + dirx[d];
                int next_j = j + diry[d];
                // check if we can move to (next_i, next_j)
                if (next_i >= 0 && next_j >= 0 && next_i < m && next_j < n && maze[next_i][next_j] == '.') {
                    // if so, we mark the next cell to `+` so that we won't visit it again
                    maze[next_i][next_j] = '+';
                    // add the next position to the queue with steps + 1
                    q.push({next_i, next_j, steps + 1});
                }
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
};

[19/10/24, 10:23:49 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-subsequence-score/description/?envType=study-plan-v2&envId=leetcode-75
[19/10/24, 10:24:29 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    long long mxScore(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2, int i, int k,
                      string s, map<pair<int, string>, int>& dp) {
        // base case
        if (s.length() == k) {
            long long sum = 0, mini = INT_MAX;
            for (char ch : s) {
                int i = ch - '0';
                sum += nums1[i];
                mini = min(mini, (long long)nums2[i]);
            }
            return sum * mini;
        }
        if (i == nums1.size())
            return -1;

        // lookup
        if (dp.find({i, s}) != dp.end())
            return dp[{i, s}];

        // recursive case
        long long ans = 0;
        ans = mxScore(nums1, nums2, i + 1, k, s + to_string(i), dp);
        ans = max(ans, mxScore(nums1, nums2, i + 1, k, s, dp));
        return dp[{i, s}] = ans;
    }

public:
    long long maxScore(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2, int k) {
        map<pair<int, string>, int> dp;
        return mxScore(nums1, nums2, 0, k, "", dp);
    }
};

[22/10/24, 8:31:06 AM] Satvik Saini: https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-word-in-dictionary-through-deleting/description/
[22/10/24, 8:35:29 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    class cmp{
    public:
        bool operator()(string &s1, string &s2){
            if(s1.length() == s2.length()){
                return s1 < s2 ? 1 : 0;
            }
            return s1.length() > s2.length();
        }
    };

    bool isFound(string s, string d, int i, int j, vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        // base case
        if(j == d.length()) return 1;
        if(i == s.length()) return 0;

        // lookup
        if(dp[i][j] != -1) return dp[i][j];

        // recursive case
        if(s[i] == d[j]) return dp[i][j] = isFound(s, d, i+1, j+1, dp);
        return dp[i][j] = isFound(s, d, i+1, j, dp);
    }

public:
    string findLongestWord(string s, vector<string>& dictionary) {
        sort(dictionary.begin(), dictionary.end(), cmp());
        
        for(auto d : dictionary){
            vector<vector<int>> dp(s.length(), vector<int>(d.length(), -1));
            if(isFound(s, d, 0, 0, dp)) return d;
        }
        return "";
    }
};

[23/10/24, 8:39:35 AM] Satvik Saini: class Solution {
    void populateMap(TreeNode* root, int level, unordered_map<int,int> &mp){
        // base case
        if(!root) return;

        // recursive case
        mp[level] += root->val;
        populateMap(root->left, level+1, mp);
        populateMap(root->right, level+1, mp);
    }

    void updateTree(TreeNode* root, int level, unordered_map<int,int> &mp){
        // base case
        if(!root) return;

        // recursive case
        int sum = 0;
        if(root->left) sum += root->left->val;
        if(root->right) sum += root->right->val;

        int newVal = mp[level+1] - sum;
        if(root->left) root->left->val = newVal;
        if(root->right) root->right->val = newVal;
        updateTree(root->left, level+1, mp);
        updateTree(root->right, level+1, mp);
    }

public:
    TreeNode* replaceValueInTree(TreeNode* root) {
        unordered_map<int,int> mp;
        populateMap(root, 0, mp);
        updateTree(root, 0, mp);
        root->val = 0;
        return root;
    }
};
‎[23/10/24, 8:40:50 AM] Satvik Saini: ‎image omitted
[23/10/24, 9:12:36 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: ‎Voice call, ‎41 sec
[23/10/24, 9:12:53 AM] Tanmay DTU CB: /**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * struct TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode *left;
 *     TreeNode *right;
 *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}
 *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}
 * };
 */
class Solution {
public:
    TreeNode* replaceValueInTree(TreeNode* root) {
        queue<pair<TreeNode*,TreeNode*>> q;
        q.push({root,NULL});

        while(!q.empty()){
            int n = q.size();
            unordered_map<TreeNode*,int> siblingSum;
            int sum = 0;
            while(n--){
                auto nodes = q.front();
                q.pop();
                if(nodes.first != NULL){
                    siblingSum[nodes.first] += nodes.first->val; 
                    if(nodes.second != NULL) siblingSum[nodes.first] += nodes.second->val;
                    if(nodes.first -> right != NULL && nodes.first -> left != NULL ) q.push({nodes.first -> right, nodes.first -> left});
                    else if(nodes.first -> right != NULL) q.push({nodes.first -> right,NULL});
                    else if(nodes.first -> left != NULL ) q.push({nodes.first -> left,NULL});
                    sum += nodes.first->val;
                }
                if(nodes.second != NULL){
                    siblingSum[nodes.second] += nodes.second->val; 
                    if(nodes.first != NULL) siblingSum[nodes.second] += nodes.first->val;
                    if(nodes.second -> right != NULL && nodes.second -> left != NULL ) q.push({nodes.second -> right, nodes.second -> left});
                    else if(nodes.second -> right != NULL) q.push({nodes.second -> right,NULL});
                    else if(nodes.second -> left != NULL ) q.push({nodes.second -> left,NULL});
                    sum += nodes.second->val;
                }
            }
            for(auto& node : siblingSum){
                node.first -> val = (sum - node.second);
            }
        }
        root -> val = 0;
        return root;
    }
};

[30/10/24, 2:58:30 PM] Satvik Saini: You are given an array arr of size N where each element represents the number of steps to move.

Positive values indicate moving forward, while negative values indicate moving backward.

The array is circular, meaning if you move past the last element, you continue from the first element, and if you move before the first element, you continue from the last element.

Given a starting index start and a target index target, determine if you can reach the target index within a specified maximum number of steps. If possible, return the minimum number of steps needed to reach the target index; otherwise, return -1.

Input Format

The first line contains a single integer N, representing the size of the array.

The second line contains N space-separated integers representing the elements of the array arr.

The third line contains a single integer 'start', representing the initial index.

The fourth line contains a single integer 'target', representing the target index.

The fifth line contains a single integer 'max_steps', representing the maximum number of steps allowed.

Output Format

Print a single integer representing the minimum number of steps required to reach the target index from the start index within the given maximum number of steps. If it is not possible to reach the target index within the given maximum number of steps, print -1.

Constraints
1≤ N ≤ 10^5

-10^9 ≤ arr[i] ≤ 10^9

0s start, target < N

1 s max_steps ≤ 10^9

Sample Testcase 1

Testcase Input

4

2234

025

Testcase Output

1

Explanation

Start at index 0.

Move 2 steps forward to index 2

The user reaches the required index 2 within the maximum number of steps.
Give code in cpp
[30/10/24, 2:59:23 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <queue>
#include <unordered_set>
using namespace std;

int minStepsToReachTarget(vector<int>& arr, int start, int target, int max_steps) {
    int n = arr.size();
    queue<pair<int, int>> q;
    unordered_set<int> visited;

    q.push({start, 0});
    visited.insert(start);

    while (!q.empty()) {
        int index = q.front().first;
        int steps = q.front().second;
        q.pop();

        if (index == target) return steps;
        if (steps >= max_steps) continue;

        int forward_index = (index + arr[index]) % n;
        if (forward_index < 0) forward_index += n;

        if (visited.find(forward_index) == visited.end()) {
            q.push({forward_index, steps + 1});
            visited.insert(forward_index);
        }

        int backward_index = (index - arr[index]) % n;
        if (backward_index < 0) backward_index += n;

        if (visited.find(backward_index) == visited.end()) {
            q.push({backward_index, steps + 1});
            visited.insert(backward_index);
        }
    }

    return -1;
}

int main() {
    int result = minStepsToReachTarget(arr, start, target, max_steps);
[30/10/24, 3:05:40 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: next ?
[30/10/24, 3:19:37 PM] Satvik Saini: Remaining value needed: 8-6=2

Adding any other block to reach the remaining value will exceed the weight limit of 6.

Since no valid combination of blocks can reach the target value of 8 without exceeding the weight limit of 6, the output is -1.

[30/10/24, 3:19:59 PM] Satvik Saini: You need to construct a structure using various types of building blocks. Each block type is represented by a specific integer value, has some weight associated with them, and each block available in limited quantity.

Your objective is to find the minimum number of blocks required to exactly achieve a specified target value for the structure. Additionally, the total weight of the blocks used must not exceed a given weight capacity.

Input Format

The first line contains a single integer N, representing the number of different types of building blocks.

The second line contains N space-separated integers, where the i-th integer represents the value of the i-th block.

The third line contains N space-separated integers, where the I-th integer represents the maximum quantity of the i-th block that can be used.

The fourth line contains N space-separated integers, where the i-th integer represents the weight of the i-th block.

The fifth line contains a single integer target, representing the target value needed to complete the structure.

The sixth line contains a single integer maxWeight, representing the maximum total weight of the blocks used.

Output Format

Print a single integer representing the minimum number of blocks required to reach the target value without exceeding the maximum weight.

If it is not possible to achieve the target, print -1.

Constraints

1 ≤ N ≤50
1s value[i] < 100

0s max Quantity[i] ≤100

1 s weight[i] ≤50

1 target ≤ 10^3

1≤ maxWeight ≤ 10^3

Sample Testcase 1

Testcase Input

3

246

311

246

8

6

Testcase Output

-1

Explanation

To reach the target value of 8 without exceeding the weight limit of 6:

Consider block with value 6:

Using this block once gives: Value: 6 and Weight: 6

Remaining value needed: 8-6=2

However, adding any other block would exceed the weight limit of 6.

Consider block with value 4:

Using this block once gives: Value: 4 and Weight: 4

Remaining value needed: 8-4 =4

Using any other block to sum up to the remaining value will exceed the

weight limit of 6.
Consider block with value 2:

Using up to 3 of these blocks gives: Value: 2+2+2 = 6 and Weight: 2+2+2

= 6

Remaining value needed: 8-6=2

Adding any other block to reach the remaining value will exceed the weight limit of 6.

Since no valid combination of blocks can reach the target value of 8 without exceeding the weight limit of 6, the output is -1.
Code in cpp
[30/10/24, 3:20:01 PM] Satvik Saini: Ye wla h
[30/10/24, 3:21:55 PM] Tanmay DTU CB: #include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <algorithm>
#include <climits>
using namespace std;

struct Block {
    int value;
    int quantity;
    int weight;
};

int minBlocksToReachTarget(int n, vector<Block>& blocks, int target, int maxWeight) {
    // Initialize dp array where dp[w][v] represents the minimum blocks needed to achieve value v with weight w
    vector<vector<int>> dp(maxWeight + 1, vector<int>(target + 1, INT_MAX));
    dp[0][0] = 0; // No blocks are needed to reach a target value of 0 with weight 0

    // Process each block type
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        int value = blocks[i].value;
        int weight = blocks[i].weight;
        int quantity = blocks[i].quantity;

        // We use a temporary dp to avoid recomputation within the same block's effects
        vector<vector<int>> temp = dp;

        for (int w = weight; w <= maxWeight; ++w) {
            for (int v = value; v <= target; ++v) {
                // Try using up to 'quantity' of the current block
                for (int k = 1; k <= quantity; ++k) {
                    int newWeight = w - k * weight;
                    int newValue = v - k * value;

                    if (newWeight >= 0 && newValue >= 0 && dp[newWeight][newValue] != INT_MAX) {
                        temp[w][v] = min(temp[w][v], dp[newWeight][newValue] + k);
                    } else break;
                }
            }
        }
        
        dp = temp; // Update the main dp array with the temporary results
    }

    // Find the minimum blocks required to reach the exact target value within the max weight
    int result = INT_MAX;
    for (int w = 0; w <= maxWeight; ++w) {
        if (dp[w][target] != INT_MAX) {
            result = min(result, dp[w][target]);
        }
    }

    return result == INT_MAX ? -1 : result;
}

int main() {
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    vector<Block> blocks(n);

    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) cin >> blocks[i].value;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) cin >> blocks[i].quantity;
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) cin >> blocks[i].weight;

    int target, maxWeight;
    cin >> target >> maxWeight;

    int result = minBlocksToReachTarget(n, blocks, target, maxWeight);
    cout << result << endl;

}
